/* =============================================================
 * 全球能源项目世界地图 —— 英文正文（双语详情卡）
 * -------------------------------------------------------------
 * window.ENERGY_EN = { <id>: { descEn, detailEn } }，由 util.buildProjects 按 id 合并进项目，
 * 仅在源数据未内联 descEn/detailEn 时填充（与 progress.js 的按 id 合并同一模式）。
 * 这样英文翻译与源数据分离、互不污染，可分批增量补全（再加 i18n-en2.js 等并用 Object.assign 续接即可）。
 * EN 模式下详情卡正文走 descBody → detailEn || descEn；本文件主供 detailEn（卡片正文）。
 *
 * 批次 1：js/data.js 核心地标项目（id 1–87，墨脱/Stargate/北方气田/Simandou 等）。
 * 翻译为中文 detail 的对应英文，力求与既有内联英文（id 1/14/17）同一简洁事实风格。
 * 注：id 1/14/17 已在 data.js 内联英文，合并时不覆盖，故此处不重复收录。
 * ============================================================= */
window.ENERGY_EN = Object.assign(window.ENERGY_EN || {}, {
  /* ===== 可再生能源发电 ===== */
  7: { descEn: "A deep-water offshore wind cluster off Guangdong.", detailEn: "Off the coast of Yangjiang in Guangdong, the Qingzhou cluster is a flagship of China's large-scale deep-water offshore wind development, with sections progressively approved, started and grid-connected toward a planned ~7 GW total. It uses large-megawatt turbines with flexible HVDC export and pilots an integrated \"offshore wind + marine ranching + hydrogen\" model." },
  8: { descEn: "Planned to be the world's largest offshore wind base.", detailEn: "Chaozhou in Guangdong plans an ~43.3 GW mega offshore wind base in the wind-rich waters west of the Taiwan Strait; if realised it would be the world's largest offshore wind project. The strait's \"funnel effect\" yields world-class wind resources, though deep-water construction, long-distance transmission and ecological coordination remain key challenges." },
  12: { descEn: "One of the world's largest CSP complexes.", detailEn: "On the edge of the Sahara near Ouarzazate, Morocco, this concentrated-solar-power complex combines parabolic-trough and tower units totalling ~580 MW with molten-salt storage, letting it keep supplying power for several hours after sunset. A benchmark for African clean energy, it has sharply cut Morocco's dependence on imported fossil fuels." },
  13: { descEn: "One of Africa's largest solar parks.", detailEn: "In Benban, Aswan Governorate, Egypt, this park comprises about 40 separate plants totalling ~1.65 GW, making it one of Africa's largest solar parks. Built with support from the World Bank and other multilateral lenders, it drew global developers, markedly boosted Egypt's power supply and created local jobs." },
  15: { descEn: "A large solar-plus-storage project in Nevada.", detailEn: "On federal land northeast of Las Vegas, Nevada, Gemini pairs 690 MW of solar with 380 MW/1.4 GWh of battery storage, fully commissioned in 2024. One of the largest solar-plus-storage projects in the US at the time, it supplies clean power to the Las Vegas metro area and provides night-time output support." },
  16: { descEn: "The first commercial-scale US offshore wind farm.", detailEn: "South of Martha's Vineyard, Massachusetts, the 806 MW Vineyard Wind 1 is the first commercial-scale offshore wind farm in the US, built by Avangrid and Copenhagen Infrastructure Partners (CIP). Generating since late 2023 and connecting in stages, it powers about 400,000 New England homes and marks the launch of the US offshore wind industry." },

  /* ===== 输变电 · 电网 ===== */
  21: { descEn: "A new UHV corridor energised in June 2025.", detailEn: "Running ~2,260 km from Barkol in Hami, Xinjiang to Chongqing at ±800 kV with 8 GW capacity, this UHVDC line was energised on 10 June 2025. It bundles Xinjiang's desert wind, solar and thermal power for export to the southwest, delivering ~36 TWh a year to Chongqing — a landmark artery for large-scale renewable export from China's northwest." },
  22: { descEn: "A new west-to-east power corridor commissioning in 2026.", detailEn: "This ±800 kV, 8 GW UHVDC line carries power from Gansu to Zhejiang, with key converter equipment supplied by Hitachi Energy and others, targeting commissioning in 2026. Once online it will deliver about 36 TWh a year to Zhejiang — a high share of it renewable — easing the power shortfall in the Yangtze River Delta load centre." },
  23: { descEn: "Ningxia renewables exported to Hunan.", detailEn: "The \"Ningxia-to-Hunan\" UHVDC link runs ~1,600 km from Zhongwei in Ningxia to Hengyang in Hunan at 8 GW, the first UHV corridor in China designed primarily to carry renewable power, paired with large wind and solar bases in the Tengger Desert. It will deliver about 36 TWh a year to Hunan, more than half of it renewable." },
  29: { descEn: "The world's longest land-and-subsea HVDC interconnector.", detailEn: "Linking Lincolnshire in the UK with western Denmark, the ~765 km, 1.4 GW Viking Link is the world's longest combined onshore-and-subsea HVDC interconnector, commissioned in 2024. It lets UK wind power trade with Danish and Nordic hydro and wind, boosting the flexibility and security of both grids." },
  31: { descEn: "The largest clean-energy transmission project in US history.", detailEn: "SunZia combines a 3.5 GW onshore wind farm in New Mexico with an ~885 km, ±525 kV HVDC line carrying the power to Arizona and into the California market — at about $11 billion the largest clean-energy infrastructure project in US history. By early 2026 all 674 turbines had been delivered and installed, with the project nearing completion." },
  32: { descEn: "Quebec hydropower delivered directly to New York City.", detailEn: "A ~545 km, 1.25 GW buried and underwater HVDC line running along Lake Champlain and the Hudson River to bring Quebec's hydropower into New York City, with power flows planned from May 2026. It will meet about 20% of the city's electricity demand, sharply cutting local fossil-fuel reliance and emissions." },
  33: { descEn: "The Middle East's first large-scale HVDC interconnector.", detailEn: "Connecting Saudi Arabia and Egypt at ±500 kV with 3 GW capacity, this is the first large-scale HVDC interconnector in the Middle East and North Africa. The two countries' demand peaks fall at different times (Saudi summer daytime, Egyptian evening), so the link lets them share peaks and reserves, improving regional grid economics and stability." },
  34: { descEn: "First link between the Texas grid and the US Southeast.", detailEn: "A ~320-mile, 525 kV, 3 GW bidirectional HVDC line that for the first time connects the relatively isolated Texas ERCOT grid with the US Southeast. Once built, the two grids can support each other during extreme weather, markedly improving supply reliability — a key US inter-regional interconnection project." },

  /* ===== 储能 ===== */
  35: { descEn: "The largest pumped-hydro storage in the Southern Hemisphere.", detailEn: "In the Snowy Mountains of New South Wales, tunnels and reversible turbines are being added between existing reservoirs for 2.2 GW of capacity and about 350 GWh of storage — the largest pumped-hydro scheme in the Southern Hemisphere. It will provide long-duration backstop balancing for Australia's high-renewables grid, in effect a giant \"water battery\"." },
  36: { descEn: "One of the Southern Hemisphere's largest battery storage systems.", detailEn: "On a former power-station site in New South Wales, the 850 MW/1,680 MWh Waratah Super Battery is one of the largest battery storage projects in the Southern Hemisphere. Acting as a grid \"shock absorber\", it rapidly absorbs and injects power during line faults to protect transmission corridors, letting existing lines carry more renewable energy." },
  38: { descEn: "The world's largest battery project by GWh to date.", detailEn: "Announced in February 2026 by Xcel Energy and Google using Form Energy's iron-air battery technology, this 300 MW/30 GWh system is the world's largest battery storage project by gigawatt-hours to date. Iron-air cells enable roughly 100 hours of long-duration storage, mainly providing multi-day reliable power to Minnesota's data centres and grid." },
  39: { descEn: "The world's first gigawatt-scale round-the-clock solar-plus-storage.", detailEn: "Developed by the UAE's Masdar with EWEC, this project pairs ~5.2 GW of solar with ~19 GWh of battery storage to deliver a steady 1 GW of round-the-clock (24/7) output — the world's first solar-plus-storage scheme at this scale. It aims to prove that solar plus batteries alone can supply near-baseload, reliable power." },
  40: { descEn: "A giant high-altitude battery storage system.", detailEn: "In India's high-altitude Ladakh region, this ~12 GWh system supports a large local renewable-energy base, smoothing output fluctuations and underpinning long-distance transmission. One of India's largest battery storage projects, it serves as a model for grid stability at high altitude." },
  41: { descEn: "A giant storage project in the Atacama Desert.", detailEn: "Built by Spain's Grenergy in Chile's Atacama Desert, this project deploys about 11 GWh of battery storage in phases alongside large-scale solar. Shifting abundant daytime sunshine to night-time release, it is one of Latin America's largest storage projects, helping Chile's grid wean off fossil-fuelled peaking plants." },
  43: { descEn: "The world's largest compressed-air energy storage.", detailEn: "In Yingcheng, Hubei, this plant uses a single 300 MW unit storing compressed air in underground salt caverns — at commissioning in 2024 the world's largest and most efficient non-combustion compressed-air energy storage station. It charts a new path for long-duration, high-capacity, low-cost storage and exemplifies the diversification of new storage technologies." },
  44: { descEn: "One of the world's largest single battery storage projects.", detailEn: "Large battery storage deployed by the Saudi Electricity Company across several sites including Bisha, with multi-GWh batches supplied by BYD and others — among the world's largest single battery storage projects. It absorbs Saudi Arabia's fast-growing solar capacity and underpins the high-renewables targets of Vision 2030." },

  /* ===== 工商业 · 配网大客户 ===== */
  46: { descEn: "The largest semiconductor investment in the US.", detailEn: "TSMC is building several advanced-process fabs in Phoenix, Arizona, with cumulative pledged investment raised to about $165 billion — the largest foreign semiconductor investment in US history. A single fab's power and water needs rival a mid-sized city, driving large-scale expansion of local grid and water systems and anchoring a full semiconductor supply chain." },
  47: { descEn: "A mega \"Silicon Heartland\" fab campus.", detailEn: "Near Columbus, Ohio, Intel plans a mega fab campus dubbed the \"Silicon Heartland\", with initial investment of about $28 billion. Its production timeline has slipped amid the semiconductor market downturn, but it remains a major project for domestic advanced-process manufacturing and grid capacity expansion." },
  49: { descEn: "India's first large-scale wafer fab.", detailEn: "The Tata Group, with Taiwan's PSMC, is building India's first large-scale wafer fab at Dholera, Gujarat, for about $11 billion. A flagship of India's chip self-reliance strategy, it comes with dedicated power, ultra-pure water and a new industrial city, creating huge new demand on the local grid and infrastructure." },

  /* ===== 数据中心 ===== */
  50: { descEn: "The largest AI infrastructure build in the US.", detailEn: "A joint venture of OpenAI, Oracle, SoftBank and MGX, Stargate plans to invest up to $500 billion by 2029 to build about 10 GW of AI computing. Its first flagship campus is in Abilene, Texas, and by 2025-2026 it had expanded to around 10 sites across Texas, New Mexico, Ohio and Michigan. Its staggering power demand (several GW per campus) is reshaping US power planning and spurring matching generation and storage investment." },
  51: { descEn: "An AI supercomputing centre in Memphis.", detailEn: "Elon Musk's xAI is building the \"Colossus\" supercomputing cluster in Memphis, Tennessee, deploying hundreds of thousands of GPUs to train large models and scaling toward gigawatt-class power demand. The project has drawn local scrutiny over temporary gas generation, power and water use — a microcosm of the grid pressure from rapid AI compute expansion." },
  52: { descEn: "The largest AI data-centre cluster outside the US.", detailEn: "In Abu Dhabi, the UAE's G42 is building this cluster with Nvidia, OpenAI, Cisco, Oracle and others, planning about 5 GW of compute — the largest AI data-centre cluster outside the US, entering service in phases from 2026. Leveraging cheap local energy and capital, the UAE aims to become the Middle East's artificial-intelligence and computing hub." },
  53: { descEn: "The world's densest concentration of data centres.", detailEn: "Around Ashburn in Loudoun County, Virginia lies the world's densest cluster of data centres, carrying a sizeable share of global internet traffic, with total power use already above 5 GW and still growing. AWS, Microsoft, Google and others are packed in here, and their power demand has forced major adjustments to local grid and generation planning." },
  54: { descEn: "Southeast Asia's fastest-growing data-centre hub.", detailEn: "Johor in Malaysia, next to Singapore, is absorbing data-centre demand spilling over from land- and power-constrained Singapore, with capacity under construction already reaching several GW — Southeast Asia's fastest-growing data-centre hub. Major cloud and AI firms are investing heavily here, driving rapid expansion of local power, solar and supporting infrastructure." },
  55: { descEn: "A Middle East AI computing centre.", detailEn: "Backed by Saudi Arabia's sovereign wealth fund, HUMAIN is building large-scale AI data centres in Riyadh and elsewhere with Nvidia, AMD and others, planning several GW of compute. Leveraging cheap energy and capital, Saudi Arabia aims to make computing a new pillar of its Vision 2030 economy." },

  /* ===== 大交通 · 轨交机场港口 ===== */
  59: { descEn: "A flagship China-CEE railway.", detailEn: "Connecting Budapest in Hungary with Belgrade in Serbia, this ~350 km electrified, upgraded-speed railway already has its Belgrade-Novi Sad section in service. A flagship of China-Central and Eastern Europe cooperation and the Belt and Road in Europe, it will improve the efficiency of the China-Europe Land-Sea Express route." },
  61: { descEn: "A new South America-Asia shipping hub.", detailEn: "North of Lima, Peru, and built and operated by COSCO Shipping, Chancay is the first smart, green deep-water mega-port on South America's west coast, opening in November 2024. Its direct route to Shanghai cuts shipping time from Peru to China by about 10 days, reshaping South America-Asia trade and driving green port infrastructure such as shore power." },
  62: { descEn: "Planned to be one of the world's largest airports.", detailEn: "Led by Saudi Arabia's PIF sovereign fund, this airport is planned with six runways and an eventual annual throughput of up to 185 million passengers, set to be one of the world's largest. It is core infrastructure for Riyadh's ambition to become a global aviation and logistics hub and to support the economic diversification of Vision 2030." },
  63: { descEn: "Vietnam's largest airport.", detailEn: "In Dong Nai Province east of Ho Chi Minh City, Long Thanh's first phase is due in 2026 with 25 million passengers a year, expanding to 100 million long term, making it Vietnam's largest airport. It will relieve pressure on Tan Son Nhat, strengthen Vietnam's position as a regional aviation hub and spur surrounding industry and power supply." },
  64: { descEn: "Sydney's second airport.", detailEn: "In Sydney's western suburbs, Western Sydney Airport is due to open in the second half of 2026 with an initial 10 million passengers a year, becoming Sydney's second international airport. It comes with a dedicated metro line, roads and power networks, easing the capacity bottleneck at Kingsford Smith Airport and driving development of Western Sydney." },
  65: { descEn: "Europe's largest air-rail hub under construction.", detailEn: "Between Warsaw and Łódź, the Central Communication Port (CPK) is planned with two parallel runways integrated with a high-speed-rail hub and motorway network, at about €30 billion, with construction from 2026, serving a catchment of some 21 million people. It is set to be Central and Eastern Europe's largest combined aviation and high-speed-rail hub, with rail offering an \"air-to-rail\" alternative." },
  66: { descEn: "The first true high-speed rail in the US.", detailEn: "Planned to link San Francisco and Los Angeles, California High-Speed Rail is under full construction along a 119-mile segment in the Central Valley, with most structures built or under way — the first true high-speed railway in the US. Repeatedly challenged on schedule and budget, it is seen as a pivotal attempt to modernise US passenger rail." },
  68: { descEn: "The China-Pakistan Economic Corridor's sea gateway.", detailEn: "On the Arabian Sea coast of Balochistan, Pakistan, Gwadar is the sea gateway of the China-Pakistan Economic Corridor (CPEC), with a free-trade zone, power plant and desalination facilities. Once complete it offers western China a shorter route to the Indian Ocean and drives local energy and infrastructure development." },

  /* ===== 石油化工 · LNG ===== */
  69: { descEn: "The world's largest LNG expansion project.", detailEn: "Drawing on the world's largest single gas field — the North Field — Qatar is lifting LNG output from about 77 million tonnes a year to roughly 142 million tonnes before 2030 via its East and South phases and further expansion. It is the world's largest LNG expansion, further cementing Qatar's position as the leading global LNG exporter." },
  70: { descEn: "A large export LNG terminal in Louisiana.", detailEn: "A large export LNG project by Venture Global in Calcasieu, Louisiana; in March 2026 its second phase reached final investment decision with about $8.6 billion of financing secured. It is emblematic of the 2025-2026 wave of new US LNG investment, further expanding US gas export capacity to Europe and Asia." },
  71: { descEn: "A large export LNG terminal in Louisiana.", detailEn: "Near the mouth of the Mississippi River in Louisiana, Plaquemines LNG has capacity of about 24 million tonnes a year, using modular construction for fast start-up and beginning phased LNG output in 2024-2025. One of Venture Global's flagship export terminals, it is helping make the US the world's largest LNG exporter." },
  72: { descEn: "A Gulf Coast LNG terminal advancing toward FID.", detailEn: "Energy Transfer is converting its existing import terminal at Lake Charles, Louisiana into an export terminal of about 16.5 million tonnes a year, advancing toward a final investment decision in early 2026 after locking in several long-term supply agreements. It is another important reserve of US LNG export capacity." },
  73: { descEn: "North Slope gas liquefied for export.", detailEn: "Led by Glenfarne, Alaska LNG would pipe abundant North Slope gas about 800 miles to Nikiski on the Kenai Peninsula for liquefaction and export, at a total cost of about $44 billion. With gas supply secured from major oil-and-gas players and a final investment decision advancing in 2026, it could offer shorter-haul LNG to Asian markets." },
  74: { descEn: "An LNG capacity expansion at Kitimat.", detailEn: "At Kitimat, British Columbia, operated by a Shell-led joint venture, the first phase is already producing and exporting LNG to Asia, with the phase-2 expansion advancing toward a final investment decision in 2026. Thanks to Canada's shorter west-coast route to Asia, it is an important addition to North American LNG supply to Asia." },
  76: { descEn: "The world's largest single-train refinery.", detailEn: "In the Lekki Free Trade Zone near Lagos, Nigeria, the Dangote Refinery processes 650,000 barrels a day — the world's largest single-train refinery — starting up from 2024. It reverses West Africa's long reliance on imported fuels, positioning Nigeria to shift from a crude exporter to a net exporter of refined products, with its own captive power plant and jetty." },
  77: { descEn: "The core of Saudi Arabia's \"gas-for-oil\" strategy.", detailEn: "In eastern Saudi Arabia, Jafurah is the Middle East's largest unconventional (shale) gas field, which Saudi Aramco plans to develop in phases for about $100 billion. The added gas will go to power, industry and blue-hydrogen production, freeing up more crude for export — the centrepiece of Saudi Arabia's \"gas-for-oil\" energy strategy." },
  78: { descEn: "A gravity-based LNG plant in the Arctic Circle.", detailEn: "On the Gydan Peninsula inside Russia's Arctic Circle and led by Novatek, Arctic LNG 2 uses modular liquefaction trains built on gravity-based structures (GBS), with planned capacity of about 20 million tonnes a year. Hit by Western sanctions, it has struggled with equipment, shipping and sales — a textbook case of geopolitics' impact on energy projects." },

  /* ===== 矿业 ===== */
  80: { descEn: "The largest high-grade iron-ore mine under development.", detailEn: "In the mountains of south-eastern Guinea, Simandou grades about 65.8% iron — one of the largest and highest-grade undeveloped iron-ore deposits in the world. Blocks 1-2 are led by the Chinese-backed WCS consortium and Blocks 3-4 by a Rio Tinto-Chinalco venture, served by the ~620 km TransGuinéen heavy-haul railway and a new port. The first ore shipped in December 2025 and reached Zhejiang in January 2026, with output ramping toward ~120 million tonnes a year, reshaping global iron-ore supply." },
  81: { descEn: "The world's highest-output copper mine.", detailEn: "In Chile's Atacama Desert, operated by BHP with Rio Tinto and others as partners, Escondida is the world's highest-output copper mine. Recent years have seen about $13 billion invested in expansion, desalination and processing upgrades, and it now runs on 100% renewable power — vital to the copper supply needed for the global energy transition." },
  86: { descEn: "The hub of global iron-ore supply.", detailEn: "The Pilbara region of Western Australia is the hub of global iron-ore supply, where Rio Tinto, BHP, FMG and others run multiple super-large mines exporting over a billion tonnes a year, mostly to China. The region's extensive use of autonomous haul trucks, driverless heavy-haul trains and remote operations centres makes it a benchmark for mining automation." },
  87: { descEn: "A frontier of new global lithium supply.", detailEn: "The \"Lithium Triangle\" where Argentina, Chile and Bolivia meet holds over half the world's lithium resources, with relatively low-cost brine extraction. Chinese firms such as Zijin and Ganfeng, together with international miners, are building brine lithium projects intensively in Argentina, making the region a leading frontier of new global lithium supply." },
});

/* ===== 批次2：全库投资额 TOP（约 ≥175 亿美元）===== */
Object.assign(window.ENERGY_EN, {
  1033: { descEn: "The largest semiconductor project in US history.", detailEn: "Micron is building a mega-campus of four DRAM fabs at the White Pine Business Park in Clay, New York, with about $100 billion of investment — the largest semiconductor manufacturing project in US history — plus the first publicly owned High-NA EUV lithography centre in the country. Groundbreaking was held in January 2026, with first output targeted for 2030 and the full campus by the 2040s, driving city-scale grid and water expansion in central New York." },
  2047: { descEn: "A trans-isthmus land bridge bypassing the Strait of Malacca.", detailEn: "Thailand's Land Bridge would build deep-water ports at Chumphon and Ranong, linked by an 89 km six-lane expressway plus standard- and metre-gauge rail to bypass the Strait of Malacca. Costing about 1 trillion baht under a single 50-year PPP concession, it aims to start tendering and construction in 2026 with the first phase open by 2030 (internal rate of return ~17.4%)." },
  1539: { descEn: "Rosneft's Arctic flagship, with phase 1 targeted for 2026.", detailEn: "Vostok Oil is Rosneft's Arctic super-cluster of oilfields on the Taymyr Peninsula, valued at about $85 billion with planned investment of over 12 trillion roubles. Trial production began in early 2025 at fields such as Payakhskoye, with an export port, oil terminal and field pipelines under construction (over 80% done by September 2025); phase 1 is slated for 2026 and output is targeted at ~67 million tonnes a year by 2030." },
  1138: { descEn: "The UK's largest railway project.", detailEn: "HS2 is Britain's largest post-war rail infrastructure project, with phase 1 linking London's Old Oak Common to Birmingham at 330 km/h. Several tunnels broke through in 2025 — including the Bromford, Northolt and the line's longest Chiltern tunnel — and all deep bored tunnels between London and Birmingham were completed by October; civil works are about two-thirds done, with services planned for the early 2030s." },
  2933: { descEn: "Four AP1000 reactors anchoring an 11 GW AI campus in Texas.", detailEn: "Dubbed the 'Trump Advanced Energy and Intelligence Campus', this project beside the DOE Pantex plant near Amarillo, Texas plans up to 11 GW of gas, solar, storage and nuclear to power 18 million sq ft of AI computing. In 2025 the NRC accepted a combined licence for four AP1000 units, with the first targeted to start construction in 2026 and operate by April 2031." },
  2934: { descEn: "Westinghouse's plan for 10 US AP1000 units (~11.5 GW).", detailEn: "In July 2025 Westinghouse announced 10 AP1000 reactors in the US to help quadruple US nuclear capacity to 400 GW by 2050. In October 2025 the US government, Brookfield and Cameco signed a framework to invest at least $80 billion, and in April 2026 a Vogtle-4-standardised AP1000 design revision was filed. (Located at the Vogtle plant, Georgia.)" },
  3152: { descEn: "Transmission master plan for ~76 GW of Brahmaputra-basin hydropower.", detailEn: "Led by India's CEA, this ~6.4 trillion-rupee plan adds over 31,400 circuit-km of lines, ~68 GVA of substation capacity and 42 GW of HVDC to evacuate some 76 GW of hydro and pumped storage across 12 sub-basins including Siang (18.7 GW), Subansiri (12.3 GW) and Dibang (8.8 GW), in two phases around 2035." },
  3014: { descEn: "Canada's first true high-speed rail.", detailEn: "Announced by the Prime Minister in February 2025, Alto is a ~1,000 km dedicated electrified line at 300 km/h linking Toronto, Ottawa, Montreal and Quebec City. The private Cadence consortium (including SNCF and Air Canada) will design, build, finance and operate it; the design phase is ~C$3.9 billion and the whole network is estimated at C$60-90 billion, with main works around 2030." },
  162: { descEn: "The world's largest planned green-hydrogen export hub.", detailEn: "Spanning ~2.26 million hectares in Western Australia, this hub plans 70 GW of wind and solar to produce ~3.5 million tonnes of green hydrogen and 20 million tonnes of green ammonia a year. It won federal 'Major Project' status in March 2025, with a ~6 GW first phase tied to feasibility deals with China's SANY and Korean firms; fully built it would generate more than Australia's entire current output." },
  1161: { descEn: "Vietnam's 1,541 km north-south high-speed railway.", detailEn: "Vietnam's North-South high-speed railway links Hanoi and Ho Chi Minh City over 1,541 km through 15 provinces with 23 stations at 350 km/h. Approved by the National Assembly in November 2024 at about $67.5 billion across 17 sub-projects, construction was brought forward to December 2025 with a 2035 target, cutting Hanoi-HCMC travel to ~5.5 hours — the largest infrastructure project in Vietnam's history." },
  2938: { descEn: "Up to 4,800 MW added at the world's largest operating nuclear site.", detailEn: "Bruce C would add up to 4,800 MW within the existing Bruce site — Ontario's first major new-build nuclear in over 30 years. It has cleared the federal impact-assessment planning phase and entered the impact-statement stage, with Bruce Power signing a C$300 million pre-development deal; lifetime economic contribution is estimated at ~C$238 billion." },
  1546: { descEn: "A giant Baltic gas-processing, LNG and petrochemical complex.", detailEn: "The Ust-Luga complex, built by RusKhimAlliance (a 50/50 JV of Gazprom and RusGazDobycha), is designed to process 45 bcm of ethane-rich gas a year into 13 million tonnes of LNG, 3.6 million tonnes of ethane and up to 1.8 million tonnes of LPG, feeding an adjacent cracker producing over 3 million tonnes of polymers. Costing about 4.9 trillion roubles, it has been delayed by Western sanctions, with Linde withdrawing in 2022." },
  521: { descEn: "A 1.8 GW AI campus in Cheyenne, Wyoming.", detailEn: "Announced by Crusoe and Tallgrass in July 2025 in Laramie County southeast of Cheyenne, Project Jade plans 1.8 GW — expandable to 10 GW long term — with Tallgrass supplying a gas power plant. With total project cost potentially reaching $50 billion, it is one of the largest AI data centres under discussion in the US interior." },
  2800: { descEn: "The UK's first new nuclear plant in decades (2×EPR).", detailEn: "In Somerset, England, Hinkley Point C is two 1.6 GW EPR reactors led by EDF (with CGN as a partner) — the UK's first new nuclear station in decades. The second reactor dome was lifted in 2025 and its pressure vessel arrived in January 2026; with costs risen to about £46 billion, the first unit is due to operate in the early 2030s." },
  2803: { descEn: "France's nuclear restart: the first six EPR2 reactors.", detailEn: "EDF's next-generation EPR2 programme will build a first batch of six 1.67 GW reactors at Penly (2), Gravelines (2) and Bugey (2). Public consultation and early works advanced in 2025, with Penly 1/2 aiming for the mid-2030s — a national flagship to restart French nuclear and secure low-carbon baseload power." },
  3002: { descEn: "Anthropic's $50 billion compute build, starting in Texas and New York.", detailEn: "Announced on 12 November 2025, Anthropic's $50 billion US AI-infrastructure plan will build custom data centres with the UK's Fluidstack in Texas and New York, coming online from 2026 and creating about 800 long-term jobs, running alongside AWS, Google TPU and Microsoft Azure capacity." },
  2801: { descEn: "Sizewell C: FID taken in July 2025, UK government holds 44.9%.", detailEn: "In Suffolk, England, Sizewell C is two 1.6 GW EPR reactors replicating Hinkley Point C to cut costs. A final investment decision was taken in July 2025 at over £38 billion, with the UK government the largest shareholder at 44.9% and a regulated-asset-base (RAB) model bringing in private investment — a centrepiece of Britain's energy-security strategy." },
  1528: { descEn: "Kazakhstan's largest oilfield expansion, with a third processing train online.", detailEn: "Chevron-led Tengizchevroil's Future Growth Project (FGP) and Wellhead Pressure Management Project (WPMP) added a third-generation processing plant with enhanced sour-gas reinjection at the Tengiz field in western Kazakhstan. WPMP finished in 2024 and FGP started up in January 2025, ramping Tengiz to about 1 million barrels a day; at ~$46.7 billion it is Kazakhstan's largest single industrial investment." },
  1459: { descEn: "One of the world's largest green-hydrogen projects (40 GW + 20 GW electrolysis).", detailEn: "Sweden's Svevind, through Hyrasia One, plans about 40 GW of wind and solar in Kazakhstan's Mangystau region — ~120 TWh a year — feeding a 20 GW electrolyser park on the Caspian coast for up to 2 million tonnes of green hydrogen annually. Costing $40-50 billion, output is planned from 2030 with full capacity around 2032 and a final investment decision expected in 2026." },
  3562: { descEn: "The world's most challenging railway; over 84% bridges and tunnels.", detailEn: "The 1,019 km Ya'an-Nyingchi section of the Sichuan-Tibet Railway includes 72 new tunnels totalling 838 km (the 42.5 km Yigong tunnel the longest), at an estimated ~320 billion yuan. Early works such as key tunnels and bridges have begun, with completion targeted for 2030 and high-standard advancement set out in the 15th Five-Year Plan." },
  2418: { descEn: "A $42 billion LNG plant at Lindi, fed by Shell and Equinor offshore gas.", detailEn: "At Likong'o in Lindi, this plant would produce about 10 million tonnes of LNG a year from Shell (Blocks 1 and 4) and Equinor (Block 2) offshore reserves, at about $42 billion — Tanzania's largest single energy project. Parties are pushing to finalise the legal framework and FID by late 2025/early 2026, though FID risks slipping to 2028 with start-up after 2032." },
  158: { descEn: "One of the world's largest planned green-hydrogen projects.", detailEn: "This project plans 30 GW of wind and solar in Mauritania's desert to produce 1.7 million tonnes of green hydrogen a year, led by Australia's CWP Global. Geological, hydrological and marine surveys were completed in 2025 (pre-FEED stage), and once built it is expected to lift Mauritania's GDP by 40-50%." },
  513: { descEn: "Three new Google data-centre campuses in West Texas ($40 billion).", detailEn: "In November 2025 Google announced a $40 billion investment (through 2027) in three data centres in West Texas and the Panhandle — two in Haskell County (one a solar-plus-storage industrial park with Intersect) and one in Armstrong County — alongside contracts for 6,200+ MW of new power." },
  1027: { descEn: "A new 12-inch fab mega-site in Texas.", detailEn: "Texas Instruments is building a mega-site of up to four connected 12-inch fabs in Sherman, Texas, with potential total investment of ~$40 billion. The first fab, SM1, started production on 17 December 2025 — in just three and a half years — ramping toward tens of millions of analog and embedded chips a day, with SM2's shell topped out; the site is a city-scale new load on the local grid." },
  1518: { descEn: "Eastern expansion of the BAM and Trans-Siberian railways.", detailEn: "Russia approved a third phase of its Eastern rail network (the 'Eastern Polygon') to 2035 at over 3.7 trillion roubles (~$40 billion), aiming to lift eastbound capacity to 270 million tonnes a year within a decade. Works include new passing loops, tunnels, an Amur River bridge and spurs to Far East ports — a key corridor for exports to Asia-Pacific." },
  2374: { descEn: "Storage and grid infrastructure for the 30 GW AMAN green-hydrogen project.", detailEn: "CWP Global's flagship AMAN project in Mauritania plans 30 GW of wind and solar (18 GW wind + 12 GW solar) generating ~110 TWh a year to make 1.7 million tonnes of green hydrogen and 10 million tonnes of green ammonia, worth about $40 billion. It includes large-scale desalination, storage and transmission aimed at clean-energy export to Europe (this entry focuses on the renewables-and-storage build-out)." },
  2804: { descEn: "Poland's first nuclear power station (3×AP1000).", detailEn: "On Poland's Baltic coast, the state company PEJ is building three 1.25 GW AP1000 reactors with Westinghouse and Bechtel — Poland's first nuclear plant. It won site-preparation and survey permits in August-September 2025, and in December the EU approved state aid (including a 40-year contract for difference); the first unit is due to start construction in 2028 and operate in 2036." },
  3013: { descEn: "A Dallas-Houston high-speed line using Japanese Shinkansen technology.", detailEn: "This ~386 km, 330 km/h line lost federal planning funding and Amtrak's involvement in April 2025, returning to private leadership under Fort Worth investor John Kleinheinz. Station sites are bought and about 500 of ~2,000 parcels acquired, with cost estimated at over $40 billion." },
  3129: { descEn: "The world's largest planned nuclear plant (6×EPR).", detailEn: "At Madban in Ratnagiri, Maharashtra, NPCIL leads with EDF supplying six EPR reactors (~1,650 MW each, ~9.9 GW total), which would make it the world's largest planned nuclear station. President Macron's February 2026 visit to India confirmed advancing the six-EPR process with accompanying small-reactor cooperation." },
  3275: { descEn: "A giant west-coast refining-petrochemical complex, now being split up.", detailEn: "RRPCL — formed by IOCL/BPCL/HPCL (50:25:25) with Saudi Aramco and ADNOC to hold 50% — originally planned 60 million tonnes/year of refining plus 18 million tonnes of petrochemicals. Hit by land and environmental protests, the centre is from 2025 considering splitting it into three dispersed 20-million-tonne refineries, but it remains central to India's refining expansion." },
  565: { descEn: "The Wuhu cluster of China's 'east-data-west-compute' Yangtze Delta hub.", detailEn: "Since approval in 2022 the Wuhu cluster has attracted 15 major projects from Huawei Cloud, ByteDance, China Mobile and others totalling over 270 billion yuan, with 21,000 racks built and over 100,000 under construction. China Mobile's first nationwide 'four-compute-in-one' scheduling platform is here, targeting over 45,000 PFLOPS of AI computing by 2027." },
  588: { descEn: "Spain's largest-ever foreign investment, across three Aragon provinces.", detailEn: "In March 2026 Spain announced that Amazon will invest a cumulative €33.7 billion in the Aragon region, building large-scale data centres and server-manufacturing facilities across Zaragoza, Huesca and Teruel, expected to add €31.7 billion in GDP and an average 29,900 full-time jobs a year." },
  288: { descEn: "The world's largest planned single AI data centre.", detailEn: "South Jeolla Province in Korea has attracted a 3 GW, ~$35 billion AI data centre able to house 200,000 GPUs, breaking ground in winter 2025 with completion targeted for 2028, backed by Korea's 65-trillion-won national AI strategy." },
  1129: { descEn: "Planned to be the world's largest airport (150M pax phase 1).", detailEn: "Dubai's Al Maktoum International Airport phase-2 expansion, approved in 2024 at about AED 128 billion (~$35 billion), will build a central terminal and four concourses for 150 million passengers a year initially, rising to five runways, ~400 gates and 260 million passengers — the world's largest airport. A ~$272 million second-runway contract and early works were awarded in 2025, with phase 1 targeted for 2032." },
  2251: { descEn: "Six green hydrogen/ammonia/steel projects worth $32.8 billion.", detailEn: "In March 2025 Morocco approved a green-hydrogen package in which consortia led by Ortus (US)/Acciona/Nordex, TAQA/Cepsa, Morocco's Nareva, Saudi ACWA Power and a Chinese UEAG/Three Gorges group will produce green ammonia, fuels and green steel. Concentrated in the south (Guelmim, Tan-Tan, Boujdour), it adds ~6 GW of wind and solar, targeting 10 TWh of exports by 2030." },
  2983: { descEn: "Intel's 18A flagship fab at Chandler, now in production.", detailEn: "Fab 52, the fifth high-volume fab at Intel's Ocotillo campus in Chandler, Arizona, began carrying 18A wafers in October 2025 and entered high-volume manufacturing by year-end, producing the first 18A Panther Lake processors that launched in late 2025 with broad availability in early 2026." },
  1409: { descEn: "Jeddah airport expanded to one of the world's largest (114M pax by 2031).", detailEn: "Jeddah Airports Company's 115 billion-riyal (~$31 billion) plan will make King Abdulaziz International one of the world's largest airports, reaching 114 million passengers a year by 2031. It includes a T1 expansion, a new T2 (construction from 2026, over $10 billion), a fourth runway (2025-2029), a new logistics zone and a Hajj terminal." },
  161: { descEn: "The world's largest planned solar-plus-storage, with a 4,300 km cable to Singapore.", detailEn: "SunCable's project would deploy 17-20 GW of solar and 36-42 GWh of storage on the Barkly Tableland in Australia's Northern Territory, sending power to Singapore via Indonesia through a ~4,300 km subsea cable. It renewed 'Major Project' status in July 2025 and won Indonesian approval, targeting cross-border supply in the mid-2030s — among the largest single renewable projects ever planned." },
  1500: { descEn: "Central Asia's largest compute park (1 GW long term).", detailEn: "In Ekibastuz, Pavlodar region, this aims to be Central Asia's largest data-centre park, with power capacity of 300 MW initially rising to 1 GW and total investment of ~$30 billion. Run by Kazakhtelecom's KT-Telecom and powered by the Ekibastuz GRES plants, it launched in January 2026 with full construction due to start in June 2026; the government is in talks with Microsoft, OpenAI, G42 and Mubadala." },
  2825: { descEn: "The Arab world's first nuclear plant (4×APR1400, all online).", detailEn: "At Barakah in western Abu Dhabi, KEPCO built four 1.4 GW APR1400 reactors — the Arab world's first nuclear plant, at about $30 billion. The fourth unit was commissioned in 2025; with all four in commercial operation they supply about a quarter of the UAE's electricity, a Middle East nuclear benchmark." },
  2827: { descEn: "Egypt and Africa's first large nuclear plant (4×VVER).", detailEn: "At El Dabaa on Egypt's Mediterranean coast in Matrouh, Russia's Rosatom is building four 1.2 GW VVER-1200 reactors — Egypt and Africa's first large nuclear plant, at about $30 billion, with all four units built concurrently. Main works advanced rapidly in 2025, with the first unit targeted to operate around 2028." },
  2984: { descEn: "Micron's second advanced DRAM fab at Boise, with HBM packaging.", detailEn: "Micron is building a second advanced DRAM fab (ID2) next to R&D at its Boise headquarters campus — part of a ~$200 billion US expansion with ~$30 billion added here. Idaho and New York together won ~$6.1 billion in CHIPS grants, bringing advanced packaging to support the HBM that AI requires." },
  3130: { descEn: "An India-US flagship nuclear plant (6×AP1000).", detailEn: "At Kovvada in Srikakulam, Andhra Pradesh, India plans six Westinghouse AP1000 reactors (~1,100 MW each); about 2,080 acres have been acquired and transferred to NPCIL and surveys completed. In 2025 NPCIL continued technical-commercial talks with Westinghouse — a flagship of India-US civil-nuclear cooperation." },
  3577: { descEn: "Shenzhen's largest-ever metro build (phase 5, 13 lines).", detailEn: "Shenzhen's fifth-phase metro plan (2023-2028) covers 13 projects totalling 185.6 km at about 195.2 billion yuan, including lines 15, 17-22, 25, 27, 29 and 32 plus extensions of lines 10 and 11. On completion Shenzhen's rail network will reach 25 lines and about 843.6 km." },
  1514: { descEn: "Russia's first dedicated high-speed railway.", detailEn: "This 679 km line with 16 stations is designed for 400 km/h (360 km/h in service), linking Moscow and St Petersburg, at over 2.3 trillion roubles (~$26 billion) including low-interest National Wealth Fund loans. Approved by Putin in March 2024, construction began in summer 2025 with the first section due in 2028, cutting travel time from ~4 hours to 2h15." },
  506: { descEn: "AWS AI cloud data centres across several Mississippi counties.", detailEn: "AWS is building data centres in Madison County (Project Atlas, $11 billion), Vicksburg in Warren County ($3 billion) and sites in Hinds County, Mississippi, announced through 2025-2026 for a cumulative $25 billion — the largest AWS expansion in the US Southeast." },
  508: { descEn: "The second-largest Stargate site, in Shackelford County, Texas.", detailEn: "Vantage Data Centers is building the Frontier campus in Shackelford County north of Abilene, Texas — 1,200 acres, 10 buildings totalling 3.7 million sq ft and 1.4 GW of compute, using a gas microgrid and water-saving closed-loop cooling. Construction began in September 2025 and it is officially confirmed as a Stargate site." },
  580: { descEn: "One of the world's largest AI data-centre plans, with gigawatt-scale green power.", detailEn: "Reliance plans up to 3 GW of AI data centres at Jamnagar, Gujarat, using Nvidia's latest Blackwell GPUs and powered entirely by on-site solar, wind and green hydrogen, at an estimated $20-30 billion. Targeting a first phase within 24 months, it would be one of the world's largest green AI computing bases." },
  1547: { descEn: "A giant LNG base on the Kola Peninsula with a 1,300 km feed pipeline.", detailEn: "Novatek's Murmansk LNG on the Kola Peninsula has capacity of about 20.4 MTPA, with a cost edge because it needs no icebreakers for year-round export. In January 2025 completion was brought forward from 2033 to 2030, with phase 1 in 2027-2029, fed by a ~1,300 km Volkhov-Murmansk pipeline (4.12 bcm/year) that Putin ordered finished by 2030." },
  2302: { descEn: "A 5,000 km trans-Atlantic gas pipeline from West Africa to Europe.", detailEn: "Nigeria and Morocco plan a 5,000 km coastal gas pipeline through 13 West African countries toward Europe. The two aim to sign an intergovernmental agreement in Q4 2026 — one of Africa's most ambitious cross-border energy infrastructure projects." },
  2810: { descEn: "The world's largest tokamak fusion experiment.", detailEn: "At Cadarache in southern France, ITER is built by China, the EU, the US, Russia, Japan, Korea and India — the world's largest magnetic-confinement tokamak, designed for 500 MW of fusion power. Key components such as superconducting magnets were completed in 2025, with first plasma targeted around 2034 and full operation by 2039 to prove fusion power feasible." },
  2935: { descEn: "A framework to deploy up to 6 GW of NuScale SMRs with TVA.", detailEn: "ENTRA1 and TVA reached a non-binding agreement to develop and own six energy plants across a seven-state service area, deploying up to 6 GW of NuScale modular reactors, part of ENTRA1's ~$25 billion power-infrastructure plan, at the planning stage. (Located in the central TVA service area.)" },
  3144: { descEn: "A reserve Westinghouse AP1000 site in Gujarat (long term).", detailEn: "At Chhaya-Mithi Virdi on the coast of Bhavnagar, Gujarat, India originally planned six Westinghouse AP1000 reactors (~6 GW). Blocked by land acquisition, the main effort moved to Kovvada in Andhra Pradesh, but Westinghouse says it still intends to build six AP1000 units here once Kovvada is done — a long-term reserve site." },
  3578: { descEn: "Guangzhou Metro phase 4 (8 lines, 175.5 km).", detailEn: "Guangzhou's fourth-phase plan (2025-2031) covers eight line segments totalling 175.5 km at about 172.1 billion yuan, reinforcing high-load central lines and strengthening the eastern centre and Nansha networks. Environmental review began in October 2024, with approval targeted for 2026." },
  1164: { descEn: "Thailand's first high-speed railway, linking to the China-Laos line.", detailEn: "The China-Thailand high-speed railway is Thailand's first, about 609 km at 250 km/h in two phases. Phase 1 (Bangkok-Nakhon Ratchasima, 251 km) was about 45% complete on civil works by June 2025, targeting 2027; phase 2 (357 km to Nong Khai) was approved in February 2025 at ~341 billion baht for 2025-2032. Connecting to the China-Laos railway, it opens the Pan-Asian central corridor from Bangkok via Vientiane to China." },
  1224: { descEn: "A large greenfield refinery in East Java.", detailEn: "At Tuban in East Java, the PRPP joint venture of Pertamina and Rosneft is designed for 300,000 barrels a day plus a large petrochemical complex, at about $24 billion. Although FID remains unsettled due to the Russian partner, the project launched EPCC prequalification tendering in May 2026 — an important reserve of Indonesian refining capacity." },
  3047: { descEn: "The Trans Mountain crude pipeline expansion, online in May 2024.", detailEn: "The Trans Mountain Expansion entered service on 1 May 2024 after 12 years and about C$34 billion, raising capacity from 300,000 to 890,000 barrels a day from Edmonton to the port of Burnaby. Since start-up China has overtaken the US as the largest buyer, sharply lifting Canadian crude exports." },
  2743: { descEn: "Europe's largest metro project: four new Paris lines.", detailEn: "The Grand Paris Express is an automated metro network around Paris, building about 200 km of new lines (15/16/17/18) and 68 new stations at ~€36 billion — Europe's largest urban rail project. Tunnelling and station works are advancing, with some lines opening after the 2024 Olympics and the main network targeted for around 2030." },
  1400: { descEn: "The world's largest single-phase driverless metro.", detailEn: "Riyadh Metro comprises 6 lines and 85 stations over 176 km — the largest metro network built in a single phase and the world's longest fully automated driverless system. The Blue, Yellow and Purple lines opened on 1 December 2024, the Red and Green on 15 December, and the Orange on 5 January 2025, completing the network." },
  3579: { descEn: "Chengdu Metro phase 5 (10 projects, ~199.8 km).", detailEn: "Chengdu's fifth-phase plan covers 10 projects totalling about 199.8 km, including extensions of lines 5, 9, 10, 12, 16, 18, 20, 22, 23 and 27. Several have entered tendering, with Sichuan's 15th Five-Year rail plan budgeting over 100 billion yuan." },
  876: { descEn: "India's first national green-hydrogen hub, inaugurated by Modi in 2025.", detailEn: "Near Visakhapatnam at Pudimadaka, Andhra Pradesh, NTPC Green Energy and the state government plan 20 GW of renewables producing 1,500 tonnes of green hydrogen a day plus green methanol, urea and SAF. PM Modi laid the foundation stone in January 2025, with core phase-1 infrastructure targeted for 2026." },
  2653: { descEn: "Melbourne's underground orbital rail, connecting radial lines.", detailEn: "The Suburban Rail Loop East (SRL East) is a ~26 km fully underground railway from Cheltenham to Box Hill, linking south-eastern radial lines with universities and medical centres. At about A$34 billion with tunnelling from 2025, it is the largest public-transport project in Victoria's history." },
  1982: { descEn: "The longest cross-border subsea HVDC for green power.", detailEn: "This link sends green power from a giant solar-plus-storage plant in Australia's Northern Territory to Singapore via a ~4,300 km subsea HVDC cable, able to supply ~1.75 GW — nearly a tenth of Singapore's demand. It won conditional Singapore EMA approval in October 2024 and an Indonesian route permit in 2025 (with a ~$2.5 billion Indonesian investment pledge), targeting power from 2035." },
  2950: { descEn: "A 3,631-mile 765 kV backbone across nine Midwest states.", detailEn: "Approved by MISO in December 2024, this package of 24 projects and 323 facilities builds a 3,631-mile 765 kV backbone across nine states, with benefits possibly exceeding $72 billion. Together with phase 1 it totals about $32 billion, with projects entering service in 2032-2034." },
  1189: { descEn: "A Saudi offshore mega-expansion, online in late 2025.", detailEn: "Marjan is a giant offshore field straddling the Saudi-Iran median line; its increment adds GOSP-4, 24 offshore platforms and export lines, raising capacity by 300,000 to about 800,000 barrels a day of Arabian Medium crude, with the Tanajib gas plant processing associated gas. Both started up together in December 2025 — a pillar of Saudi Arabia's 12-million-barrel maximum sustainable capacity." },
  2067: { descEn: "Indonesia's largest LNG project in development (Abadi).", detailEn: "INPEX's Abadi LNG in the Masela block, at about $21 billion, will build a 9.5 MTPA liquefaction plant. It received Indonesian environmental approval in February 2026, with FID set for 2026 and start-up targeted for 2030; it has signed LNG offtake heads of agreement with bp, PGN, PLN and Shell and is seeking up to $14 billion in project finance, with construction tenders from mid-2026." },
  281: { descEn: "France's largest single data-centre investment commitment.", detailEn: "In February 2025 Brookfield and Data4 announced over $20.7 billion over five years to develop AI data-centre infrastructure in France, covering several campuses around Paris in line with the French government's AI strategy." },
  361: { descEn: "A $20 billion landmark LNG project, fully restarting in 2026.", detailEn: "Taking FID in 2019 at Afungi in Cabo Delgado, Mozambique, this 13 MTPA project was about 40% complete when suspended in 2021 due to armed conflict. Full restart was announced on 29 January 2026, remobilising over 4,000 workers, with first LNG in 2029." },
  500: { descEn: "Meta's 5 GW Hyperion AI super-data-centre in Louisiana.", detailEn: "Meta is building the Hyperion AI super-data-centre in Richland Parish, Louisiana — over 4,000 acres planned for up to 5 GW (a 1.5 GW first phase by end-2027), with 10 gas plants and 2.5 GW of renewables. Built by Turner/DPR/Mortenson, it began construction in 2025." },
  585: { descEn: "Europe's largest planned AI campus, nuclear-powered.", detailEn: "Announced at the May 2025 'Choose France' summit, MGX, Bpifrance, Mistral AI and Nvidia formed a joint venture to build Europe's largest AI campus in the Paris region — a 1.4 GW first phase from late 2026, operating in 2028, expanded in June 2026 to 3 GW nationwide, running on low-carbon nuclear power." },
  592: { descEn: "A $20 billion Qatar sovereign-AI JV with Brookfield.", detailEn: "The Qatar Investment Authority's Qai, established in December 2025, formed a $20 billion joint venture with Brookfield to build integrated computing campuses in Qatar and strategic markets, leveraging Qatar's gas resources and its location at the crossroads of Europe, Asia and Africa." },
  1025: { descEn: "A new line at the world's largest fab campus.", detailEn: "Pyeongtaek is the world's largest semiconductor campus; its fourth fab P4 is being converted from foundry to a dedicated sixth-generation 1c DRAM line of about 80,000 wafers/month, also for HBM4. Conversion runs from late 2025 with production expected in 2026, plus some NAND lines switched to DRAM for AI servers; the campus consumes billions of kWh a year." },
  1028: { descEn: "A mega-expansion by China's leading DRAM maker.", detailEn: "CXMT is building a 12-inch DRAM mega-fab in Lingang, Shanghai, planned for 400,000-600,000 wafers/month — 2-3 times its Hefei headquarters — focused on high-end DDR5, LPDDR5X and HBM3 (a dedicated 50,000 wafers/month), advancing equipment localisation. It moved into substantive progress in March 2026, with tool install in the second half, mass production in 2027 and full capacity in 2028 — a huge new industrial load on the Lingang grid." },
  1761: { descEn: "A new 420 MW hyperscale campus in Jundiaí, São Paulo.", detailEn: "In October 2025 Scala announced a new data-centre campus in Jundiaí planned for 420 MW, with up to $20 billion including direct customer investment, separate from its Tamboré and Eldorado campuses. Creating about 2,500 construction jobs, it is positioned as a Latin American AI-computing and sustainability hub, phasing into service from 2027." },
  2652: { descEn: "A 1,700 km freight rail spine along Australia's east coast.", detailEn: "Inland Rail is a 1,700+ km freight network linking Melbourne and Brisbane at about A$31 billion, built in segments. Using an inland corridor to cut east-coast freight times and improve supply chains, some segments are open and the Melbourne-Parkes section continues — Australia's largest rail project." },
  2659: { descEn: "Australia's largest undeveloped gas field, backfilling the North West Shelf.", detailEn: "In the Browse Basin off Western Australia, this is one of Australia's largest undeveloped conventional gas resources, planned to backfill the existing North West Shelf (NWS) Karratha plant via a subsea pipeline to extend its LNG exports. Subject to environmental approval, it advanced assessment and commercial arrangements in 2025, targeting the 2030s." },
  2739: { descEn: "The EU's €20 billion plan for 4-5 AI 'gigafactories'.", detailEn: "The European Commission proposed in 2025 to invest €20 billion in 4-5 AI 'gigafactories' as an anchor to leverage €200 billion of AI investment. A call for interest drew 76 applications across 60 sites in 16 countries proposing over €230 billion; the formal tender slipped to early 2026, aiming to build a sovereign European AI computing base." },
  2826: { descEn: "Turkey's first nuclear power station (4×VVER-1200).", detailEn: "At Akkuyu in Mersin province, southern Turkey, Russia's Rosatom is building four 1.2 GW VVER-1200 reactors on a build-own-operate basis — Turkey's first nuclear plant, at about $20 billion. Russia added ~$9 billion of financing in 2025, with the first unit aiming to start generating in 2026, eventually supplying about 10% of Turkey's electricity." },
  3026: { descEn: "A 15.6 km new metro line across central Toronto.", detailEn: "The Ontario Line runs 15.6 km from Exhibition Place through downtown to Don Mills (connecting to Line 5), adding 15 stations, at about C$27 billion with over C$4 billion of federal funding. Twin tunnel boring in the downtown section launched in April 2026, with heavy works at four eastern stations, targeting completion in 2031." },
  3580: { descEn: "Chongqing Metro phase 5 (~200 km new lines).", detailEn: "Chongqing's fifth-phase plan adds about 200 km of new lines, with eight lines (including Line 16 phase 1 and several extensions) entering feasibility studies, aiming to bring lines under construction and operating to 850 km. Preliminary phase-5 research will be carried out during the 15th Five-Year period." },
  1542: { descEn: "The world's largest helium source, reaching full capacity in 2025.", detailEn: "The Amur Gas Processing Plant treats gas from the Power of Siberia pipeline across six 7-bcm trains; the fourth came online in 2024 and full design capacity of 42 bcm/year was reached in 2025. At capacity it yields 2.4 million tonnes of ethane, 1.5 million tonnes of LPG and 60 million m³ of helium a year — the world's largest helium base — feeding ethane to the neighbouring Amur GCC." },
  1191: { descEn: "South America's largest shale play, breaking output records in 2025.", detailEn: "In Argentina's Neuquén province, Vaca Muerta is the largest shale oil-and-gas play outside North America. In October 2025 Argentine crude output hit a record 859,500 barrels a day, with Vaca Muerta shale oil ~570,000 b/d, about two-thirds of the nation's total. With 38-40 rigs and over $18 billion of 2025-26 investment, it could top a million barrels a day before 2028, ranking among the world's top three shale plays." },
  2916: { descEn: "A 2,250 MW hydro plant on the Churchill River, Labrador.", detailEn: "On the Churchill River in Newfoundland and Labrador, Gull Island is a 2,250 MW plant with a financed total cost of about C$24.9 billion, a JV of Newfoundland Hydro (60%) and Hydro-Québec (40%) arising from the two provinces' landmark December 2024 memorandum, targeting operation in 2035." },
  2926: { descEn: "A 17-year, up-to-1,920 MW PPA from Talen to power AWS.", detailEn: "In June 2025 Talen and Amazon reached a 17-year, up-to-1,920 MW carbon-free power deal, shifting from a behind-the-meter to a front-of-meter grid structure, with Talen becoming a licensed retail supplier for AWS in Pennsylvania; the two also explore new on-site SMRs and uprates." },
  3499: { descEn: "CXMT Hefei phase-2 DRAM, China's bid for global #4.", detailEn: "CXMT is directing about 130 billion yuan of IPO proceeds into phase-2 wafer manufacturing, pushing its Hefei headquarters toward ~300,000 wafers/month by end-2025 (up ~50% year on year). The phase-2 building is under way and moving to the next process node, consolidating its position as the world's fourth-largest DRAM maker." },
  1179: { descEn: "The finale of Qatar's LNG expansion (North Field West).", detailEn: "The North Field West (NFW) project caps QatarEnergy's North Field expansions, with two 8-MTPA mega-trains adding ~16 million tonnes a year to push Qatar's total toward 142 million tonnes by the 2030s. In February 2026 the onshore liquefaction EPC was awarded to a Technip Energies-led consortium, with first cargo expected by end-2031." },
  1206: { descEn: "The world's largest coal-chemical project under construction.", detailEn: "In the Qingshui Industrial Park of Yulin, Shaanxi, this is the world's largest coal-chemical project under construction, with planned total investment of 126.2 billion yuan over ~13 km² converting 24+ million tonnes of coal a year. Phase 1 focuses on coal-to-ethylene-glycol and phase 2 (~175.9 billion yuan) on coal-to-olefins/aromatics and high-value materials; by September 2025 most phase-2 basic design and long-lead procurement were complete, aiming for a trillion-yuan coal-chemical cluster." },
  1403: { descEn: "Baghdad's first metro network (7 lines, 148 km).", detailEn: "In July 2024 an international consortium (Alstom, Systra, SNCF, Talgo, SENER and Deutsche Bank) won a $17.5 billion contract to build the Baghdad metro on a DBOMFT basis — 7 lines, 148 km and 64 stations, targeting May 2029. In July 2025 the government decided to reassess the financial and technical terms." },
  3220: { descEn: "Microsoft's largest India data-centre region (Hyderabad).", detailEn: "Microsoft announced in 2025 a $17.5 billion four-year (2026-2029) investment to expand AI and cloud infrastructure in India, on top of an earlier $3 billion pledge. Its new Hyderabad region has three availability zones and will be Microsoft's largest in India, due mid-2026, with more land bought in Pune." },
  248: { descEn: "Samsung's largest US investment: an advanced-process fab.", detailEn: "At Taylor, Texas, Samsung's first phase is about $17 billion (eventually up to $44 billion); the main structure was finished by late 2024, with EUV tools installed and risk production in 2026, and Tesla has contracted to use its AI-chip capacity." },
});

/* ===== 批次3：全库投资额 TOP（约 110–170 亿美元）===== */
Object.assign(window.ENERGY_EN, {
  1217: { descEn: "A large new refinery on Mexico's Gulf coast.", detailEn: "At the Dos Bocas port in Paraíso, Tabasco, Pemex's Olmeca refinery is designed for 340,000 barrels a day, producing gasoline and diesel in phases from 2024. By late 2025/early 2026 two crude trains were running at a combined ~320,000 b/d, nearing full capacity by end-2026 — a flagship of Mexico's drive for fuel self-sufficiency." },
  1401: { descEn: "A rail-and-road corridor from Faw port to the Turkish border.", detailEn: "The Development Road is a 1,200 km rail-plus-road corridor linking Iraq's southern Grand Faw Port to the Turkish border, at about $17 billion, intended as an alternative route from the Gulf to Europe. By December 2025 the rail design was ~87% and the road ~73% complete; in September 2025 Iraq said a first Basra-Baghdad high-speed section would be built by 2031." },
  2654: { descEn: "Victoria's largest road project, with a double-deck tunnel.", detailEn: "Melbourne's North East Link includes a ~6.5 km double-deck tunnel connecting the Eastern Freeway with the M80 Ring Road — the largest road project in Victoria's history at about A$26 billion. Tunnelling advanced in 2025, with opening planned for 2028 to ease north-eastern congestion." },
  2805: { descEn: "New Czech nuclear: Korea's KHNP wins two APR1000 units.", detailEn: "At Dukovany in the Czech Republic, Korea's KHNP won the contract to build two 1 GW APR1000 reactors, signed in June 2025 — a major breakthrough for Korean nuclear in Europe — with the first unit targeted around 2036 to strengthen low-carbon baseload supply." },
  3440: { descEn: "CNNC's fusion-industry platform, launched in Shanghai in 2025.", detailEn: "China National Nuclear Corporation renamed and restructured its former fuel arm into China Fusion Energy Co., listed in Shanghai in July 2025 as CNNC's fusion-industry vehicle and investment platform. CNNC, China National Nuclear Power, Zhejiang Energy and others injected about 11.5 billion yuan, accelerating fusion commercialisation by the national team." },
  3583: { descEn: "Yulong Island phase 2, toward a 40-million-tonne refining base.", detailEn: "The Yulong Island integrated refining-petrochemical base in Longkou, Shandong is planned at 40 million tonnes/year in two phases; phase 1 (20 million tonnes of refining + 3 million tonnes of ethylene) started up in 2024-2025. Phase 2 adds another ~20-million-tonne complex, part of Shandong's high-end chemical base, making Yulong Island China's largest single refining-petrochemical base." },
  1145: { descEn: "The core of New York's Gateway program; TBM contract awarded in 2025.", detailEn: "The Hudson Tunnel is the core of the Gateway program's phase 1, building a 3.8 km twin-track rail tunnel under the Hudson River and rehabilitating the century-old, hurricane-damaged existing tunnels, at about $16.1 billion — key to relieving the Northeast Corridor bottleneck. In February 2025 the Gateway Commission awarded a $1.29 billion Hudson River TBM contract (Traylor/Walsh/Skanska), completing all tunnelling contracts, with boring due to begin in spring 2026." },
  511: { descEn: "A Stargate site in Santa Teresa, New Mexico (up to 4.5 GW).", detailEn: "Project Jupiter in Doña Ana County, New Mexico (near El Paso) spans 1,400 acres and four buildings, developed by Stack Infrastructure, leased 18 years by Oracle and mainly used by OpenAI; the county approved $165 billion in industrial revenue bonds — the largest such authorisation for a single US AI data centre to date." },
  512: { descEn: "Stargate's newest site, in Saline Township, Michigan.", detailEn: "OpenAI, Oracle and Related Digital are developing the Stargate campus (codenamed The Barn) in Saline Township, Washtenaw County, Michigan — three 550,000 sq ft buildings exceeding 1 GW — breaking ground on 1 June 2026 with water-saving closed-loop cooling, the largest investment project in Michigan to date." },
  1029: { descEn: "A $16 billion US reshoring expansion.", detailEn: "In January 2025 GlobalFoundries announced $16 billion to expand mature and specialty manufacturing, advanced packaging and silicon photonics in Malta, New York and Vermont, addressing AI's need for power-efficient, high-bandwidth chips, with a new advanced-packaging and photonics centre in New York. The Malta fab has drawn over $16 billion since 2011 and ~2,500 staff — a major local grid customer." },
  1030: { descEn: "The first fab of the world's largest mega-fab cluster.", detailEn: "SK hynix is building a four-fab mega-cluster on a 4.15 million m² site in Yongin, Gyeonggi — billed as the world's largest mega-fab. The first fab broke ground in February 2025 with planned investment of ~21.6 trillion won, due to complete and produce in 2027; the cluster is a huge new power and water node for Korean semiconductors." },
  1143: { descEn: "Set to be the world's longest suspension bridge.", detailEn: "The Strait of Messina Bridge would link Sicily to mainland Italy with a 3,300 m main span — the world's longest suspension span — carrying road and rail. On 6 August 2025 Italy's CIPESS approved the final design, enabling the Webuild-led Eurolink contract (€10.6 billion supplement); works are planned from late 2025 toward 2032 completion, though the Court of Auditors declined to register the decision in October, leaving it not yet formally in force." },
  285: { descEn: "India's largest AI data-centre park.", detailEn: "Adani, via AdaniConneX with Google, is developing India's largest AI data-centre park at Visakhapatnam, Andhra Pradesh — $15 billion, a 1 GW first phase built in 2026-2030 and 5 GW long term, with renewable power." },
  365: { descEn: "An Indigenous-owned floating LNG project in Canada.", detailEn: "Developed by the Nisga'a Nation with Rockies LNG and Western LNG, Ksi Lisims won federal and provincial approval in September 2025 for two floating liquefaction units totalling 12 million tonnes/year, with 5 million tonnes of long-term offtake signed with TotalEnergies, Shell and SEFE; FID is targeted for 2026." },
  505: { descEn: "Amazon's AI data-centre phase-2 expansion in northwest Indiana.", detailEn: "In November 2025 Amazon announced an additional $15 billion for new campuses in northwest Indiana, adding 2.4 GW and up to 22 buildings from 2026 across LaPorte and other counties — the largest construction project in Indiana's history." },
  510: { descEn: "A Stargate Midwest site at Port Washington, Wisconsin.", detailEn: "The Lighthouse campus, developed by OpenAI, Oracle and Vantage at Port Washington north of Milwaukee, comprises four data centres totalling nearly 1 GW, breaking ground in December 2025 for 2028 completion and creating over 4,000 union construction jobs." },
  1135: { descEn: "West Africa's largest integrated mining rail-and-port project.", detailEn: "The Simandou project built a 600+ km multipurpose trans-Guinea railway linking the south-eastern iron-ore zone to a new barging and trans-shipment port on the Atlantic. It opened in early November 2025 with the first export — 9,850 tonnes shipped from Morebaya port on a Winning barge. At capacity the WCS and Rio Tinto/SimFer operations can export 120 million tonnes a year, making Guinea a major supplier of high-grade iron ore; the infrastructure is operated by the JV company CTG." },
  1404: { descEn: "A national railway linking Oman's main ports and cities.", detailEn: "Oman National Railway plans about 2,224 km and 46 stations linking Sohar, Muscat, Duqm and Salalah, at about $15 billion, led by ASYAD's Oman Rail with AIIB financing. Phases include Sohar-Muscat (242 km), Muscat-Duqm (486 km) and Duqm-Salalah (646 km)." },
  1755: { descEn: "A 6.5 GW offshore wind project off Rio Grande do Sul.", detailEn: "Ventos do Sul, ~21 km off Rio Grande do Sul and developed by Ocean Winds, is planned at up to 6.5 GW — one of the largest offshore wind projects in Brazil's pipeline — alongside the 700 MW Tramandaí project nearby. It is seeking preliminary permits from IBAMA, awaiting Brazil's first offshore-area auction (planned 2027)." },
  1869: { descEn: "A Red Sea green hydrogen/ammonia hub, nearly twice NEOM's size.", detailEn: "The first phase of the ACWA Power-EnBW Yanbu green-hydrogen hub on the Red Sea, with its own renewables, desalination and export jetty, has 4 GW of electrolysers producing 400,000 tonnes of green hydrogen and 2.2 million tonnes of green ammonia a year — about twice the NEOM project under construction. FEED by Técnicas Reunidas and Sinopec is due mid-2026, with FID in 2026 and start-up in 2030." },
  2057: { descEn: "A giant reclaimed-land airport north of Manila in Bulacan.", detailEn: "On the Bulacan coast ~35 km north of Manila, San Miguel Corporation (SMC) is developing this airport under a ~734 billion-peso concession with four runways. A Manila Bay sand-mining ban pushed phase 1 back a year; SMC commits to start the passenger terminal in January 2026, targeting opening in November 2028 with ~35 million passengers a year to relieve NAIA." },
  2063: { descEn: "The world's largest fully automated container port.", detailEn: "Singapore's largest-ever infrastructure project, Tuas Port is reclaimed in four phases for an eventual 65 million TEU a year — the world's largest single fully automated container terminal. In May 2025 it hit a 10-million-box milestone using 200 fast-charging automated guided vehicles, progressively consolidating city berths like Tanjong Pagar, with full completion in the 2040s." },
  2068: { descEn: "Deepwater gas fields in East Kalimantan feeding Bontang LNG.", detailEn: "In March 2026 Eni took a double FID on the deepwater Geng North-Gehem (North Hub) and Gendalo-Gandang (South Hub) gas clusters in Indonesia's Kutai Basin, at about $15 billion. Using the Jangkrik FPU and existing Bontang LNG facilities, the North Hub adds an FPSO (>1 Bcf/d, 90,000 b/d condensate), targeting 2028 start-up, a 2 Bcf/d peak in 2029 and the restart of an idle Bontang train." },
  3005: { descEn: "A 1.8 GW, 40-building data-centre campus in Buckeye, Arizona.", detailEn: "In August 2024 Tract acquired ~2,069 acres in Buckeye — one of the largest single data-centre land purchases in the US — planning up to 20 million sq ft and 40 facilities, with 1.8 GW delivered by the local utility over multi-phase construction lasting up to 15 years." },
  3037: { descEn: "A Pacific-coast LNG project in Sonora, advancing toward FID.", detailEn: "At Puerto Libertad in Sonora, Mexico, this 30-million-tonne/year project is pushing for a phase-1 FID (three 5-million-tonne trains), with gas from the Permian's Waha hub via the Saguaro Connector and Sierra Madre pipelines, arranging ~$15 billion of financing with MUFG, Santander and JPMorgan." },
  3207: { descEn: "A 3-million-tonne greenfield aluminium smelter in Odisha with captive power.", detailEn: "Vedanta Aluminium is building a greenfield integrated aluminium plant near Kamakhyanagar in Dhenkanal, Odisha on 1,447 acres, with 3 million tonnes/year of smelting and a 4,900 MW captive power station, at about 1.3 trillion rupees — set to be one of the world's largest aluminium smelters, approved at Odisha's 41st high-level clearance and expected to create 30,000 jobs." },
  1024: { descEn: "An HBM-focused fab for the AI era.", detailEn: "M15X is SK hynix's new 12-inch fab in Cheongju, with over 20 trillion won of investment focused on HBM and next-generation DRAM to meet AI-driven high-bandwidth memory demand, lifting HBM capacity by ~20-30%. The building was completed in November 2025 with tool move-in from December — a huge new industrial load on Cheongju's grid." },
  3253: { descEn: "An ~865 km Delhi-Varanasi high-speed railway.", detailEn: "The DVHSR is designed for 350 km/h over 865 km, including a 135 km Ayodhya/Lucknow spur and ~12 stations, at about 1.21 trillion rupees. NHSRCL has submitted the DPR to the Railway Ministry; the most advanced of the new HSR corridors, it would cut Delhi-Varanasi to ~4-4.5 hours." },
  3565: { descEn: "A road-rail sea crossing set to be China's longest sea bridge.", detailEn: "About 70 km long — longer than the Hong Kong-Zhuhai-Macao Bridge — this combined road-and-rail crossing (carrying cars and 350 km/h high-speed rail) east of the Hangzhou Bay Bridge would cost about 100 billion yuan. Included in the national 15th Five-Year Plan and Zhejiang's plan, it would put Shanghai-Ningbo high-speed rail within a half-hour." },
  1171: { descEn: "A large export LNG expansion on the Texas Gulf coast.", detailEn: "Sempra's phase-2 expansion of its Port Arthur, Texas LNG base adds two liquefaction trains and storage for ~13 million tonnes a year nameplate. It reached FID in September 2025, with Blackstone leading equity and ConocoPhillips as anchor buyer, targeting 2030-2031 start-up — an important addition to US LNG supply to Europe and Asia." },
  1222: { descEn: "Aramco exits; Petronas takes full ownership of the RAPID complex.", detailEn: "At the Pengerang complex in Johor, Malaysia, the RAPID integrated base pairs a 300,000 b/d refinery with large petrochemicals. In May 2026 Saudi Aramco announced its exit, transferring its stake to Petronas so PRefChem becomes a wholly-owned Petronas subsidiary; Aramco had invested ~$7 billion for 50% in 2017. The plant resumed operation after a 2025 gasoline-unit turnaround and brief RFCC shutdown." },
  1549: { descEn: "A cornerstone gas field for the Irkutsk region, full capacity in 2027.", detailEn: "Kovykta started up in late 2022 with the Kovykta-Chayanda section of the Power of Siberia pipeline; with ~1.8 trillion m³ of reserves and 27 bcm/year design output, it is the cornerstone of the Irkutsk gas zone. Power of Siberia reached its 38 bcm design capacity in 2025, and in September 2025 Russia and China agreed to raise supply to 44 bcm, with the pipeline at full capacity in 2027." },
  2809: { descEn: "Two new AP1000 units in Bulgaria.", detailEn: "At Kozloduy on the Danube in Bulgaria, two 1.1 GW Westinghouse AP1000 reactors are planned, advancing engineering contracts and financing in 2025 to replace retiring units and strengthen low-carbon baseload supply in southeastern Europe, targeting the mid-2030s." },
  2811: { descEn: "A series-build base for the Hualong One reactor; unit 2 online in 2026.", detailEn: "At Zhangzhou in Fujian, this base uses China's home-grown third-generation 'Hualong One' reactor, with six 1.2 GW units planned. Unit 1 started up in 2024 and unit 2 connected in November 2025 and entered commercial operation on 1 January 2026, with more units following — the flagship for series, scaled Hualong One construction." },
  1011: { descEn: "Toyota's first battery plant outside Japan, online in November 2025.", detailEn: "On an ~1,850-acre mega-site in Liberty/Randolph County, North Carolina, this nearly $13.9 billion plant is Toyota's 11th globally and its only battery plant outside Japan. Planned for 14 lines and ~30 GWh supplying HEV/PHEV/BEV batteries across ~7 million sq ft, it is a regional-scale power user creating up to 5,100 jobs; it began production on 12 November 2025, first making hybrid batteries." },
  1199: { descEn: "BASF's third-largest global site; core units online in late 2025.", detailEn: "On Donghai Island in Zhanjiang, Guangdong, this is BASF's largest overseas wholly-owned investment at about €10 billion, set to become its third-largest global site with 30+ lines and 100+ products. The core is a 1-million-tonne/year steam cracker with integrated downstream; the first core-unit products started in November 2025 with 100% green-power supply, serving autos, electronics, new energy and food packaging." },
  4212: { descEn: "China's largest private overseas investment; PMB refining phase 2 in Brunei.", detailEn: "Hengyi's PMB project on Pulau Muara Besar, Brunei has a ~$13.65 billion phase 2 adding 14 million tonnes/year of refining, 1.65 million tonnes of ethylene, 2 million tonnes of paraxylene and downstream PTA/PET, fully to Chinese standards. Phase 1 started up in 2019; phase 2 was confirmed in early 2026 with ~3-year construction, with CPECC-system engineering firms involved in design and EPC." },
  102: { descEn: "Inner Mongolia's first 10-GW-class desert wind-and-solar base.", detailEn: "This base plans 8 GW of solar and 4 GW of wind, with 4 GW of supporting coal power and 5 GWh of storage, at 98.8 billion yuan. A 2 GW pilot solar phase is connected, with the ±800 kV 'Ordos-Cangzhou' UHV line as export; full construction began in September 2025, targeting completion by end-2027." },
  2081: { descEn: "PMB refining phase 2, a flagship China-Brunei joint venture.", detailEn: "Hengyi Petrochemical's phase-2 refining-petrochemical project on Pulau Muara Besar (PMB), Brunei fully launched in January 2026 with a ~$13.6 billion package (Bank Islam Brunei financing and tax incentives). It adds a 1.65-million-tonne/year naphtha cracker and PE/PP units (Brunei's first polymer plant) and expands PTA/PET, lifting total refining capacity to 20 million tonnes/year (~400,000 b/d); completion is planned for end-2028 and start-up in 2029, adding over 2,000 jobs." },
  1220: { descEn: "A major Russia-to-China gas artery via Mongolia.", detailEn: "Advanced by Gazprom and CNPC, Power of Siberia 2 would carry West Siberian gas via the ~963 km Soyuz Vostok section through Mongolia to China, with 50 bcm/year design capacity over a term of up to 30 years. In September 2025 Russia and China signed a legally binding memorandum in Beijing — the project's biggest progress in years — though the sales contract and pricing remain unsettled, with the Mongolian section targeted for 2027-2028." },
  3554: { descEn: "A new 350 km/h line from Hunan to Guangzhou, starting 2026.", detailEn: "About 390 km at 350 km/h and ~95.1 billion yuan, this line runs from Yongzhou via Lianzhou and Qingyuan to north Guangzhou. It would cut Yongzhou-Guangzhou from 3h10 to 1.5 hours, strengthening links between southern Hunan and the Greater Bay Area; both Hunan and Guangdong have set 2026 construction starts." },
  309: { descEn: "India's first high-speed rail, using Japanese Shinkansen technology.", detailEn: "Using Japan's E5 Shinkansen technology, this 508 km, 320 km/h line with 12 stations is 88% financed by JICA soft loans. Civil works were 56% complete by early 2026, with the first Surat-Bilimora section likely to open in 2026." },
  322: { descEn: "A core rail-capacity project for Brisbane.", detailEn: "Cross River Rail is 10.2 km including a 5.9 km twin-track tunnel under the Brisbane River and CBD with four new underground stations, with costs rising from A$5.4 billion to over A$17 billion and opening pushed to 2029." },
  582: { descEn: "Europe's largest dedicated AI data centre, at Blyth, Northumberland.", detailEn: "Blackstone's QTS is investing about £10 billion at Blyth in Northumberland, England, building a 540,000+ m² hyperscale AI campus with 10 data halls on the former Britishvolt battery site; approved in 2025, it would become Europe's largest dedicated hyperscale AI data centre when built." },
  833: { descEn: "World Bank backing to revive the Grand Inga hydropower scheme.", detailEn: "At the Inga Falls on the Congo River in DR Congo, Inga III is planned at ~4.8 GW, with full Grand Inga development reaching 44 GW. In June 2025 the World Bank approved $250 million of first-phase credit for preparatory studies and the AFD signed technical support in 2026; total investment exceeds $10 billion, with no FID yet." },
  1141: { descEn: "A 57.5 km cross-Alps tunnel; main-tunnel boring began in 2025.", detailEn: "The Lyon-Turin base tunnel is the core of Europe's Mediterranean corridor, with a 57.5 km main tunnel that will rank among the world's longest rail tunnels. TBM Viviana was unveiled at Saint-Martin-la-Porte on 1 April 2025 and the first French-side machine began boring at La Praz in July; by late October ~45.3 km was excavated. Seven TBMs will ultimately bore 75% of the base tunnel, shifting France-Italy freight from road to rail, with Italian-side boring expected in 2027." },
  1142: { descEn: "The UK's largest road-tunnel project; approved and funded in 2025.", detailEn: "The Lower Thames Crossing is Britain's largest road-tunnel project — 23 km linking Kent's A2/M2 with Essex's A13/M25, centred on a 4.2 km twin-bore tunnel under the Thames (the UK's longest road tunnel) to relieve the Dartford Crossing. The Development Consent Order was approved on 25 March 2025; the government committed £590 million in June and a further £891 million in November for the public share, with private finance to follow and early works from March 2026." },
  1176: { descEn: "A new LNG export train for Papua New Guinea.", detailEn: "Led by TotalEnergies with ExxonMobil and Santos, Papua LNG would pipe gas ~320 km to new electric-drive trains at the liquefaction base outside Port Moresby, exporting about 5.6 million tonnes a year. Environmental permits and EPC contracts came together in late 2025, with FID advancing to early 2026." },
  2269: { descEn: "A trans-Saharan gas pipeline from Nigeria via Niger to Algeria (30 bcm/year).", detailEn: "The long-planned Trans-Saharan Gas Pipeline (TSGP) aims to start construction in 2026, carrying Nigerian gas via Niger to Algeria and on to Europe, with 30 bcm/year design capacity. The Algerian section crosses the Hassi R'Mel hub into the existing export network — a flagship cross-border project to boost Algeria's supply to Europe, partly overlapping the SoutH2 hydrogen corridor." },
  2806: { descEn: "Hungary's nuclear expansion (2×VVER-1200).", detailEn: "At Paks in Hungary, Russia's Rosatom is building two 1.2 GW VVER-1200 reactors, pouring first concrete in February 2025 to enter main construction. The new government is reviewing financing and costs, but the project is advancing and will sharply raise Hungary's nuclear share." },
  2820: { descEn: "Bangladesh's first nuclear plant; fuel loading in 2026.", detailEn: "At Rooppur in Pabna, Bangladesh, Russia's Rosatom is building two 1.2 GW VVER-1200 reactors — Bangladesh's first nuclear plant, at about $12.7 billion. The first unit completes fuel loading in April-May 2026 and will start generating that year, marking Bangladesh's entry into the nuclear age." },
  2832: { descEn: "The West's first grid-scale small modular reactor.", detailEn: "At Darlington in Ontario, OPG is building four GE Hitachi BWRX-300 small modular reactors (~1.2 GW total); the first unit formally began construction in 2025 — the first grid-scale SMR in the G7/West. At about C$20.9 billion, the first unit targets 2030, providing a template for global BWRX-300 deployment." },
  2954: { descEn: "Texas's first 765 kV lines, strengthening Permian supply.", detailEn: "In April 2025 the Texas PUC approved the ERCOT Permian reliability plan, building the state's first 765 kV lines with three import paths. Driven by data centres, hydrogen and electrification, ERCOT's 2030 summer peak is projected above 150 GW." },
  3007: { descEn: "Microsoft's ~C$19 billion AI and cloud build in Canada (2023-2027).", detailEn: "In December 2025 Microsoft announced a landmark Canadian investment of ~C$19 billion over 2023-2027, including over C$7.5 billion in the next two years for new digital and AI infrastructure, with new capacity from late 2026 deepening cloud regions such as Toronto." },
  3054: { descEn: "One of the world's largest potash mines (~8.5 Mt/year across two phases).", detailEn: "BHP's giant Jansen potash project in Saskatchewan, Canada (phase 1 ~$8.4 billion, phase 2 $4.9 billion) doubles capacity to about 8.5 million tonnes. Phase 1 was ~68% complete in early 2026, with costs rising on inflation and first production pushed to mid-2027." },
  4211: { descEn: "Power of Siberia support: one of the world's largest gas-processing plants.", detailEn: "The Amur Gas Processing Plant (AGPP) in Russia's Amur region is key to Gazprom's east-route supply to China, processing 42 bcm of gas a year and extracting helium. The CPECC system (including HQC) executed the EPC for package 2 — six trains of gas drying, purification, fractionation and compression — worth about $2.52 billion, built in five stages with start-ups through 2024-2025." },
  4231: { descEn: "The world's largest ethylene complex; CNCEC FEED+EPC ~€12 billion.", detailEn: "The Baltic Chemical Complex (BCC) at Ust-Luga, Russia, invested by RusGasDobycha, is the world's largest integrated ethylene project, producing 2.8 million tonnes of ethylene and 2.88 million tonnes of polyethylene a year. China National Chemical Engineering signed the FEED+EPC contract in 2019 worth about €12 billion, using world-leading process technology." },
  1193: { descEn: "Stabroek's fifth development; first oil in 2026.", detailEn: "Uaru is ExxonMobil's fifth development in Guyana's Stabroek block, ~200 km offshore in 1,750 m of water with over 800 million barrels of recoverable reserves. The Errea Wittu FPSO (250,000 b/d, 2 million barrels storage) completed mooring pre-installation in February 2026, with first oil expected within the year, continuing Guyana's rapid offshore ramp-up." },
  3589: { descEn: "A 100-billion-yuan-class coal-to-liquids plant using world-first 2nd-gen direct technology.", detailEn: "In the Chahaquan park of Barkol, Hami, Xinjiang, this project plans ~170 billion yuan total (~90 billion for stage 1), with a 15-million-tonne/year open-pit mine feeding 19 units including 3.2 million tonnes/year of direct and 800,000 tonnes/year of indirect coal liquefaction — China's first to use home-grown second-generation direct coal-liquefaction technology. Started in October 2024 and in civil works, it targets completion by end-2027." },
  1185: { descEn: "Stabroek's fourth and highest-capacity FPSO.", detailEn: "About 200 km offshore in 1,800 m of water in Guyana's Stabroek block, this is ExxonMobil's fourth development there. The ONE GUYANA FPSO produced first oil on 8 August 2025, about four months ahead of plan, at 250,000 b/d and 2 million barrels storage, pushing Guyana's total above 900,000 b/d and cementing its status as an emerging major producer." },
  1833: { descEn: "Phase 2 of the Middle East's largest unconventional gas field, online 2027.", detailEn: "As phase 2 of Aramco's $100-billion-class Jafurah project, a ~$12.4 billion contract was signed in June 2024 adding ~1,350 million cubic feet/day of processing. Phase 1 saw first gas in December 2025; phase 2 is due in 2027, driving the field toward 2 bcf/d of sales gas and ~630,000 b/d of high-value liquids by 2030, supplying low-cost feedstock for blue hydrogen and petrochemicals." },
  348: { descEn: "A $12 billion China-Saudi integrated refining-petrochemical JV in Liaoning.", detailEn: "A JV of Saudi Aramco (30%), Norinco (51%) and Panjin Xincheng (19%), this complex in Panjin, Liaoning began in 2023 at about $12 billion, building 300,000 b/d of refining and 1.65 million tonnes of ethylene; ~60% complete in 2025 with start-up expected in 2026." },
  1023: { descEn: "Japan's national 2nm breakthrough fab.", detailEn: "In the Bibi industrial park of Chitose, Hokkaido, Rapidus is Japan's national push for 2nm, co-developing GAA transistors with IBM. It installed Japan's first production-grade ASML EUV in late 2024, started a pilot line in April 2025 and announced working 2nm GAA transistors in July; the advanced EUV fab is a very-high-density grid load, targeting mass production in 2027." },
  1144: { descEn: "The first true US high-speed rail, along the I-15 corridor.", detailEn: "Brightline West is the first true US high-speed railway, ~350 km along the I-15 median linking Las Vegas and Rancho Cucamonga in Southern California, with all-electric trains over 300 km/h covering the route in about 2h10. Backed by a $3 billion federal grant and private activity bonds, it ran geotechnical drilling and surveys along I-15 through 2025; the Las Vegas station garage takes shape in early 2026, with heavy rail construction from April 2026 toward a late-2029 opening." },
  1158: { descEn: "A 1,500 km heavy-haul freight corridor from JNPT to Dadri.", detailEn: "Built by DFCCIL, the Western Dedicated Freight Corridor runs 1,506 km from Mumbai's JNPT to Dadri near Delhi — a double-track electrified heavy-haul line for containers and bulk that, with the eastern corridor, is reshaping Indian rail freight. After the JNPT-Vaitarna section was commissioned on 31 March 2026, DFCCIL declared the Western corridor fully open; ~96.4% of the two corridors' 2,843 km is now in service, sharply raising daily freight trains." },
  1175: { descEn: "A large WA gas-liquefaction expansion.", detailEn: "Woodside's Scarborough gas field is piped to a new Train 2 at the Pluto base in Karratha, ~5 million tonnes/year, with Train 1 modified for lean gas. By early 2026 it was over 96% complete, with 56,000-tonne modules delivered from Batam, Indonesia, sprinting to start-up — an important new WA LNG supply to Asia." },
  1754: { descEn: "A 5 GW giant offshore wind project off Rio de Janeiro.", detailEn: "Developed by OW Brasil (Ocean Winds, a 50/50 EDPR-ENGIE JV) in the South Atlantic off Rio de Janeiro, this 5 GW project with 371 13.5 MW turbines is one of Brazil's largest offshore wind projects under review. Ocean Winds has ~15 GW planned in Brazil (including Ventos do Sul 6.5 GW and Tramandaí 700 MW) and is seeking a preliminary licence from IBAMA, awaiting the offshore-area auction." },
  1900: { descEn: "A 45-billion-riyal Jeddah transit plan with a four-line light-rail network.", detailEn: "Saudi Arabia's cabinet approved a ~$12 billion (45 billion-riyal) Jeddah transport master plan with a 108 km light-rail network. The first Blue Line (~35 km) links King Abdulaziz International Airport to the Haramain high-speed station, and the Orange Line runs ~44.8 km along Medina and Old Mecca roads. Blue Line design tenders were issued in January 2026 (closing March), targeting operation before the 2034 World Cup, with Foster + Partners involved in design." },
  2071: { descEn: "Southwest offshore gas plus pipeline supplying the Ca Mau power complex.", detailEn: "The Block B (48/95 and 52/97) offshore gas field is piped ~400 km to the O Mon power complex in Ca Mau, Vietnam, with the value chain totalling nearly $12 billion. FID was taken on 28 March 2024 for ~490 million cubic feet/day; Petrovietnam has secured a $1 billion loan from Vietcombank. The central processing platform was completed in 2025, with first gas planned for Q3 2027." },
  2642: { descEn: "Microsoft's A$25 billion Australian cloud and AI supercomputing expansion.", detailEn: "In April 2026 Microsoft announced about A$25 billion to build new Azure AI supercomputing capacity in Australia and expand existing data centres by ~140%, concentrated around Western Sydney. The investment is ~1.9 times AWS's A$13.2 billion pledge, aimed at sovereign cloud and GPU-intensive AI workloads." },
  3116: { descEn: "A Gujarat green hydrogen/ammonia hub, about $12 billion.", detailEn: "At the Deendayal Port Authority in Kandla, Gujarat, Reliance, L&T, Greenko and Welspun New Energy are developing a ~$12 billion hub producing 1.4 million tonnes of green hydrogen and 7 million tonnes of green ammonia a year — a flagship cluster of India's National Green Hydrogen Mission, aimed at fertiliser and export." },
  3218: { descEn: "Planned 2.5 GW — potentially India's largest single data-centre park.", detailEn: "At Davos in January 2026, Lodha and Maharashtra signed to build a 2.5 GW data-centre park (about 1.3 trillion rupees) on ~350 acres of a 5,000-acre Palava site, expected to create over 16,000 jobs; Amazon has bought land and locked in 15-year power, and STT GDC has also acquired land." },
  3255: { descEn: "An ~1,738 km east-west freight corridor (planned).", detailEn: "The East-West Dedicated Freight Corridor (EWDFC) is planned for ~1,738 km from Palghar in Maharashtra to Dankuni in West Bengal; its DPR was sent to the Railway Board in July 2024 and remained under review as of November 2025, not yet sanctioned." },
  1114: { descEn: "A high-speed trunk line in the Chengdu-Chongqing Yangtze corridor.", detailEn: "The Chengda-Wan high-speed railway, part of the national Yangtze corridor, is designed for 350 km/h at about 85.1 billion yuan. It entered ballastless-track works in April 2025; by end-2025, 130 of 136 tunnels were through, bridges 86% and subgrade 96% complete. Targeting completion in September 2027, it would cut Chengdu-Dazhou from ~3 hours to just over one." },
  2951: { descEn: "An $11.8 billion PJM expansion to meet surging data-centre load.", detailEn: "Selected from 134 proposals, this PJM package includes a new 765 kV line and multiple 500 kV upgrades, mainly to serve Virginia data-centre load, with ~$4.8 billion in Dominion's territory — a sharp increase from 2024." },
  2910: { descEn: "The largest US offshore wind farm (2.6 GW, 176×14 MW turbines).", detailEn: "Off the southeast coast of Virginia, this 2.6 GW farm with 176 Siemens Gamesa 14 MW turbines will be the largest US offshore wind farm, owned by Dominion and Stonepeak at about $11.5 billion. The first commercial turbine sent power in March 2026 with the project ~75% complete." },
  3276: { descEn: "A new BPCL greenfield refinery in Nellore, Andhra Pradesh.", detailEn: "In October 2025 Andhra Pradesh allotted BPCL 6,000 acres near the Ramayyapatnam deep-water port, with ~960 billion rupees invested over FY26-FY30 for 9-12 million tonnes/year of refining plus petrochemicals, targeting January 2029 start-up. The state pledges up to 75% capex subsidy over 20 years — the first sub-project to land after the west-coast mega-refinery was split up." },
  3555: { descEn: "A new 350 km/h line filling a gap in the Qingdao-Yinchuan corridor.", detailEn: "239 km at 350 km/h and about 81.3 billion yuan, this line is part of the Qingdao-Yinchuan high-speed corridor, linking Shanxi toward Yulin in Shaanxi. Shanxi has listed it as a priority high-speed start for 2026." },
  195: { descEn: "One of Japan's largest infrastructure projects.", detailEn: "Japan's first long-distance HVDC subsea cable, ~800 km and 2 GW, links Hokkaido with the Sea-of-Japan side of Honshu to bring Hokkaido's abundant renewables to the Tokyo area. OCCTO evaluates and awards bids in March 2026, with an ~8-year build toward completion around 2033." },
  349: { descEn: "A world-class petrochemical complex at Jubail, Saudi Arabia.", detailEn: "SATORP, a JV of TotalEnergies and Saudi Aramco, took FID in December 2022 to build 1.65 million tonnes of ethylene and two 500,000-tonne polyethylene units at Jubail, using refinery off-gases as feedstock, with commercial operation expected in 2027." },
  504: { descEn: "The world's largest AI training supercluster, built for Anthropic in Indiana.", detailEn: "AWS's Project Rainier in New Carlisle, Indiana spans 1,200 acres, planned for 30 buildings and 2.2 GW of IT load running ~500,000 Trainium2 chips — the world's largest non-Nvidia AI training cluster. Construction began in September 2024 and phase 1 came online in October 2025, dedicated to Anthropic training its Claude models." },
  942: { descEn: "Germany's largest transmission project, sending northern wind south.", detailEn: "SuedLink runs ~700 km from Wilster in the north to Bergrheinfeld in Bavaria, comprising two parallel ±525 kV DC lines totalling 4 GW at about €10 billion, built by Prysmian and NKT. First trenching began in August 2024, with works across several states through 2025." },
  980: { descEn: "The largest US transmission project under construction.", detailEn: "Grain Belt Express crosses Kansas, Missouri, Illinois and Indiana as a ±600 kV/5 GW HVDC line, ~1,280 km long. It won all state permits in 2025 and awarded $1.7 billion of construction contracts, with construction in 2026 and a first section expected in service in 2029." },
  1022: { descEn: "Europe's first FinFET-capable foundry JV.", detailEn: "Controlled by TSMC with Bosch, Infineon and NXP in the Dresden 'Silicon Saxony' cluster, this over-€10 billion plant is the EU's first pure-play foundry with FinFET capability, planned for 40,000 12-inch wafers/month for automotive and industrial chips — a city-scale power and water user driving Saxon grid and ultra-pure-water expansion. The structure topped out in November 2025, with tools in late 2026 and production in 2027." },
  1162: { descEn: "A passenger-and-freight railway across the Malay Peninsula.", detailEn: "The East Coast Rail Link connects Kelantan, Terengganu and Pahang on the east coast with Selangor and Port Klang on the west, 665 km, built by MRL with China Communications Construction — a key Belt and Road project carrying passengers and freight. Civil works reached 91.7% by January 2026, ahead of schedule; phase 1 (Kota Bharu-Gombak) is set for testing in June 2026 and opening in January 2027, with phase 2 to Port Klang due in 2027." },
  1299: { descEn: "A new Brazilian oil frontier; SBM to build two FPSOs.", detailEn: "In April 2026 Petrobras's board took FID on SEAP I in the Sergipe-Alagoas basin, and on 29 May signed for two SBM Offshore FPSOs (BOT model) totalling 240,000 b/d and 22 million m³/day of gas processing. At over 60 billion reais and expected to recover over a billion barrels of oil equivalent, SEAP II plans oil in 2030 and gas exports in 2031." },
  1432: { descEn: "The Middle East's only fully integrated bauxite-to-aluminium base.", detailEn: "At Ras Al Khair on Saudi Arabia's east coast, the Ma'aden-Alcoa JV is the only aluminium base in the Middle East with its own alumina supply — an 1.8-million-tonne alumina refinery, a 740,000-tonne smelter (two potlines) and a 380,000-tonne rolling mill, fed by 4 million tonnes/year of bauxite from Az Zabirah / Al Baitha in the north." },
  1541: { descEn: "Set to be one of the world's largest base-polymer plants.", detailEn: "The Amur Gas Chemical Complex near Svobodny, adjacent to the Amur GPP for ethane feedstock, is a JV of SIBUR (60%) and Sinopec (40%) at about $11 billion, designed for 2.3 million tonnes of polyethylene and 400,000 tonnes of polypropylene a year. After European contractors Linde and Technip withdrew in 2022, SIBUR and Sinopec redesigned it and changed licensors; it was 87.9% complete by end-September 2025." },
  2650: { descEn: "A fully underground metro from Parramatta to Sydney CBD.", detailEn: "A ~24 km fully underground automated metro linking Parramatta and Sydney CBD, greatly boosting capacity between the two business centres. Tunnelling has advanced, and it is one of NSW's largest rail projects, targeting opening around 2030." },
  3048: { descEn: "A BC gas trunkline feeding LNG Canada, online in November 2024.", detailEn: "Coastal GasLink entered commercial service in November 2024, running 670 km from Dawson Creek over the Rockies to Kitimat, carrying Montney gas to the LNG Canada export terminal at 2.1 bcf/d, expandable to 5 bcf/d." },
});

/* ===== 批次4：全库投资额 TOP（约 85–110 亿美元）===== */
Object.assign(window.ENERGY_EN, {
  3217: { descEn: "A nationwide AI-ready compute network with Reliance and Nvidia (up to 2 GW).", detailEn: "Nvidia and Reliance Jio are building AI infrastructure for India hosted in AI-ready data centres, expanding to 2,000 MW long term. Reliance unveiled a ~$110 billion AI plan in February 2026 with nationwide sites beyond Jamnagar, bringing 120+ MW online in late 2026 on the Nvidia Blackwell platform." },
  3400: { descEn: "The first 10-GW-class export project of Inner Mongolia's largest desert base.", detailEn: "In the north-central Kubuqi Desert of Ordos, this base plans 12.2 GW of renewables (8 GW solar, 4 GW wind) with 4 GW of supporting coal power and 5 GWh of storage, exporting to north China via a ±800 kV line. Prioritising desertification control, full grid connection is targeted for end-2027." },
  4261: { descEn: "An east-west electrified railway across the Malay Peninsula, EPC by a Chinese firm.", detailEn: "Malaysia's East Coast Rail Link (ECRL), with EPC by China Communications Construction, runs ~665 km from Kota Bharu on the east coast to Port Klang/Gombak in the west at 160 km/h, with electric trainsets. At about RM50.3 billion (~$11 billion) it is a signature Belt and Road project; the Gombak tunnel broke through in early 2025, with commercial operation planned for January 2027." },
  4396: { descEn: "HQC's role in the Amur GPP, one of the world's largest gas-processing plants.", detailEn: "The Amur Gas Processing Plant near Svobodny in Russia's Amur region is one of the world's largest, processing 42 bcm of gas and 60 million m³ of helium a year across six trains as the supply hub for the Russia-China east-route pipeline. The first train started in June 2021 with all online through 2025; HQC (Huanqiu) handled design and EPC work, mastering large-scale gas-processing and helium-extraction technology." },
  140: { descEn: "A giant North Sea offshore wind farm under construction off Yorkshire.", detailEn: "About 120 km off the Yorkshire coast, this ~2.85 GW farm uses up to 231 14 MW turbines. After FID in December 2023, Ørsted sold a 50% stake to an Apollo fund in November 2025 to advance construction; the first export cable landed in April 2026, with full output expected in 2027 — set to be one of the world's largest single offshore wind farms." },
  1190: { descEn: "Suriname's first offshore oilfield development, with an FPSO under construction.", detailEn: "In Block 58 ~150 km off Suriname, GranMorgu develops the Sapakara and Krabdagu discoveries (over 750 million barrels recoverable) — Suriname's first offshore oil project. FID was taken in October 2024 and SBM won the 220,000 b/d FPSO in June 2025; the hull was about half built by end-2025, with first oil planned for 2028 to launch Suriname's oil era." },
  157: { descEn: "One of the world's largest planned onshore wind projects.", detailEn: "Over ~3,025 km² in western Sohag governorate, Egypt, this onshore wind project is developed by Masdar, Infinity Power and Hassan Allam, with a land-access deal signed in May 2024; once built it would cut 23.8 million tonnes of CO₂ a year, ~9% of Egypt's emissions." },
  279: { descEn: "Europe's largest planned AI data-centre campus.", detailEn: "On Portugal's Atlantic coast at Sines, this 1.2 GW campus saw SIN01 go live in April 2025, with Microsoft committing $10 billion and Nscale deploying 12,600+ Nvidia Blackwell Ultra GPUs, using zero-water-withdrawal ocean cooling with a target PUE of 1.1." },
  357: { descEn: "The ninth US LNG export terminal.", detailEn: "At Sabine Pass, Texas, Golden Pass LNG is developed by QatarEnergy (70%) and ExxonMobil (30%) with three trains for ~18 million tonnes a year, cooling down in late 2025 and first export in early 2026 to become the ninth operating US LNG export terminal." },
  363: { descEn: "A giant oilfield in Namibia's Orange Basin.", detailEn: "Discovered in 2022 with estimated reserves over 3 billion barrels, Venus is one of the most important recent deep-water discoveries globally, operated by TotalEnergies. An FPSO-based development targets FID in early 2026 for 150,000-180,000 b/d, with first oil in 2029-2030." },
  501: { descEn: "A multi-gigawatt AI training campus in New Albany, Ohio, nuclear-backed.", detailEn: "Meta is building the Prometheus campus in New Albany, Ohio with ~1.5 GW of IT load, powered mainly by nuclear and renewables — a core base for training Meta's next-generation models, with the first facilities due in early 2026 using dense liquid cooling." },
  517: { descEn: "QTS's largest-ever single campus, in Cedar Rapids, Iowa.", detailEn: "In August 2025 QTS announced $10 billion on 612 acres in the Big Cedar industrial park at Cedar Rapids, Iowa, planning seven buildings; three topped out in October, with first use expected in 2027 — next to a Google campus and the largest economic-development project in Cedar Rapids' history." },
  643: { descEn: "The largest undeveloped US copper mine; a 2025 Supreme Court ruling cleared a land appeal.", detailEn: "Near Superior, Arizona, this deposit lies 5,000-7,000 ft underground with potential reserves of ~40 billion lb of copper, enough for ~25% of US demand. A shaft-conversion milestone was reached in June 2025, the same month the Supreme Court declined a Native American appeal clearing the land transfer, with construction expected around the 2030s." },
  1136: { descEn: "Planned to be East Africa's largest deep-water port.", detailEn: "Bagamoyo Port restarted after over a decade stalled. On 6 December 2025 Tanzania's TPA signed an MoU with France's AGL (an MSC subsidiary) to design, build and operate a first three berths in ~36 months, with works from early January 2026. The ~$10 billion master plan envisions 28 berths and an SEZ for 20 million TEU a year — 25 times Dar es Salaam's port — reshaping East African trade." },
  1170: { descEn: "An LNG export expansion at an operating Texas terminal.", detailEn: "Cheniere's 7-train midscale expansion at Corpus Christi, Texas adds over 10 million tonnes a year, lifting the site above 25 million tonnes. The first trains produced LNG by end-2024 and the first cargo shipped in February 2025, with more trains reaching substantial completion through 2025-2026 — emblematic of the new US LNG export wave." },
  1198: { descEn: "The first wholly US-owned major petrochemical project in China, online July 2025.", detailEn: "At the Daya Bay petrochemical zone in Huizhou, Guangdong, this is the first major petrochemical project wholly owned by a US company in China, at about $10 billion. Phase 1 includes a 1.6-million-tonne flexible-feed cracker, two 1.2-million-tonne LLDPE lines, a world-largest single 500,000-tonne LDPE unit and two 950,000-tonne PP units; it produced on-spec ethylene on 15 July 2025, helping make Huizhou a world-class green petrochemical base." },
  1267: { descEn: "A major AI-computing hub at Rio's Olympic Park.", detailEn: "Elea is converting Rio de Janeiro's Olympic Park into an AI-computing hub planned for 1.5 GW in 2027 and 3.2 GW by 2032, running on 100% clean power with direct submarine-cable links. In August 2025 it signed MoUs with Oracle and the city; Elea's 1+ GW national pipeline needs over $10 billion of capital, backed by Goldman Sachs and others." },
  1386: { descEn: "HUMAIN, AMD and Cisco building AI infrastructure across Saudi Arabia and the US.", detailEn: "HUMAIN and AMD announced a combined $10 billion to deploy 500 MW of AMD computing within five years across data centres in Saudi Arabia and the US. In November 2025 they formed a JV with Cisco, with a first 100 MW using AMD Instinct MI450 GPUs and Cisco infrastructure, expected online in 2026." },
  1388: { descEn: "A gigawatt AI park by stc's center3 and HUMAIN.", detailEn: "stc's center3 and HUMAIN formed a JV to develop and operate AI data centres in Saudi Arabia, planned for 1 GW with a first 250 MW for large AI loads. center3 has invested ~$3 billion and plans another $10 billion by end-2030 for high-density hyperscale facilities in Riyadh, Jeddah and Dammam." },
  1420: { descEn: "A petrochemical expansion beside one of the world's largest integrated complexes.", detailEn: "KIPIC is building a ~$10 billion petrochemical complex beside the Al-Zour refinery (615,000 b/d) in Kuwait, with olefins and aromatics units for ~2.7 million tonnes of aromatics and polypropylene and 1.7 million tonnes of gasoline a year — making it one of the world's largest integrated refining-petrochemical bases, split into gasoline, petrochemical and marine EPC packages." },
  1421: { descEn: "A petrochemical cracker study alongside the Duqm refinery.", detailEn: "The OQ8 Duqm refinery reached full output in 2024 and raised nameplate capacity from 230,000 to 255,000 b/d. Beside it, a Duqm petrochemical complex is planned with a large mixed-feed cracker and several world-class derivative units for regional and Asian markets, part of OQ's $10 billion-plus strategic investment in Duqm." },
  1426: { descEn: "Two new LNG trains in the North Field South expansion.", detailEn: "NFS is the second phase of Qatar's North Field expansion, adding two trains totalling 16 MTPA which, with the 32 MTPA North Field East, lift Qatar's LNG capacity from 77 to 142 MTPA. In October 2024 McDermott won the subsea pipeline and cable EPCI contract." },
  1538: { descEn: "An 1,814 km gas export trunkline across four countries, now under construction.", detailEn: "The TAPI pipeline carries gas from Turkmenistan's Galkynysh field via Afghanistan and Pakistan to India, 1,814 km with 33 bcm/year design capacity. The ~214 km Turkmen section finished in 2024 and the Afghan Serhetabat-Herat section began in September 2024 (14 km built and 24 km graded by 2025, aiming to reach Herat by end-2026), while the Pakistani and Indian sections remain on hold." },
  1772: { descEn: "Elea's AI data-centre expansion to Recife and Belém.", detailEn: "Elea operates nine interconnected campuses in Brazil with over 1 GW under construction (needing $10 billion-plus of capital). After I Squared Capital took a controlling stake in April 2026, it accelerated national expansion into Recife and Belém with high-density AI infrastructure (location shown at Recife); specific capacity and timeline are to be announced." },
  1891: { descEn: "A 500 MW Nvidia GB300 AI factory in Saudi Arabia.", detailEn: "PIF's HUMAIN is partnering with Nvidia to build up to 500 MW and hundreds of thousands of top GPUs within five years. A first phase of 18,000 GB300 Grace Blackwell systems with InfiniBand activates multi-exaFLOP computing in early 2026, with the two committing up to $10 billion for the 500 MW deployment." },
  1903: { descEn: "A large new inland NEOM airport, aiming long-term to be the world's largest.", detailEn: "Located inland in NEOM near Tabuk and far larger than the existing NEOM Bay airport, this airport has AECOM as PMC consultant for master planning through operations, with Turkey's IC Ictas and Limak bidding for the terminal. Phase 1 targets ~25 million passengers a year, phase 2 up to 50 million and the long-term vision 100 million — among the world's largest — serving NEOM and Vision 2030 tourism." },
  2062: { descEn: "Changi Airport's largest-ever expansion: a reclaimed Terminal 5.", detailEn: "Built on ~1,080 hectares of reclaimed land east of Changi at about S$10 billion (~$13 billion), T5 is Changi's largest expansion. Groundbreaking was in May 2025, with initial capacity of 50 million passengers a year lifting the airport to 135 million total, featuring solar roofs and under-runway tunnels, with phase 1 due in the mid-2030s." },
  2270: { descEn: "A 3,300 km green-hydrogen corridor from Algeria to Italy, Austria and Germany.", detailEn: "Ministers of Algeria, Tunisia, Germany, Austria and Italy signed a joint declaration to build the 3,300 km SoutH2 corridor linking Algeria and Tunisia to industrial hubs in Italy, Austria and Germany, ~70% repurposing existing gas pipelines to cut costs, targeting 4 million tonnes of green hydrogen a year by 2030. Algeria has begun feasibility studies — its flagship green-hydrogen export route to Europe." },
  2350: { descEn: "A flagship Mauritania green-hydrogen project targeting 10 GW of electrolysers by 2030.", detailEn: "Developed by Chariot and TE H2 (a TotalEnergies-EREN JV), the Nour project plans 10 GW of electrolysis with an initial 3 GW of renewables for ~150,000 tonnes of green hydrogen a year, leveraging Mauritania's excellent wind and solar for export to Europe — the country's other mega green-hydrogen project alongside AMAN." },
  2461: { descEn: "A deep-water-port green-hydrogen export zone in the Northern Cape.", detailEn: "At Richtersveld in South Africa's Northern Cape, ~60 km north of Port Nolloth near the Namibian border, this deep-water-port scheme led by Sasol completed a pre-feasibility study confirming viability. It plans 10 GW of electrolysers and 240,000 hectares for renewables to export green hydrogen and ammonia to Europe, with a strategic environmental assessment under way from March 2024; no investment decision yet." },
  2564: { descEn: "A high-grade Gabon hematite mine; first shipment to China in late 2025.", detailEn: "Fortescue and the Gabon government jointly develop the high-grade Belinga hematite deposit, shipping the first ore to China in December 2025 and ramping toward 15-20 million tonnes in 2026. With a ~450-560 km rail corridor, deep-water port and hydro plants, the mining ministry estimates ~$10 billion of total infrastructure, targeting an integrated mine-rail-port by 2030." },
  2707: { descEn: "One of the world's largest planned offshore wind farms (4.1 GW off Scotland).", detailEn: "In the outer Firth of Forth off eastern Scotland, SSE's ~4.1 GW Berwick Bank is one of the world's largest planned offshore wind projects, able to power ~6 million homes. It advanced Scottish consent and grid connection in 2025 as a flagship of UK energy security, targeting the early 2030s." },
  2742: { descEn: "A European-gauge high-speed railway linking the Baltics with Poland.", detailEn: "Rail Baltica is a nearly 900 km European-standard-gauge high-speed railway through Estonia, Latvia and Lithuania into Poland and the EU network, with a ~€15.3 billion first phase. Large-scale construction proceeded across Poland and the Baltics in 2025 and the first platform of Tallinn's Ülemiste terminal opened, targeting phase-1 completion in 2030." },
  2747: { descEn: "A large coordinated North Sea oil-and-gas development.", detailEn: "In the central Norwegian North Sea, Aker BP leads an integrated development of the Hugin, Munin and Fulla fields (Yggdrasil/NOAKA) at about NOK 115 billion — one of Norway's largest recent offshore clusters. Platform and subsea works advanced in 2025, targeting start-up around 2027." },
  3001: { descEn: "Meta's 29th data centre, a 1 GW campus in El Paso, Texas.", detailEn: "Broken ground in October 2025 at an initial $1.5 billion expandable to 1 GW, this El Paso campus saw investment jump sixfold to over $10 billion in March 2026 with 12 buildings, expected online in 2028 with a peak workforce of 4,000, planned to rely mainly on gas power." },
  3006: { descEn: "A 500 MW, seven-building QTS campus in Van Wert, northwest Ohio.", detailEn: "On 29 May 2026 the city of Van Wert and QTS unveiled a ~$10 billion, 902-acre mega-site for up to seven buildings and 500 MW with zero-water-use closed-loop cooling; QTS fully funds the energy-infrastructure upgrades, with groundbreaking expected in Q4 and full build-out around 2032." },
  3293: { descEn: "A planned 300,000 b/d refining complex with Saudi Aramco at Gwadar.", detailEn: "Pakistan plans to bring in ~$10 billion from Saudi Arabia to build an integrated refining complex at Gwadar processing at least 300,000 b/d plus petrochemicals, on a Saudi 60% / Pakistan 40% basis, with land allocation advancing in early 2026 and start-up around 2030, potentially saving Pakistan ~$3 billion a year." },
  3427: { descEn: "The world's first Hualong One plus high-temperature-gas-reactor cogeneration project.", detailEn: "At the Xuwei New Area of Lianyungang, Jiangsu, CNNC Su Energy plans four Hualong One units plus two high-temperature gas-cooled reactors; phase 1 builds two Hualong One and one HTGR, mainly for industrial heat with some power, approved by the State Council in August 2024 and started in January 2026." },
  3446: { descEn: "China's home-designed next-generation fusion engineering test reactor.", detailEn: "Led by ASIPP and designed with international collaboration, this reactor builds on Hefei's EAST and Kuafu platforms. Its overall integrated engineering design is complete, targeting construction before 2035 for physics experiments and a commercial fusion demonstration plant around 2050." },
  3507: { descEn: "YMTC Wuhan phase 3, including China's first fully domestic NAND line.", detailEn: "YMTC's third Wuhan fab has entered tool install and commissioning, due online by end-2026 reaching 50,000 wafers/month in 2027, alongside the first pilot line built entirely from domestic equipment. With all three new fabs at capacity, total output rises from ~200,000 to 500,000 wafers/month, aiming for 15% of the global NAND market." },
  3582: { descEn: "A 100-billion-yuan China-Saudi refining-petrochemical complex in Fujian.", detailEn: "On the Gulei Peninsula in Zhangzhou, Fujian, this JV of Fujian Petrochemical (50%), Sinopec (25%) and Saudi Aramco (25%) at 71.1 billion yuan builds 16 million tonnes of refining, 1.5 million tonnes of ethylene and 2 million tonnes of aromatics across 30+ units. Started in November 2024, it entered substantive operation in November 2025 and targets full production by 2030 — a flagship of China-Saudi energy cooperation." },
  4085: { descEn: "A world-class copper mine, MMG's flagship overseas asset.", detailEn: "At ~4,000 m in Peru's Apurímac region, Las Bambas is one of the world's largest copper mines, with ~410,000 tonnes of copper-in-concentrate in 2025, a multi-year high. The Chalcobamba pit started up and was approved for development in 2025 (~$130 million phase 1), supporting 380,000-400,000 tonnes a year with Ferrobamba; MMG keeps investing in tailings and mine infrastructure." },
  4097: { descEn: "State Grid's wholly-owned ±800 kV link carrying Amazon hydro to Rio.", detailEn: "The Belo Monte phase-2 UHVDC is State Grid's first wholly-owned overseas UHVDC, running 2,539 km from the Xingu converter in Pará to a Rio de Janeiro converter at 4 GW. After milestone documents were signed by China and Brazil in April 2024, the line is fully in service, operated by State Grid Brazil Holding." },
  3592: { descEn: "A 4,269 km gas artery from Sichuan-Chongqing to East China.", detailEn: "Running 4,269 km through eight provinces from Sichuan-Chongqing to Fujian, this 10 MPa pipeline carries 14 bcm/year, approved and built in western and eastern segments. The western section (started September 2023) is over 70% done; the 2,698 km eastern section saw its first part commissioned in August 2025, with full completion expected in 2027, lifting the Sichuan-East gas system to 26 bcm/year." },
  321: { descEn: "Australia's largest rail expansion in nearly 40 years.", detailEn: "A 9 km twin-track tunnel under Melbourne's CBD with five new metro stations opened on 30 November 2025, with full operation by February 2026, adding over 1,000 weekly services and doubling Melbourne's underground rail network." },
  584: { descEn: "AWS's largest single-region investment in Europe, in the Frankfurt region.", detailEn: "AWS announced a cumulative €8.8 billion in its Frankfurt cloud region by 2026, building a 7+ hectare campus at Schöneck and a 10.6-hectare campus at Maintal, supporting over 15,200 jobs — its largest single-region investment in Europe to date." },
  1148: { descEn: "Toronto's Line 5 (Eglinton Crosstown), opening February 2026.", detailEn: "The 19 km, 25-station Eglinton Crosstown LRT (Line 5) runs east-west along Toronto's Eglinton Avenue with over 10 km underground. Built by Ontario's Metrolinx and the Crosslinx consortium (including Aecon), it was substantially handed over on 5 December 2025 after years of delay and opened by the TTC on 8 February 2026, connecting Kennedy and Mount Dennis stations." },
  3018: { descEn: "A $9.5 billion new international terminal at JFK, first phase mid-2026.", detailEn: "Built on the former T1/T2/T3 site, the New Terminal One is the core of the Port Authority's $19 billion JFK overhaul. The first phase, with arrivals/departures halls and 14 gates, opens in mid-2026, reaching 23 gates and over 2.6 million sq ft by 2030 to become JFK's largest terminal." },
  3024: { descEn: "The Purple Line extension to West LA, first section opening for the World Cup era.", detailEn: "Extending west from Koreatown to the West LA VA Medical Center with seven new stations. Section 1 (~4 miles, 3 stations) opens on 8 May 2026; section 2 reaches Century City by late 2026 and section 3 the VA by 2027, racing toward the 2028 Olympics." },
  3556: { descEn: "A new second Shanghai-Hangzhou high-speed corridor, early works begun.", detailEn: "About 197 km at 350 km/h and ~67.1 billion yuan, this line runs from Shanghai via Jinshan to Hangzhou West, relieving the existing Shanghai-Hangzhou line and serving Yangtze Delta integration. Approved by the NDRC, it has entered early construction." },
  3588: { descEn: "A 67.3-billion-yuan mega coal-to-olefins base, Baofeng's third.", detailEn: "In the Jiangjunmiao mining area of eastern Junggar, Xinjiang, this ~67.3 billion-yuan project plans 4×2.8-million-tonne methanol, 4×1-million-tonne methanol-to-olefins, olefin separation and 1.95 million tonnes each of PP and PE plus EVA and UHMWPE units. It is Baofeng's third coal-to-olefins base after Ningdong and Inner Mongolia, lifting company olefin capacity toward 9.7 million tonnes/year, with start-up in 2027-2028." },
  3557: { descEn: "A new 350 km/h line forming a Central Plains-Jianghuai corridor.", detailEn: "389 km at 350 km/h and ~66.6 billion yuan, this line links Nanyang and Xinyang in Henan with Hefei (toward Jinzhai) in Anhui. It has passed NDRC project-proposal review and is expected to start after feasibility approval in the first half of 2026." },
  3569: { descEn: "A major hub-airport expansion with two new runways and a 730,000 m² T2, due 2029.", detailEn: "Designed for 95 million passengers and 1 million tonnes of cargo by 2030, this expansion adds East-2 and West-3 runways, a 730,000 m² T2 terminal, a ground transport centre and parking at ~66.5 billion yuan, with a solar-plus-storage low-carbon energy system. The East-2 runway passed acceptance by end-2025 and the T2 main structure was 67.6% complete." },
  606: { descEn: "ByteDance/TikTok's first Latin American data centre, wind-powered.", detailEn: "In December 2025 ByteDance's TikTok announced a 300 MW wind-powered data centre with Omnia and Casa dos Ventos at the Pecém port industrial complex in Ceará, Brazil (an initial $9.3 billion), starting construction in April 2026 and operating in 2027 — Latin America's largest single-customer data centre." },
  1140: { descEn: "The world's longest underground rail tunnel; exploratory tunnel holed through in 2025.", detailEn: "The Brenner Base Tunnel crosses the Alps linking Innsbruck (Austria) and Fortezza (Italy); with the Inn Valley tunnel it totals 64 km, set to be the world's longest underground rail tunnel. In May 2025 Webuild completed mechanised boring on the Italian Mules 2-3 lot, with a TBM reaching the border after 14+ km, and on 18 September the 56 km exploratory tunnel was holed through. Shifting road freight to rail, it would cut Fortezza-Innsbruck to under 25 minutes, targeting 2032." },
  3509: { descEn: "A 40 GWh battery base in Fuzhou, CATL's 15th domestic site.", detailEn: "Signed in January 2025 with phase 1 started in April, this 40 GWh, 65-billion-yuan base in Fuzhou's Taiwanese Investment Zone builds a full chain from materials to recycling, due online in mid-2027 with annual output value exceeding 100 billion yuan at capacity." },
  350: { descEn: "A large mixed-feed cracker and aromatics complex at Yanbu.", detailEn: "In April 2025 Saudi Aramco, Sinopec and Yasref signed a framework to build a 1.8-million-tonne mixed-feed cracker and 1.5-million-tonne aromatics complex beside the Yanbu refinery to maximise conversion of refinery feed into chemicals, currently in engineering study." },
  515: { descEn: "Two new Google campuses in South Carolina ($9 billion).", detailEn: "In October 2025 Google announced $9 billion (through 2027) in South Carolina, expanding its Berkeley County campus and building new campuses at Ridgeville and St. George in Dorchester County for cloud and AI — its largest single-state expansion in the US Southeast." },
  516: { descEn: "A $9 billion Google expansion in Virginia.", detailEn: "In August 2025 Google announced an additional $9 billion in Virginia (through end-2026), building a Meadowville campus in Chesterfield County and a near-million-sq-ft campus in Botetourt County, and expanding facilities in Loudoun and Prince William counties." },
  1131: { descEn: "Egypt's first high-speed line connecting the Red Sea and the Mediterranean.", detailEn: "Egypt and Siemens are building a 2,000+ km high-speed network; the first ~660 km Green Line with 21 stations runs from Ain Sokhna on the Red Sea via the New Administrative Capital, Alexandria and El Alamein to Marsa Matrouh — the first rail link between the two seas at 250 km/h, dubbed the 'Suez Canal on rails'. The first line was 67% done by September 2025, with a test run launched in November, serving ~90% of the population and opening in December 2026." },
  1300: { descEn: "A Campos Basin pre-salt gas field, Brazil's first offshore-processed gas into the grid.", detailEn: "Comprising the Pao de Acucar, Gavea and Seat pre-salt discoveries in ~2,900 m of water with over a billion barrels of oil equivalent, this development uses a MODEC FPSO (modules lifted at Seatrium's Angra yard in March 2026) with a 204 km line to the Cabiunas terminal at Macaé — Brazil's first offshore-processed gas into the grid. Drilling starts in March 2026 for 2028 start-up, supplying ~15% of national gas demand." },
  2569: { descEn: "Integrating gas sources to feed the Punta Europa LNG plant.", detailEn: "Equatorial Guinea's gas mega-hub centres on the 3.7-MTPA Punta Europa LNG plant and a 1.1-million-tonne methanol plant, integrating regional gas to extend output. In 2026 it aims to finalise PSCs for blocks B/4 and EG-27 with ConocoPhillips (unlocking ~$9 billion), with Chevron's Aseng gas supplying via a $690 million deal and a Gulf-of-Guinea pipeline planned to bring Nigerian gas." },
  2607: { descEn: "Australia's most advanced offshore wind project, 2.2 GW off Gippsland.", detailEn: "Off Gippsland in Victoria, this is Australia's fastest-moving offshore wind project at up to 2.2 GW, able to power ~1.2 million homes. Holding a feasibility licence and advancing environmental and grid-connection design as a Gippsland front-runner, it targets supplying the grid in the early 2030s." },
  2626: { descEn: "Queensland's flagship pumped hydro: 2 GW, up to 48 GWh.", detailEn: "At Borumba reservoir near Imbil, Queensland, this 2 GW pumped-hydro scheme stores up to ~48 GWh for ~24 hours of discharge — the flagship long-duration storage of Queensland's energy transition. It won federal environmental approval in 2025 for early works, with QIC taking over commercial development in June, and is in site preparation." },
  2999: { descEn: "Tesla's sixth gigafactory near Monterrey; FID confirmed May 2026.", detailEn: "Tesla's Giga Mexico at Santa Catarina near Monterrey, Nuevo León is about $9 billion. Repeatedly delayed by tariff and EV-policy uncertainty, it formally confirmed FID in May 2026, with early and road-access works advancing and some suppliers already locating nearby." },
  3003: { descEn: "A planned 2 GW AI campus in the Permian Basin, West Texas.", detailEn: "On the 568-acre Longfellow Ranch site at Fort Stockton, Texas, AI firm Poolside plans a 2 GW campus in eight 250 MW phases. Originally partnered with CoreWeave (October 2025), the two ended their deal in April 2026 and Poolside is in talks with cloud providers including Google for new partners." },
  3143: { descEn: "A planned new nuclear cluster in Punjab, Pakistan (two large units).", detailEn: "At Muzaffargarh in Punjab, Pakistan, PAEC plans two ~1,100 MW units (M-1, M-2) as a new nuclear cluster after Chashma. The regulator has completed siting studies, with ~3,300 MW planned in Punjab medium-term at an estimated ~$13 billion." },
  3282: { descEn: "Reliance polyester-chain expansion: the world's largest single 3-million-tonne PTA.", detailEn: "In 2025 Reliance announced ~750 billion rupees of petrochemical expansion, building the world's largest single-train 3-million-tonne/year PTA and a 1-million-tonne PET at Dahej (both targeting 2026), plus phased 1.5-million-tonne PVC expansions at Dahej and Jamnagar, matched to US ethane feedstock arriving in the late 2020s." },
  4232: { descEn: "One of the world's largest single-train methanol plants; CNCEC EPC ~€8.4 billion.", detailEn: "A gas-to-methanol complex at Ust-Luga on Russia's Baltic produces 5,400 tonnes/day (~1.8 million tonnes/year) from a single train — among the world's largest. CNCEC's Seventh Construction Company signed the EPC contract with Baltic Methanol worth about €8.4 billion (~65 billion yuan), with a 48-month schedule." },
  3498: { descEn: "A 100,000-wafer/month 12-inch foundry in Lingang, Shanghai.", detailEn: "In the Lingang free-trade zone of Shanghai, this foundry plans 100,000 wafers/month at ~$8.87 billion across three stages — one of China's largest single fabs. A phase-1 revision was published in February 2025, with capacity ramping from 2025 to full output by end-2027, focused on mature and specialty processes." },
  622: { descEn: "Pakistan's first world-class copper-gold mine, first output ~2028.", detailEn: "In Balochistan, Reko Diq is one of the world's great copper-gold deposits. An updated feasibility and ~$5.57 billion phase-1 capital were approved in April 2025 with early works begun; the ADB committed $410 million and IFC $700 million, and phase 1 will produce ~200,000 tonnes of copper a year." },
  824: { descEn: "Canada's most expensive dam; all units online in August 2025.", detailEn: "On the Peace River in British Columbia, Site C began in 2015 and connected its sixth and final unit in August 2025, with 1,100 MW and ~5,100 GWh a year. At over C$16 billion it is the costliest dam in Canadian history, adding ~15% to BC's power supply." },
  1214: { descEn: "A new refining-petrochemical complex in northwest India.", detailEn: "At Pachpadra in Barmer, Rajasthan, this HPCL-Rajasthan JV pairs a 9-million-tonne/year refinery with 2.4 million tonnes of petrochemicals. Crude is in storage and the 180,000 b/d CDU plans to start up by late January 2026, with petrochemicals about a quarter later, strengthening northwest India's fuel and chemical self-sufficiency." },
  247: { descEn: "TSMC's first volume fab in Japan.", detailEn: "At Kikuyo in Kumamoto, this fab focuses on 22/28nm and 12/16nm at 55,000 wafers/month, reaching volume production in late 2024 for automotive and image sensors; with phase 2 launched, total investment will exceed $20 billion." },
  4254: { descEn: "Segment 4 of the Lagos-Kano railway, completing the central corridor.", detailEn: "The Ibadan-Kaduna section is the fourth segment of Nigeria's ~1,315 km Lagos-Kano standard-gauge railway, contracted to CRCC's CCECC — a ~616 km double-track main line plus an ~81 km single-track spur (via Osun-Ado-Ekiti) at up to 150 km/h, ~48-month build. Once through it joins the existing Lagos-Ibadan and Abuja-Kaduna sections into a central corridor, fully to Chinese standards — key to modernising Nigeria's railways." },
  547: { descEn: "The Greater Bay Area hub of China's 'east-data-west-compute' plan.", detailEn: "Shaoguan has attracted 22 AI-compute projects totalling 62.1 billion yuan, with 67,400 racks and 50,600 PFLOPS built and ten 400G all-optical links to the Bay Area cutting latency to Guangzhou/Shenzhen to 1.3/1.66 ms, targeting 500,000 racks by 2025." },
  1550: { descEn: "A giant Chukotka copper-gold mine, one of the world's largest undeveloped.", detailEn: "In the Bilibino district of Chukotka in Russia's Far East, Baimskaya processes 70 million tonnes of ore a year, averaging ~300,000 tonnes of copper a year in its first decade. With a 428 km all-weather road and a port exporting via the Northern Sea Route using automation and IoT, VEB and others pledged over 1.1 trillion roubles, of which 260+ billion is deployed." },
  2058: { descEn: "The Philippines' first subway, Japan-financed.", detailEn: "At about 488.5 billion pesos with Japanese financing, the Metro Manila Subway runs 33 km from Valenzuela to Ninoy Aquino International Airport. Land clearing reached ~90.76% by end-2025 (from 51% at year-start); originally due 2029, it has slipped to 2032 at the latest, with funding concentrated in the first half of 2026." },
  2643: { descEn: "AWS's A$13.2 billion Australian data-centre expansion.", detailEn: "AWS pledged about A$13.2 billion over 2023-2027 to expand cloud data-centre infrastructure in Sydney and Melbourne, with large renewable PPAs, supporting Australian business and government cloud and generative-AI demand — one of the country's largest cloud-infrastructure investments." },
  2651: { descEn: "A heavy-rail link from Melbourne Airport to the city, ~A$7 billion federal.", detailEn: "This heavy-rail link between Melbourne Airport and the CBD has ~A$7 billion of federal funding (total ~A$13 billion). The phase-1 West Footscray-Albion rail upgrade has begun for 2030 completion, with track realignment around the airport station from 2026 — a major Victorian transport project." },
});

/* ===== 批次5：全库投资额 TOP（约 65–85 亿美元）===== */
Object.assign(window.ENERGY_EN, {
  2655: { descEn: "Sydney Harbour's second road tunnel.", detailEn: "The ~6.5 km Western Harbour Tunnel relieves the existing Harbour Bridge and tunnel, linking the Western Distributor with North Sydney at about A$13 billion. Immersed-tube and bored construction is advancing, with opening planned for 2028 — a key piece of the Greater Sydney road network." },
  3016: { descEn: "The first line of Sheinbaum's passenger-rail plan, 226 km to Querétaro.", detailEn: "About 226 km from Mexico City to Querétaro, started in April 2025 with a 2.5-year schedule. Needing six tunnels and 14 viaducts, its cost rose to ~$8.5 billion; the Querétaro station will later extend toward Nuevo Laredo and Nogales, forming the backbone of a national passenger-rail network." },
  3038: { descEn: "A CPChem-QatarEnergy ethane cracker complex in Orange, Texas, in commissioning.", detailEn: "Owned 51% by CPChem and 49% by QatarEnergy in Orange, Texas, this complex has a 2.08-million-tonne/year ethane cracker and two 1-million-tonne HDPE units. The $8.5 billion project enters commissioning in 2026 and full production in 2027, with ~25% lower greenhouse gases than comparable plants." },
  3401: { descEn: "An 11 GW wind-and-solar base in Gansu's Badain Jaran Desert; supporting works started 2025.", detailEn: "Planned for at least 11 GW of renewables (4.3 GW wind, 6.7 GW solar, 0.2 GW CSP) with 4 GW of peaking coal power and 1.4 GW/5.6 GWh of storage, exporting via the 'Gansu-to-Shanghai' corridor. On 27 February 2025 four 1 GW supporting coal units broke ground together, with renewables advancing in parallel." },
  3564: { descEn: "The Hefei-Wuhan section of the Shanghai-Chongqing-Chengdu Yangtze HSR.", detailEn: "About 360 km at 350 km/h from Hefei via Lu'an, Jinzhai, Macheng and Hong'an to Wuhan — a key section of the Yangtze high-speed corridor. Started in late 2023 with the Hubei portion progressing well, it will join the operating Wuhan-Yichang line, putting Wuhan-Hefei within about an hour." },
  2962: { descEn: "A ~$8.2 billion CFE grid build: 275 new lines, 6,735 km, 524 substations.", detailEn: "CFE's 2025-2030 reinforcement plan, ~$8.2 billion (164 billion pesos), builds 275 new lines totalling 6,735 km and 524 substations, with 66 priority projects scheduled for 2025-2026 across many states to support nearshoring power demand." },
  3020: { descEn: "An $8.2 billion-plus O'Hare terminal overhaul, with a new Concourse D and Global Terminal.", detailEn: "ORDNext replaces Terminal 2 with a Global Terminal, adds a 24-gate Satellite Concourse E and underground tunnels. The initial $1.3 billion Concourse D began in August 2025, with vertical construction from spring 2026 and completion in 2028; the Global Terminal's sequencing was renegotiated in late 2025." },
  143: { descEn: "The Netherlands' largest offshore wind project, with green-hydrogen production.", detailEn: "This project pairs 2 GW of offshore wind (IJmuiden Ver Beta), 50 MW of floating offshore solar and 1 GW of onshore electrolysers, with green hydrogen distributed via Rotterdam's industrial pipeline network. Approved in June 2024 and restructured into two phases in August 2025, it has a 250 MW PPA with Google." },
  240: { descEn: "CATL's largest battery gigafactory in Europe.", detailEn: "At Debrecen, Hungary, this ~€7.3 billion plant plans 100 GWh a year to supply Volkswagen, BMW and Stellantis. Phase 1's structure has topped out with tools being installed, expected online in early 2026 and employing ~9,000." },
  319: { descEn: "A metro line linking Riyadh's giga-projects.", detailEn: "About 65 km (47 km underground) with 19 stations, this line links the Qiddiya entertainment city, King Salman Park and Diriyah Gate. Bidding closed in January 2026, targeting a contract signing and construction start in 2026." },
  1139: { descEn: "The world's longest immersed-tube tunnel; first element sunk in 2025.", detailEn: "The Fehmarn Belt tunnel links Lolland in Denmark with Fehmarn in Germany, 18 km — set to be the world's longest combined road-and-rail immersed tunnel, with twin electrified rail tracks and a four-lane motorway. In May 2025 Femern A/S sank and joined the first standard element to the Danish portal; built from 79 elements, it will cut the Rødby-Puttgarden train crossing to 7 minutes, targeting 2029 and slashing the Hamburg-Copenhagen journey." },
  1159: { descEn: "India's largest deep-water port, built on an artificial island.", detailEn: "Near Dahanu in Palghar, Maharashtra, Vadhavan is India's planned all-weather deep-water mega-port, a JNPT-Maharashtra Maritime Board PPP built on an artificial island — India's first offshore mega-port, designed for ~23 million TEU a year to enter the global top ten. PM Modi laid the foundation in August 2024, with construction and reclamation under way from 2025 toward operational readiness by December 2029." },
  1186: { descEn: "Equinor's largest overseas oilfield, the first foreign-led pre-salt project.", detailEn: "In the Santos Basin pre-salt off Brazil in over 2,000 m of water, Bacalhau is Equinor's largest overseas oilfield and Brazil's first pre-salt project developed entirely by an international operator. Its 370 m FPSO is designed for 220,000 b/d and produced first oil on 15 October 2025; phase-1 recoverable reserves exceed a billion barrels." },
  1301: { descEn: "Shell's 2025-FID Santos Basin pre-salt gas-condensate project.", detailEn: "In March 2025 Shell Brazil took FID on the Gato do Mato pre-salt project in the Santos Basin, covering the BM-S-54 concession and the Sul de Gato do Mato production-sharing area in 1,750-2,050 m of water. A new MODEC FPSO will produce up to 120,000 b/d from ~370 million barrels of recoverable resources, targeting 2029." },
  1385: { descEn: "A flagship AI compute centre near Riyadh training Grok.", detailEn: "Announced at the November 2025 US-Saudi investment forum, this is built by Musk's xAI with Saudi sovereign-AI firm HUMAIN and Nvidia near Riyadh, at over 500 MW. A first phase of ~18,000 Nvidia GB300 GPUs serves as the training base for xAI's next-generation Grok models, with xAI the first customer." },
  1406: { descEn: "A 350 km/h line linking Abu Dhabi and Dubai in 30 minutes.", detailEn: "In early 2025 the UAE's Etihad Rail announced a 150 km high-speed railway linking Abu Dhabi and Dubai at 350 km/h for a 30-minute trip, at about $8 billion, targeting 2030. The Abu Dhabi section went to NPC, Trojan, Turkey's Kalyon and China State Construction; the Dubai section to India's L&T, China Harbour and Wade Adams." },
  1548: { descEn: "New gas supply to China via the Sakhalin-Khabarovsk system.", detailEn: "The Far East route is a new spur supplying China via the Sakhalin-Khabarovsk-Vladivostok pipeline system on Russia's Pacific coast. In September 2025 Gazprom and CNPC agreed to raise supply from 10 to 12 bcm/year, with exports starting in 2027 at an initial 2 bcm rising to 12 bcm; China said construction was advancing in late 2025." },
  1551: { descEn: "Russia's largest undeveloped copper mine; phase 1 ramping up.", detailEn: "In Zabaikalye, Udokan started phase 1 in 2023, targeting ~135,000 tonnes of copper a year at capacity, with 160,000 tonnes of copper equivalent exported by September 2025. The phase-2 international feasibility study is done, planned to start in 2028, lifting ore throughput to 24-28 million tonnes a year and copper capacity toward 450,000 tonnes." },
  1680: { descEn: "Europe's largest battery investment; 100 GWh, online early 2026.", detailEn: "On a 221-hectare site in southern Debrecen, Hungary, this ~€7.3 billion, 100 GWh plant is the EU's largest battery investment and Hungary's largest greenfield FDI, supplying Mercedes, BMW, Stellantis and Volkswagen. Phase-1 40 GWh is fully booked by customers; module assembly began in 2024 with cell mass production planned for Q1 2026." },
  1870: { descEn: "The main renewable supply for NEOM's off-grid smart microgrid.", detailEn: "Built by NEOM's energy-and-water unit ENOWA to power the new city, this plans 2+ solar farms totalling 6.5 GW and 2+ wind farms totalling 1.6 GW, coming online from 2026 into the world's first HVDC smart microgrid — distinct from the NGHC green-hydrogen power, serving city loads like Oxagon." },
  1901: { descEn: "Phase 1 (Lines B and C) of Mecca's four-line metro.", detailEn: "The Royal Commission for Makkah plans a four-line (A-D), 89-station metro in three phases over 2032-2045. Phase 1 focuses on Lines B and C — over 62 km and 31 stations (21 underground), including a 2.4 km tunnel beneath the Masar project and integration with the existing Mashaaer pilgrim line. Phase 1 is ~$8 billion and the full network up to $16.5 billion; preliminary design tenders were issued in 2025, closing 5 August." },
  2277: { descEn: "Eni's $8 billion A&E Structures gas project, 0.75 bcf/d by 2026.", detailEn: "Developed by Italy's Eni with Libya's NOC, the $8 billion A&E Structures gas project targets 750 million cubic feet/day by 2026 to meet Libyan domestic demand and stabilise supply to Europe — a flagship of Libya's oil-and-gas recovery, aligned with NOC's 45 new and upgrade projects and a 2-million-barrel-a-day output goal." },
  2608: { descEn: "The Hunter region's first offshore wind project with a feasibility licence.", detailEn: "In the declared Hunter offshore wind zone off Newcastle, NSW, this ~2 GW project won a feasibility licence in February 2025. The developer has applied to extend its development period; as the Hunter's pioneer offshore project it aligns with local coal-plant retirements and industrial decarbonisation." },
  2746: { descEn: "The Barents Sea's largest oilfield, opening a new Arctic oil province.", detailEn: "In the Norwegian Barents Sea, Equinor (46.3%) leads the Johan Castberg development of the Skrugard, Havis and Drivis fields via an FPSO peaking at 220,000 b/d. First oil came in August 2025 — the largest producing field in the Barents Sea, opening a new Arctic oil era and reinforcing Norway as a long-term European energy exporter." },
  2807: { descEn: "Romania completing two CANDU heavy-water reactors.", detailEn: "At Cernavoda in Romania, units 3 and 4 (each ~700 MW), begun in the 1980s, are being completed, advancing in 2025 toward around 2031 — significantly raising Romania's nuclear share and cementing its regional power-export role." },
  2814: { descEn: "Phase 1 of the Lianjiang Hualong One plant in Guangdong.", detailEn: "At Lianjiang in Zhanjiang, Guangdong, this uses the home-grown third-generation Hualong One, with two 1.2 GW units in phase 1 — an important clean baseload source for western Guangdong, recently approved and under construction to support the province's low-carbon transition." },
  2815: { descEn: "China's home-grown large Gen-III reactor 'Guohe One' demonstration.", detailEn: "At Shidao Bay in Rongcheng, Shandong, this demonstrates China's indigenous large advanced PWR 'Guohe One' (CAP1400) at 1.5 GW per unit. The first unit started up in late 2024 with more under construction, moving CAP1400 into scaled deployment, listed among 2026 large-investment-supported projects." },
  2823: { descEn: "Korea completing two indigenous APR1400 reactors.", detailEn: "At Uljin in North Gyeongsang, KHNP is building two 1.4 GW APR1400 indigenous Gen-III reactors, restarted and advancing through 2024-2025 — emblematic of Korea's nuclear revival, with the same APR1400 exported to the UAE and Czechia." },
  3525: { descEn: "A 56 GW integrated solar super-factory in Taiyuan — the world's largest single PV base.", detailEn: "JinkoSolar's 56 GW vertically integrated base in Shanxi, at about 56 billion yuan, builds 56 GW each of ingots/wafers/cells/modules in four phases. Phases 1-2 started in 2024 and 3-4 in 2025, creating the world's largest, highest-efficiency TOPCon integrated digital super-factory, employing ~30,000 at capacity." },
  1019: { descEn: "A Weichai-BYD blade-battery base, online March 2025.", detailEn: "The Weichai-FinDreams (Yantai) new-energy park in Fushan, Yantai spans ~1,700 mu with ~56 billion yuan planned — a key new-energy pivot for Weichai, China's largest diesel-engine maker. Phase 1 builds 20 GWh of cells and 20 GWh of blade-battery PACK lines; the first blade battery rolled off on 28 March 2025 — a huge new Yantai industrial power load." },
  2004: { descEn: "A $7.8 billion TSMC-affiliated VIS-NXP 12-inch fab in Singapore.", detailEn: "VisionPower (VSMC), a JV of VIS (a TSMC affiliate) and NXP, announced ~$7.8 billion in June 2024 for a 300mm fab in Singapore, starting in late 2024 with production in 2027 reaching 55,000 wafers/month by 2029 across 130-40nm — process technology licensed from TSMC, targeting auto, industrial and consumer markets and creating ~1,500 jobs." },
  1530: { descEn: "Kazakhstan's largest petrochemical project, ending all-import polyethylene.", detailEn: "KazMunayGas, with Russia's SIBUR and Sinopec, is building a 1.25-million-tonne/year polyethylene plant at the Atyrau industrial petrochemical park, fed by Tengiz gas. First pile in late 2024 and formal start in March 2025, with Sinopec Engineering as EPC; at ~$7.7 billion, it is due in 2028 and onstream in 2029, ending Kazakhstan's 100% polyethylene imports." },
  351: { descEn: "The Middle East's first clean-power-driven LNG export terminal.", detailEn: "At Ruwais Industrial City in Abu Dhabi, two liquefaction trains total 9.6 million tonnes/year, doubling ADNOC LNG capacity to 15 million tonnes. FID was taken in June 2024 with a $5.5 billion EPC contract; the first train is due in 2028." },
  2000: { descEn: "The world's largest 200mm silicon-carbide power-chip fab, phase 3.", detailEn: "Phase 1 (€2 billion) started in August 2024; phase 2 (up to €5 billion) and phase 3 bring the total to ~€7 billion built in stages to the late 2020s, making it Infineon's largest 200mm front-end base in Kulim, Malaysia. SiC capacity is underpinned by ~€5 billion of design wins and €1 billion of prepayments from auto and industrial customers." },
  2204: { descEn: "A fully privately-funded million-tonne green-ammonia flagship.", detailEn: "Signed by Egypt and France, the Ras Shukheir green-hydrogen and derivatives complex on the Red Sea has €7 billion of fully private investment in three phases, producing 1 million tonnes of green ammonia a year at capacity, mainly as marine fuel for Suez Canal traffic. It includes a 368 km² wind-solar base, desalination, a 7 km transmission corridor and a dedicated Red Sea jetty; phase 1 (EDF Renewables and Zero Waste, €2 billion, 300,000 t/year) targets 2029." },
  2988: { descEn: "A 500,000-vehicle/year Hyundai megaplant with an LG battery JV.", detailEn: "The Hyundai Motor Group Metaplant America (HMGMA) at Ellabell in Bryan County, Georgia is $7.6 billion and over 16 million sq ft; the first IONIQ 5 rolled off in October 2024, IONIQ 9 entered production, and the first Kia model arrives in 2026, with a $4.3 billion HL-GA battery JV. Hyundai is adding $21 billion of US investment over 2025-2028." },
  3240: { descEn: "Chennai Metro phase 2: three corridors, ~119 km, 128 stations.", detailEn: "Phase 2 comprises the Madhavaram-SIPCOT, Lighthouse-Poonamallee and Madhavaram-Sholinganallur corridors, with 30 billion rupees in FY2025-26 from the centre, planning partial opening in 2026 and full operation by 2028-29, lifting Chennai's metro network to 173 km." },
  1111: { descEn: "A northwest high-speed line completing the Beijing-Lanzhou corridor.", detailEn: "The Baoyin high-speed railway runs 519 km from Baotou to Yinchuan via Bayannur, Ordos, Wuhai and Shizuishan at 250 km/h, ~54.6 billion yuan. The Baotou-Huinong section opened on 23 December 2025, completing the line (Baotou-Yinchuan in 2h38). With it the 'Beijing-Lanzhou' corridor is fully through, bringing Bayannur and Wuhai into the high-speed era." },
  786: { descEn: "A Danish-German multi-terminal HVDC offshore wind hub.", detailEn: "Turning Denmark's Bornholm island into an offshore wind hub with 3 GW nearby (~2 GW for Germany, 1.2 GW for Denmark) to power three million homes. Germany and Denmark signed a bilateral deal in January 2026 and won a €645 million EU grant, targeting operation in 2032 — the world's first cost-shared cross-border offshore wind project." },
  1150: { descEn: "An inter-oceanic isthmus railway; Line K phase 1 opened November 2025.", detailEn: "Mexico's Interoceanic Corridor railway crosses the Tehuantepec Isthmus linking the Pacific port of Salina Cruz with the Atlantic port of Coatzacoalcos — a land alternative to the Panama Canal. The Z Line fully opened in late 2023; the 459 km K Line toward the Guatemala border was over 87% complete by early 2026 with phase 1 opening in November 2025. In spring 2025 Hyundai ran a first international vehicle-transport test across it in ~72 hours, ~5 days faster than the Panama Canal." },
  1752: { descEn: "A 3 GW offshore wind flagship off Ceará.", detailEn: "Neoenergia (Iberdrola group) plans the Jangadas offshore wind farm off Ceará — 3 GW, 200 15 MW turbines — having applied to IBAMA in December 2019, now in early environmental review. With Rio's Maravilha and Rio Grande do Sul's Águas Claras it forms a 9 GW Brazilian offshore portfolio, awaiting 2026 guidelines and first permits." },
  1753: { descEn: "A 3 GW offshore wind project off Rio Grande do Sul.", detailEn: "The Águas Claras offshore wind farm off Rio Grande do Sul, developed by Neoenergia, plans 3 GW with 200 15 MW turbines, applied to IBAMA in December 2019 and in early environmental licensing. The southern waters' strong winds make it a priority Brazilian offshore area, awaiting the first offshore auction and IBAMA's first permits in 2026." },
  2985: { descEn: "The most advanced 300mm silicon-wafer fab in the US; first wafers in 2025.", detailEn: "GlobalWafers' Sherman, Texas 300mm wafer fab produced first wafers in Q1 2025 — the most advanced high-volume 300mm wafer facility in the US. Phase 1 reached an initial 300,000 wafers/year in December 2025, with phase 2 starting in January 2026, at a planned ~$7.5 billion total." },
  3039: { descEn: "The world's first net-zero-emissions ethylene complex, in Alberta (delayed).", detailEn: "Dow's Path2Zero would be the world's first scope-1-and-2 net-zero ethylene cracker and derivatives complex, with carbon capture and blue-hydrogen power. Approved in November 2023, paused in April 2025 on tariffs and demand, and in January 2026 phase 1 slipped to 2029 and phase 2 to 2030, with cost up to ~C$10.3 billion." },
  1122: { descEn: "China's first airport with five commercial runways.", detailEn: "Guangzhou Baiyun Airport's ~53.8 billion-yuan phase-3 expansion opened its T3 terminal and fifth runway on 30 October 2025 after five years, making it China's first airport with five commercial runways and three terminals. It can handle 120 million passengers and 3.8 million tonnes of cargo near-term (ultimate 140 million); from January 2026 all 30 international airlines moved to T3, strengthening the Greater Bay Area hub." },
  1431: { descEn: "Phase 3 of Saudi Arabia's northern phosphate city; started early 2025.", detailEn: "At the Wa'ad Al Shamal mining city in Turaif, northern Saudi Arabia — one of the Middle East's largest mining projects — phase 3 is ~28 billion riyals (~$7.5 billion), launched by Prince Faisal in February 2025, lifting Saudi phosphate capacity to ~9 million tonnes a year. ~$922 million of construction contracts went to Chinese and Turkish contractors in January 2025." },
  1218: { descEn: "Indonesia's largest refinery upgrade.", detailEn: "At Balikpapan in East Kalimantan, Pertamina's refinery master plan (RDMP) raises capacity from 260,000 to 360,000 b/d and adds residue catalytic cracking to improve fuel quality. Inaugurated by President Prabowo in January 2026, it will help Indonesia stop diesel imports within 2026 and sharply cut gasoline imports." },
  3202: { descEn: "AM/NS India expanding Hazira crude steel from 9 to 15 million tonnes.", detailEn: "ArcelorMittal-Nippon Steel's AM/NS India is investing ~600 billion rupees to raise crude-steel capacity at Hazira, Gujarat from 9 to 15 million tonnes, adding a blast furnace, sinter, coke, converters and a hot-strip mill. Ground was broken in January 2025 with completion in H2 2026, eyeing 24 million tonnes by 2030." },
  183: { descEn: "The world's first UHV four-terminal flexible HVDC project.", detailEn: "This 2,681 km line spans Tibet, Yunnan, Guangxi and Guangdong at 10 GW rated capacity, with an integrated hydro-wind-solar base of over 150 billion yuan. Launched in September 2025 with the Guangdong section starting in January 2026, it targets full operation in 2029, delivering over 43 TWh of clean power a year." },
  502: { descEn: "The first site of the world's most powerful AI super-factory, in Wisconsin.", detailEn: "Microsoft is investing over $7.3 billion in the Fairwater 1 campus at Mount Pleasant, Wisconsin — 15 buildings, nearly 9 million sq ft, 3.3 GW at full power. A 400 MW phase 1 comes online in early 2026, joined with Atlanta's Fairwater 2 via dedicated fibre to form the world's first 'AI super-factory' for joint training." },
  2469: { descEn: "A R127 billion Transnet rail-and-port overhaul.", detailEn: "South Africa's state logistics giant Transnet announced R127 billion (~$7.3 billion) over five years to overhaul ageing rail and ports. Its three priority corridors are Richards Bay coal, Saldanha iron ore and Durban containers; an RFI to bring in private capital was issued in March 2025, with the Richards Bay dry-bulk terminal to expand 45% (18.5 to 26.9 million tonnes), focused on chrome and magnetite." },
  3279: { descEn: "IOCL's largest-ever single-site petrochemical complex at Paradip, Odisha.", detailEn: "In April 2025 IOCL signed an MoU with Odisha for a ~610.8 billion-rupee integrated PX and PTA complex with phenol, polypropylene and other downstream at Paradip, fed by its existing 15-million-tonne/year refinery — IOCL's largest single-site investment, expected to save over 300 billion rupees of forex a year." },
  3558: { descEn: "A new 350 km/h line across Anhui, Henan and Hubei.", detailEn: "318.4 km at 350 km/h and ~52.1 billion yuan from Fuyang West via Henan and Hubei to Huangzhou — a new north-south passenger corridor in central China. It has NDRC feasibility approval, with provinces along the route set to start in 2026." },
  1110: { descEn: "A key Yangtze-corridor high-speed section, opened December 2025.", detailEn: "The Wuhan-Yichang high-speed railway runs 313 km from Hankou via Tianmen, Jingshan, Jingmen and Dangyang to Yichang North at 350 km/h, ~52.3 billion yuan, opening on 26 December 2025 (Wuhan-Yichang in 69 minutes). A key section of the national Yangtze corridor, it links the Wuhan hub west toward the building Yichang sections, helping bring Shanghai-Chengdu within 6 hours." },
  2516: { descEn: "A second floating LNG vessel in the Rovuma Basin.", detailEn: "For the Coral North floating LNG project in Area 4 of Mozambique's Rovuma Basin, Eni took a $7.2 billion FID in October 2025 with partners CNPC, KOGAS, Mozambique's ENH and Abu Dhabi's XRG, producing 3.6 million tonnes of LNG a year from 2028. Technip Energies won key contracts; with the operating Coral South it lifts Mozambique's LNG above 7 million tonnes a year." },
  2649: { descEn: "An automated metro to the new Western Sydney Airport, opening 2026.", detailEn: "This ~23 km automated metro links St Marys with Western Sydney International Airport and the new Aerotropolis at about A$11 billion with several new stations. It is due to open in late 2026 alongside the new airport — one of NSW's largest rail projects, driving the Western Sydney aerotropolis." },
  1123: { descEn: "The world's largest offshore artificial-island airport.", detailEn: "Dalian Jinzhou Bay International Airport is China's first offshore artificial-island airport, ~50.9 billion yuan, built to 4F standard with four planned runways and a 900,000 m² terminal. Reclamation accelerated in 2025, forming 19.15 km² of land and ~95% of total works by mid-year; main completion is expected in 2028, set to be a Northeast Asian hub and the world's largest offshore airport." },
  105: { descEn: "Three 10-GW-class wind-and-solar bases in Xinjiang.", detailEn: "Northern Hami's Gobi and the Junggar Basin host multiple GW-scale wind and solar projects; in H1 2024 the Hami, Junggar and southern-Tarim 10-GW-class bases completed their 14th Five-Year tasks early, with Xinjiang adding 35.57 GW of renewables in 2024, the most of any province." },
  129: { descEn: "Shantou's drive to be a national offshore-wind industry base.", detailEn: "Built around an 'International Wind Power Innovation Port' strategy with a full offshore-wind supply chain, Shantou has attracted leaders like Mingyang and Goldwind, with several offshore projects approved and under construction, planning ~10 GW across nearshore and deep-sea waters." },
  263: { descEn: "North Africa's largest green-ammonia plant.", detailEn: "At Tarfaya in southwest Morocco, OCP uses local wind and solar to electrolyse green hydrogen for ammonia — 200,000 tonnes in 2026 rising to 1 million in 2027 — winning EU renewable-fuel pre-certification in June 2025 to open the European green-ammonia market." },
  514: { descEn: "A new Google campus in Cedar Rapids, Iowa.", detailEn: "In June 2025 Google committed $7 billion to expand its Iowa data centres, including a new campus in the Big Cedar industrial park at Cedar Rapids (first building due 2026, five phases) and an expansion at Council Bluffs, lifting Google's total Iowa investment above $13.8 billion." },
  1127: { descEn: "A freight railway land bridge linking the Red Sea to the capital.", detailEn: "The Saudi Landbridge builds over 1,500 km of railway, centred on the ~900 km Riyadh-Jeddah trunk plus a 146 km extension to King Abdullah Port on the Red Sea, giving direct freight access between the Red Sea and the capital. Built by the SAR-CRCC 'Saudi-China Landbridge' consortium with Al-Ayuni as local partner, it began in 2025 with phased tendering, targeting the 2030s — a backbone of the Vision 2030 logistics strategy." },
  1756: { descEn: "Ceará offshore wind directly supplying Pecém green hydrogen.", detailEn: "France's Qair plans the 1.2 GW Dragão do Mar offshore wind farm on the Ceará shelf, supplying a 2.2 GW electrolyser at Pecém port for ~296,000 tonnes of green hydrogen a year. At nearly $7 billion, it is a model of integrated offshore wind and green hydrogen, in IBAMA's offshore permit pipeline and the Pecém green-hydrogen hub, awaiting the offshore auction." },
  1872: { descEn: "~7 GW of long-duration pumped hydro across NEOM phases 2-4.", detailEn: "NEOM plans four pumped-hydro plants; besides phase-1 Nestor, the Al-Qimmah, Nima and Beach Mountain stations are planned at ~3,000/1,000/3,000 MW, totalling ~7 GW, providing intraday peaking and long-duration storage for the off-grid renewable system, phased in after Nestor for 2029-2031." },
  1964: { descEn: "A large Thai green hydrogen and ammonia value chain.", detailEn: "Thailand's PTT and EGAT signed an MoU with Saudi ACWA Power to build a green hydrogen-and-ammonia value chain at ~$7 billion, targeting 225,000 tonnes of green hydrogen converted to ~1.2 million tonnes of green ammonia a year for power co-firing, exports to Japan and Korea and marine fuel. PTTGC-BIG cooperation and a Map Ta Phut hub are advancing in parallel — a flagship of Thailand's energy transition." },
  2001: { descEn: "A ~$7 billion advanced-packaging base in Penang; first phase in 2026.", detailEn: "Announced in 2021 at ~$7 billion (RM30 billion), Intel's Penang plant was paused then restarted under CEO Lip-Bu Tan, with another RM860 million added in December 2025 for assembly and test. With the building nearly done, advanced-packaging first-phase operation is set for 2026, reinforcing Malaysia's ~13% share of global assembly and test." },
  2253: { descEn: "OCP's green-ammonia plant at Tarfaya, reaching 3 million tonnes by 2032.", detailEn: "At the core of OCP's $13 billion green investment, ~$7 billion builds a green-ammonia plant at Tarfaya via the green-hydrogen route: 200,000 tonnes/year first output in 2026, 1 million in 2027 and 3 million by 2032 to decarbonise its own fertiliser supply chain. OCP earned $5 billion of H1 2025 revenue, issued a $1.75 billion bond in April and won SACE and AFD green loans." },
  2266: { descEn: "An eastern Algerian phosphate-to-fertiliser complex, ~$7 billion.", detailEn: "Sonatrach with China's CITIC develops an integrated phosphate project: the Tebessa facility (~$7 billion) processes Bled El Hadba ore into ~5.4 million tonnes of fertiliser a year, with a downstream plant near Souk Ahras (~$2 billion). Saipem won the FEED in June 2025; ~$1.5 billion more goes to mining the Bled El Hadba and Djebel El Onk deposits (~4.7 billion tonnes of reserves)." },
  3022: { descEn: "The Q line extended north to 125th Street, adding three East Harlem stations.", detailEn: "New stations at 106th, 116th and 125th Streets connect to Metro-North. Full FTA funding of $3.4 billion was secured in November 2023, with a ~$7 billion budget partly backed by congestion pricing; Skanska signed a ~$1 billion contract in June 2026, with boring expected in 2027 and opening in 2032." },
  3040: { descEn: "A planned world-largest low-carbon hydrogen-ammonia plant at Baytown, with CCS.", detailEn: "ExxonMobil plans the world's largest low-carbon hydrogen and ammonia facility at Baytown, Texas — up to 1 billion cubic feet/day of blue hydrogen and over 1 million tonnes of blue ammonia a year, capturing up to 7 million tonnes of CO₂ (~98% of production CO₂). ADNOC plans a 35% stake, with FID expected in 2025 and start-up in 2028-2029." },
  3219: { descEn: "AWS's $7 billion 14-year Hyderabad data-centre expansion.", detailEn: "AWS announced $7 billion over 14 years to expand its Asia Pacific (Hyderabad) cloud infrastructure, on top of an $8.3 billion Mumbai-region top-up the same year, targeting 2-3 GW of data-centre capacity in India for AI and cloud demand." },
  3266: { descEn: "A ~$7 billion double-tracking upgrade of the 1,687 km Karachi-Peshawar ML-1.", detailEn: "ML-1 is Pakistan's main railway, ~1,687 km from Karachi's Kiamari to Peshawar; phase 1 (~929 km, $3.32 billion) and phase 2 (~796 km, $3.36 billion) are planned with a China-led financing consortium including the ADB and AIIB. In December 2025 Pakistan Railways reached an agreement with the ADB on the project." },
  3438: { descEn: "The largest China-Russia nuclear project; Tianwan phase 4, unit 7 cold-tested in 2025.", detailEn: "At the Tianwan base in Lianyungang, Jiangsu, developed by Jiangsu Nuclear Power, phase-4 units 7 and 8 use Russia's AES-2006 (VVER-1200) at 1.265 GW each. Construction was witnessed by the Chinese and Russian presidents via video in May 2021, with unit 7 completing cold tests in 2025." },
  3570: { descEn: "A hub-airport phase-3 expansion: a 610,000 m² T3 and third runway.", detailEn: "This expansion adds a 3,600 m third runway and taxiway system south of the second runway, plus a 610,000 m² T3 terminal west of T1/T2, 174 stands and a ground transport centre, at ~50 billion yuan. It would lift the airport to 65 million passengers and 900,000 tonnes of cargo a year; Nanjing has made it the city's top project for 2026, aiming to start by end-2026." },
  4516: { descEn: "Datang's 1 GW solar MoU with Zambia's ZESCO.", detailEn: "In October 2024, witnessed by Zambia's science minister and ZESCO's chairman, Datang Overseas Investment signed a 1 GW solar MoU and an energy-technology-innovation-centre MoU with ZESCO, building on an earlier 220 MW cooperation. The 1 GW solar would greatly boost Zambia's clean-energy supply, with an accompanying innovation centre; it is in early planning." },
  1194: { descEn: "Stabroek's seventh development; FID in September 2025.", detailEn: "Hammerhead is ExxonMobil's seventh approved development in Guyana's Stabroek block, taking FID in September 2025 at about $6.8 billion, with the SBM-built FPSO Jaguar producing an initial 150,000 b/d. With block reserves near 11 billion barrels of oil equivalent, it targets 2029 start-up — an important part of Guyana's mid-term growth." },
  2061: { descEn: "A railway giving landlocked Laos sea access via Vietnam's Vung Ang port.", detailEn: "Linking Vientiane in Laos with Vung Ang port in Ha Tinh, Vietnam, this gives landlocked Laos its first direct rail route to the sea, at about $6.6 billion as a PPP by Laos's PTL and Vietnam's Deo Ca Group. In December 2025 it was announced the Laos section starts in 2026 and the Vietnam section in 2027, targeting completion by 2030." },
  3533: { descEn: "A 46.8-billion-yuan hyperscale AI-compute centre in Pinghu, part of a national 10,000-GPU cluster.", detailEn: "In Xindai, Pinghu, Jiaxing, Zhejiang, this 46.8-billion-yuan centre adds 344 mu and over 560,000 m² of floor area for four high-grade AI-compute halls over a four-year build, becoming an important part of the national integrated compute network's 10,000-GPU cluster project." },
  251: { descEn: "The world's first large-scale green-hydrogen DRI plus electric-arc steel plant.", detailEn: "At Boden in northern Sweden, this plant uses a 690 MW electrolyser to make wind-powered green hydrogen to reduce iron ore instead of coke. Electrolyser modules were installed by end-2025 (~60% overall), with 2.5 million tonnes of green steel after hot commissioning in 2026 — the most important green-metallurgy demonstration globally." },
  630: { descEn: "A top-ten global copper mine, shut since 2023, awaiting a 2026 restart decision.", detailEn: "In Coclé, Panama, Cobre Panamá produced ~400,000 tonnes of copper a year (~1% of global) until it was shut in November 2023 amid nationwide protests. An environmental-social audit finished in late 2025, with the president promising a decision on its fate by June 2026; a restart would add major copper supply globally." },
});

/* ===== 批次6：全库投资额 TOP（约 56–65 亿美元）===== */
Object.assign(window.ENERGY_EN, {
  1146: { descEn: "North America's largest driverless light-rail network; phase 2 opened November 2025.", detailEn: "The REM is a ~67 km fully automated driverless light-rail system for Greater Montreal, built and operated by CDPQ Infra. It launched on 14 November 2025, with the 33 km/14-station Deux-Montagnes branch through the Mount Royal tunnel opening on the 17th; four western stations follow in May 2026 and the Trudeau Airport spur in 2027." },
  1221: { descEn: "The fourth Central Asia-to-China gas line.", detailEn: "Line D runs ~966 km from Turkmenistan's Galkynysh field via Uzbekistan, Tajikistan and Kyrgyzstan into Xinjiang at 30 bcm/year, greatly raising total Central Asia-China pipeline capacity. Long delayed over transit and pricing, Galkynysh phase-4 development and Line D construction advanced in early 2026 — key to diversifying China's overland energy imports." },
  1764: { descEn: "Four green-powered data centres at the Pecém green digital hub in Ceará.", detailEn: "In November 2025 Ceará's export-processing zone approved Exportdata's four data centres (partnered with Casa dos Ventos executives) at R$349 billion, phased to 2032, forming the Pecém port green digital hub alongside the ByteDance project, powered 100% by new Casa dos Ventos wind farms and creating ~95,000 jobs." },
  2024: { descEn: "Oracle's $6.5 billion Malaysia public cloud region.", detailEn: "Oracle is investing over $6.5 billion in a Malaysian public cloud region — its 12th in Asia-Pacific — with 150+ cloud services and an OCI supercluster of 130,000 Blackwell GPUs, likely in Johor (a 15-year lease on Yondr's 98 MW first phase), phased from 2025 to capture Southeast Asian sovereign-cloud and AI demand." },
  2255: { descEn: "Africa's first battery gigafactory; Gotion's 20 GWh first phase at Kenitra.", detailEn: "Led by China's Gotion High-Tech at ~$5.6-6.8 billion, Africa's first battery gigafactory at Kenitra, Morocco broke ground in May 2025 for a 20 GWh first phase (expandable to 100 GWh) making cells, cathode and anode materials, ~85% for the EU, drawing a full chain of Chinese suppliers." },
  3323: { descEn: "The region's largest iron-ore deposit (~2.2 billion tonnes).", detailEn: "Hajigak in Bamyan province, central Afghanistan is the region's largest iron-ore deposit at ~2.2 billion tonnes, a world-class find. After an Indian consortium won then withdrew in 2011, the Taliban signed seven mining contracts worth ~$6.5 billion with Chinese, Iranian, Turkish and UK firms in August 2023, including a 30-year Herat iron deal giving the government a 13% share." },
  787: { descEn: "The finale of Iberdrola's East Anglia offshore wind cluster.", detailEn: "In the southern North Sea off England, ScottishPower Renewables' wholly-owned 960 MW East Anglia THREE began substation works in Q4 2025, with foundations in 2027 and operation in 2028 to power ~950,000 homes." },
  3017: { descEn: "A six-lane cable-stayed bridge across the Detroit River, among North America's longest.", detailEn: "With an 853 m main span and six lanes plus a walkway, the Canada-funded Gordie Howe International Bridge linking Windsor and Detroit cost about C$6.4 billion. The main structure was largely done by end-2025, with opening pushed to early 2026 on testing and border handover — set to be one of the busiest US-Canada freight crossings." },
  3559: { descEn: "A new 350 km/h line opening a high-speed corridor through the Wuling Mountains.", detailEn: "About 222 km at 350 km/h and ~45.4 billion yuan, this line links Qianjiang in Chongqing with Jishou in western Hunan, joining the Chongqing-Hunan and Zhangjiajie-Jishou-Huaihua high-speed lines; pre-review and industry review were completed in January 2026." },
  1463: { descEn: "The world's tallest dam; rising to 1,110 m in 2025.", detailEn: "On the Vakhsh River, Rogun's 335 m clay-core rockfill dam is the world's tallest, with 3,780 MW that would double Tajikistan's generation and power ~10 million people. By August 2025 the dam neared 1,110 m elevation (up ~100 m and 13 million m³ in a year); built by Italy's Webuild, with two units already running, Tajikistan aims for energy independence by 2027." },
  3572: { descEn: "Chongqing's second airport, a greenfield 4F hub, targeting 2030.", detailEn: "Sited at Zhengxing in Bishan, this 4F greenfield airport covers ~37 km² with 3-4 runways of 3,200-3,800 m, planned long-term for 70 million passengers and 3.5 million tonnes of cargo. Phase 1 (T1, two runways and a transport hub) is ~45 billion yuan; it is a key reserve project, to start early in the 15th Five-Year period and aim for 2030." },
  784: { descEn: "Poland's largest offshore wind project; FID January 2025.", detailEn: "In the Baltic 40 km off Poland, Baltica 2 is a 50/50 Orsted-PGE JV of 1.5 GW with 107 turbines and four offshore substations. After FID in January 2025, monopile installation starts in May 2026 for full operation by end-2027, powering 2.5 million Polish homes." },
  1212: { descEn: "The world's largest single polyolefins base.", detailEn: "At Ruwais Industrial City, Abu Dhabi, ADNOC-OMV's Borouge adds ~1.4 million tonnes/year of polyethylene/polypropylene with a world-largest ~1.8-million-tonne mixed-feed cracker. The first XLPE unit started up in April 2026 with the rest onstream through 2026, making Ruwais the world's largest single polyolefins complex." },
  2023: { descEn: "AWS's second Southeast Asia cloud region, live August 2024.", detailEn: "AWS launched its Asia Pacific (Malaysia) cloud region with three availability zones on 21 August 2024, planning $6.2 billion of cumulative investment by 2038, mainly in Selangor. It is expected to add ~$12.1 billion to Malaysian GDP and support 3,500+ jobs a year, strengthening local data residency and low latency." },
  2528: { descEn: "A world-class new refinery in Angola.", detailEn: "Sonangol's $6.2 billion Lobito refinery, 200,000 b/d, is in talks for a ~$4.8 billion Chinese loan to finish, targeting 2027 to sharply raise Angola's fuel self-sufficiency and cut imports." },
  3434: { descEn: "Zhejiang's fourth nuclear base; Jinqimen phase-1 island works fully started August 2025.", detailEn: "At Xiangshan in Ningbo, Zhejiang, CNNP-controlled Jinqimen plans six MW-class PWRs; phase-1 units 1-2 use Hualong One at 1.2 GW each with a 60-year design life, approved by the State Council in December 2023 with nuclear-island works in full swing from August 2025." },
  3563: { descEn: "A 350 km/h coastal-corridor line from Wenzhou to Fuzhou; started September 2025.", detailEn: "About 287.7 km at 350 km/h and ~44 billion yuan from Wenzhou via Rui'an, Cangnan, Fuding and Ningde to Fuzhou — part of the national coastal corridor. It started on 29 September 2025 for 2030 completion, putting Wenzhou-Fuzhou within about an hour." },
  879: { descEn: "Xinjiang's largest green hydrogen-ammonia-methanol investment to date.", detailEn: "Led by Energy China at 44.5 billion yuan in Kashgar, Xinjiang, this plans a GW-scale off-grid integrated green-power-to-hydrogen-ammonia-methanol park; environmental review began in September 2025, with approvals by end-2025 and core construction in Q1 2026." },
  3254: { descEn: "The Eastern Dedicated Freight Corridor's core section is fully in service.", detailEn: "The EDFC core from Ludhiana in Punjab to Sonnagar in Bihar (1,337 km) was fully commissioned in November 2025; the full ~1,856 km to Dankuni in West Bengal is under construction at ~510 billion rupees, running ~385 freight trains a day." },
  3407: { descEn: "Qingdao's first large 3 GW offshore wind project.", detailEn: "In national-managed waters of Qingdao's southeast EEZ, this project plans 214 14 MW turbines (~2,996 MW) with offshore and onshore converter stations. The offshore part was approved in November 2024, with environmental review in September 2025 and the 3.1-billion-yuan onshore export works approved on 31 December 2025." },
  3430: { descEn: "China's first nuclear project with private (Geely) capital; phase-2 unit 3 started November 2025.", detailEn: "At Xiaguan in Cangnan, Wenzhou, Zhejiang, CGN-controlled Cangnan plans six Hualong One units; phase 2 builds units 3-4 at 1.2 GW each, approved by the State Council in August 2024 and among Zhejiang's Q1 construction starts." },
  3435: { descEn: "The starting point for series deployment of the Guohe One (CAP1400); siting EIA approved December 2025.", detailEn: "At Dongmajiapo in Laiyang, Yantai, Shandong, SPIC plans six Guohe One units at ~128.3 billion yuan; fully built, over 9.2 GW would make it one of China's largest nuclear bases, with two units in phase 1." },
  3436: { descEn: "SPIC's Lianjiang nuclear phase 2; two Guohe One units, preparatory work fully launched in 2025.", detailEn: "At Cheban in Lianjiang, Zhanjiang, Guangdong, SPIC's base plans two CAP1000 plus four Guohe One units; phase 2 builds Guohe One units 3-4 at ~1.53 GW each over a 60-month schedule, with phase 1 already started." },
  163: { descEn: "Africa's largest single-country renewable-development agreement.", detailEn: "In June 2024 Infinity Power (an Egypt Infinity-UAE Masdar JV) signed an MoU with Cameroon's West Region to phase in up to 4 GW of solar, wind, hydro and biomass by 2035 — a pillar of its 10 GW African expansion." },
  242: { descEn: "CATL's largest full-chain battery base in Southeast Asia.", detailEn: "At nearly $6 billion, this covers nickel mining in North Maluku, cathode materials and battery and vehicle production in Karawang; phase 1 is 6.9 GWh rising to 15 GWh at capacity, expected online by end-2026." },
  264: { descEn: "Australia's largest aluminium smelter goes green.", detailEn: "At Gladstone, Queensland, this 500,000-tonne/year smelter saw Rio Tinto sign Australia's largest renewable PPA (2.8 GW wind, solar and storage) in 2024; with federal and state subsidies, green aluminium could be produced from 2028." },
  273: { descEn: "Inner Mongolia's 'east-data-west-compute' hub, top-ranked for green computing.", detailEn: "Horinger New Area has landed 39 data-centre projects with 50,600 PFLOPS in use (94% AI compute) and 84.57% green power by May 2025, using wind, solar and a cold climate to serve Beijing-Tianjin-Hebei compute demand." },
  518: { descEn: "A CoreWeave Mid-Atlantic AI supercomputing campus in Lancaster, Pennsylvania.", detailEn: "In July 2025 CoreWeave announced converting two former printing plants in Lancaster, Pennsylvania into AI data centres with an initial 100 MW (expandable to 300 MW), developed by Chirisa and Machine Investment Group and leased exclusively by CoreWeave." },
  581: { descEn: "The UK's largest AI supercomputer, the first Stargate UK node.", detailEn: "Nscale is building the UK's largest AI supercomputing campus at Loughton, England, with Microsoft signing a $6 billion GPU-capacity lease; a first phase deploys 23,040 Nvidia GB300 GPUs and OpenAI places a Stargate UK node here, expandable to 90 MW and due online in Q1 2027." },
  631: { descEn: "One of the world's largest copper-gold mines, restarting in phases after a 2025 accident.", detailEn: "In West Papua, Indonesia, Grasberg — one of the world's largest single copper-gold mines — went underground in 2019. After a September 2025 mudflow accident it declared force majeure, restarting main production zones in Q2 2026, aiming to recover ~85% of capacity in H2 and full capacity by 2027-2028." },
  877: { descEn: "A 6 GW green-hydrogen project in WA, with Australian government funding.", detailEn: "On the WA coast in the Murchison region, Copenhagen Infrastructure Partners plans 6 GW of wind and solar for ~1.3 million tonnes of green ammonia export a year, winning A$814 million from the Hydrogen Headstart program in 2025 and fast-track status, targeting FID in 2027 and phase-1 operation in 2029." },
  1181: { descEn: "Argentina's first large-scale LNG export.", detailEn: "Southern Energy — Pan American Energy, YPF, Pampa, Harbour and Golar — deploys two floating liquefaction vessels at Punta Colorada (San Matías Gulf), Río Negro: Hilli Episeyo (2.45 MTPA) and the converting MkII (3.5 MTPA), fed by Vaca Muerta gas. The second vessel's FID came in 2025 with an 8-year deal with Germany's SEFE, targeting exports from late 2027." },
  1196: { descEn: "An expansion of the supergiant Caspian Kashagan field, with gas plants.", detailEn: "Kashagan in the northern Caspian produces ~450,000 b/d; the NCOC consortium is building two gas plants (~2.5 bcm/year of sales gas with LPG) and pursuing further expansion to reach 500,000 b/d in 2026 and 700,000 b/d by 2031. In October 2025 Kazakhstan and ExxonMobil discussed further growth — key to Central Asian output and gas use." },
  1213: { descEn: "The Middle East's largest ethane cracker.", detailEn: "At Ras Laffan Industrial City, Qatar, the QatarEnergy-Chevron Phillips Chemical JV builds a 2.08-million-tonne/year ethane cracker (the Middle East's largest) and two HDPE units totalling 1.68 million tonnes. Started in 2022 with $4.4 billion financing in 2023, it targets late 2026, lifting Qatar's petrochemical capacity to ~14 million tonnes/year." },
  1529: { descEn: "Compressors to sustain the Karachaganak condensate plateau.", detailEn: "KPO's expansion adds a fifth gas-reinjection compressor (2020-2025, fuel gas introduced July 2024) and a sixth (phase 1B, 2022-2028); by raising reinjection capacity to manage rising gas-oil ratios, it sustains liquids output at Kazakhstan's second-largest oil-and-gas field." },
  1540: { descEn: "Vostok Oil's Arctic export terminal, shipping via the Northern Sea Route.", detailEn: "Sever Bay is the Arctic crude export terminal of the Vostok Oil project, on the Kara Sea at the Yenisei mouth, with oil shipped by icebreaking tankers via the Northern Sea Route. Two cargo berths and a fleet berth are near completion, with throughput planned to reach 50 million tonnes a year by 2027." },
  1552: { descEn: "The world's largest undeveloped gold mine, Polyus's flagship.", detailEn: "In Irkutsk region, Sukhoi Log is called the world's largest undeveloped gold deposit. A trial at the Verninskaya plant produced first gold in 2024; the processing plant began construction in 2025 ($650-800 million capex that year), with ~$6 billion total. Phase 1 reaches 10 million tonnes/year of ore in 2028, with 30 million planned." },
  1716: { descEn: "A deepwater module 2 in the Sergipe-Alagoas basin, a new northeast producing area.", detailEn: "SEAP II (P-87) develops the ultra-deepwater Budião and other fields in the Sergipe-Alagoas basin ~80 km off Aracaju, producing 120,000 b/d and processing 12 million m³/day of gas. FID came in April 2026 with an SBM BOT contract in May (SEAP I+II over R$60 billion combined); oil from 2030 and gas from 2031 would lift northeast gas supply from 16% to 31%." },
  1898: { descEn: "The Saudi backbone of the GCC railway, linking the Kuwaiti and UAE borders.", detailEn: "As the core of the 2,117 km GCC rail network, the Saudi section runs ~672 km from Al-Khafji near Kuwait in the Eastern Province south to Al-Batha on the UAE border. SAR issued design-consultancy tenders in May 2025 (closing 30 June); the network targets 2030, with the Saudi section starting in 2026 to enable Gulf-wide rail interconnection." },
  1917: { descEn: "Saudi Arabia's fourth integrated phosphate-fertiliser project.", detailEn: "In January 2026 Ma'aden won an energy-ministry gas-feedstock allocation to begin engineering on its fourth phosphate project, adding ~2.5 million tonnes/year of phosphate and specialty fertilisers and ~1.1 million tonnes of ammonia, lifting group phosphate-fertiliser capacity toward 12 million tonnes/year — a net addition beyond Phosphate 3, on the northern phosphate belt." },
  2563: { descEn: "A cross-border iron-ore mine with a 510 km haul railway and the Kribi deep-water port.", detailEn: "Straddling the Cameroon-Congo border, Mbalam-Nabeba plans 35 million tonnes/year of iron ore, needing a ~510 km railway to the Kribi deep-water port. Formerly Sundance's Cam Iron, it passed to local firm Cameroon Mining after a licence dispute, forming a multi-billion-dollar integrated mine-rail-port development." },
  2656: { descEn: "Transport infrastructure for the Brisbane 2032 Olympics.", detailEn: "A cluster of transport works for the Brisbane 2032 Olympics — rail, bus rapid transit (Brisbane Metro expansion), venue links and airport upgrades — boosting Southeast Queensland's transit capacity and connectivity, with planning and construction advancing from 2025." },
  2716: { descEn: "A 1.5 GW offshore wind farm off Lincolnshire.", detailEn: "Off the Lincolnshire coast in eastern England, this ~1.5 GW offshore wind farm (developed by Corio Generation and others) can power ~1.6 million homes, advancing DCO consent and grid connection in 2025 as an important North Sea expansion." },
  2802: { descEn: "The UK's first small modular reactors, sited at Wylfa, Anglesey.", detailEn: "Great British Energy-Nuclear selected Rolls-Royce SMR as preferred partner and in November 2025 chose Wylfa on Anglesey, Wales as the UK's first SMR site, planning several 470 MW-class units for factory-built, series nuclear, targeting the 2030s." },
  2812: { descEn: "Haiyang CAP1000 phase 3, approved in 2025.", detailEn: "At Haiyang in Yantai, Shandong, using the localised Gen-III CAP1000, phase-3 units of 1.25 GW each were approved by the State Council in April 2025. The Haiyang base also pioneers nuclear district heating ('Warm Nuclear No.1'), a benchmark for nuclear power and zero-carbon heat in northern China." },
  2813: { descEn: "Sanmen Gen-III nuclear phase 3, approved in 2025.", detailEn: "At Sanmen in Taizhou, Zhejiang — one of the world's first AP1000 sites — phase-3 units were approved by the State Council in April 2025. Built on passive Gen-III safety technology, the continuing expansion serves Yangtze Delta clean power." },
  2817: { descEn: "China's demonstration sodium-cooled fast reactor with a closed fuel cycle.", detailEn: "At Xiapu in Fujian, the CFR-600 is China's demonstration sodium-cooled fast reactor, two 600 MW units. Fast reactors greatly improve uranium use and transmute long-lived waste — key to Gen-IV nuclear and a closed fuel cycle; the first unit is near start-up and the second under construction, targeting around 2026." },
  2821: { descEn: "India's largest nuclear base completing two more VVER units.", detailEn: "At Kudankulam in Tamil Nadu, India's largest nuclear base, Russia's Rosatom is helping complete units 5 and 6 (1 GW VVER-1000 each), with main works advancing in 2025 toward around 2027 to support southern India's power and clean-energy goals." },
  2830: { descEn: "A world-leading commercial fusion effort; Google to buy ARC power.", detailEn: "At Devens, Massachusetts, Commonwealth Fusion Systems is building the SPARC tokamak (demonstrating net fusion gain), largely done by end-2026 with first plasma in 2027, and plans a ~400 MW ARC commercial fusion plant in Virginia. Google has agreed to buy 200 MW from ARC, becoming the first fusion firm to apply to join the PJM grid in 2026 — a global commercial-fusion frontrunner." },
  3036: { descEn: "A midscale LNG export terminal at the Port of Brownsville, EPC with Kiewit.", detailEn: "Glenfarne's Texas LNG at the Port of Brownsville has 4 million tonnes/year total in two phases. FERC re-approved it early in August 2025, and in March 2026 it signed a full-facility EPC with Kiewit, aiming for completion by end-2029." },
  3294: { descEn: "Five Pakistani refineries upgrading to Euro-V, ~$6 billion total.", detailEn: "Pakistan's 2023 brownfield refining policy is pushing PARCO, Attock, NRL, Cnergyico and PRL to upgrade for Euro-V fuels, drawing at least $6 billion, with capacity potentially rising from ~21-23 million tonnes/year toward ~33 million by 2035; PARCO plans to bring in ~$1.3 billion from the UAE for a hydrocracker." },
  3571: { descEn: "A Silk Road hub expansion: a new T4 and twin runways; North Terminal opened April 2025.", detailEn: "This rebuild lifts terminal space to 500,000 m² and upgrades the airfield to 4F with three runways and 198 stands, designed for 35 million passengers and 550,000 tonnes of cargo at ~42.84 billion yuan. T4 and the two northern runways opened on 17 April 2025, with the airport renamed Urumqi Tianshan International." },
  4206: { descEn: "Tsingshan-led integrated nickel-stainless super-park at Morowali, Indonesia.", detailEn: "At Morowali in Central Sulawesi, this 2,000+ hectare park is a JV of Shanghai Decent (66.25%) and Indonesia's Bintang Delapan (33.75%), producing 4.2 million tonnes of nickel-iron, 4 million tonnes of stainless steel, 7 million tonnes of carbon steel and 90,000 tonnes of HPAL nickel a year, with coke power, ferrochrome, a 140-million-tonne port and 2,000+ MW of captive power (~4,300 MW total) — the world's first full mining-to-stainless chain park." },
  3560: { descEn: "A new 350 km/h line, part of the Baotou(Yinchuan)-Haikou corridor.", detailEn: "About 276 km at 350 km/h and ~42 billion yuan, this line links Baotou and Ordos in Inner Mongolia with Yulin in Shaanxi as part of the Bao(Yin)-Hai corridor; the pre-feasibility study is done, aiming to start in 2026." },
  3561: { descEn: "China's southernmost cross-strait high-speed link, using rail plus ferry across the Qiongzhou Strait.", detailEn: "With ~132 km of onshore mainline at 350 km/h and a ~23 km ferry crossing of the Qiongzhou Strait, at ~41.94 billion yuan, this is part of the Bao(Yin)-Hai corridor. The NDRC approved the ferry crossing and related lines on 31 December 2025, aiming for completion within the 15th Five-Year period." },
  3585: { descEn: "An 11-million-tonne refining phase 2 at Zhenhai, lifting the base above 50 million tonnes.", detailEn: "At Zhenhai in Ningbo, Zhejiang, this 41.6-billion-yuan phase 2 covers 18 chemicals-focused units (11-million-tonne CDU, FCC, propane dehydrogenation, polypropylene). The core 11-million-tonne refining unit started up in January 2025, lifting Zhenhai's refining to 40-million-tonne class and the Ningbo petrochemical base above 50 million tonnes." },
  244: { descEn: "One of the largest new US battery campuses.", detailEn: "At Glendale, Kentucky, this twin-plant BlueOval SK campus totals 86 GWh, mainly for the Ford F-150 Lightning; first cells rolled off in August 2025 with ~5,000 jobs, backed by a US DOE loan." },
  255: { descEn: "Korea's largest US steel investment.", detailEn: "In Louisiana, this plant will make 2.7 million tonnes/year of low-carbon automotive sheet with 70% lower emissions than a blast furnace, with POSCO holding 20%; construction starts in Q1 2026 for 2029 production, mainly for the US-Mexico auto market." },
  874: { descEn: "South Africa's largest green hydrogen-ammonia export project.", detailEn: "At the Coega industrial zone in Eastern Cape, a JV of UK's Hive Energy and South Africa's BuiltAfrica plans $5.8 billion for 3.5 GW of wind and solar and 1 million tonnes/year of green ammonia for Europe, with $20 million of SA-H2 fund development finance, FID targeted for H2 2026 and operation from 2029." },
  2054: { descEn: "An east-west metro trunk line across Bangkok; western section under construction.", detailEn: "35.9 km (27 km underground, 22 stations; 8.9 km elevated, 7 stations) in eastern (22.5 km) and western (13.4 km) sections at ~200 billion baht. BEM holds a 140-billion-baht, 30-year PPP for the western section; the eastern civil works finished in June 2023 and the western started in July 2024, targeting the east by May 2028 and the west by 2030." },
  2460: { descEn: "South Africa's first large-scale green-ammonia export project, with Topsoe technology.", detailEn: "Hive Hydrogen is developing a 1-million-tonne/year green-ammonia plant at the Coega SEZ powered by 1,499 MW of wind and 1,430 MW of solar (3.5 GW total). Denmark's Topsoe won a ~$1 billion technology contract and the SA-H2 fund injected $20 million; full output is designed for 2029, expandable to 4 million tonnes." },
  1223: { descEn: "A petrochemical expansion at the Bina refinery in central India.", detailEn: "At Bina in Madhya Pradesh, BPCL is raising refining from 7.8 to 11 million tonnes/year and adding a petrochemical complex with a 1.2-million-tonne dual-feed cracker plus PE, PP and aromatics. A ~318-billion-rupee syndicated loan closed financing in January 2025; ~11% complete by March 2025, it targets 2028 — central to BPCL's shift from fuels to chemicals." },
  1810: { descEn: "A green-iron project in Bahia's Chapada Diamantina.", detailEn: "Brazil Iron and state miner CBPM develop a green-iron project in Bahia's Chapada Diamantina (Piatã, Abaíra, Jussiape) at ~$5.7 billion, using direct reduction to make ultra-low-carbon hot-briquetted iron (HBI), with three open-pit mines, a 120 km rail spur, a pellet plant and a coastal HBI plant at Porto Sul. With ~1.7 billion tonnes of resources, it starts in late 2026 for 2030 production." },
  2989: { descEn: "Twin battery plants at Kokomo; plant 1 online, plant 2 in 2027, 67 GWh combined.", detailEn: "The Stellantis-Samsung SDI StarPlus JV is investing over $5.7 billion in two lithium plants at Kokomo, Indiana; plant 1 started up in December 2024 (33 GWh) and plant 2 is due in early 2027 (initially 34 GWh), totalling 67 GWh, with a ~$7.54 billion DOE loan." },
  4298: { descEn: "State Grid holds ~21% of HK Electric Investments, in Hong Kong's grid.", detailEn: "State Grid subscribed ~21% (~$5.7 billion) as the largest cornerstone investor when HK Electric Investments listed in 2014. HK Electric is the sole power supplier to Hong Kong Island and Lamma Island, a vertically integrated utility from generation to supply — a key Hong Kong grid asset giving State Grid stable returns and an overseas-grid platform." },
  1128: { descEn: "Dubai Metro's third line, opening 2029.", detailEn: "The 30 km Blue Line (15.5 km underground, 14.5 km elevated) links several hubs; the design-build contract went to MAPA-Limak-CRRC in late 2024, with CRRC supplying 28 driverless trains. Works began in June 2025 with tunnelling, ~12% complete by December, targeting 9 September 2029 (the metro's 20th anniversary)." },
  1147: { descEn: "The world's first floating-bridge light rail; cross-lake link opens March 2026.", detailEn: "Seattle's Sound Transit Line 2 (East Link), ~23 km, links downtown Seattle with Redmond via 10 stations including Bellevue and Mercer Island. On 28 March 2026 the cross-Lake-Washington segment opens, running ~7 miles on the world's first floating-bridge electrified light rail along I-90, with Judkins Park and Mercer Island stations — connecting Seattle and Bellevue in ~20 minutes after 18 years of planning." },
});

/* ===== 批次7：全库投资额 TOP（约 50–60 亿美元）===== */
Object.assign(window.ENERGY_EN, {
  4222: { descEn: "Aramco-Sinopec Yanbu petrochemical expansion: 1.8 Mt ethylene + 1.5 Mt aromatics.", detailEn: "In April 2025 Saudi Aramco, Sinopec and YASREF signed a framework to build a 1.8-million-tonne/year mixed-feed steam cracker and 1.5-million-tonne/year aromatics complex at Yanbu Industrial City, creating a world-class petrochemical cluster. The Yanbu refinery processes 430,000 b/d of Saudi heavy crude, with Aramco holding 62.5% and Sinopec 37.5%." },
  4501: { descEn: "CATL's Karawang battery plant and full nickel-to-recycling chain in Indonesia, ~$6 billion.", detailEn: "CATL and Indonesian partners are building a battery plant in Karawang, West Java plus a full chain from nickel mining through materials, cells and recycling, with eventual investment near $6 billion. Phase 1 is 6.9 GWh built to lighthouse-factory standard; at capacity it would produce 142,000 tonnes of nickel and 30,000 tonnes of cathode a year and recycle ~20,000 tonnes of batteries, with Brunp's DRT process giving Indonesia its first recycling system (>95% metal recovery), later extending to storage." },
  2092: { descEn: "The Philippines' largest undeveloped copper-gold mine.", detailEn: "In southern Mindanao ~40 km from General Santos, Tampakan is one of the world's largest undeveloped copper-gold deposits, planned for ~375,000 tonnes of copper and 360,000 ounces of gold a year over a 17-year life. First production slipped from 2026 to 2028; it is seeking a strategic partner with advanced technology, with Chinalco set to take a ~$2 billion stake in parent Indophil." },
  1187: { descEn: "China's largest offshore gas field; phase 2 fully online June 2025.", detailEn: "In the Qiongdongnan Basin of the South China Sea ~150 km off Hainan in ~1,500 m of water, Deep Sea No.1 is China's first deep-water high-pressure gas field. Phase 2 added 12 subsea wells with a new manifold platform and subsea production system, fully online on 25 June 2025, lifting capacity above 4.5 bcm a year to become China's largest offshore gas field, supplying the Greater Bay Area and Hainan." },
  1805: { descEn: "South America's largest auto investment; Leapmotor production at Goiana.", detailEn: "Stellantis announced ~30-32 billion reais of South American investment over 2025-2030 (~30 billion in Brazil), its largest ever. From 2026 it SKD-assembles China's Leapmotor B10 and C10 EVs at Goiana, Pernambuco, launches its first electrified model at Betim the same year and adds six Bio-Hybrid ethanol models, deepening localisation." },
  2987: { descEn: "BlueOval City battery plant, run by SK On, in production 2028.", detailEn: "Ford's BlueOval City near Stanton, Tennessee is ~$5.6 billion overall (vehicles, supplier park and battery plant). In December 2025 Ford and SK On signed a deal: Ford buys two Kentucky battery plants and SK On runs the 45 GWh Tennessee plant, with mass production in 2028." },
  1117: { descEn: "A coastal high-speed artery across Hangzhou Bay.", detailEn: "The Tong-Su-Jia-Yong high-speed railway, part of the national coastal corridor, runs ~309.8 km at 350 km/h, with a Hangzhou Bay sea-crossing rail bridge as its key structure. In 2025 the bridge entered over-water construction, with the 200 m main tower of the north navigation bridge advancing; due by end-2027, it directly links Nantong-Suzhou-Jiaxing-Ningbo, reshaping Yangtze Delta travel." },
  103: { descEn: "China's first UHVDC corridor powered mainly by a desert wind-solar base.", detailEn: "Supporting the Longdong-Shandong ±800 kV UHVDC line, this builds ~16 GW of wind and solar in the Qingyang area of Gansu — the first UHV corridor in China powered mainly by a desert mega-base — with construction from 2024 and source-grid coordinated start-up." },
  131: { descEn: "China's earliest 10-GW-class wind base.", detailEn: "Jiuquan (Guazhou, Yumen) in Gansu is China's earliest large-scale wind base, with over 10 GW of wind plus growing solar and CSP, exporting via several UHV lines as a hub of west-to-east clean power." },
  142: { descEn: "Germany's largest offshore wind cluster under construction in the North Sea.", detailEn: "Comprising Nordlicht I (980 MW) and II (630 MW) ~85 km north of Borkum, Vattenfall took FID on phase I in March 2025 and confirmed FID for the whole cluster after full permits in January 2026, with both phases fully online in 2028 — Vattenfall's largest single German investment." },
  245: { descEn: "LG Energy Solution's largest wholly-owned US battery base.", detailEn: "At Queen Creek, Arizona, two plants make 27 GWh of cylindrical cells and 16 GWh of LFP storage cells; the cylindrical plant was completed in late 2025 and the LFP plant comes online in 2026." },
  270: { descEn: "One of the world's densest concentrations of hyperscale data centres.", detailEn: "Gui'an New Area hosts 27 large data centres from Huawei, Tencent, Apple and the three telecoms operators, with over 160 EFLOPS of compute (>98% AI), where Huawei Cloud is building the world's largest AI-compute centre — a core 'east-data-west-compute' site." },
  544: { descEn: "A core node of the Yangtze Delta Wuhu 'east-data-west-compute' hub.", detailEn: "Huawei Cloud's East China (Wuhu) data centre spans three districts over ~6,000 mu, planned for 3 million servers and opened in June 2024, with liquid cooling giving a ~1.1 annual PUE and 10-millisecond dedicated links across six East China provinces and Shanghai." },
  593: { descEn: "Microsoft and G42 add 200 MW via Khazna in the UAE, with a GB300 export licence.", detailEn: "In November 2025 Microsoft and G42 announced 200 MW of new UAE capacity via Khazna, winning a US export licence to deploy Nvidia GB300 equivalent to 60,000 A100s, online by end-2026 — central to Microsoft's $7.9 billion 2026-2029 UAE plan." },
  599: { descEn: "AWS's Asia Pacific (Thailand) cloud region, live January 2025.", detailEn: "AWS launched its Asia Pacific (Thailand) region with three availability zones covering Bangkok on 8 January 2025, pledging over $5 billion of investment over 2025-2037, expected to add $10 billion to Thai GDP and support 11,000 jobs a year." },
  640: { descEn: "BHP and Lundin merged two giant Argentine copper deposits in 2025.", detailEn: "In San Juan, Argentina, the world-class Filo del Sol and Josemaria copper deposits hold over 31.7 million tonnes of combined copper. BHP and Lundin merged them 50/50 in January 2025 and issued a pre-feasibility study in February, planning ~395,000 tonnes of copper-in-concentrate a year over the first 25 years, targeting a start around 2030 — one of Argentina's largest-ever mining investments." },
  1026: { descEn: "Europe's largest self-funded semiconductor investment.", detailEn: "Infineon is self-funding €5 billion in a Smart Power Fab in Dresden — its largest single investment — making power and analog/mixed-signal 12-inch wafers for EVs, renewables and data-centre power. Started in 2023, the cleanroom shell topped out in April 2025 and it won ~€1 billion of final EU Chips Act subsidy in May, targeting 2026 production." },
  1553: { descEn: "The world's largest palladium producer's nickel-palladium capacity and SO2 cleanup.", detailEn: "Nornickel's nickel-palladium-copper smelting base in Taymyr, Siberia committed $5.5 billion of environmental investment in 2020 ($3.6 billion for sulphur-dioxide capture), targeting a 90% SO2 cut by 2025. Its 2025 budget is ~210 billion roubles, with nickel capacity 204,000-211,000 tonnes and palladium 2.62-2.73 million ounces." },
  2706: { descEn: "Ireland's largest offshore wind farm, off Dublin.", detailEn: "Off Ireland's east coast near Dublin, the ~1.3 GW Dublin Array is Ireland's largest offshore wind project, a JV of EDF and Fred Olsen. As the core of Ireland's first ORESS offshore auction, it advanced planning consent and grid connection in 2025, targeting 2030." },
  3004: { descEn: "A 300 MW HPC campus at Barber Lake, West Texas.", detailEn: "On a 587-acre site near Colorado City, Texas, Cipher signed a $5.5 billion, 15-year, 300 MW turnkey compute lease with AWS supplying from July 2026, plus a 10-year full lease with Fluidstack (with a $333 million Google debt backstop)." },
  3023: { descEn: "A 14-mile light rail linking Brooklyn and Queens along existing freight lines.", detailEn: "Using the LIRR Bay Ridge and CSX Fremont branches, the ~14-mile Interborough Express links Bay Ridge in Brooklyn with Jackson Heights in Queens, estimated at ~$5.5 billion (half secured). In July 2025 Jacobs and HDR took the ~$166 million design contract." },
  3239: { descEn: "Delhi Metro phase 4 extensions, ~112 km.", detailEn: "Phase 4 covers the Inderlok-Indraprastha, Lajpat Nagar-Saket and Rithala-Narela-Kundli corridors among others, ~450 billion rupees network-wide. Priority sections target March 2026 and all works 2028, with the Janakpuri West-Krishna Park section already opened in January 2025." },
  320: { descEn: "Africa's longest high-speed railway under construction.", detailEn: "Extending from Kenitra to Casablanca and south to Marrakech, 430 km at 320 km/h, this is the large extension of Africa's first high-speed line, Al-Boraq. Started in April 2025 with 18 Alstom high-speed trains ordered, it targets 2029." },
  1201: { descEn: "A 1.5-million-tonne ethylene expansion at Zhenhai, completed 2025.", detailEn: "At Zhenhai in Ningbo, Zhejiang, this ~38.08 billion-yuan Sinopec chain-strengthening project adds 1.5 million tonnes/year of ethylene and 18 process units (POE, LDPE/EVA, adiponitrile and other new materials). Due in 2025, it gives Zhenhai 38 million tonnes of refining and 3.7 million tonnes/year of ethylene, feeding Yangtze Delta EV, solar and high-end-equipment chains." },
  3256: { descEn: "A deep-water container transhipment port at Galathea Bay, Great Nicobar.", detailEn: "Part of the Great Nicobar integrated development, the ICTP at Galathea Bay was designated India's 13th major port in September 2024, built in four phases — phase 1 (~2028) at ~4 million TEU rising to 16 million by 2058 — at ~440 billion rupees, with the DPR complete." },
  243: { descEn: "VW PowerCo's largest North American battery plant.", detailEn: "At St. Thomas, Ontario, PowerCo is investing up to €4.8 billion for 90 GWh a year at capacity; main construction reached October 2025, with production expected in 2027 — Canada's largest new-energy manufacturing project." },
  2311: { descEn: "Senegal's first offshore oilfield, 100,000 b/d.", detailEn: "Sangomar is Senegal's first offshore oilfield, led by Australia's Woodside at $5.2 billion, with first export in July 2024 at 100,000 b/d. 2025 output is expected at 34.5 million barrels, above initial estimates — a pillar of Senegal's oil sovereignty." },
  596: { descEn: "Korea's largest AI data centre, a 15-year SK-AWS partnership.", detailEn: "SK Group and AWS signed a 15-year deal to build Korea's largest AI data centre at the Ulsan national industrial park, ~7 trillion won, with a 41 MW first phase by 2027 expanding to 103 MW by 2029 and 1 GW long term, deploying 60,000+ GPUs, with groundbreaking in August 2025." },
  1210: { descEn: "A leading coal-to-liquids upgrade demonstration, advancing in 2025.", detailEn: "In the Shengyuan industrial park of Ejin Horo Banner, Ordos, Inner Mongolia, next to the world's first million-tonne direct coal-liquefaction unit, China Energy is building a ~36.5 billion-yuan, 3-million-tonne/year coal-to-liquids project (2.2 million tonnes direct, 800,000 indirect plus gasification, 18 units) making military/vehicle diesel, jet fuel, naphtha and asphalt — a 2025 priority for Ordos, supporting energy security and clean coal conversion." },
  1536: { descEn: "An expansion of the world's second-largest gas field, supporting exports to China.", detailEn: "Turkmengaz and CNPC signed for Galkynysh phase 4, with CNPC building a 10-bcm/year sales-gas facility at ~$5.1 billion for domestic use and exports to China. The field plans seven phases totalling ~200 bcm/year — the world's second-largest — with ~90% of Turkmen gas exported to China via the Central Asia-China pipeline." },
  3123: { descEn: "A 4,500 MW mega gravity dam on the Indus in Gilgit-Baltistan.", detailEn: "A concrete gravity dam across the Indus between Kohistan in KP and Diamer in Gilgit-Baltistan, developed by WAPDA with two underground powerhouses of six units each totalling 4,500 MW, at ~1.4 trillion rupees, targeting 2028." },
  3567: { descEn: "A sea bridge from Xiamen Xiang'an toward Kinmen; main line by end-2026.", detailEn: "The 17.34 km main line (14.2 km over water), eight lanes at 100 km/h, plus a 2.275 km Xiang'an spur, at ~36 billion yuan. By early 2026 over 13 billion yuan (~36%) was invested and works were 37% done, with the island-ring tunnel right bore through, aiming to open the offshore main bridge by end-2026 and the full line by December 2027." },
  1989: { descEn: "A 1,400 MW pumped-hydro station in Laguna, among Asia's largest.", detailEn: "The Pakil pumped-hydro station in Laguna, developed by Prime Infra's Ahunan Power, is 1,400 MW with 14,000 MWh of daily storage at ~$5.03 billion (296 billion pesos). A notice to proceed launched access-road and upper-reservoir works, with First Gen set to buy 40% in 2026, targeting 2030 — one of Asia's largest pumped-hydro plants." },
  124: { descEn: "China's earliest 10-GW-class solar park.", detailEn: "Built on the Longyangxia hydro-solar complementary scheme for steady output and famed for its 'solar sheep' grazing land restoration, this continually expanding park is a key part of China's second batch of desert mega-bases." },
  145: { descEn: "New York's largest offshore wind project under construction.", detailEn: "Off New York at 810 MW, wholly owned by Equinor, Empire Wind closed $3 billion of financing in late 2024. Halted then resumed by federal order in 2025 and with its lease suspended again at year-end, Equinor filed a legal challenge in early 2026; it remains under construction, aiming to power over 500,000 homes." },
  275: { descEn: "A flagship net-zero AI data centre in NEOM.", detailEn: "DataVolt and NEOM signed a $5 billion deal in February 2025 to develop a 1.5 GW AI data centre in the Red Sea Oxagon industrial zone, 100% renewable-powered with LG advanced cooling for net-zero emissions, with a 300 MW first phase expected in 2028." },
  783: { descEn: "Poland's first offshore wind farm, due online 2026.", detailEn: "On ~130 km² of Polish Baltic near-shore waters, this JV of Poland's ORLEN and Canada's Northland Power uses 76 Vestas 15 MW turbines; turbine and substation installation began in 2025 for full operation in 2026, powering 1.5 million Polish homes." },
  820: { descEn: "Africa's largest hydro plant, formally inaugurated September 2025.", detailEn: "On the Blue Nile in Ethiopia, the Grand Ethiopian Renaissance Dam totals 5.15 GW; started in 2011 and inaugurated in September 2025 after ~14 years, it is Africa's largest hydro plant, doubling Ethiopia's generation and enabling power exports, though Nile water-rights disputes with downstream Egypt and Sudan persist." },
  831: { descEn: "India's largest planned hydro plant.", detailEn: "In the Lower Dibang Valley of Arunachal Pradesh, this 2,880 MW project is India's largest single planned hydro plant; a diversion-tunnel breakthrough in 2025 marked a key milestone, with a 108-month schedule and 2032 completion to become India's largest hydro plant." },
  1013: { descEn: "A Hyundai-SK On battery plant, in production H2 2025.", detailEn: "At Cartersville in Bartow County, Georgia, Hyundai Motor Group and SK On (50/50, ~$5 billion) plan 35 GWh, enough for 300,000 Hyundai/Kia/Genesis EVs a year, beside the Hyundai Metaplant, adding ~3,500 jobs — a record-scale Georgia industrial power user, with cell mass production from H2 2025." },
  1177: { descEn: "A Train 7 expansion at Bonny Island LNG.", detailEn: "Nigeria LNG's Train 7 at Bonny Island lifts total capacity from 22 to 30 million tonnes/year, with EPC by Saipem, Chiyoda and Daewoo emphasising local content. It reached 80% in June 2025 and over 92% by 2026, entering system completion and pre-commissioning, with start-up expected in 2027." },
  1197: { descEn: "Uganda's first oil, with the East African Crude Oil Pipeline.", detailEn: "The Kingfisher field southeast of Lake Albert, operated by CNOOC at 40,000 b/d peak, sends crude via the 1,443 km East African Crude Oil Pipeline (EACOP) to Tanga port in Tanzania for export. By December 2025 EACOP was ~79% done, the Kingfisher central plant over 90% and all 19 initial wells drilled, targeting Uganda's first oil in H2 2026 — a landmark of the emerging East African oil corridor." },
  1387: { descEn: "An AWS-HUMAIN AI zone in Saudi Arabia.", detailEn: "AWS and HUMAIN announced over $5 billion for a Saudi AI zone, with AWS deploying up to 150,000 AI accelerators. Twin 100 MW campuses in Riyadh and Dammam broke ground in 2025, combining Nvidia GB300 and AWS Trainium chips, with first operation expected in Q2 2026." },
  1396: { descEn: "A scalable 22 MW campus at KIZAD, Abu Dhabi.", detailEn: "In January 2025 Gulf Data Hub signed with KKR to jointly invest over $5 billion expanding in the UAE and GCC. GDH has a 22 MW facility under construction at KIZAD in Abu Dhabi (four more planned there) and a fully pre-leased fifth Dubai facility due in Q1 2026, with ~90 MW under construction overall." },
  1405: { descEn: "Doha Metro phase 2: a new Blue Line plus Green and Gold extensions, to four lines and 300 km.", detailEn: "Phase 2 adds ~70 stations, centred on a semi-orbital Blue (City) Line linking Hamad Airport T2 with West Bay and other districts, plus extensions of the 2019-opened Green and Gold lines (the Green extension has ~10 km of tunnel and 10 km surface). The network reaches four lines and ~300 km, targeting around 2026." },
  1517: { descEn: "A railway from Central Asia through Afghanistan to the Indian Ocean.", detailEn: "Running ~573 km from the Uzbek border at Termez via Mazar-i-Sharif and Kabul to the Pakistani border, designed for 20 million tonnes/year. On 17 July 2025 the three countries' transport ministers signed a framework in Kabul; estimated at ~$5 billion (some figures $7 billion), it would cut Uzbekistan-Pakistan freight from 35 days to 3-5." },
  1521: { descEn: "A new southwest radial Moscow metro line, opening in sections.", detailEn: "The Troitskaya Line (Line 16) is a new Moscow metro radial built in sections toward Troitsk in New Moscow. The Tyutchevskaya-Novomoskovskaya section opened on 28 December 2024 and Novatorskaya-ZIL on 13 September 2025, with Sosenki, Vatutinki and Troitsk stations planned for 2029, serving the fast-growing southwest." },
  1535: { descEn: "A large gas-chemical complex making polymers via methanol-to-olefins.", detailEn: "MTO Central Asia is building a methanol-to-olefins complex in Karakul district, Bukhara region, converting domestic gas via methanol to ethylene and propylene and polymerising ~1.1 million tonnes/year of HDPE, LDPE, EVA, PET and polypropylene. It drew ~$5 billion of investment and technology from the US, Germany, Denmark, Austria, Italy and China, targeting full operation by end-2025." },
  1673: { descEn: "BYD's first European passenger-car plant, trial production early 2026.", detailEn: "At Szeged, Hungary, BYD's first self-built European passenger-car plant plans 200,000 vehicles a year, starting with the Dolphin Surf. A strategic pivot to local European production avoiding EU tariffs, the first lines arrived in December 2025, with trial production from late January 2026 and mass production in Q2 2026." },
  1718: { descEn: "A high-quality pre-salt discovery in the Santos Aram block.", detailEn: "The Aram block, won in the sixth production-sharing round in 2020, lies 248 km off Santos in 1,952 m of water. In May 2025 a discovery of clean, high-quality pre-salt crude was announced, with appraisal including two more wells; the ANP extended the exploration phase to June 2029, making it a key prospect for Petrobras's 2026-2030 plan and a likely base for a next-generation pre-salt FPSO." },
  1840: { descEn: "Upgrading the Yanbu Samref refinery into a crude-to-chemicals base.", detailEn: "On 8 December 2025 Aramco, ExxonMobil and Samref signed a venture framework to study upgrading the 400,000 b/d Samref refinery at Yanbu into an integrated petrochemical complex making high-value chemicals and low-emission distillates, advancing Aramco's liquids-to-chemicals strategy (4 million b/d by 2030). FEED has begun, with FID subject to market and approvals, targeting around 2030." },
  1885: { descEn: "An AI-ready data centre at First Tech Park, East Riyadh.", detailEn: "DataVolt agreed a lease with MODON for a 55,000 m² plot at First Tech Park in East Riyadh to build an advanced AI-processing, liquid-cooled data centre for hyperscale and cloud customers, part of DataVolt's $5 billion Saudi pipeline, targeting operation around 2027." },
  1969: { descEn: "A 2 GW floating offshore wind project in the Philippines.", detailEn: "Off North Ilocos in the Philippines, this floating offshore wind project — a JV of PetroGreen Energy and Denmark's Copenhagen Energy (BuhaWind Energy) — is 2 GW, targeting full operation before 2030. It won a pre-development environmental certificate in June 2025 and grid approval in August, one of 16 green-lit Philippine offshore wind farms, kick-starting the country's deep-water floating wind." },
  1971: { descEn: "Singapore's first round-the-clock large-scale green-power import.", detailEn: "Sembcorp and Sarawak Energy won conditional Singapore EMA approval on 17 October 2025 to import ~1 GW of mostly-hydro green power from Sarawak via a ~700 km subsea cable, with a priority supply deal signed with Prysmian and a landing point from Tondong to Changi. Power flows from 2031 and scales by 2035, serving Singapore's 6 GW low-carbon import target." },
  2005: { descEn: "A 22/28nm advanced fab in Singapore, mass production 2026.", detailEn: "UMC announced ~$5 billion in 2022 for a new 300mm fab (Fab12i P3) beside its existing Fab12i in Singapore; an opening ceremony was held in April 2025, with phase-1 30,000 wafers/month of 22/28nm and mass production deferred to 2026, lifting UMC's Singapore capacity above a million wafers a year and adding ~700 engineering jobs." },
  2052: { descEn: "A super transhipment hub port planned at Can Gio, Ho Chi Minh City.", detailEn: "Covering ~571 hectares with a ~7.5 km main quay, this port is ~128.9 trillion dong (~$5 billion), a JV of Vietnam's VIMC (36%), Saigon Port (15%) and MSC's TiL (49%), able to berth 250,000-tonne (24,000 TEU) ships, designed for 4.8 million TEU in 2030 rising to 16.9 million by 2047. It won the PM's investment-policy approval in January 2025 with a 10-year equity lock-in." },
  2275: { descEn: "Southern Tunisian solar sent to Italy's Lazio via a 2,000 MW cable.", detailEn: "TuNur, a UK-French-Maltese-Tunisian JV, builds large solar in Kebili in southern Tunisia and an HVDC line to a substation in Lazio, Italy, transmitting 2,000 MW to power ~2 million European homes — a flagship for exporting Saharan solar to Europe." },
  2300: { descEn: "Dangote's planned largest deep-water port in Africa.", detailEn: "In mid-2025 Dangote applied to build a 10,000+ hectare seaport-industrial complex at Olokola on the Ondo-Ogun border, ~100 km from the Lekki refinery, to handle future LNG exports and heavy-equipment imports — which the group says would become Africa's largest and deepest seaport." },
  2558: { descEn: "Eni's Marine XII gas liquefaction and power supply in Congo.", detailEn: "Eni Congo develops the Marine XII gas; phase 2 adds three production platforms, a Scarabeo 5 processing-compression unit and the Nguya FLNG, lifting Congo LNG to 3 million tonnes/year. Phase 2 started early in December 2025, supplying Congo's power plant (70% of national generation) and upgrading the Pointe-Noire-Brazzaville high-voltage line." },
  2604: { descEn: "A 3 GW electrolyser green-ammonia project at Gove, with 4.75 GW solar-storage.", detailEn: "On the Gove Peninsula in the Northern Territory, this plans 3 GW of electrolysers for ~958,500 tonnes of green ammonia a year, with 4.75 GW of solar and 1.6 GWh of daily battery storage. It signed an engineering deal with ABB in 2025 to accelerate FID, mainly for ammonia export to Asia — one of northern Australia's largest green-hydrogen plans." },
  2660: { descEn: "PNG's next LNG expansion after Papua LNG.", detailEn: "At the P'nyang field in PNG's Western Province, led by ExxonMobil, this would add a liquefaction train to the PNG LNG plant; originally parallel with Papua LNG, it was sequenced after it by the PNG government, advancing commercial talks and the development concept in 2025." },
  2704: { descEn: "A 2 GW mega offshore wind farm in the Dutch North Sea.", detailEn: "At the IJmuiden Ver Alpha site ~60 km off the Netherlands, this 2 GW farm was awarded in June 2024 with FID advancing in late 2025, with green-hydrogen coupling and Delta Rhine corridor export — one of the flagships of the Dutch energy transition." },
  2741: { descEn: "AWS's €7.8 billion independent European Sovereign Cloud in Germany.", detailEn: "AWS is investing ~€7.8 billion to build the 'European Sovereign Cloud' in Brandenburg, Germany, with data and operations entirely in the EU run by EU staff to meet government and regulated-industry data-sovereignty needs; the first region is being built from 2025 toward operation around 2027." },
  2745: { descEn: "A high-speed and freight corridor linking Genoa port with Milan.", detailEn: "Italy's 'Terzo Valico dei Giovi' high-speed line links the port of Genoa with the Milan/Turin plain, with the ~27 km Giovi tunnel — a passenger-and-freight corridor connecting the Mediterranean at Genoa with Europe's Rhine-Alpine corridor, at ~€6.8 billion. Tunnelling advanced in 2025, targeting 2027." },
  2912: { descEn: "A planned world-largest green-hydrogen hub in South Texas making 1 million tonnes of green ammonia for export.", detailEn: "GHI plans Hydrogen City in South Texas, ultimately 60 GW producing over 2.5 billion kg of green hydrogen a year with salt-cavern storage. Phase 1's 280,000 tonnes/year of green hydrogen is piped to Corpus Christi and Brownsville to make 1 million tonnes/year of green ammonia for export, partnered with Japan's INPEX, targeting 2026 construction and 2029 commercial operation." },
  2929: { descEn: "Amazon-funded deployment of up to 12 Xe-100 reactors at Hanford, Washington.", detailEn: "On the DOE Hanford reservation next to Energy Northwest's Columbia plant, this builds reactors in ~320 MW segments — funded by Amazon, with X-energy supplying the reactors and Energy Northwest operating. In October 2025 phase 1 was expanded from 4 to 12 units, targeting the mid-2030s." },
  2939: { descEn: "SaskPower selects Estevan for Saskatchewan's first BWRX-300 SMR.", detailEn: "SaskPower chose the GE-Hitachi BWRX-300, securing two ~320-acre sites by reservoirs near Estevan (up to two units each). A final site is expected in 2026 and FID in 2029, with the first ~315 MWe unit targeted for 2034." },
  2953: { descEn: "New 500 kV lines for 7,500 MW of new data-centre load.", detailEn: "NextEra's MARL and Gore-Doubs-Goose Creek upgrades are part of PJM's B3800 series, approved in late 2023. Dominion is building 500 kV lines along existing corridors in Virginia to serve up to 7,500 MW of new Virginia and Maryland data-centre load." },
  3000: { descEn: "A Stargate data centre and AI-server factory in Lordstown, Ohio.", detailEn: "One of Stargate's five new sites, SoftBank has broken ground using a rapidly replicable advanced design; a SoftBank-Foxconn JV doubles it as an AI-server and data-centre-equipment factory, reaching 1.5 GW within 18 months together with the Milam County site." },
  3011: { descEn: "AWS's Mexico (Central) cloud region, in Querétaro.", detailEn: "AWS launched its Mexico (Central) region with local availability zones in January 2025, planning over $5 billion of investment over 15 years. Querétaro concentrates ~65% of Mexico's data-centre capacity under construction, with AWS, Azure and Google Cloud all present." },
});

/* ===== 批次8：全库投资额 TOP（约 42–50 亿美元）===== */
Object.assign(window.ENERGY_EN, {
  3015: { descEn: "A freight expansion of the 1,525 km Yucatán passenger loop, possibly extending to Belize/Guatemala.", detailEn: "On the existing 1,525 km Maya Train passenger loop, freight is being added with four hubs and in-station tracks at Palenque, Poxila, Progreso and Cancún. Freight was ~47.5% done by May 2026, with start-up expected by end-2026; the president has also proposed a ~300 km extension toward Belize and Guatemala." },
  3115: { descEn: "A million-tonne green-ammonia plant in Kota, Rajasthan, ~$5 billion.", detailEn: "Avaada and the Rajasthan government are building a ~$5 billion, million-tonne/year renewable-ammonia plant in Kota. Avaada also won 50 MW/year of electrolyser capacity under the NGHM and 240 MW in SECI's eighth tranche — a leading Indian green hydrogen-ammonia developer." },
  3134: { descEn: "India's first nuclear plant built by the NPCIL-NTPC joint venture.", detailEn: "At Napla in Banswara, Rajasthan, four indigenous 700 MW PHWRs (2.8 GW total) are being built at ~420 billion rupees by ASHVINI, a JV of NPCIL (51%) and NTPC (49%). PM Modi laid the foundation in September 2025 with excavation approved and first concrete in March 2026." },
  3216: { descEn: "OpenAI's first large AI-compute anchor in India via Stargate, with Tata deploying AMD GPUs.", detailEn: "At the February 2026 India AI Impact Summit in New Delhi, OpenAI became the first customer of TCS's HyperVault data centre, a 100 MW first phase expandable to 1 GW. TCS, with a $1 billion TPG injection, plans sites in Navi Mumbai, Hyderabad and Chennai, with $6-7 billion of platform investment over 5-7 years deploying AMD accelerators." },
  3286: { descEn: "Reliance and bp developing three deep-water gas fields in the KG-D6 block.", detailEn: "Reliance (66.67%) and bp (33.33%) have invested ~$5 billion in the R-Cluster, Satellite cluster and MJ deep-water fields off India's east coast in the KG-D6 block, peaking at ~30 million m³/day. The MJ high-pressure/high-temperature gas-condensate field has an onshore terminal at Gadimoga, with added investment approved in 2024-25." },
  3601: { descEn: "China's largest ultra-deep condensate gas field; output topped 10 bcm in 2025.", detailEn: "On the northern Tarim Basin at the Wensu-Baicheng border in Xinjiang, this is a trillion-cubic-metre-class ultra-deep gas region after Kela-Keshen, with ultra-deep, ultra-high-pressure/temperature, low-porosity, low-permeability characteristics. The 15th Five-Year period launches a 10-bcm capacity build with 85 new wells and processing and export facilities; output topped 10 bcm in December 2025, with processing capacity rising from 5 to 12 bcm/year." },
  4207: { descEn: "A Tsingshan-led integrated nickel park at Weda Bay, using laterite ore vertically.", detailEn: "On Halmahera in North Maluku, Indonesia, this JV of Tsingshan (40% via Perlus), Huayou Cobalt (30%) and Zhenshi (30%) is the world's first vertical laterite-ore-to-nickel-intermediates-to-stainless-and-battery-materials park. Weda Bay Nickel (Tsingshan 57%/Eramet) has ~3 million tonnes/year of RKEF nickel-iron and ~3,400 MW of captive power; phase 1 started in 2020." },
  4394: { descEn: "HQC's installation works for ADNOC's Ruwais LNG, its first overseas tie-up with JGC.", detailEn: "After ADNOC's June 2024 FID, a Technip Energies-JGC-NMDC Energy consortium won the EPC for two 4.8-million-tonne/year trains (9.6 million total) at Ruwais. In early 2025 the Huanqiu (HQC) system signed the installation contract, handling feed-gas compression, cryogenic liquefaction, utilities and flare systems — its first overseas tie-up with JGC, targeting 2028 to make the UAE a major LNG exporter." },
  755: { descEn: "The world's largest approved solar-plus-storage project.", detailEn: "On ~9,500 acres of retired farmland in Fresno County, California, Intersect Power's project won AB 205 fast-track approval in June 2025, with 1,150 MW of solar and 1,150 MW/4,600 MWh of storage — a world-record storage size — able to power 850,000 homes for four hours." },
  1034: { descEn: "A fully electrified fossil-free steel plant in northern Sweden, with twin arc furnaces.", detailEn: "SSAB is building a fully electrified integrated mill in the Svarton zone of Luleå with two scrap-charging arc furnaces, secondary metallurgy and direct strip rolling to replace its blast furnaces, making 2.5 million tonnes/year of fossil-free special steel. At ~€4.5 billion, it cuts 2.8 million tonnes of CO₂ a year (90%); ground was broken in September 2025 with permits confirmed in November, targeting 2029." },
  1240: { descEn: "Brazil's first long-distance flexible HVDC, carrying northeast wind-solar south.", detailEn: "Defined by EPE and ONS as a fast corridor, this runs ~2,500 km from Angicos in Rio Grande do Norte to Itaporanga 2 in Paraná using VSC HVDC — Brazil's first long-distance VSC project. At 26.5 billion reais (~17.1 billion for the DC system), it relieves the bottleneck on 60+ GW of northeast wind and solar." },
  3594: { descEn: "A 10-million-tonne-class LNG terminal in Yantai, PipeChina's first.", detailEn: "At Longkou port in Yantai, Shandong, this 20-million-tonne/year, 35-billion-yuan terminal builds six 220,000 m³ tanks and a 266,000 m³ berth in phase 1 (5 million tonnes/year) — PipeChina's first 10-million-tonne-class LNG terminal, the core of Yantai's drive to be northern China's largest LNG hub, extending into the 15th Five-Year period." },
  1454: { descEn: "Central Asia's largest wind farm, a $4.85 billion PPA.", detailEn: "ACWA Power signed a $4.85 billion PPA with Uzbekistan's grid to build 5 GW of wind in Gungrad, Karakalpakstan in five phases for ~18.5 TWh a year — set to be Central Asia's largest onshore wind farm, transferred to the government after a 25-year concession, in development in 2025." },
  184: { descEn: "The world's first cross-region UHVDC with flexible HVDC at both ends.", detailEn: "From Minqin in Wuwei, Gansu to Shangyu in Shaoxing, Zhejiang through six provinces, with a 2,370 km DC line; tower assembly on the first lot began in January 2026, targeting July 2027, helping integrate over 21.2 TWh of northwest renewables a year." },
  781: { descEn: "RWE's 1.4 GW flagship on Dogger Bank in the North Sea.", detailEn: "On Dogger Bank 195 km off northeast England, RWE's wholly-owned Sofia uses 100 Siemens Gamesa 14 MW turbines on 252 m towers; by end-2025 all foundations and over half the turbines were done, with completion and commissioning in 2026 to power 1.2 million homes." },
  1231: { descEn: "A 2.4 GW electrolyser green-ammonia project at Pecém, online 2030.", detailEn: "On 60 hectares at Pecém port in Ceará, this has up to 2.4 GW of electrolysers producing 960 tonnes of hydrogen a day for 2.2 million tonnes of green ammonia a year. The plant is ~12 billion reais with ~13 billion reais of supporting generation; TotalEnergies is a partner, aiming to export to European refineries." },
  1304: { descEn: "A pre-salt gas-processing and lubricants hub at Itaboraí, the reborn Comperj.", detailEn: "On the former Comperj site, fed pre-salt gas via the Rota 3 line, the first gas-processing module started in 2024 and a second reached commercial operation in May 2025 (21 million m³/day). A ~13 billion-reais phase 2 builds South America's first Group II lube base oils (12,000 b/d) plus diesel and jet fuel and a 19,000 b/d HVO/SAF facility, with full output in 2028." },
  1683: { descEn: "Indonesia's integrated upstream: nickel smelting, cathode materials and battery recycling.", detailEn: "As the upstream and materials end of CATL's full-chain Indonesia battery project, this is at the FHT park in East Halmahera, North Maluku, planned for 142,000 tonnes of nickel and 30,000 tonnes of cathode a year and 20,000 tonnes of battery recycling (>95% recovery), forming a closed mining-materials-manufacturing-recycling loop with the Karawang plant toward Indonesia's 2060 carbon neutrality." },
  2310: { descEn: "A Senegal-Mauritania cross-border offshore LNG project; first export in 2025.", detailEn: "The Greater Tortue Ahmeyim (GTA) project on the Senegal-Mauritania maritime border, led by bp and Kosmos, has a ~2.5-million-tonne/year phase 1. It made its first LNG export in 2025 with strong output, with further phases to expand it — a flagship West African gas project." },
  2351: { descEn: "A deepwater floating LNG project shared by Mauritania and Senegal, online 2025.", detailEn: "Led by bp with Kosmos Energy across the Mauritania-Senegal maritime border, GTA saw first gas to the FPSO in late 2024, first LNG in February 2025 and first export in April, reaching ~2.3 MTPA (2.7 nameplate) at full capacity in December 2025. Phase 2 would add 2.5-3 MTPA via a gravity-based subsea structure for over 5 MTPA total." },
  2718: { descEn: "Poland's first large offshore wind farm in the Baltic, 1.2 GW.", detailEn: "In the Polish Baltic, this JV of Poland's ORLEN and Canada's Northland Power is 1.2 GW with 76 15 MW turbines — Poland's first completed large offshore wind farm, at ~€4.5 billion. Offshore works advanced in 2025, targeting 2026 to launch Poland's offshore wind era." },
  3010: { descEn: "Mexico's largest hyperscale campus, six buildings and 900 MW at Querétaro.", detailEn: "CloudHQ is investing ~$4.8 billion at Galeras in Querétaro for six data centres on 52 hectares, up to 900 MW of critical IT load (a 200 MW first phase secured), due in 2027 — billed as Mexico's largest hyperscale hub." },
  3142: { descEn: "Pakistan's largest single nuclear unit, China's Hualong One.", detailEn: "At Chashma in Mianwali, Punjab, Pakistan, this uses China's Gen-III Hualong One (HPR1000) at 1,200 MW — Pakistan's largest single nuclear unit. China and Pakistan signed a $4.8 billion deal, with first concrete on 30 December 2024; it is the third Hualong One in Pakistan, helping move its nuclear capacity toward 8,800 MW." },
  1208: { descEn: "A Zhundong 2025 priority: an 800,000-tonne coal-to-olefins plant.", detailEn: "In the Wucaiwan Huoshaoshan park of Zhundong, Xinjiang, Shandong Energy's Yankuang Xinjiang Energy & Chemical is building a 33.8-billion-yuan project with 800,000 tonnes/year of coal-to-olefins, a 23-million-tonne/year open-pit mine phase 1 and a rail spur, using home-grown 3,000-t/d OMB gasification and MTO. Started on 23 February 2025 over ~2.5 years, it would yield ~4.7 billion yuan a year in profit and tax — a landmark of Xinjiang's coal-chemical scaling." },
  1513: { descEn: "A landmark cross-border railway linking China and Central Asia.", detailEn: "A groundbreaking was held in Kyrgyzstan on 27 December 2024 with formal works from July 2025. About 486 km (311 km in Kyrgyzstan, 69 km in Uzbekistan) at 120 km/h with 50 bridges and 29 tunnels (three over 12 km), built over six years toward around 2030 — China's shortest overland route to Central Asia." },
  3568: { descEn: "A greenfield 4F hub airport able to handle the world's largest airliners, opening end-2026.", detailEn: "Designed for 45 million passengers, 750,000 tonnes of cargo and 380,000 movements a year, with a 3,800 m 4F North-1 runway and a 118,000 m² metal-roof terminal at ~33.5 billion yuan; substantially complete by end-2025, calibration flights in March 2026 and opening by end-2026." },
  1623: { descEn: "CPECC's $4.6 billion turnkey EPC megadeal in Central Asia.", detailEn: "CNPC subsidiary CPECC signed a $4.614 billion (~31.6 billion yuan) turnkey EPC for Galkynysh phase-4 sales-gas capacity in Turkmenistan, adding 10 bcm/year for owner Turkmengaz. Tied directly to Central Asia-China lines A/B/C and supporting Line D, it lifts overall capacity from 40 to 65 bcm/year — strategic for China's Central Asian gas supply." },
  109: { descEn: "The largest hydro plant on the upper Jinsha River.", detailEn: "On the upper Jinsha at the Sichuan-Tibet border, Yebatan has a 217 m dam and 2.24 GW; started in 2017, it pushed toward first-unit start-up in 2025, completing the upper Jinsha cascade." },
  283: { descEn: "Australia's (and the Southern Hemisphere's) largest data-centre project.", detailEn: "NextDC and OpenAI unveiled the S7 campus at Eastern Creek in Western Sydney in December 2025, targeting 650 MW Tier IV at ~$4.6 billion, helping make Australia the world's second-largest AI-infrastructure destination." },
  943: { descEn: "The world's first commercial ±525 kV XLPE HVDC cable project.", detailEn: "SuedOstLink runs 540 km from Wolmirstedt to the Isar substation near Munich — the world's first large commercial 525 kV XLPE HVDC project. Prysmian won a ~€4.6 billion contract, with cable installation from 2024 and operation expected in 2027/28." },
  1285: { descEn: "An Amazon grain railway from Sinop to Miritituba.", detailEn: "Linking Sinop in Mato Grosso with the Miritituba terminal in Pará, ~933 km, Ferrogrão relieves soy haulage on the BR-163 highway, with 65 bridges and claimed savings of 8 billion reais a year. The transport ministry approved updated technical studies, sent to the Federal Court of Accounts." },
  1807: { descEn: "The world's largest single-line pulp mill, at Inocência.", detailEn: "Chile's Arauco's first Brazilian pulp venture, at Inocência in Mato Grosso do Sul, is the world's largest single-phase bleached-pulp mill at $4.6 billion and 3.5 million tonnes a year, with 400 MW of captive power (~220 MW exportable). Started in 2025, it targets late 2027." },
  1821: { descEn: "A State Grid-controlled CPFL five-year distribution expansion.", detailEn: "State Grid-controlled CPFL is investing ~24.7 billion reais in distribution in its 2025-2029 capex plan, covering 7.8 million customers in São Paulo and Rio Grande do Sul to expand, modernise and strengthen the network — one of the largest Chinese grid investments in Brazil." },
  3504: { descEn: "A 33-billion-yuan 12-inch IC line in Yizhuang, Beijing, 50,000 wafers/month.", detailEn: "GigaDevice's Yandong Micro, with BOE and Yizhuang state capital, raised capital for BD United Integrated at 33 billion yuan and 50,000 wafers/month. Tool move-in starts in Q4 2025 with mass production by end-2026 and full output by 2030, focused on power devices, display drivers and power-management chips." },
  241: { descEn: "A CATL-Stellantis 50/50 LFP plant in Zaragoza.", detailEn: "Beside the Stellantis vehicle plant in Zaragoza, Spain, this €4.1 billion plant makes 50 GWh/year of LFP batteries; started in November 2025 and targeting end-2026 production, with over €300 million of EU support." },
  386: { descEn: "One of Indonesia's largest nickel HPAL projects.", detailEn: "At Pomalaa in Sulawesi, this JV of PT Vale, Huayou Cobalt and Ford (~$4.5 billion) processes 28 million tonnes/year of limonite via high-pressure acid leaching to MHP, yielding 120,000 tonnes of nickel and 15,000 tonnes of cobalt a year, targeting Q3 2026." },
  1155: { descEn: "Mumbai's first fully underground metro, north-south.", detailEn: "The Aqua Line is Mumbai's first fully underground metro, 33.5 km with 27 stations from Cuffe Parade in the south to Aarey JVLR in the north, connecting the international airport and business districts. Opened in three stages — BKC-Aarey in October 2024, BKC-Acharya Atre Chowk in May 2025 and the final ~11 km to Cuffe Parade in October 2025 — it greatly eases east-west and north-south traffic." },
  1215: { descEn: "One of India's largest refinery expansions.", detailEn: "At Panipat in Haryana, IOC is raising refining from 15 to 25 million tonnes/year with downstream polypropylene and butadiene rubber. By 2025 it was ~84% complete, starting up in phases over FY2025-26 — central to IOC's strategy to triple petrochemical capacity by 2030." },
  1596: { descEn: "A 2,172 MW hydro plant on the Kwanza, Angola's largest power project.", detailEn: "EPC by China Energy's Gezhouba, on the middle Kwanza near Dondo in Cuanza Norte, Angola, with a 103 m concrete dam and four 530 MW units (plus an ecological station) totalling 2,172 MW. Excavation began in August 2023, with the first unit's pit done by March 2025 (243,000 m³ excavated) — a strategic project for Angola." },
  1808: { descEn: "A large new pulp mill at Bataguassu, Mato Grosso do Sul.", detailEn: "Singapore's RGE group's Bracell announced ~$4.5 billion for a new pulp mill at Bataguassu in Mato Grosso do Sul, ~2.8 million tonnes a year. Relocated from Água Clara for logistics and strategy, it is in feasibility and early stages — another pulp hub for the state." },
  1899: { descEn: "A second Saudi-Bahrain road-and-rail causeway, parallel to the King Fahd Causeway.", detailEn: "Linking the Dammam rail station with the King Hamad rail station at Ramli, Bahrain, ~25 km with road and twin GCC-rail tracks to relieve the King Fahd Causeway, at ~$4-5 billion on a 25-30-year PPP concession. The Dammam station becomes Saudi Arabia's main rail hub; feasibility is done, targeting 2026 construction and 2028 operation." },
  2064: { descEn: "A Central Java refinery upgrade for cleaner fuels.", detailEn: "Pertamina's RU IV Cilacap RDMP would raise capacity from 350,000 to 400,000 b/d, lifting gasoline 59→138 and diesel 82→137 thousand b/d. In 2026 Pertamina reaffirmed it and kept seeking a JV partner (having courted Saudi Aramco), part of the ~$6.2 billion three-refinery RDMP plan (Dumai/Plaju/Cilacap by 2027)." },
  2213: { descEn: "A passenger-and-freight high-speed line linking the Red Sea and Mediterranean.", detailEn: "Egypt signed a $4.5 billion contract with a Siemens-led consortium for the 660 km Green Line connecting the Red Sea and Mediterranean in as little as 3 hours. Part of Egypt's 2,000+ km three-line electrified network, track-laying began in 2025 toward 2026 completion, linking Upper Egypt, the Delta and new cities." },
  2515: { descEn: "Southern Africa's largest hydro plant in half a century.", detailEn: "A 1,500 MW run-of-river plant on the Zambezi in Mozambique, ~$4.5 billion, developed by France's EDF and TotalEnergies with EDM and HCB; the World Bank has pledged debt, equity and risk guarantees plus $1.4 billion of transmission support. A February 2026 technical workshop in Maputo advanced credit enhancement, targeting 2031." },
  2525: { descEn: "Angola's largest single power source.", detailEn: "The Caculo Cabaça hydro plant on the middle Kwanza in Cuanza Norte, Angola, 2,172 MW, will become Angola's largest single power source (above the downstream 2,070 MW Laúca). Built by China's Gezhouba (CGGC), its spillway tunnel was holed through in June 2025, clearing the way for unit installation and impoundment, targeting 2026 and ~8.57 TWh a year." },
  2744: { descEn: "A Y-shaped high-speed line linking Bilbao, San Sebastián and Vitoria.", detailEn: "The 'Basque Y' high-speed railway in northern Spain links Bilbao, San Sebastián and Vitoria and ties into the Spanish HSR network and France — a key segment of the Iberia-Europe Atlantic corridor. Multiple lots advanced in 2025, targeting around 2028." },
  2992: { descEn: "A low-carbon recycled-aluminium rolling mill at Bay Minette, online H2 2026.", detailEn: "Novelis is building a low-carbon recycled-aluminium rolling mill at Bay Minette, Alabama, recycling ~15 billion cans a year for packaging and automotive sheet. Originally for mid-2025, it now targets H2 2026 commissioning — one of North America's first new integrated aluminium rolling mills in decades." },
  3043: { descEn: "A blue-hydrogen and blue-ammonia complex at Darrow, Louisiana, revived via Yara.", detailEn: "Air Products plans a $4.5 billion blue-hydrogen complex at Darrow, Louisiana producing over 750 million cubic feet/day of blue hydrogen and capturing ~95% of CO₂. Paused in 2025, it regained momentum after deep talks with Yara on a 25-year blue-hydrogen offtake and the sale of ammonia-making assets, with start-up pushed to 2028." },
  3462: { descEn: "A Qinghai desert mega-base sending power to the Greater Bay Area; generation started November 2025.", detailEn: "Qinghai's Hainan clean-energy export base plans 19.44 GW (86.4% renewable: 9.6 GW solar, 6 GW wind, 2.64 GW coal and 1.2 GW/4h storage), sending power to Guangdong via one ±800 kV, 8 GW UHVDC line at ~36 TWh a year — the largest approved renewable desert-base in China." },
  3503: { descEn: "China's first volume 8-inch automotive silicon-carbide line, online 2025.", detailEn: "Sanan Optoelectronics and STMicroelectronics' ~$3.2 billion JV (Sanan-ST) in Chongqing built an 8-inch automotive SiC fab, reaching first line in February 2025 with volume production in Q4 toward ~10,000 wafers/week, plus a 7-billion-yuan Chongqing Sanan 8-inch substrate line already started." },
  871: { descEn: "Namibia's flagship green-hydrogen project, Africa's largest.", detailEn: "In the Tsau Khaeb National Park of southern Namibia, Hyphen (with ENERTRAG) and the government plan ~$9.4 billion total, with a 2 GW wind-solar phase 1 for ~800,000 tonnes of green ammonia a year. The AfDB provided $10 million for FEED in 2024, with FID targeted for 2026 and green ammonia for Europe and East Asia." },
  1012: { descEn: "A Honda-LG pouch-battery plant, in production 2025.", detailEn: "At Jeffersonville in Fayette County, Ohio (~40 miles southwest of Columbus), the Honda-LG Energy Solution JV is ~$4.4 billion for ~40 GWh of pouch cells for Honda's North American EV plants. Over 2 million sq ft, it is a core local grid load creating ~2,200 jobs, topping out and ramping production in 2025." },
  1056: { descEn: "BYD's first European passenger-car gigafactory.", detailEn: "At Szeged, Hungary, up to ~€4 billion, this is BYD's first European passenger-car plant. The first lines arrived in December 2025, with trial production from late January 2026 and mass production in Q2 2026, starting with the Dolphin Surf — initially 150,000 vehicles a year rising to 200,000, with ~960 staff, to localise production and avoid EU tariffs." },
  1681: { descEn: "A 50/50 CATL-Stellantis LFP plant, 50 GWh planned.", detailEn: "CATL and Stellantis (50/50) are building a large LFP plant at Figueruelas in Zaragoza, Spain, next to the Stellantis vehicle plant, at up to €4.1 billion and 50 GWh/year using renewable power, with over €300 million of EU support; ground was broken in late November 2025, targeting end-2026." },
  3027: { descEn: "A new double-deck companion bridge and 8-mile corridor on I-71/I-75 at Cincinnati.", detailEn: "A new double-deck companion bridge carries interstate traffic on I-71/I-75 between Ohio and Kentucky over ~8 miles, with the existing bridge handling local traffic. At ~$4.4 billion split between the states (with ~$1.6 billion federal), works began on 8 May 2026, with the companion bridge open in 2031 and full completion in 2033." },
  3270: { descEn: "Dhaka Metro Line 1 (Airport and Purple lines), JICA-financed, with an underground section.", detailEn: "MRT-1 is ~539.8 billion taka with ~394.5 billion of JICA aid, comprising the Airport and Purple lines — Dhaka's first underground metro. The depot was over 95% built by April-May 2025, targeting 2028." },
  3277: { descEn: "CPCL building a new 9-million-tonne greenfield refinery at Nagapattinam, Tamil Nadu.", detailEn: "CPCL is demolishing its old small refinery and building a new 9-million-tonne/year greenfield refinery at Nagapattinam via a JV at ~364 billion rupees, making LPG, BS-VI fuels and jet fuel with polypropylene; it has environmental clearance, owned 50/50 by IOCL and CPCL." },
  3566: { descEn: "Part of the Shanghai-Zhoushan-Ningbo sea crossing, linking Beilun and Zhoushan; fully started August 2025.", detailEn: "Built to six-lane expressway standard across the Huibie Yang waters at ~31.3 billion yuan, this is a key part of Zhejiang's Shanghai-Zhoushan-Ningbo and Yiwu-Ningbo-Zhoushan corridors. Fully started on 29 August 2025, it will strengthen Ningbo-Zhoushan port collection and distribution." },
  181: { descEn: "The world's highest-altitude UHVDC project.", detailEn: "From two converter stations in Chamdo (Tibet) and Garze (Sichuan) to Huangshi in Hubei, ~1,900 km, using the world's first high-altitude split-site cascade technology with a sending altitude of 3,720 m and line up to 4,800 m. It entered service on 18 December 2025, delivering ~40 TWh of clean power a year." },
  1149: { descEn: "The Americas' first metro built and run end-to-end by a Chinese firm; over 75% done.", detailEn: "Bogotá Metro Line 1 is Colombia's capital's first metro, 24 km elevated with 16 stations, invested, built and operated by a JV of China Harbour (CHEC) and Xi'an Rail Transit — the first metro in the Americas a Chinese firm handles from construction to operation, ~$4.3 billion. Viaduct and station works continued in 2025, passing 75% completion, with Qingdao-made driverless trains arriving by sea, targeting 2028 and over a million daily riders." },
  912: { descEn: "A line carrying southern Xinjiang clean power to Sichuan-Chongqing, 40+ TWh a year.", detailEn: "From Ruoqiang in Xinjiang via Qinghai to Mianyang in Sichuan, ~1,996 km; a cooperation deal among Xinjiang, Sichuan and Chongqing was signed in January 2026, with ~10% private capital sought in February, aiming for approval and start in 2026 and completion in 2028." },
  4218: { descEn: "The Middle East's largest refinery (615,000 b/d); SEG's first Kuwait turnkey project, full output 2024.", detailEn: "The Al-Zour refinery in southern Kuwait is the Middle East's largest, processing 615,000 b/d of crude. Sinopec Engineering (SEG), with Spanish and Hanwha partners, won a ~$4.24 billion turnkey contract (SEG ~40%, ~$1.696 billion), with units like Luoyang Engineering and No.5 Construction building the core; trial run in 2020, full output February 2024." },
  123: { descEn: "The world's largest integrated green hydrogen-ammonia-methanol project.", detailEn: "At Songyuan in Jilin, this plans 3 GW of renewables in phases producing ~800,000 tonnes/year of green synthetic ammonia and methanol; phase 1 started up in December 2025 — an important demonstration of scaled green hydrogen entering chemicals in China." },
  326: { descEn: "The core of JFK's $19 billion overhaul.", detailEn: "At ~$4.2 billion and ~112,000 m², serving ANA, Lufthansa, Cathay Pacific, JetBlue and 12+ airlines, the first six gates of the New Terminal One open in 2026 and the whole terminal completes in 2028." },
  362: { descEn: "East Africa's largest LNG project.", detailEn: "Led by Shell, Equinor and ExxonMobil, Tanzania LNG would use ~60 trillion cubic feet of deepwater Rovuma-basin gas for ~10 million tonnes/year at $42 billion total. A legal framework is targeted for H1 2026 with FID in 2028." },
  782: { descEn: "A 1.08 GW Scottish North Sea offshore wind farm, first power end-2026.", detailEn: "Off Scotland's east coast in the North Sea, Inch Cape (a Red Rock Renewables-ESB JV) is 1,080 MW; it reached financial close and started offshore works in early 2025, with the first giant monopiles delivered in October 2025, targeting first power by end-2026 and full operation in 2027." },
  804: { descEn: "New York's largest offshore wind under construction, restarting February 2026.", detailEn: "Off eastern New York, Orsted's wholly-owned Sunrise Wind (after buying Eversource's 50% in 2024) has 84 turbines and 924 MW; started in summer 2024 and ~45% done before a late-2025 stop order, a court ordered work to resume in February 2026, targeting 2027 to power ~600,000 homes." },
  1461: { descEn: "One of Central Asia's largest hydro plants; tripartite financing from 2026.", detailEn: "On the Naryn River in Kyrgyzstan, Kambarata-1 is 1,860 MW with a 256 m dam, 5.4 bcm reservoir and ~5.6 TWh a year, at ~$4.2 billion (Kyrgyzstan 34%, Uzbekistan and Kazakhstan 33% each). A ministerial deal was signed in June 2024, the EU and EIB pledged €900 million, and the three countries launch joint financing and construction in 2026 — a flagship for regional power security." },
  2501: { descEn: "A flagship Zambezi hydro plant jointly built by Zambia and Zimbabwe.", detailEn: "Below Victoria Falls on the Zambezi, this 2,400 MW plant (~1,200 MW each) is jointly built by Zambia and Zimbabwe; in late 2025 each pledged $220 million ($440 million total) to improve bankability, re-tendered as a PPP. Delayed by financing and tender disputes, it is in engineering studies and investor mobilisation, with main works not started by March 2026." },
  2703: { descEn: "A 1.6 GW wind cluster north of Juist in the German North Sea.", detailEn: "About 50 km north of Juist in the German North Sea, RWE leads a two-phase development — A (~660 MW, 2027) and B (~900 MW) — totalling 1.6 GW, one of Germany's largest recent offshore clusters, with large turbines and offshore substations supplying NRW industry." },
});

/* ===== 批次9：全库投资额 TOP（约 38–42 亿美元）===== */
Object.assign(window.ENERGY_EN, {
  2948: { descEn: "A 525 kV line from Las Vegas to Yerington connecting Nevada's north and south grids.", detailEn: "Greenlink Nevada's West line follows the US-95 corridor ~350 miles. EPC contractor MasTec has logged ~800,000 work-hours and ~150 towers; a section east of Beatty is delayed by test-range airspace limits, with the 120 kV portion of a substation online in October 2025." },
  3167: { descEn: "The world's first integrated wind-solar-storage base, with 1,680 MW closed-loop pumped hydro (~10.8 GWh).", detailEn: "Greenko's base at Pinnapuram in Kurnool, Andhra Pradesh is the world's first to integrate wind, solar and pumped hydro — ~3.5 GW of wind and solar plus 1,680 MW of closed-loop pumped hydro storing over 10,800 MWh, at ~$4.2 billion, with the pumped-hydro units coming online over 2025-2026 for multi-hour peaking." },
  3285: { descEn: "ONGC's MRPL drops refining expansion for ~$3.6-4.8 billion of petrochemicals.", detailEn: "MRPL, an ONGC subsidiary at Mangalore, Karnataka, has 15 million tonnes/year of refining and 905,000 tonnes of paraxylene. It cancelled a refining expansion in favour of ~$3.6-4.8 billion of new petrochemical units within 3-5 years, part of ONGC's plan to grow petrochemical capacity from 3.4 to 8 million tonnes by 2030." },
  3404: { descEn: "A 4.2 GW hydro plant on the upper Yellow River, aiming to start in the 15th Five-Year period.", detailEn: "On the Cihaxia reach of the Yellow River in Qinghai, with a normal pool level of 2,990 m and ~4.2 GW, this is one of the largest in the planned upper-Yellow-River cascade. Pre-feasibility and survey-design tenders launched in August 2025 with a land-use freeze notice issued, aiming for approval and start during the 15th Five-Year period." },
  3420: { descEn: "The world's largest wind-to-hydrogen green-methanol project, 500,000 t/year, first output October 2025.", detailEn: "In the Xing'an League development zone of Inner Mongolia, this pairs 2 GW of wind-to-hydrogen with corn-straw biomass carbon for 500,000 tonnes/year of green methanol at ~30 billion yuan. A 250,000-tonne phase 1 started up first, with phases 2-3 adding 13.1 billion yuan signed in October 2025 toward 1.45 million tonnes long term." },
  3421: { descEn: "A Songyuan 3 GW wind-solar plus 800,000-tonne green ammonia-methanol project, started September 2025.", detailEn: "At Songyuan in Jilin, using direct wind-solar supply, storage peaking, efficient electrolysis and dynamic synthesis, this plans 3 GW of renewables and 800,000 tonnes of green synthetic ammonia and methanol in phases — among the first large hydrogen-based-chemical demonstrations of 'Hydrogen-Powered Jilin', at ~29.6 billion yuan." },
  3455: { descEn: "A 15th-Five-Year HVDC carrying Ulan Buh desert-base power to Zhejiang.", detailEn: "From the Ulan Buh Desert base in Alxa, Inner Mongolia to Zhejiang, planned at ±800 kV and ~8 GW to export clean wind and solar; Inner Mongolia's 2026 plan lists the Ulan Buh-Zhejiang corridor as a project to approve as soon as possible." },
  3584: { descEn: "A 30-billion-yuan Maoming upgrade adding a million-tonne ethylene unit.", detailEn: "At Maoming in Guangdong, over 30 billion yuan retrofits refining without adding capacity, retiring the existing 360,000-tonne ethylene and building 1 million tonnes/year of ethylene plus downstream, using Sinopec's efficient low-energy cracking with 98.65% domestic equipment. Started in 2023, 59 of 112 main items are under way, targeting 2026-2027." },
  3586: { descEn: "A million-tonne ethylene at Tianjin Nangang, lifting Sinopec's Tianjin ethylene to 2.5 Mt.", detailEn: "In the Tianjin Nangang industrial zone, over 30 billion yuan builds a 1.2-million-tonne/year ethylene unit anchoring 13 plants (HDPE, LLDPE, alpha-olefins, UHMWPE). It started up successfully in November 2024, raising Sinopec's Tianjin ethylene to 2.5 million tonnes/year and pioneering ethylene-LNG cold-energy coupling, supplying 4 million tonnes of downstream feedstock a year." },
  3591: { descEn: "A 3,340 km gas trunkline from Wuqia to Zhongwei, fully online June 2025.", detailEn: "Running ~3,340 km from Wuqia in Xinjiang to Zhongwei in Ningxia, with 1,219 mm pipe and 15 bcm/year design capacity, this is another strategic Central Asia energy corridor after the West-East lines 1-3. Started in September 2023, the Xinjiang section came online in September 2024 and the Gansu-Ningxia section on 26 June 2025, completing the line; with the West-East lines 2-3 it lifts the network to 100 bcm/year." },
  1116: { descEn: "A new coastal high-speed line in the Shandong-Jiangsu section.", detailEn: "The Weisu high-speed railway runs ~399 km from Weifang North via Rizhao, Linyi and Xuzhou to Yanghe North in Suqian at 350 km/h. In 2025 the Jiangsu section's Grand Canal continuous beam and the 108.78 km Qingdao connection (23.7 billion yuan) advanced, with the Qingdao link fully girder-laid in August. Part of the national coastal corridor, it strengthens Shandong-Yangtze Delta links and fills a rail gap in southern Shandong and northern Jiangsu." },
  1121: { descEn: "The world's largest-span double-deck suspension bridge.", detailEn: "The Lion Ocean (Shiziyang) crossing runs ~35 km from Nansha in Guangzhou to Humen in Dongguan, double-deck with 16 lanes; its key Shiziyang Bridge crosses the river in a single 2,180 m main span, set to claim five world firsts (span, 342 m towers, 130 m anchorage diameter, 1.5 m main cable, lane count). Towers passed 200 m and the halfway point in 2025, with topping-out expected in 2026 — another mega-link across the Pearl River estuary in the Greater Bay Area." },
  101: { descEn: "Renewables for one of China's first desert-base export corridors.", detailEn: "In the Santanghu Gobi of Hami, Xinjiang, 10.2 GW of renewables (7 GW wind, 3 GW solar, 0.2 GW CSP) with 1.2 GW/4.8 GWh of storage is the first desert-base export-corridor renewable project, started in February 2024 and due fully online by end-2025, sending ~36 TWh of green power a year to Sichuan-Chongqing." },
  192: { descEn: "One of India's first competitively-bid HVDC links, exporting Gujarat renewables.", detailEn: "From the Khavda renewable base in Gujarat to Nagpur in Maharashtra, 1,200 km at ±800 kV/6,000 MW, built by a BHEL-Hitachi Energy consortium, targeting 2029." },
  541: { descEn: "Tencent's largest North China data-centre base, with China's first integrated wind-solar-storage microgrid.", detailEn: "Tencent's three campuses at Huailai in Hebei span ~1,050 mu, planned for ~1 million servers with over 71% green-power use; in 2024 it deployed China's first 'wind-solar-storage' data-centre microgrid — Tencent's core North China compute base." },
  1712: { descEn: "A second production system for the Atapu pre-salt field.", detailEn: "P-84 serves phase 2 of the Atapu field in the Santos Basin ~200 km off Rio in over 2,000 m of water, producing 225,000 b/d and processing 10 million m³/day of gas with ~30% lower per-barrel carbon. Bundled with P-85 in an $8.15 billion two-FPSO Seatrium contract, it started construction in Q1 2025 for first oil in 2029-2030." },
  4043: { descEn: "A flagship deep-water port on Bubiyan Island; a $4.1 billion CCCC EPC.", detailEn: "China Communications Construction signed the ~$4.1 billion (1.219 billion-dinar) phase-1 EPC for Mubarak Al-Kabeer Port on Bubiyan Island, Kuwait — ~1,161 hectares with eventually 24 berths and 8.1 million TEU a year, including quays, shore power and logistics. A Vision 2035 flagship, it is the first major Middle East port partly using Chinese standards." },
  4198: { descEn: "Tianqi holds ~22% of Chile's SQM, indirectly owning world-class Atacama lithium.", detailEn: "In 2018 Tianqi bought ~23.77% of SQM for $4.066 billion to become its second-largest shareholder, holding ~22% by early 2024 and ~21.90% (A shares) by early 2026. SQM operates the world's largest lithium resource at the Atacama salt flat; Chile's push for an SQM-Codelco public-private JV (effective from 2025) may affect Tianqi's returns." },
  289: { descEn: "Two new tranches totalling 1.2 GW after Singapore lifted its moratorium.", detailEn: "After lifting its 2019 data-centre moratorium, Singapore approved two tranches totalling 1.2 GW of hyperscale capacity, with AWS, Google and others cleared to expand, positioned as green, high-quality AI-load centres." },
  290: { descEn: "AWS's first South American (Chile) cloud region.", detailEn: "AWS is investing $4 billion in a three-availability-zone cloud region in Santiago, Chile, expected online by end-2026 for AI and machine learning — a milestone in AWS's Latin American digital-infrastructure push." },
  642: { descEn: "The world's largest underground copper mine adds its first open pit.", detailEn: "At Libertador in Chile, El Teniente is the world's largest underground copper mine, and Rajo Sur is its first open-pit supplement, begun in 2024 to offset declining underground grades toward 500,000+ tonnes a year. A July 2025 tunnel collapse cost 33,000 tonnes of copper, but construction continues." },
  785: { descEn: "A nearly 1 GW German Baltic project, permitted December 2025.", detailEn: "About 15 km north of the Fischland peninsula in the German Baltic, Skyborn Renewables' Gennaker is 976.5 MW with 63 15 MW-class turbines and ~4 TWh a year; it won a construction-and-operation permit in December 2025, with FID targeted for summer 2026 and operation in 2028 to power ~1 million people." },
  822: { descEn: "Phase 1 of Pakistan's largest planned hydro plant.", detailEn: "On the Indus in Khyber Pakhtunkhwa, Dasu is 2,160 MW in phase 1 (4,320 MW ultimately), with a $1.57 billion World Bank loan. Main-dam roller-compacted-concrete works start in Q2 2026, targeting power generation from late 2027, after repeated delays on terrain and security." },
  841: { descEn: "The UK's largest renewable power source; BECCS retrofit approved.", detailEn: "At Selby in North Yorkshire, Drax's four biomass units (~2.6 GW) provide ~4% of UK generation and ~9% of its renewable power. It won a record ~£1 billion biomass subsidy in 2025, and the government approved converting two units to BECCS (bioenergy with carbon capture and storage), able to capture ~8 million tonnes of CO₂ a year." },
  1010: { descEn: "The largest US battery plant, opened July 2025.", detailEn: "On a 300-acre site at the Astra business park in De Soto, Kansas, ~4.7 million sq ft, this is Panasonic's largest North American — and claimed world's largest — auto battery plant, making 2170 cylindrical cells with ~32 GWh planned rising to 59 GWh. It opened on 14 July 2025 with ~4,000 jobs at capacity, mainly for Tesla, a core local grid load, ramping to ~50% by early 2026 with a second wing under way." },
  1041: { descEn: "The first new US primary aluminium smelter in ~50 years, using low-carbon power.", detailEn: "Century Aluminum and the UAE's EGA are building the first new US primary aluminium smelter since 1980 at the Tulsa Port of Inola, Oklahoma — 750,000 tonnes a year, EGA 60% / Century 40%, with a $500 million DOE grant. Using dedicated low-carbon power for ~75% lower emissions, the JV was confirmed in January 2026, targeting a late-2026 start and end-of-decade production — a giant grid load." },
  1172: { descEn: "The first US deepwater floating LNG project.", detailEn: "Delfin Midstream's first US deepwater floating LNG export project off Louisiana uses existing subsea pipelines, planned as three FLNG vessels of ~4 million tonnes/year each. It won a MARAD deepwater-port licence in March 2025 and signed a first-vessel build letter of intent with Samsung Heavy in October, advancing toward FID." },
  1174: { descEn: "A Pacific-coast Mexican LNG export terminal.", detailEn: "Sempra is converting its existing import terminal at Ensenada, Mexico into an export terminal, with a ~3.25-million-tonne/year phase 1 for shorter-haul Asian markets. Over 95% complete by 2026 and in commissioning, satellite monitoring showed gas-in from April 2026 and flaring in May, with first LNG expected in 2026." },
  1219: { descEn: "A threefold expansion of a northeast Indian refinery.", detailEn: "At Numaligarh in Assam, NRL is raising refining from 3 to 9 million tonnes/year, with a 1,640 km crude pipeline from Paradip to Assam plus product lines. New units started up from the CDU in December 2025 and were ~85% complete by February 2026, greatly boosting northeast India's energy supply and refining self-sufficiency." },
  1297: { descEn: "A Sépia phase-2 FPSO, part of Seatrium's ~$8.2 billion two-vessel deal.", detailEn: "Petrobras and partners took FID on Sépia phase 2 in the Santos Basin pre-salt, building a fully electrified low-carbon FPSO of 225,000 b/d, part of the ~$8.2 billion two-FPSO Seatrium contract (with Atapu phase 2's P-85); construction began in Q1 2025 for delivery and start-up in 2029." },
  1298: { descEn: "An Atapu phase-2 FPSO with a fully electrified low-carbon design.", detailEn: "After FID on Atapu phase 2 in the Santos Basin pre-salt, this new FPSO produces 225,000 b/d and processes 10 million m³/day of gas, using full electrification, heat recovery and a closed flare. Part of the ~$8.2 billion two-FPSO Seatrium deal with Sépia phase 2's P-84, it started construction in Q1 2025 for 2029 delivery." },
  1305: { descEn: "A 355 km pre-salt gas pipeline from the Tupi field to Boaventura.", detailEn: "Petrobras's largest wholly-Brazilian-built gas pipeline, 355 km (307 km offshore, 48 km onshore) crossing 2,200 m of water from the Tupi field in the Santos Basin via Búzios north to the Boaventura plant at Itaboraí, carrying 18 million m³/day. The whole system came online in November 2024, with a second processing module in commercial operation in 2025." },
  1365: { descEn: "Abu Dhabi commits to 8 GW of battery storage.", detailEn: "In May 2026 Masdar and EWEC signed a framework to deploy 8 GW of battery storage in Abu Dhabi with 30 GW of solar, with a streamlined development process, supporting Abu Dhabi's 2035 target of 60% clean power — a further expansion after the 5.2 GW/19 GWh round-the-clock solar-plus-storage." },
  1376: { descEn: "Saudi Arabia's first full-process hydrogen-ready steel-plate mill.", detailEn: "BAP Al-Khair, a JV of China Baowu, Saudi Aramco and PIF (50:25:25) at Ras Al Khair Industrial City, uses gas-based direct reduced iron plus an electric arc furnace to make 1.5 million tonnes/year of heavy plate — Saudi Arabia's first full-process plate mill, with hydrogen-capable DRI for up to 90% future emissions cuts, at ~$4 billion." },
  1407: { descEn: "A Bahrain-Saudi road-and-rail causeway parallel to the King Fahd Causeway.", detailEn: "The King Hamad Causeway is a Bahrain-Saudi road-and-rail crossing at ~$4-5 billion with four road lanes and two rail tracks; a 57 km railway links a planned King Hamad station in Bahrain's Ramli area with the Dammam rail station, parallel to the existing King Fahd Causeway, on a 25-30-year PPP — a key link in GCC rail integration." },
  1427: { descEn: "An FCC and deep-conversion upgrade at the Basra refinery.", detailEn: "The Basra refinery (210,000 b/d) is being upgraded with a 34,500 b/d fluid catalytic cracker, 55,000 b/d vacuum distillation and 40,000 b/d diesel desulphurisation, lifting product output from 60,000 to 160,000 b/d. JGC builds it with Axens technology and JICA financing." },
  1526: { descEn: "A new Moscow metro line to the northwest suburbs.", detailEn: "The Rublyovo-Arkhangelskaya Line (Line 17), started in 2021, is 27.6 km with 12 stations from Moscow City across the MKAD toward Krasnogorsk. The first section, Delovoy Tsentr to Bulvar Generala Karbysheva (three new stations), is planned for 2026, with tunnels through and track and equipment being installed." },
  1555: { descEn: "A Far East coking-coal mine with Russia's longest private railway.", detailEn: "In Sakha (Yakutia), Elga produced 28.6 million tonnes of coal in 2024, targeting ~30-32 million in 2025 and 45 million after phase 2, served by the 531 km Pacific Railway (Russia's longest private railway) and Elga port. A second track began in April 2025, with 350 km built." },
  1628: { descEn: "Africa's longest crude pipeline; first export May 2024.", detailEn: "Led by CNPC and built by the China Petroleum Pipeline Bureau, the Niger-Benin crude export pipeline runs ~1,950 km from Niger's Agadem field to the Sèmè-Kraké offshore terminal in Benin at 90,000 b/d design — Africa's longest oil pipeline. Built over 2019-2023, it made its first export in May 2024 after China mediated a Niger-Benin border dispute; ~90% of Niger's oil exports depend on it." },
  1651: { descEn: "Europe's second-largest copper producer, targeting 500,000 t/year long term.", detailEn: "Comprising Zijin Bor Copper (63%) and the Timok (Čukaru Peki) copper-gold mine in Serbia. The upper zone started in 2021, producing 172,000 tonnes of copper and 5.18 tonnes of gold in 2025; total 2025 output of 296,000 tonnes of copper and 9.1 tonnes of gold ranks second in Europe. The lower zone, JM block caving and Bor upgrades advance, with a new plant targeted for June 2027 toward a long-term 500,000 tonnes a year to lead Europe." },
  1659: { descEn: "A ~28 billion-yuan deal to acquire three African gold mines in early 2026.", detailEn: "On 26 January 2026 Zijin Gold International announced the acquisition of all shares of Toronto/Nasdaq-listed Allied Gold at C$44 a share, ~28 billion yuan. Core assets include the producing Sadiola gold mine in Mali, the Bonikro and Agbaou complex in Côte d'Ivoire and Ethiopia's Kurmuk mine (due H2 2026); on completion Zijin Gold International will own 12 large gold mines in 12 countries." },
  1713: { descEn: "A second production system for the Sépia field.", detailEn: "P-85 serves Sépia phase 2 in the Santos Basin pre-salt in over 2,000 m of water, producing 225,000 b/d and processing 10 million m³/day of gas — among Brazil's most efficient FPSOs (30% lower per-barrel carbon). Built by Seatrium with P-84 (~$8.15 billion combined), its compression module is due in 2027 and first oil around 2030 — a main capacity addition in Petrobras's 2025-29 plan." },
  1750: { descEn: "An early-stage offshore wind project off Icaraí, Ceará.", detailEn: "Asa Branca off Icaraí in Ceará, 100% held by Eólica Brasil, is one of Brazil's earliest offshore wind environmental filings (2017), with a ~50-turbine first phase ~3 km offshore. It is in IBAMA's ~230+ GW pipeline, awaiting the first offshore auction; IBAMA plans dedicated guidelines and first permits in 2026." },
  1824: { descEn: "Brazil's third nuclear unit, awaiting a final decision on resumption.", detailEn: "Angra 3 is a 1,405 MW PWR, stalled for years. In October 2025 Eletronuclear submitted an updated techno-economic model to the CNPE; ~20-23 billion reais more is needed to finish. The government will decide on resumption or termination in mid-2026, with operation around 2031 if resumed, Tractebel leading the completion plan." },
  1836: { descEn: "An ~4,150 km east-west 56-inch gas trunkline expansion.", detailEn: "As phase 3 of the Master Gas System (an $8.8 billion 2023 deal), ~4,153 km of 56-inch east-west trunkline lifts network capacity to ~15.7 bcf/d (adding 0.315 bcf/d), extending in segments from EWPS-1 via Shedgum west to EWPS-10. Started in Q2 2024, it targets Q4 2028 to support gas-field output growth." },
  1838: { descEn: "A specialty-chemicals cluster at Jubail fed by Amiral feedstock.", detailEn: "Anchored by the Amiral complex (online 2027), this Jubail downstream park could unlock ~$4 billion of investment in carbon fibre, lubricants, drilling fluids, detergents, food additives, auto parts and tyres. INEOS will build a unit using Amiral propylene to make acrylonitrile (a carbon-fibre precursor); the investment ministry signed with SATORP in April 2026, with derivative units due 2027-2029." },
  2066: { descEn: "A West Java refinery upgrade with new petrochemical units.", detailEn: "The Balongan refinery (West Java) RDMP runs in three phases: phase 1 raised capacity to 150,000 b/d in 2022; phase 2 improves yields; phase 3 adds petrochemical units to cut imports, originally targeted around 2026. Indonesia's last large new refinery (1994), it is key to Pertamina cutting net petrochemical imports." },
  2098: { descEn: "A giant aluminium complex in Vietnam's Central Highlands.", detailEn: "In Lam Dong in Vietnam's Central Highlands, THACO plans ~50-103 trillion dong (~$4 billion) for 32,500 tonnes/year of beneficiation, 1.3 million tonnes of alumina and 300,000 tonnes of aluminium in three phases over ~10 years. Without formal investment approval by mid-2026, it aims for approval in 2026 and production in 2030." },
  2206: { descEn: "A trans-Mediterranean line carrying Egyptian green power to Europe.", detailEn: "The GREGY project would link Egypt with mainland Greece via a ~954 km HVDC subsea cable carrying up to 3,000 MW of renewable power, ~€3.57 billion (~$4 billion), driven by Greece's Copelouzos group with EU Global Gateway support. Added to the EU's PCI/PMI list in December 2025 with EU funding for studies, it targets FID by May 2028 and operation in 2031." },
  2254: { descEn: "Three new granulation lines at Jorf Lasfar plus a 4.2-million-tonne Mzinda complex.", detailEn: "Part of OCP's $13 billion green investment (2023-2027), this adds three 1-million-tonne granulation units at Jorf Lasfar and a 4.2-million-tonne new chemical complex at Mzinda, adding 8 million tonnes of fertiliser capacity by 2027, with desalination and green power, at $4.54 billion (2025), $5.25 billion (2026) and $4.25 billion (2027)." },
  2422: { descEn: "A $4 billion Kabaale refinery, 60,000 b/d, a UNOC-Alpha MBM JV.", detailEn: "At Kabaale in Hoima, Uganda, this ~$4 billion, 60,000 b/d refinery is a JV of Uganda's UNOC (40%) and the UAE's Alpha MBM Investments (60%), targeting 2028, also producing petrochemicals, fertiliser and gas. With Kabalega International Airport (~94% done) and the EACOP export pipeline, it forms an integrated Ugandan oil-and-gas hub." },
  2556: { descEn: "A strategic railway from the copper-cobalt belt to the Atlantic port of Lobito.", detailEn: "The Lobito Corridor links DR Congo's copper-cobalt belt via Zambia to the port of Lobito in Angola, with a ~315 km new spur in DRC tying into the Benguela railway. In December 2025 the Lobito Atlantic Railway won $553 million from the US DFC and $200 million from the DBSA, with ~$6 billion of total corridor investment (the US pledging $4 billion)." },
  2740: { descEn: "Google's major German data-centre investment through 2029.", detailEn: "Google announced ~€5.5 billion in Germany by 2029, building and expanding data centres (at Hanau and elsewhere) and cloud regions with renewable PPAs for German and European cloud and AI demand — one of its largest single-country investments in Europe." },
  2753: { descEn: "The Black Sea's largest gas development, a major new EU source.", detailEn: "In Romania's deep-water Black Sea EEZ, OMV Petrom and Romgaz develop ~100 bcm of recoverable gas peaking at ~10 bcm a year, at ~€4 billion — the largest Black Sea gas development, set to make Romania one of the EU's largest gas producers. Offshore drilling and completion advanced in 2025, targeting 2027." },
  2808: { descEn: "Europe's first NuScale small modular reactor project.", detailEn: "At the former Doicești coal plant in Romania, this uses US NuScale VOYGR SMRs (6×77 MW, 462 MW total) — Europe's first NuScale SMR project, advancing FEED and licensing in 2025, targeting around 2030." },
  2819: { descEn: "China's compact fusion experiment, due 2027.", detailEn: "On 'Science Island' in Hefei, Anhui, BEST (Burning Plasma Experimental Superconducting Tokamak) is China's next-generation compact fusion device; in 2025 it completed the 400-tonne cryostat base installation. Targeting 2027 completion and a fusion-power demonstration (lighting a bulb), it aims to lead global magnetic-confinement fusion engineering." },
  2828: { descEn: "The first US commercial non-light-water fast reactor, with molten-salt storage.", detailEn: "At a former coal plant in Kemmerer, Wyoming, Bill Gates's TerraPower is building the Natrium sodium-cooled fast reactor (345 MW) with molten-salt storage (briefly up to 500 MW). It won the NRC's first commercial non-light-water construction permit and broke ground in March 2026; Meta has contracted for up to eight Natrium units, leading the US advanced-nuclear revival." },
  2931: { descEn: "Holtec's twin SMR-300 units at the Palisades site, possibly among the first US SMRs.", detailEn: "Pioneer 1 and 2 are ~340 MW SMR-300 PWRs developed with Hyundai E&C and Mitsubishi Electric, with a $400 million DOE first-mover award. In January 2026 Holtec filed a partial construction permit with the NRC, planning site preparation after restarting and reconnecting Palisades, targeting the early 2030s." },
  3445: { descEn: "A national fusion research platform, fully built in 2025, supporting CFETR and BEST.", detailEn: "On Science Island in Hefei, Anhui, built by the CAS Hefei Institutes, Kuafu is the first major science facility of the Hefei comprehensive national science centre — the world's highest-parameter, most complete fusion research and test platform, providing key technology for the CFETR engineering reactor." },
  3453: { descEn: "A 15th-Five-Year HVDC carrying Kubuqi desert-base power to Jiangsu.", detailEn: "From the Kubuqi Desert base in Ordos, Inner Mongolia to the Jiangsu load centre, planned at ±800 kV and ~8 GW to support the Yangtze Delta; Inner Mongolia's 2026 plan lists it among export corridors to start as soon as possible." },
  3454: { descEn: "A 15th-Five-Year HVDC carrying Kubuqi desert-base power to Anhui.", detailEn: "From the Kubuqi Desert base in Inner Mongolia to Anhui, planned at ±800 kV and ~8 GW for the second Kubuqi desert-renewable export batch to East China; Inner Mongolia's 2026 plan lists it as a corridor to approve as soon as possible." },
  3457: { descEn: "China's largest 750 kV ring grid, around the Tarim Basin, fully closed July 2025.", detailEn: "Built over ~15 years from nine 750 kV transmission projects, with ~4,197 km of lines, nine substations and nearly 10,000 towers around five prefectures of southern Xinjiang. It closed the loop on 13 July 2025 with the Hotan-Minfeng-Qiemo-Ruoqiang section — China's largest 750 kV extra-high-voltage ring grid." },
  3575: { descEn: "Shanghai port's largest single automated terminal: 22 berths, 11.6 million TEU/year.", detailEn: "The Yangshan North zone builds 6,100 m of quay with seven 70,000-tonne and 15 20,000-tonne container berths, designed for 11.6 million TEU a year for sea-river and coastal feeder traffic, pioneering a caisson-breakwater foundation. Over 6 billion yuan was invested by end-2024 with 4+ billion more in 2025." },
  4224: { descEn: "Offshore compression for the world's largest gas field; a COOEC-Saipem win (>$800M share).", detailEn: "QatarEnergy's NFPS COMP5 is an offshore compression project for North Field production sustainability, with two compression platforms. COOEC and Italy's Saipem won the ~$4 billion EPCI as a consortium, with COOEC's share over $800 million and offshore installation in 2029-2030 over a ~5-year schedule." },
  4225: { descEn: "A Chinese firm's largest single Middle East offshore oil-and-gas contract; Qatar's Bul Hanine.", detailEn: "COOEC won the BH-EPIC1 and BH-EPIC2 lots of QatarEnergy's Bul Hanine field development, ~$4 billion (~28.6 billion yuan), covering subsea pipelines, cables and umbilicals and facilities — the largest offshore oil-and-gas contract a Chinese firm has won in the Middle East. The contract took effect in October 2025, due June 2031." },
  4295: { descEn: "A Chinalco-EGA 2-million-tonne alumina refinery in Boké, Guinea.", detailEn: "On 1 June 2024 Chinalco and the UAE's EGA signed a framework to develop an alumina refinery in Boké, Guinea, next to EGA's GAC bauxite and export facilities, designed for 2 million tonnes/year (1.2 million initially), targeting around September 2026 at ~$4 billion — a strategic tie-up between Chinalco and a Gulf aluminium major on Guinean bauxite value-add." },
  4380: { descEn: "Tianqi holds ~22% of SQM, whose Atacama lithium is being folded into an SQM-Codelco JV.", detailEn: "Tianqi bought ~23.8% of SQM for $4.1 billion in 2018 (now ~22%), indirectly holding Atacama salt-flat lithium. Over 2024-2025 Chile pushed an SQM-Codelco JV with Codelco controlling Atacama through 2060; Tianqi continues to contest governance and approvals as the ownership is restructured." },
  4387: { descEn: "A Huayou-led full mining-to-battery-recycling chain at the IPIP Pomalaa park, 20 GWh battery.", detailEn: "Huayou subsidiary HYD (Huayou 70%, EVE Energy and PT Daaz Bara Lestari 15% each) signed a framework with Indonesia's ANTAM and IBC to build a full chain at the IPIP park in Pomalaa, Kolaka, Southeast Sulawesi: 100,000 tonnes of pyrometallurgical plus 50,000 tonnes of hydrometallurgical nickel, 105,000 tonnes/year of precursor, 20 GWh of nickel batteries (7 GWh phase 1) and recycling — taking over the ~55.88 billion-yuan Indonesian battery-chain project an LG consortium exited." },
  903: { descEn: "China's first high-altitude UHV AC project, lifting the southwest grid to 1,000 kV.", detailEn: "In Sichuan-Chongqing, this builds four 1,000 kV substations (Garze, Tianfu South, Chengdu East, Tongliang) and 1,316 km of double-circuit lines with 24,000 MVA of capacity. It entered service on 27 December 2024, able to transmit up to 35 TWh a year to integrate southwest clean energy." },
  1200: { descEn: "A million-tonne ethylene at Yangpu, mid-completion July 2025.", detailEn: "In the Yangpu zone of Hainan, this Hainan-Sinopec project of over 28 billion yuan builds 1 million tonnes/year of ethylene plus a refining upgrade. On 2 July 2025 three main units (pygas hydrogenation, aromatics extraction, light-hydrocarbon recovery) and 14 supporting works reached mid-completion (>97% overall), entering start-up preparation; it would drive over 100 billion yuan of downstream industry for Hainan's free-trade port." },
  1211: { descEn: "Huainan coal-chemical phase 2, a 5.6-million-tonne methanol-to-olefins chain.", detailEn: "In the Huainan modern coal-chemical park, Anhui, built by Zhong'an United (a JV of Sinopec's Great Wall Energy & Chemical and Wanbei Coal-Electricity). Phase-1 1.7-million-tonne MTO runs steadily; phase 2's first stage builds 5.6 million tonnes/year of coal-to-methanol, 1.48 million tonnes of MTO and downstream for 2.77 million tonnes/year of PE, PP, EVA, SAP and other products. The methanol-distillation EPC was won by Hualu Engineering (227 million yuan) in July 2025." },
  2673: { descEn: "A high-grade FMG magnetite mine, 22 million tonnes of concentrate a year.", detailEn: "In the Pilbara of WA, the FMG-Formosa Plastics JV magnetite project makes ~22 million tonnes a year of high-grade (67%) magnetite concentrate at ~$3.9 billion, with first concentrate in 2023 and ramp-up through 2025, supplying higher-grade feed better suited to green steel." },
  1195: { descEn: "The UK's largest undeveloped oilfield, facing environmental litigation.", detailEn: "About 130 km northwest of Shetland, Rosebank is the UK's largest undeveloped oilfield, ~300 million barrels recoverable. In January 2025 an Edinburgh court ruled the original approval failed to assess downstream emissions and must be re-consented, but allowed construction to continue meanwhile. Equinor and Ithaca have invested over £2.2 billion and awarded many supply contracts, targeting 2026-2027 — a focus of the UK's North Sea oil-and-climate debate." },
  1615: { descEn: "State Grid's third UHVDC concession, Brazil's largest-ever transmission concession.", detailEn: "After Belo Monte phases 1 and 2, State Grid independently won a third ±800 kV UHVDC with a 30-year concession — 1,468 km of new line, converter stations at both ends and AC works, 5 GW rated, through Maranhão, Tocantins and Goiás to mainly supply the capital Brasília. China Electric Power Equipment supplies and builds it, targeting 2029." },
  2657: { descEn: "An offshore gas field backfilling Darwin LNG; first gas 2025.", detailEn: "About 300 km north of Darwin in the Northern Territory, Santos-led Barossa uses an FPSO and subsea pipeline to backfill the Darwin LNG plant, ~3.7 million tonnes/year of LNG at full capacity. First production gas came in October 2025, moving from construction to start-up — an important northern Australian gas source." },
});

/* ===== 批次10：全库投资额 TOP（约 32–38 亿美元）===== */
Object.assign(window.ENERGY_EN, {
  2720: { descEn: "Connecting Sicily, Sardinia and the mainland, setting a deepest-cable record.", detailEn: "Terna's bipolar HVDC subsea cable links Sicily, Sardinia and mainland Italy, ~970 km and 1,000 MW. In December 2025 Nexans completed laying 500 kV cable at 2,150 m depth — a world HVDC-cable depth record — with converter stations due by end-2028, boosting Mediterranean grid resilience and renewable integration." },
  3204: { descEn: "A JSW-JFE 50/50 JV adding 6 million tonnes at the Odisha Bhushan (BPSL) plant.", detailEn: "JSW Steel and Japan's JFE Steel formed a 50/50 JV (~320 billion rupees) to expand the Bhushan Power and Steel (BPSL) plant at Sambalpur, Odisha by 6 million tonnes/year — from ~4.5 to over 10 million tonnes — creating a large integrated steel hub in eastern India, with the JV signed on 24 April 2026." },
  3278: { descEn: "A Visakhapatnam refinery upgrade to 15 million tonnes/year.", detailEn: "HPCL's ~314 billion-rupee VRMP raises the Visakh refinery from 8.33 to 15 million tonnes/year, commissioning a 3.55-million-tonne residue upgrader in 2025 (the world's first LC-Max residue hydrocracker) that converts ~93% of residue into high-value products, with plans for 18 million tonnes within 3-4 years and 10,000 tonnes/year of SAF from 2027." },
  3452: { descEn: "A 15th-Five-Year HVDC carrying Gansu Hexi renewables to Sichuan.", detailEn: "From the Wuwei area of Gansu to inland Sichuan, planned at ±800 kV and 8 GW, bundling Hexi desert wind, solar and supporting thermal power for Sichuan-Chongqing; Gansu government documents aim for a 2025 start and source-grid completion mid-15th-Five-Year." },
  3500: { descEn: "A 12-inch automotive specialty-process phase 2 in Lingang, Shanghai, to 50,000 wafers/month.", detailEn: "JuTai Semiconductor's specialty-process line (35.9 billion yuan in two phases) has a ~27 billion-yuan phase 2 expanding 12-inch specialty processes to 50,000 wafers/month for automotive analog, power and display-driver chips; registered capital rose to 16.9 billion yuan with lithography tools installed." },
  4058: { descEn: "East Africa's flagship Mombasa-Nairobi standard-gauge railway, built and operated by CRBC.", detailEn: "China Road and Bridge built and operates Kenya's 472 km Mombasa-Nairobi standard-gauge railway, linking East Africa's largest port-city with the capital using Chinese standards, technology and management. Since opening in 2017 operations have improved (2023 passenger revenue +11.7%, freight +7.3%) — a Belt and Road flagship in East Africa." },
  402: { descEn: "The last large undeveloped coalfield in the Shanxi-Shaanxi-Inner Mongolia core.", detailEn: "In Ejin Horo Banner, Ordos, Inner Mongolia, this is the only undeveloped large coalfield in the Jin-Shaan-Meng core, ~15.3 billion tonnes of reserves, with two 8-million-tonne mines (16 million total) at 26.5 billion yuan, started in 2024 and due in 2029." },
  1203: { descEn: "China's first alpha-olefin park, completing by end-2025.", detailEn: "In the Xuwei New Area of Lianyungang, Jiangsu, this is China's first integrated alpha-olefin high-end-materials park at ~26.6 billion yuan. Phase 1 (~12.15 billion yuan) has two 100,000-tonne alpha-olefin and 900,000-tonne polyethylene units, started in June 2024, completing through end-2025 for early-2026 start-up; phase 2 adds three alpha-olefin and three 200,000-tonne POE units by end-2026, filling China's high-end polyolefin-elastomer gap." },
  1684: { descEn: "GEM's nickel core base in Indonesia, with multiple units online in 2025.", detailEn: "QMB at IMIP in Morowali, Sulawesi, is 55%-controlled by GEM with Tsingshan, Brunp (CATL), ECOPRO, Hanwa and Yibin Libao, ~$3.7 billion cumulative, with 150,000 tonnes/year of MHP nickel, 30,000 tonnes of electro-nickel, 50,000 tonnes of high-nickel precursor and 30,000 tonnes of cathode. Electro-nickel started in September 2025 and cathode in December, with Q3 nickel shipments near 36,000 tonnes." },
  1781: { descEn: "A new metro line linking Guarulhos with central São Paulo.", detailEn: "Line 19 runs 17.6 km from Bosque Maia in Guarulhos to Anhangabaú in central São Paulo with 15 stations, serving over 630,000 riders a day at ~20 billion reais. Using three large-diameter TBMs (including Brazil's first EPB+slurry dual-mode), excavating 5.7 million m³, with civil works in three lots, it targets a 2026 start and 2032 completion." },
  2084: { descEn: "The world's largest single-line copper smelter.", detailEn: "At the JIIPE industrial port in Gresik, East Java, this processes 1.7 million tonnes of copper concentrate for ~650,000 tonnes of cathode copper a year plus gold and silver. Commissioned in June 2024, damaged by an October 2024 fire and restarted in May 2025, it ramped to full capacity within 2025, anchoring Indonesia's copper downstream chain." },
  3296: { descEn: "Sinopec's 200,000 b/d export refinery at Hambantota, Sri Lanka's largest-ever FDI.", detailEn: "Sinopec plans a 200,000 b/d (~10-million-tonne/year) refinery at Hambantota at ~$3.7 billion, mostly for export — Sri Lanka's largest-ever FDI. After years of talks, an October 2025 Sinopec visit reached consensus to start immediately, with Sri Lanka raising the local-sales share to 40% to clear the main obstacle." },
  152: { descEn: "Taiwan's largest offshore wind under construction off Changhua, supplying TSMC.", detailEn: "Greater Changhua 2b (337 MW) and 4 (582 MW) total 920 MW off Changhua, with FID in 2023, offshore works from February 2025 and ~DKK 20 billion of financing in July; all power is contracted to TSMC under a long-term PPA, targeting full grid connection in 2026." },
  284: { descEn: "A hyperscale liquid-cooled AI data centre in Melbourne.", detailEn: "On a new site in northwest Melbourne, over 354 MW and over $3.6 billion, this uses liquid cooling for dense AI loads — a core project of AirTrunk's Australian expansion." },
  546: { descEn: "Shanghai Lingang's largest operator-grade compute centre.", detailEn: "China Telecom's Lingang phase 2 plans ~25 billion yuan for a ~300,000 m² supercompute centre supporting 300,000 GPUs ultimately; in March 2024 it delivered and commercialised China's first single-pool 10,000-GPU domestic liquid-cooled cluster, supporting trillion-parameter model training from 2025." },
  1163: { descEn: "Penang's first light rail, linking George Town and the airport area.", detailEn: "The Mutiara Line is Penang's first LRT, ~29.5 km with 22 stations running north-south along George Town's east coast to Jelutong, Sungai Nibong and the Bayan Lepas airport area, with a ~5 km sea bridge to Penang Sentral on the mainland, later extending to Silicon Island. PM Anwar broke ground on 11 January 2025 with main works from late July, at up to RM16 billion, targeting December 2031." },
  1232: { descEn: "Pecém's most advanced green-hydrogen project, with preliminary permits.", detailEn: "At the Pecém industrial port zone in Ceará, this phased project (phases 1-2 1,200 MW, phase 3 900 MW) would produce 168,000 tonnes of green hydrogen a year (using 2.1 GW of renewables), equivalent to ~946,000 tonnes of green ammonia for export. Conceptual engineering is done and a pre-contract signed with Pecém port." },
  2995: { descEn: "A 100 GWh 4680 cell and first Semi plant at the Sparks gigafactory.", detailEn: "In early 2025 Tesla confirmed ~$3.6 billion to expand its Nevada Gigafactory with a 100 GWh 4680 cell plant and its first high-volume Semi electric-truck plant, adding ~4 million sq ft. 4680 yields rose sharply in mid-2025, with over $330 million of Nevada tax incentives." },
  2996: { descEn: "Canada's first large battery plant, in production November 2025, pivoting to grid storage.", detailEn: "NextStar (formerly an LG-Stellantis JV) at Windsor, Ontario is Canada's first large battery plant, ~4.23 million sq ft and 49.5 GWh. Series production began in November 2025 with over a million cells made; it now makes only stationary-storage cells, with LG buying Stellantis's stake in early 2026 after Stellantis exited." },
  3192: { descEn: "India's first domestic semiconductor assembly-and-test (OSAT) mega-plant, at Jagiroad, Assam.", detailEn: "Tata Semiconductor Assembly & Test is investing ~2.7 trillion rupees in India's first domestic OSAT plant at Jagiroad in Morigaon, Assam, making 48 million chips a day at capacity using wire-bonding, flip-chip and home-grown ISP for automotive, EV and communications, creating ~15,000 direct jobs, with first lines due in 2026." },
  3426: { descEn: "China's first Hualong One base with a cooling tower; main works started November 2025.", detailEn: "At Zhangxing in Zhaoyuan, Yantai, Shandong, CGN-controlled, this plans six Hualong One units with two in phase 1, using a 203 m high-position natural-draft cooling tower to switch the conventional-island cooling source from sea to air — a Hualong One first in China; unit 1 was approved by the State Council in August 2024." },
  3428: { descEn: "CGN's Lufeng CAP1000 Gen-III phase 1, twin units started in 2025.", detailEn: "At Tianweishan in Jieshi, Lufeng, Shanwei, Guangdong, on the east shore of Jieshi Bay, the base plans six MW-class units (5-6 Hualong One); phase-1 units 1-2 use CAP1000 passive Gen-III technology, approved by the State Council in August 2024." },
  3429: { descEn: "SPIC's first nuclear plant in Guangxi, main works started late 2024.", detailEn: "At the southern tip of the Jiangshan Peninsula in Fangchenggang, Guangxi, SPIC plans two CAP1000 plus four Guohe One units totalling 8.62 GW; phase 1 builds the CAP1000s, approved by the State Council in August 2024." },
  3431: { descEn: "CGN's Fangchenggang Hongsha Hualong One phase 3, fully launched May 2025.", detailEn: "At the Hongsha base in Fangchenggang, Guangxi, CGN-controlled, phases 1-2's four units are in commercial operation; phase 3 builds Hualong One units 5-6 at 1.208 GW each (~20 TWh a year combined), approved by the State Council in April 2025." },
  3432: { descEn: "Taishan (home of the first EPR) switches to Hualong One for phase 2, approved April 2025.", detailEn: "At Yaogu in Chixi, Taishan, Jiangmen, Guangdong — where Taishan phase 1 is the world's first EPR — phase-2 units 3-4 use Hualong One at 1,200 MW each; CGN bought Taishan Second Nuclear for 1.2 billion yuan in January 2025." },
  3433: { descEn: "CGN's Huizhou Taipingling Hualong One demonstration base phase 2; unit 3 started June 2025.", detailEn: "At Longzi in Huangbu, Huidong, Huizhou, Guangdong, on the northwest shore of Honghai Bay, this is one of China's first Hualong One fusion demonstration bases, planned for six units; phase-2 units 3-4 are 1,209 MW each with over 95% domestic equipment, approved in December 2023." },
  3437: { descEn: "The largest China-Russia nuclear project; Xudabao Russian Gen-III units, online 2027-2028.", detailEn: "At Xudapu in Xingcheng, Huludao, Liaoning, developed by CNNC Liaoning, units 3-4 use Russian VVER-1200/V491 reactors at 1.2 GW each; construction was witnessed by Xi Jinping and Putin via video in May 2021." },
  3447: { descEn: "China's candidate first inland nuclear plant, with signs of renewed activity in 2025-26.", detailEn: "At Heyeshan in Zhanxi, Taojiang, Yiyang, Hunan, controlled by CNNC with China Yangtze Power and others, the site is planned for 4 GW (2 GW phase 1). Inland nuclear awaits a national policy go-ahead, with the project company maintaining the site and preparatory work." },
  3448: { descEn: "An expansion of the Huaneng Shidao Bay base with Hualong One; unit 2 started May 2025.", detailEn: "At Shidao Bay in Rongcheng, Weihai, Shandong (also home to a high-temperature-gas-reactor demonstration), developed by Huaneng, expansion phase 1 units 1-2 use Hualong One at 1.2 GW each, distinct from the existing Gen-IV HTGR demonstration." },
  3451: { descEn: "Reserved units 7-8 at the Haiyang base, tied to long-term cross-region nuclear heating.", detailEn: "At Haiyang in Yantai, Shandong, SPIC's Shandong Nuclear plans six MW-class units plus an integrated small reactor, with the site reserved for expansion units 7-8; Haiyang is also China's largest nuclear district-heating source." },
  1637: { descEn: "Peru's largest distribution utility, controlled and operated.", detailEn: "In 2020 Three Gorges-controlled China Yangtze Power acquired 83.6% of Peru's largest distributor Luz del Sur for ~$3.59 billion, serving 1.3 million-plus customers (~30% of Peru's regulated distribution). It has expanded into renewables — two Arequipa solar plants (44 MW, 2023) and two Ica wind farms (129 MW, 2024) — forming an integrated hydro-wind-solar clean distribution-and-retail system." },
  110: { descEn: "The world's tallest dam under construction (315 m rockfill).", detailEn: "On the upper Dadu River in Aba, Sichuan, Shuangjiangkou's 315 m rockfill dam is the world's tallest under construction, with 2 GW and a 1.9 bcm regulating reservoir. First impoundment finished in May 2025 and the first stator was lifted in November, targeting first units by end-2025." },
  141: { descEn: "Germany's largest North Sea offshore wind farm.", detailEn: "At 913 MW with 83 11 MW turbines, this Ørsted-Nuveen JV first connected in December 2025 with full operation in Q1 2026, pioneering a 66 kV direct-connect converter platform (no offshore substation), with 786 MW of corporate PPAs signed by Amazon, BASF and Google." },
  146: { descEn: "The largest clean-energy project for Connecticut and Rhode Island.", detailEn: "About 40 km off Massachusetts, Revolution Wind's 65 11 MW turbines total 704 MW; it began supplying the New England grid on 13 March 2026 after a late-2025 federal stop and legal battle, powering ~350,000 homes." },
  246: { descEn: "A GM-Samsung SDI battery plant in Indiana.", detailEn: "At New Carlisle, Indiana, the GM-Samsung SDI JV starts at 27 GWh expanding to 36 GWh with 1,600+ jobs; construction slowed on a design change in late 2025 but it still targets production before end-2027." },
  583: { descEn: "Microsoft building a data-centre cluster at three sites around Cologne.", detailEn: "Under a €3.2 billion German AI-and-cloud plan, Microsoft is building simultaneously at Bergheim, Bedburg and Elsdorf industrial parks in North Rhine-Westphalia, breaking ground at Bergheim in March 2026, all water-free cooled, coming online over 2026-2027." },
  1016: { descEn: "A French low-carbon battery plant, inaugurated December 2025.", detailEn: "French battery start-up Verkor's first low-carbon gigafactory at Bourbourg in Dunkirk was built in ~2 years; it starts at 16 GWh (50 GWh planned by 2030), mainly for the Renault Alpine A390, creating ~1,200 direct and 3,000 indirect jobs with over €3 billion raised — a landmark of French battery sovereignty, inaugurated before Macron on 11 December 2025." },
  1490: { descEn: "Seven new EV and auto-electronics plants in Kaliningrad.", detailEn: "Avtotor in Kaliningrad is building seven plants under an investment plan (~285 billion roubles) for EV and auto-electronics production, with a home-designed compact EV at 50,000 vehicles/year and deeply localised motors, inverters, gearboxes, controllers and batteries, while assembling Chinese brands like BAIC and SWM." },
  1638: { descEn: "Three Gorges is the largest shareholder of Portugal's EDP.", detailEn: "In 2011 Three Gorges took a 21.35% stake in Portugal's EDP for ~€2.7 billion, later raised to ~23.27% as the long-time largest single shareholder, deeply tied to its renewables arm EDPR's global wind and solar (~19.3 GW of renewables by end-2024, +3.8 GW that year) — the core of Three Gorges' strategic European holdings." },
  1688: { descEn: "Johor's largest LEED-certified hyperscale campus, directly linked to Singapore.", detailEn: "DayOne (formerly GDS International) is building a flagship hyperscale AI campus at Nusajaya Tech Park in Iskandar, Johor; with the Kempas campus, operating and under-construction capacity exceeds 478 MW toward 500 MW. In June 2025 it raised RM1.5 billion (~$3.5 billion) of dual-currency green Islamic financing — among Asia-Pacific's largest data-centre syndications — with a 500 MW CRESS green-power deal with TNB and over RM8.1 billion invested in Malaysia since 2022." },
  1714: { descEn: "A new platform reviving the Campos Basin Marlim field, tendered on a BOT basis.", detailEn: "P-86 serves the revitalization of the old Marlim Sul/Marlim Leste fields in the Campos Basin, producing ~180,000 b/d on a BOT model, with a tender invitation issued in 2024. Part of Petrobras's Campos revitalization (Marlim/Albacora/Barracuda, ~$22 billion through 2028), it targets around 2031." },
  1743: { descEn: "A gigawatt-scale green-ammonia export hub at the Port of Açu, Rio.", detailEn: "In early 2025 the UK's Yamna and the Port of Açu signed a 3 km² land-reservation deal for 1 million tonnes/year of green ammonia needing ~1.8 GW of electrolysers. Açu is Brazil's largest private deep-water port industrial zone, handling ~40% of national oil exports; FID is targeted for 2027 and first green molecules in 2030, mainly for Europe." },
  1966: { descEn: "Malaysia's largest-ever solar tender.", detailEn: "Malaysia's Energy Commission launched its fifth large-scale solar tender (LSS PETRA) at 2 GW (over twice the prior round), awarded in 2024 at an average RM0.1699/kWh. With LSS5+ and LSS6, ~RM15-18 billion of contracts will come over two years — the country's largest solar rollout — with local developers like Cypark, Malakoff, Solarvest and Sunview, connecting around 2026." },
  2017: { descEn: "VinFast's flagship vehicle base, targeting 950,000 units in 2026.", detailEn: "VinFast's 335-hectare vehicle complex in the Cat Hai Dinh Vu zone, Hai Phong, in production since 2019, is its flagship base targeting 950,000 vehicles/year in 2026; with a second Ha Tinh plant (~$231 million, 200,000 phase 1, online June 2025, 400,000 by 2027) it drives the group's million-vehicle goal." },
  2043: { descEn: "Vietnam's largest planned data centre, $3.5 billion and 300 MW in three phases.", detailEn: "Vietnam's largest private firm Vingroup signed an MoU with the UAE's Benya Technologies to invest $3.5 billion in a hyperscale data centre developed in three phases totalling 300 MW. Signed at a Vietnam-UAE business forum during PM Pham Minh Chinh's UAE visit, it would be one of Vietnam's largest data-centre projects, with a site to be decided." },
  2218: { descEn: "A $3.5 billion industrial cluster in the Suez Canal Economic Zone.", detailEn: "At the Ain Sokhna industrial zone in Egypt's Suez Canal Economic Zone, three projects totalling $3.5 billion are landing from a Kemet Industries-Al Qalaa Red Flag (UAE-China) agreement, including a 250,000-tonne/year seamless-steel-pipe plant to meet infrastructure demand and cut imports — a flagship of SCZONE's drive to build a manufacturing hub." },
  2304: { descEn: "A planned African-largest methanol and fertiliser complex on Brass Island, Bayelsa.", detailEn: "At Odioama on Brass Island in Bayelsa State, Nigeria, this would be Africa's largest methanol plant at up to 10,000 tonnes/day, a JV including Shell, TotalEnergies and Eni. A gas-supply deal of ~270 million cubic feet/day is signed, at ~$3.5 billion." },
  2462: { descEn: "One of the first gas plants in South Africa's IPP programme.", detailEn: "Nersa approved Eskom's 3,000 MW gas plant at Richards Bay, among the first in the IPP gas-procurement programme, with South Africa's first LNG import terminal (a phase-1 floating storage unit and onshore regasification, ~400 million scf/d). Environmental groups successfully challenged the EIA, forcing a re-do; LNG phase-1 FID is expected in 2026 and operation in 2028." },
  2994: { descEn: "Integrated cathode and anode materials at Camp Hall, with recycling from late 2025.", detailEn: "Redwood Materials is investing ~$3.5 billion in a battery-recycling, refining and cathode/anode-materials plant at Camp Hall in Berkeley County, South Carolina, planning 100 GWh/year of cathode active material and anode copper foil, reaching 100 GWh capacity by late 2025 and 500 GWh by 2030, partnering with Toyota, Ford and Panasonic." },
  3019: { descEn: "Rebuilding Newark's 2.5-mile automated people mover, serving the new Terminal A.", detailEn: "A 2.5-mile replacement of the aging AirTrain links terminals, parking, rail and rental cars, raising daily capacity from 33,000 to 50,000 and connecting directly to the new Terminal A. Tutor Perini won a $1.2 billion contract in 2024, with works from October 2025 and passengers expected in 2030." },
  3297: { descEn: "Bangladesh expanding the Eastern Refinery at Chittagong, adding 3 million tonnes to 4.5 million.", detailEn: "Eastern Refinery phase 2 (ERL modernisation and expansion) at Chittagong would add 3 million tonnes/year to reach 4.5 million making Euro-5 fuels, at ~429.7 billion taka; after failing to attract foreign investors, it shifted to government self-funding to keep 51% control, targeting 2030." },
  3414: { descEn: "Guangxi's first subsidy-free offshore wind demonstration, full capacity 2025, extending to Qinzhou deep-sea.", detailEn: "The A and F sites off Fangchenggang total 1.8 GW at ~24.5 billion yuan — China's first fully rock-socketed, zero-subsidy grid-parity offshore wind; the A site reached full capacity on 7 February 2025. Guangxi's 14th Five-Year aims to approve and start 7.5 GW, with Qinzhou deep-sea preparation advancing." },
  4044: { descEn: "A smart deep-water gateway to South America, built by CCCC's Fourth Harbor.", detailEn: "Built by a China Harbour-CCCC Fourth Harbor consortium for COSCO Shipping-controlled investment, Chancay Port in Huaral, Peru has four berths, breakwaters, yards and shore power, designed initially for 1 million TEU, 6 million tonnes of bulk and 160,000 vehicles a year. It opened on 14 November 2024 — a new gateway for China-South America trade and the first smart deep-water port." },
  4398: { descEn: "HQC's role in Hengyi's PMB phase-1 refinery (8 million tonnes/year) in Brunei.", detailEn: "Hengyi (Brunei) PMB on Pulau Muara Besar has a phase-1 design of 8 million tonnes/year of crude, making gasoline, diesel, jet fuel and paraxylene, at ~$3.45 billion, started in November 2019 — China's largest investment in Brunei. HQC took part in the design and engineering, with phase 2 (14-million-tonne refining + ethylene) advancing to extend downstream chemicals." },
  917: { descEn: "A clean-energy export line from the Qinghai-Tibet plateau to Guangxi.", detailEn: "Using ±800 kV UHV flexible HVDC from Qinghai to Guangxi, ~36.5 TWh a year; site leveling and corridor planning were done by end-2025, with feasibility and approval expected to advance in 2026." },
  1373: { descEn: "Saudi Arabia's first car plant, EV CKD/CBU.", detailEn: "At King Abdullah Economic City (KAEC) north of Jeddah, this is Saudi Arabia's first car-assembly plant and Lucid's first overseas factory; phase 1 reassembles Lucid Air kits (~5,000/year), shifting to full manufacturing toward 155,000 vehicles a year. PIF is the main shareholder, with ~$3.4 billion of Saudi government incentives and purchase commitments." },
  1534: { descEn: "Central Asia's first large gas-to-liquids plant, at full capacity in 2025.", detailEn: "The Uzbekistan GTL plant near Shurtan in Kashkadarya, using Sasol technology, started in 2021 and reached full design capacity in 2025, processing 3.6 bcm of gas a year for ~1.5 million tonnes of synthetic liquid fuels — over 307,000 tonnes of jet fuel, 724,000 tonnes of diesel, 437,000 tonnes of naphtha and 53,000 tonnes of LPG — Central Asia's first large GTL." },
  3271: { descEn: "Dhaka Metro Line 5 North, JICA-financed, started late 2023.", detailEn: "MRT-5 North began on 4 November 2023 at ~412.4 billion taka with JICA financing, targeting 2028; the ~17.2 km southern line would have a ~$4.5 billion package (ADB $3 billion, Korea $1.5 billion)." },
  911: { descEn: "A line carrying Badain Jaran desert-base clean power to Sichuan.", detailEn: "From the Badain Jaran desert renewable base in Jiuquan, Gansu to Ziyang in Sichuan, ~1,436 km and 8 GW rated; ~10% of equity opened to private firms in February 2026, with approval and start expected in 2026 and completion in 2028." },
  1119: { descEn: "The world's largest-span suspension bridge under construction.", detailEn: "The Zhangjinggao Yangtze River Bridge links Zhangjiagang, Jingjiang and Rugao, 7,859 m with a 2,300 m main span — mainland China's first suspension span over 2,000 m, with six world firsts and six world records. Works sped up in 2025 (south tower past 200 m in March, north tower closed to millimetre precision in December), with the world's largest diaphragm-wall anchorage due mid-2026; started in 2022, targeting 2028." },
  191: { descEn: "A new corridor exporting Brazil's northeast renewables to the central-south.", detailEn: "Linking Maranhão and Goiás via Tocantins, ~1,500 km and 4 GW, won in a 2023 national-grid auction; started on 30 June 2025 for 2029 completion to relieve large-scale northeast wind and solar." },
  944: { descEn: "A DC corridor from North Rhine to Baden-Württemberg, built on a retired nuclear site.", detailEn: "Ultranet runs 342 km linking North Rhine-Westphalia and Baden-Württemberg, with a converter station on the former Philippsburg nuclear site — Germany's first to convert a retired nuclear site into a DC converter station. Full planning approval came in October 2025, targeting operation by end-2026." },
  945: { descEn: "A DC corridor from Emden to North Rhine, carrying North Sea wind to the Ruhr.", detailEn: "A-Nord runs ~305 km from Emden in Lower Saxony to Osterath; Sumitomo Electric won a €500 million-plus cable contract, with 525 kV DC underground cable laying launched in July 2025, targeting 2027." },
  1166: { descEn: "New Zealand's largest-ever transport project, twin-track tunnels under the city.", detailEn: "The City Rail Link is New Zealand's largest transport project, a pair of 3.45 km twin tunnels linking the rebuilt Waitematā (Britomart) and Maungawhau (Mount Eden) stations plus two new underground stations (Te Waihorotiu and Karangahape), doubling Auckland's rail capacity. The first test train ran on 13 February 2025, with construction and testing due by end-June 2026 and public service in H2 2026." },
  1207: { descEn: "Coal-to-polyolefins phase 2 in Yulin, mid-completion and commissioning in 2026.", detailEn: "In the Yushen industrial zone of Yulin, Shaanxi, China Coal Shaanxi Energy & Chemical's project (~23.888 billion yuan) builds 2.2 million tonnes/year of methanol and 900,000 tonnes of polyolefins plus a phase-1 upgrade and a 250,000-tonne LDPE/EVA chain. ~53% complete by September 2025 with long-lead equipment in place, targeting mid-completion and start-up in 2026." },
  1632: { descEn: "Three Gorges' largest overseas acquisition, Brazil's second-largest private power firm.", detailEn: "In 2015 Three Gorges Brazil won 30-year concessions for the Jupiá (1,551 MW) and Ilha Solteira (3,444 MW) cascade hydro plants for ~23.4 billion yuan — its largest overseas acquisition. It controls and operates them, undertaking a ~10-year upgrade of 22 units; the first two batches of 12 upgraded units are complete and in commercial operation, anchoring its position as a clean-power backbone in southeast Brazil." },
  2264: { descEn: "Sonelgaz's first 3 GW of solar across 12 provinces and 20 plants.", detailEn: "Algeria's Sonelgaz is advancing the first 3,000-3,200 MW of solar (toward 15 GW by 2035) across 20 projects in 12 provinces under 19 contracts. First plants came online in 2025 (Tendla 200 MW in El Meghaier, El Ghrous 200 MW in Biskra), with winners including CSCEC (300 MW), Turkey's Ozgun (300 MW) and Cosider+Fimer (250 MW), built in two years with local-content rules." },
  2617: { descEn: "An 840 km North Queensland artery linking Townsville and Mount Isa.", detailEn: "Built by Powerlink, CopperString first builds ~840 km of new line from Townsville to Mount Isa, tying into a North Queensland mining and renewables corridor — one of Australia's largest new grid projects. The eastern section targets pre-2032, with the A$225 million Flinders substation winning infrastructure approval to start in December 2025." },
  3263: { descEn: "Chennai's second airport, a greenfield at Parandur, ~274 billion rupees.", detailEn: "Parandur airport is ~274 billion rupees, one of south India's largest aviation projects, needing 3,331.25 acres (~1,700 acquired by 2025), with phase 1 due late 2029/early 2030, though land-acquisition protests in villages like Ekanapuram continue." },
  3269: { descEn: "A ~169 km Dhaka-Jashore railway via the Padma Bridge, built by CRCC.", detailEn: "Linking Dhaka and Jashore over ~169 km (Dhaka-Gandaria, Gandaria-Mawa, Mawa-Bhanga, Bhanga-Jashore), at ~374 billion taka with a ~210.4 billion-taka China Exim Bank loan, built by China Railway Construction; the 82 km Dhaka-Bhanga section is already open." },
  3470: { descEn: "A Sichuan Panxi clean-energy export and Sichuan-Yunnan grid-strengthening project, approved 2025.", detailEn: "In Liangshan, Sichuan, this builds two 1,000 kV UHV AC substations and 1,006 km of 1,000 kV AC lines, approved by Sichuan's NDRC in October 2025 with construction by year-end, strengthening Panxi hydro-wind-solar export and the Sichuan-Chongqing main grid." },
  4220: { descEn: "An NGL fractionation plant for the Jafurah gas field; an SEG-Técnicas Reunidas win.", detailEn: "The Riyas NGL project serves Aramco's Jafurah unconventional gas field with 2×36,000 t/d of NGL fractionation. Sinopec Engineering (SEG) and Spain's Técnicas Reunidas formed a JV, signing over $3.3 billion of contracts in early 2024 (P1/P2 EPC ~$1.173 billion), with No.5 Construction handling mechanical-electrical installation — among the Middle East's largest single contracts." },
  151: { descEn: "The world's largest solar-plus-storage project under construction.", detailEn: "Spanning ~3,500 hectares in Bulacan and Nueva Ecija, the Philippines, this plans 3.5 GW of solar with 4.5 GWh of storage; phase 1 was unveiled in November 2024 and 1,288 MW was grid-connected by January 2026, making it the Philippines' largest operating solar plant, and the world's largest single solar-plus-storage project once complete." },
  292: { descEn: "Microsoft's largest single digital-infrastructure commitment in Spain.", detailEn: "Microsoft is investing €2.9 billion in a hyperscale data-centre campus at Zaragoza, Spain, part of its European AI-infrastructure expansion, powered by local renewables, with construction in 2025." },
  780: { descEn: "Scotland's largest offshore wind farm, fully operational April 2025.", detailEn: "In the Moray Firth off northeast Scotland, 60 Siemens Gamesa 14.7 MW turbines total 882 MW, operated by the EDPR-Engie JV Ocean Winds; first power came in July 2024 and full capacity in April 2025, covering about half of Scottish households." },
});

/* ===== 批次11：全库投资额 TOP（约 28–32 亿美元）===== */
Object.assign(window.ENERGY_EN, {
  1165: { descEn: "Jakarta's north-south metro extended into the old city.", detailEn: "Jakarta MRT phase 2 extends the north-south line ~11.8 km fully underground from the HI roundabout through the old city to Ancol, JICA-financed; the HI-Kota section was ~53% done by September 2025, targeting 2026 for tunnelling to Kota and a ~27.8 km corridor." },
  1204: { descEn: "A 400,000-tonne POE phase 2 at the Penglai base, online end-2025.", detailEn: "At Wanhua Chemical's integrated base in Penglai, Yantai, Shandong (>23.1 billion yuan), the 200,000-tonne phase-1 POE started in June 2024; the 400,000-tonne/year phase-2 polyolefin-elastomer project, started March 2025, completes by end-2025 for 600,000 tonnes total with a 900,000-tonne PDH unit, leading China's domestic high-end POE for solar film and lightweight autos." },
  1205: { descEn: "A century-old northwest refiner builds 1.2-million-tonne ethylene.", detailEn: "At the Xigu chemical park in Lanzhou, Gansu, PetroChina's ~23.17 billion-yuan Lanzhou Petrochemical upgrade builds a 1.2-million-tonne/year ethylene cracker (reusing 460,000 tonnes) plus seven downstream units (UHMWPE, POE, EVA); polyolefins moved to design in January 2025, targeting start-up by end-October 2026." },
  1411: { descEn: "A flagship port on Kuwait's Bubiyan Island, a China-Kuwait Belt and Road project.", detailEn: "Mubarak Al-Kabeer Port on the Khor Abdullah channel of Bubiyan Island is a Vision 2035 flagship, ~$3.2 billion over ~3 km² with over 8 million TEU a year. Kuwait signed the phase-1 EPC with a Chinese state firm in late 2024, with site works from March 2025 and overall handover planned for 2026." },
  2949: { descEn: "A 420-mile DC line linking the US Eastern and Western grids for the first time.", detailEn: "Grid United's North Plains Connector from North Dakota to Montana is 3,000 MW at up to 525 kV, the first to connect the Eastern and Western interconnections, with a $700 million DOE GRIP grant; it signed converter-station early works with Hitachi Energy in October 2025, targeting a 2028 start and 2032 operation." },
  3053: { descEn: "Idaho's gold-antimony mine, the only large US antimony source under development, with a $2.9 billion EXIM loan.", detailEn: "Antimony is a national-security and storage-critical mineral; the Stibnite project won final federal permits and a $2.9 billion EXIM loan in May 2025, broke ground on 21 October 2025 and starts critical-path works in May 2026." },
  3201: { descEn: "Tata Steel's Odisha Kalinganagar phase 2, crude steel from 3 to 8 million tonnes.", detailEn: "At Kalinganagar in Jajpur, Odisha, Tata Steel's ~2.7 trillion-rupee phase 2 raises crude steel from 3 to 8 million tonnes/year, centred on India's largest blast furnace (5,870 m³ effective volume) unveiled in May 2025, with a long-term plan toward 16 million tonnes." },
  4268: { descEn: "Jeddah Central waterfront development, built by a CHEC-CRCC consortium.", detailEn: "In March 2024 China Harbour's Arabia arm and China Railway Construction's Saudi arm won a ~$3.2 billion contract for the Jeddah Central Development — a large Red Sea waterfront mixed-use scheme with marine works, a sea bridge, roads and power — a Vision 2030 urban-renewal flagship, with CHEC also winning the Red Sea Laheq link road and sea bridge." },
  4279: { descEn: "Hoa Phat's Dung Quat phase-2 integrated steel base, EPC by MCC firms.", detailEn: "At the Dung Quat zone in Quang Ngai, Vietnam, owned by Hoa Phat, MCC's WISDRI, MCC South and China MCC5 handle design and EPC for the phase-2 long-process base — two 4,350 m³ blast furnaces, 2×360 m² sinter, 2×300-tonne converters, a hot-strip line and captive power for ~5.6 million tonnes/year of steel. The phase-1 furnace lit on 25 December 2024 — set to be one of Southeast Asia's largest steel bases." },
  4470: { descEn: "Zijin advancing a 450,000-t/year copper expansion in Serbia, eyeing Europe's largest.", detailEn: "Zijin is accelerating a 450,000-tonnes-of-copper-a-year expansion at the lower zone of the Čukaru Peki copper-gold mine and the Bor copper mine in Serbia, with the lower zone holding 14.3 million tonnes of copper (0.86% grade) and 299 tonnes of gold. In 2024 its two Serbian mines produced ~293,000 tonnes of copper (second in Europe); at 450,000 tonnes it could become Europe's largest copper producer, with a new Malka Golaja discovery ~7 km from Timok." },
  4164: { descEn: "CGN's integrated wind-solar-storage mega-project in Piauí, Brazil.", detailEn: "CGN started an integrated wind-solar-storage project in Lagoa do Barro, Piauí at ~$3.17 billion, planning ~1.4 GW combining solar, wind and storage — one of Brazil's largest renewable projects, serving the energy transition and exploring green hydrogen." },
  185: { descEn: "A new corridor exporting Shanxi coal-and-renewable power to Beijing-Tianjin-Hebei.", detailEn: "From Datong in Shanxi to coastal Tianjin across Shanxi, Hebei and Tianjin, 770 km, started on 18 March 2025 for June 2027 operation, enabling 8 GW of wind and solar export and integrating 14.6 TWh of renewables a year." },
  700: { descEn: "Asia's largest single underground iron mine.", detailEn: "At Anshan in Liaoning, ~1.3 billion tonnes of proven reserves, designed for 30 million tonnes of ore and 10.41 million tonnes of iron concentrate a year over 36 years. Started in 2022 using TBM hard-rock tunnelling and green-smart tech, it targets end-2027 — a flagship of China's steel 'Cornerstone Plan'." },
  4039: { descEn: "The Dhaka-Jashore Padma Bridge rail link, fully through, built by CREC.", detailEn: "China Railway built Bangladesh's ~169 km Padma Bridge rail link from Dhaka to Jashore; it completed full-line trial running in November 2024 and passed the owner's completion test, including track, stations, bridges and power — a landmark of Bangladesh's rail modernisation." },
  869: { descEn: "A €2.8 billion green hydrogen-ammonia export flagship at Sines.", detailEn: "At the ZILS industrial and logistics zone in Sines, Portugal, a Portuguese-Dutch-Danish consortium plans ~€2.8 billion for green hydrogen and ammonia piped to Sines port for export to Europe, built over 2026-2027 for 2029." },
  940: { descEn: "The first direct UK-Germany HVDC power interconnector.", detailEn: "NeuConnect links the Isle of Wight in the UK with Wilhelmshaven in Germany, ~725 km and 1.4 GW — the first direct UK-Germany electricity interconnector. Prysmian launched phase-2 cable-laying in UK waters in July 2025, continuing to 2027, with converter stations under construction at both ends." },
  1780: { descEn: "A north-south Blue Line metro along Curitiba's BRT corridor.", detailEn: "Curitiba revived its north-south Blue Line metro, ~22.4 km with 21 stations along the historic BRT structural corridor, with a phase-1 PPP; the city planning institute IPPUC tendered the environmental study, with the project in study and modelling, part of a ~17 billion-reais citywide rail expansion." },
  3516: { descEn: "A Wuhan Jiangxia phase-2 EV and storage battery base, 80 GWh planned, ~22 billion yuan.", detailEn: "Chuneng New Energy's Wuhan Jiangxia phase 2 is ~22 billion yuan and 80 GWh, mainly EV and storage cells and packs, starting Q1 2026 and producing from Q1 2027 (~24 billion yuan output value at capacity); Chuneng's storage-cell shipments rank among the global top three." },
  1115: { descEn: "China's first north-south coastal high-speed railway.", detailEn: "The Tianjin-Weifang high-speed railway runs 348.9 km at 350 km/h from Tianjin Binhai to Weifang North on the Jinan-Qingdao line. Its key Jinzu Haihe tunnel (the only tunnel, the first under the Haihe) was holed through on 27 November 2025; as China's first north-south coastal HSR it links Beijing-Tianjin-Hebei with the Shandong Peninsula, targeting 2027." },
  193: { descEn: "A Rajasthan renewable-base export line to Uttar Pradesh.", detailEn: "From Bhadla in Rajasthan to Fatehpur in Uttar Pradesh, 950 km at ±800 kV/6,000 MW, built by BHEL-Hitachi Energy, signed in February 2025 with Adani securing Japanese bank financing, targeting 2029." },
  252: { descEn: "Germany's largest green-hydrogen direct-reduced-iron plant.", detailEn: "At the Duisburg steel base, with ~€2 billion of government subsidy, this makes 2.5 million tonnes of DRI a year cutting 3.5 million tonnes of CO₂, in commissioning by end-2026 to replace blast furnaces — a core German steel-decarbonisation project." },
  259: { descEn: "Western China's largest synthetic-fibre feedstock base.", detailEn: "At Qinzhou in Guangxi, ~32 billion yuan plans 6 million tonnes of PTA and an olefin chain ultimately; phase 1 (3 million tonnes of PTA, 600,000-tonne propane dehydrogenation) partly started up in December 2025." },
  286: { descEn: "India's leading data-centre city.", detailEn: "Mumbai holds 52% of India's data-centre capacity; Microsoft announced $3 billion of Indian cloud and AI investment in January 2025, with AWS and Oracle also expanding, widely using liquid cooling for AI loads." },
  318: { descEn: "A 'desert sail' terminal designed by Foster + Partners.", detailEn: "Kuwait International Airport's Terminal 2, designed by Foster + Partners with a triangular 'desert sail' form and 28 gates, was 81% complete by end-2025, targeting civil completion in November 2026 to lift airport capacity to 50 million passengers a year." },
  400: { descEn: "Europe's largest lithium mine, able to meet ~90% of European demand.", detailEn: "In Serbia's Jadar Basin, Rio Tinto plans ~$3 billion for 58,000 tonnes/year of battery-grade lithium carbonate plus boric acid, listed by the EU as a strategic critical mineral; it entered 'care and maintenance' in November 2025, with first production targeted around 2028-2029." },
  542: { descEn: "North China's largest third-party data-centre park, serving ByteDance and other AI loads.", detailEn: "Runze Technology's Langfang International Information Port plans 1 million m² and ~130,000 racks, fully built by end-2025, with 80,000+ racks running and 7,209 PFLOPS (85.2% of Langfang's total), mainly for ByteDance and other majors." },
  591: { descEn: "A 250 MW hyperscale AI campus by HUMAIN and AirTrunk.", detailEn: "Announced in Riyadh in October 2025, HUMAIN signed a $3 billion deal with Blackstone-backed AirTrunk to build a 250 MW hyperscale AI campus in Riyadh for training, inference and cloud, with advanced liquid cooling — key to Saudi Arabia's top-five AI-compute ambition." },
  600: { descEn: "Two more AirTrunk hyperscale campuses in Johor.", detailEn: "In May 2026 AirTrunk announced JHB3 and JHB4 at Iskandar Puteri, Johor, totalling 280 MW and ~RM12 billion, bringing its four Malaysian campuses above 700 MW and ~$6.8 billion cumulative — the largest single operator in the Johor cluster." },
  821: { descEn: "Africa's fourth-largest hydro plant, all units online 2025.", detailEn: "At Stiegler's Gorge on the Rufiji River, Tanzania, nine 235 MW units total 2,115 MW, built by PowerChina; the last unit was handed over in March 2025 for ~6,307 GWh a year, exceeding Tanzania's peak demand and ending its chronic load-shedding." },
  827: { descEn: "The 12th cascade hydro plant on the upper Jinsha River.", detailEn: "On the Jinsha at the Sichuan-Yunnan border, four 600 MW units total 2.4 GW with ~10.5 TWh a year; the river was closed in November 2023 and the powerhouse excavation and diversion tunnel done in 2025, targeting 2029 — a China Energy flagship on the upper Jinsha." },
  830: { descEn: "India's largest hydro project, first unit online December 2025.", detailEn: "On the Subansiri at the Arunachal-Assam border, eight 250 MW units total 2,000 MW; started in 2005 but stalled repeatedly over geology and environment, the first unit connected in December 2025 with the other seven through 2026 — northeast India's largest hydro project." },
  875: { descEn: "India's first commercial-scale green-ammonia project.", detailEn: "Near Kakinada port in Andhra Pradesh, with FID in 2024, phase 1 has 7.5 GW of wind and solar plus 1,950 MW of electrolysers for 1 million tonnes of green ammonia a year, phasing in from H2 2026, with a 500,000-tonne Uniper offtake; the cluster's ecosystem investment exceeds $15 billion — a flagship of India's National Green Hydrogen Mission." },
  910: { descEn: "Reinforcing the Sichuan-Chongqing UHV AC ring grid.", detailEn: "This builds new 1,000 kV substations at Northern Sichuan (Mianyang) and Fuling (Changshou) and expands the Tongliang substation with 1,000 kV AC lines, completing the Sichuan-Chongqing UHV AC ring; first environmental disclosure was in January 2025." },
  981: { descEn: "A high-voltage DC line sending Wyoming wind to Nevada.", detailEn: "TransWest Express carries ~3,000 MW of Wyoming wind via Colorado and Utah to near Las Vegas, Nevada, ~728 miles combining HVDC and HVAC. Started in 2023, the Wyoming and Utah sections advanced in 2025, targeting phase-1 completion in 2027." },
  1037: { descEn: "A twin-arc-furnace mega-mill in Arkansas, adding low-carbon DRI.", detailEn: "Big River 2 at Osceola, Arkansas is Arkansas's largest private project, with two arc furnaces for 3 million tonnes a year, finished early in late 2025 to give the Big River campus 6 million tonnes, full by early 2026. Part of Nippon Steel's $11 billion US pledge, a ~$2 billion DRI plant was also confirmed at the campus in November 2025 — a giant regional grid load." },
  1045: { descEn: "Closing blast furnace 7 for a hydrogen-ready DRI and arc furnace.", detailEn: "At IJmuiden, Tata Steel Netherlands will close blast furnace 7 and build a 2.5-million-tonne hydrogen-ready Energiron DRI plant (initially gas) plus high-scrap arc furnaces, targeting ~40% lower carbon by 2030 and neutrality by 2045. It signed a letter of intent with the Dutch government in late September 2025 (€2 billion plus ~€300 million EU innovation funding), pending FID — a giant future grid load." },
  1049: { descEn: "The world's first quartz-to-module fully integrated solar plant.", detailEn: "At the Dhirubhai Ambani Green Energy giga-complex in Jamnagar, Gujarat, the first line started in April 2025 with the first 200 MW of HJT modules, planning a full 'quartz-to-module' chain (polysilicon, wafers, cells, modules, glass) expanding from 10 to 20 GW — a huge electrified load with electrolysers and storage." },
  1126: { descEn: "A cross-border railway linking Oman's Sohar Port with Abu Dhabi.", detailEn: "Hafeet Rail is a UAE-Oman JV railway, 303 km via Al Ain linking Sohar Port and Abu Dhabi at 200 km/h (Sohar-Abu Dhabi in 1h40). A ~$1.3 billion civil contract (Trojan-Galfar) and a Siemens-Hassan Allam systems package were awarded in February 2025, ~30% complete by January 2026 — a key GCC rail link." },
  1178: { descEn: "A second floating LNG vessel off Congo.", detailEn: "Eni's second floating LNG, Nguya, in Congo's Marine XII block adds ~2.4 million tonnes/year, taking Congo LNG with the existing Tango FLNG to 3 million tonnes. Built in 33 months with a Shanghai sail-away ceremony in August 2025, it produced first phase-2 LNG in February 2026, mainly for Europe." },
  1188: { descEn: "Bohai's seventh 100-million-tonne oilfield, discovered end-2025.", detailEn: "On 24 December 2025 CNOOC announced a 100-million-tonne discovery in the shallow Neogene of the central Bohai — the Qinhuangdao 29-6 field, ~44 km from Jingtang port — its seventh such find since 2019, with single-well output ~370 tonnes/day, identifying many subtle lithologic traps." },
  1192: { descEn: "Argentina's largest oil-export project, started 2025.", detailEn: "About 437 km, this carries Vaca Muerta crude to a new Atlantic export terminal at 550,000 b/d (expandable to 700,000) — Argentina's largest oil-export infrastructure. Started in February 2025 with the first mainline weld in May and a $2 billion loan in July, it targets end-2026 to unlock shale-oil export." },
  1202: { descEn: "A Lianyungang solar-grade EVA base, units online through 2025.", detailEn: "At Shenghong's integrated base in the Xuwei New Area of Lianyungang, Jiangsu, ~21.6 billion yuan builds 700,000 tonnes/year of EVA and 50,000 tonnes of high-end polyolefins across five EVA units; the first started in October 2024 and the second in March 2025, lifting Lianyungang's EVA to 1 million tonnes/year mainly for solar film, cutting import reliance." },
  1302: { descEn: "Reviving the Campos Basin Albacora field with new FPSO P-88.", detailEn: "Petrobras is advancing the Albacora revitalization in the Campos Basin with a new 120,000 b/d FPSO P-88, expected after 2030; on 13 November 2025 it extended the P-88 build tender from December 2025 to 25 May 2026, with a Campos gas-export arrangement reached with PRIO." },
  1307: { descEn: "Brazil's first drilling permit in the Equatorial Margin, off the Amazon mouth.", detailEn: "On 20 October 2025 IBAMA approved Petrobras to drill an exploration well in block FZA-M-59 in the Foz do Amazonas basin ~175 km off Amapá in deep water — the Equatorial Margin's first drilling permit. The rig is in place for a ~5-month well; Petrobras plans $3 billion for 15 wells in the Equatorial Margin." },
  1308: { descEn: "A large HEFA SAF and renewable-diesel biorefinery in Bahia.", detailEn: "Acelen Renováveis is building a biorefinery beside its refinery at São Francisco do Conde, Bahia — $1.5 billion phase 1, over $3 billion total — using HEFA for 1 billion litres a year of SAF and 100% renewable diesel (~20,000 b/d). It secured $1.5 billion led by IFC and HSBC in May 2026, planting 180,000 hectares of macauba." },
  1379: { descEn: "Oman's first hydrogen-ready green-steel plant.", detailEn: "Jindal's Vulcan Green Steel is building at Duqm SEZ, Oman, over $3 billion, using Energiron hydrogen-ready DRI (up to 80% hydrogen) at 2.5 million tonnes a unit, planning 5 million tonnes/year of green steel across two phases with ~85% lower carbon than the global average." },
  1423: { descEn: "A phased expansion of the world's second-largest offshore oilfield.", detailEn: "Upper Zakum, 84 km off Abu Dhabi, is the world's second-largest offshore field; ADNOC with ExxonMobil (28%) and INPEX/JODCO (12%) is raising sustainable capacity from 1 to 1.5 million b/d using smart drilling, AI control and electrification, with a ~$30 billion concession capex budget." },
  1504: { descEn: "A large AI campus in Bukhara, up to 250 MW long term.", detailEn: "DataVolt plans a data-centre park in the ancient city of Bukhara starting at ~40 MW and reaching 250 MW, ~€2.8 billion (~$3 billion) — part of its 5-year €4.6 billion-plus Uzbekistan plan and a national 500 MW data-centre project." },
  1710: { descEn: "The tenth FPSO at the Búzios pre-salt field, lifting it past a million barrels.", detailEn: "Built by Seatrium, P-82 in the ultra-deep Búzios pre-salt field in the Santos Basin produces 225,000 b/d and processes 12 million m³/day of gas with over 1.6 million barrels of storage. Part of Petrobras's 2025-29 Búzios finale, started in Q1 2024 and targeting 2027 to push the field past 1.5 million b/d." },
  1715: { descEn: "Búzios's twelfth FPSO, a strategic pre-salt gas-export hub.", detailEn: "P-91 (Búzios 12) will be a strategic gas hub for the Búzios field, also exporting gas from platforms lacking export capacity, connecting 16 wells (8 producing, 8 injecting) at 180,000 b/d and 12 million m³/day of gas. A BOT tender (≥25% local content) launched in October 2025, targeting ~2031." },
  1751: { descEn: "A 1.2 GW offshore wind project off Caucaia, Ceará.", detailEn: "Developed by BI Energia off Caucaia in Ceará, 1.2 GW with 100 12 MW turbines, one of IBAMA's earliest offshore assessments (2016). In early environmental licensing, it awaits Brazil's first offshore auction (rules due H1 2026, auction perhaps 2027), with IBAMA's first permits planned for 2026." },
  1770: { descEn: "A Singapore-backed green-powered hyperscale compute complex in Brazil (site TBD).", detailEn: "Singapore's Nova Complex, reaffirming at COP30, plans $3 billion for a three-site PowerDataCampus in Brazil: 1 GW of wind-solar-hydro green power with 800 MW of IT load. It is in talks with the government and partners on site, policy and delivery (location shown at Rio)." },
  1897: { descEn: "A regional express linking Riyadh airport, KAFD and Qiddiya.", detailEn: "Launched as a call for interest by the Royal Commission for Riyadh in September 2025 on a PPP basis in two phases: phase 1 links King Khalid International Airport and the KAFD financial district to Qiddiya at 250 km/h (30-minute trip), phase 2 extends to New Murabba, central Riyadh and the southern industrial city. With 145+ firms interested, it targets 2027-2028 for Vision 2030 tourism." },
  1904: { descEn: "A fully automated Red Sea container hub, online 2026.", detailEn: "At NEOM Oxagon industrial city, with a 900 m advanced automated quay, Saudi Arabia's first fully automated cranes and 1.5 million TEU a year, able to berth the world's largest ships. BESIX with MBL and Boskalis built 4.6+ km of quay and seven 10.5-18.5 m berths; a Hassan Allam-El Seif-China Harbour consortium built the terminal-1 EPC, ~68% done, with full container operations in 2026." },
  2026: { descEn: "One of Johor's largest hyperscale campuses, almost fully leased.", detailEn: "AirTrunk's JHB1 and JHB2 in Johor total over 420 MW of IT load and are nearly 100% leased; JHB1 (150+ MW) opened in July 2024 and the 270 MW JHB2 was announced in February 2025, both cloud- and AI-ready, powered by TNB — core AirTrunk assets in Malaysia (~$6.8 billion committed)." },
  2069: { descEn: "A phase-2 expansion study at Vietnam's Nghi Son refinery.", detailEn: "Nghi Son (NSRP) — Idemitsu and Kuwait Petroleum International 35.1% each, PVN 25.1%, Mitsui Chemicals 4.7% — started its 200,000 b/d phase 1 in 2018. The PM has asked shareholders to finalise a phase-2 expansion plan for approval; the refinery ran at 120% in 2026 and began feedstock diversification (first non-Kuwaiti crude)." },
  2076: { descEn: "Expanding the Bintulu LNG complex to ~30 MTPA.", detailEn: "Petronas's Bintulu LNG Train 9 entered commercial operation on 1 January 2026, adding 3.6 MTPA to bring the Bintulu complex to ~30 MTPA. Train 9 has both liquefaction and regasification capability with new tanks, a jetty and loading; the complex is ~40.5% of Sarawak exports and ~4.2% of Malaysian GDP." },
  2214: { descEn: "A 57 km monorail to the New Administrative Capital.", detailEn: "The Cairo East Nile Monorail is 57 km linking the New Administrative Capital with the east Nile bank, designed, built and operated by an Alstom-led consortium (€2.7 billion for both lines). It was unveiled on 20 March 2026 and opened on 6 May — one of the world's longest driverless monorails, greatly improving commuting to the new capital." },
  2260: { descEn: "An 1,400 km, 3 GW north-south HVDC artery carrying southern wind-solar power.", detailEn: "ONEE is building an 1,400 km north-south HVDC line at 3 GW from Ouled Lekraa north of Dakhla to Mediouna near Casablanca, with converter stations at Laayoune, Tan-Tan, Agadir and Marrakech. Phase 1 (1.5 GW) targets 2026 and phase 2 (1.5 GW) 2028; ONEE's grid spend is ~30 billion dirhams (~$3 billion), with EPC bidders including GE Vernova, Siemens Energy, PowerChina SEPCO1, TBEA and L&T." },
  2267: { descEn: "A new 5-million-tonne refinery in Ouargla, started February 2025.", detailEn: "Sonatrach is building a 5-million-tonne/year refinery at Hassi Messaoud (Ouargla), started in February 2025 and targeting end-2027 to meet domestic fuel demand and cut imports — central to Algeria's $7 billion 2025-2029 refining plan to lift hydrocarbon value-add from 32% to 50%." },
  2352: { descEn: "A Danish GreenGo green hydrogen-ammonia project in Mauritania, on 100,000 hectares.", detailEn: "In February 2025 GreenGo signed a framework with Mauritania for 100,000 hectares for green hydrogen-ammonia development; a final phase 1 is due online by end-2029 with 500 MW of electrolysers, 600 MW of onshore wind and 600 MWp of solar for ~339,000 tonnes of green ammonia a year, scaled down from an original 35 GW." },
  2455: { descEn: "Phase 1 of South Africa's transmission backbone plan.", detailEn: "NTCSA's 2025-2034 transmission plan envisions 14,500 km of new lines and 133,000 MVA of transformers to connect 56 GW of new generation; phase 1 (2025-2027), ~4,500 km of lines and substations, is in construction or detailed design, prioritising corridors from the Cape provinces to Gauteng and KwaZulu-Natal, targeting ~37 GW of new connection capacity by 2030." },
  2609: { descEn: "A 2.5 GW Queensland solar-storage giant, developed in phases.", detailEn: "Near Millmerran in Queensland, planned for 2.5 GW of solar, phase 1 pairs 300 MW of solar with 425 MW/1,700 MWh of batteries to absorb midday solar (the duck curve); financial close and start moved to 2028 — one of Queensland's largest integrated solar-storage plans." },
  2644: { descEn: "Google's ongoing Australian cloud and AI expansion.", detailEn: "Google keeps expanding cloud data centres and AI infrastructure in Sydney and Melbourne with a Digital Future plan and renewable PPAs, serving Australia-NZ enterprise cloud, search and generative-AI loads — a major hyperscale-cloud player in Australia." },
  2719: { descEn: "Denmark's largest offshore wind farm, 1 GW in the North Sea.", detailEn: "Off Denmark's west coast in the North Sea, RWE's Thor is ~1.08 GW with 72 15 MW turbines — Denmark's largest offshore wind farm. Offshore works advanced in 2025, targeting full operation in 2027, with some power for green hydrogen and industrial decarbonisation." },
  2722: { descEn: "One of the world's largest multi-terminal offshore interconnectors, linking the UK, Netherlands and wind.", detailEn: "Developed by National Grid and TenneT, LionLink is a 1.8 GW HVDC multi-terminal interconnector tying North Sea offshore wind into both the UK and Dutch grids, powering ~2.5 million homes; FID is expected in 2026 with operation in 2030-2032 — a landmark of Europe's 'offshore grid'." },
  2724: { descEn: "Carrying northern wind to the Rhine-Main load centre.", detailEn: "An Amprion-50Hertz multi-circuit HVDC corridor carries northern German and North Sea wind to the Rhine-Main (Frankfurt) industrial load centre, planned as several ±525 kV circuits of 2 GW each — a key southbound route in Germany's grid build-out (like SuedLink), advancing approval in 2025 toward the early 2030s." },
  2726: { descEn: "A subsea DC line sending Scottish wind to England.", detailEn: "An SSEN-National Grid 2 GW HVDC subsea cable carries abundant northeast-Scotland wind to English load centres, an extension of the Eastern Green Link series (EGL1/2 already advancing), progressing approval and grid connection in 2025 toward the early 2030s." },
  2730: { descEn: "Italy's first long-duration storage auction, 10 GWh landing in the south.", detailEn: "Terna's MACSE long-duration storage mechanism held its first auction in September 2025, securing ~10 GWh mainly in renewable-rich southern Italy; by guaranteeing long-term capacity revenue it unlocks billions of euros of investment, coming online from 2028." },
  2818: { descEn: "An expansion of the world's first commercial high-temperature gas reactor.", detailEn: "At Shidao Bay in Rongcheng, Shandong, the world's first modular high-temperature gas-cooled reactor plant (HTR-PM) started in 2023, with inherent safety and high-temperature process heat. A 600 MW expansion (HTR-PM600) is planned to commercialise Gen-IV HTGR and industrial high-temperature heat." },
  2944: { descEn: "Urenco adds ~700,000 SWU/year at Eunice, New Mexico, approved to 10% enrichment.", detailEn: "Urenco USA is adding ~700,000 SWU/year (~15%) at Eunice over 2025-2027, with new cascades online early in 2025. In October 2025 the NRC approved enrichment to 10% (LEU+), with first deliveries in 2026 as HALEU feedstock to strengthen domestic nuclear-fuel supply." },
  2955: { descEn: "A 370-mile 765 kV line from near Fort Stockton to San Antonio.", detailEn: "One of three 765 kV paths in the Permian reliability plan, built by AEP Texas and CPS Energy from the Solstice substation to the Howard substation in San Antonio, ~370 miles, with a joint CCN application filed to the PUCT in March 2026." },
  3012: { descEn: "Linking Orlando and Tampa along the I-4 median, ~1 hour.", detailEn: "A ~137 km line along the I-4 median, with Tampa station candidates downtown, Ybor and Channelside. Brightline is seeking up to $400 million of tax-exempt bonds from the Florida Development Finance Corporation; Tampa's council agreed to continue bond talks in July 2025, with the project in financing and early engineering." },
  3034: { descEn: "A ~$3 billion expansion of Mexico's largest port, doubling container capacity to 10 million TEU.", detailEn: "The expansion quadruples port area and lifts container capacity from 3.7 million to 10 million TEU by 2030, making Manzanillo Latin America's largest. Phase-1 T2/T3 public site works run 2025-2026 with private construction 2026-2028; phase-2 T4-T6 follows, with Contecon investing over $300 million more." },
  3046: { descEn: "A Shell Garden Banks deepwater development replicating the Whale design.", detailEn: "Shell took FID on the Sparta deepwater project in the Garden Banks area of the Gulf of Mexico in over 1,400 m of water — a semi-submersible production platform with an initial 8 wells and ~90,000 boe/d peak, replicating ~95% of the Whale platform hull, targeting 2028 (Whale started up in January 2025)." },
  3138: { descEn: "Two 600 MW commercial fast reactors following the prototype.", detailEn: "At BHAVINI's Kalpakkam site next to the PFBR, India plans its first two 600 MW commercial fast breeder reactors, designed by IGCAR using mixed uranium-plutonium oxide fuel. After PFBR criticality in April 2026, per a parliamentary reply, financial approval for the twin units would follow, advancing a closed fuel cycle." },
  3203: { descEn: "Jindal Steel's Odisha Angul plant doubling crude steel to 12 million tonnes, India's largest single-site.", detailEn: "Jindal Steel completed expansion at Angul, Odisha, doubling crude steel from 6 to 12 million tonnes/year to become India's largest single-site steel plant; Odisha approved its ~246.5 billion-rupee plan toward 25.2 million tonnes, with the 12-million-tonne target largely met by end-2025." },
  3261: { descEn: "A planned southern Indian transhipment gateway port at Enayam, Tamil Nadu.", detailEn: "The Colachel (Kanniyakumari) transhipment port is planned at Enayam near Nagercoil, ~250 billion rupees (~65.8 billion phase 1), to be a southern Indian transhipment gateway handling ~2 million tonnes initially rising to 8 million." },
  3274: { descEn: "A ~141 km cross-border broad-gauge railway from India's Raxaul to Kathmandu, ~$3 billion.", detailEn: "Linking Raxaul in India with Kathmandu over ~141 km, with cost up from ~$2 billion to ~$3 billion on material prices; India's Konkan Railway finished the final alignment survey and proposed broad gauge to Nepal, competing with China's Gyirong-Kathmandu line." },
  3299: { descEn: "Bangladesh's first onshore LNG terminal at Matarbari, ~7.5 million tonnes/year.", detailEn: "Bangladesh's two floating terminals at Moheshkhali ran at ~96% in 2025 near their limit; Japan's Tokyo Gas finished a full feasibility study for a first onshore LNG terminal on Matarbari Island, ~7.5 million tonnes/year (~1,000 mmcfd), prioritised by Petrobangla for storage and peaking." },
  3322: { descEn: "One of the world's largest undeveloped copper mines, finally starting after a 2008 MCC deal.", detailEn: "Mes Aynak in Logar province ~40 km southeast of Kabul is the world's second-largest copper deposit, ~690 million tonnes of ore at 1.65%. MCC signed a 30-year mining deal in 2008 but it stalled ~17 years over security and archaeology; site works accelerated in 2025 with over $430 million spent, optimistically starting mining from 2026." },
  3506: { descEn: "Nexchip Hefei phase 4, a 12-inch line for 40/28nm CIS, OLED and logic.", detailEn: "After phase 3 (21 billion yuan, 50,000 wafers/month), Nexchip is advancing phase 4 with a new 55,000-wafer/month 12-inch foundry line for 40nm and 28nm CIS, OLED and logic, consolidating its lead in global display-driver foundry." },
  3598: { descEn: "The world's largest metamorphic buried-hill oilfield, phase 1 online February 2025.", detailEn: "In the central Bohai ~170 km from Tianjin in ~20 m of water, with over 200 million m³ of proven reserves, this is the world's largest metamorphic buried-hill field and a major recent Chinese offshore find. Phase 1 (a central platform, an unmanned wellhead platform and 33 wells) started in February 2025 at ~22,300 boe/d of light crude, just 3 years from discovery, 100% CNOOC." },
  3599: { descEn: "Bohai's largest shallow lithologic oilfield, full output May 2026.", detailEn: "In the southern Bohai ~245 km from Tianjin in ~20 m of water, with over 100 million tonnes of proven crude, this is the Bohai Bay basin's first 100-million-tonne shallow lithologic field and China's first offshore dendritic heavy-oil reservoir. Phase 1 (a central platform, two unmanned wellhead platforms and 79 wells with cold and thermal recovery) reaches full output on 27 May 2026 at over 2,800 tonnes/day." },
  3600: { descEn: "A 100-billion-m³-class deep shale gas field at Yongchuan, Chongqing; reserves certified 2025.", detailEn: "At Yongchuan in Chongqing in the complex structural zone of southern Sichuan, mostly deeper than 3,500 m, this is a major Sinopec deep-earth Sichuan-Chongqing gas breakthrough; 124.588 billion m³ of newly proven reserves were certified in August 2025, creating another 100-billion-m³-class deep shale gas field to support a 100-billion-m³ Sichuan-Chongqing gas base." },
  4028: { descEn: "Norinco (stake) and CNPC develop Iraq's Ahdab field, ~140,000 b/d.", detailEn: "Norinco and CNPC's JV Al-Waha Petroleum develops the Ahdab field in the Nahrawan area east of Baghdad, an integrated oil-gas-water-LPG-sulphur operation now producing ~140,000 b/d and ~800 million m³ of gas a year — a model Middle East oil-and-gas cooperation, boosting Iraqi revenue." },
  4102: { descEn: "State Grid holds ~97% of Chile's largest distributor CGE and 100% of Chilquinta.", detailEn: "Via SGID, State Grid acquired ~97.145% of Chile's CGE and 100% of Chilquinta Energía; CGE is Chile's widest-coverage distribution operator serving millions of customers with some transmission assets, with State Grid upgrading, modernising and digitalising its distribution network." },
  4162: { descEn: "Europe's first LFP battery gigafactory.", detailEn: "Envision's AESC is building Europe's first LFP battery gigafactory at Navalmoral de la Mata, Spain, started in July 2024 and due online in 2026, supplying storage and EV batteries to strengthen European localisation." },
  4213: { descEn: "Novatek's giant Gydan LNG, with deep Chinese engineering and module participation.", detailEn: "Arctic LNG 2 on Russia's Gydan Peninsula is designed for 19.8 million tonnes/year across three trains. After Technip Energies' main contract, many modules were subcontracted to Chinese yards and firms, with the CPECC system (including HQC) handling process design and module engineering; hit by sanctions, some trains began trial running from 2024." },
  4226: { descEn: "EPCI for Aramco's Marjan increment GOSP; COOEC delivered the heaviest international offshore platform from Qingdao.", detailEn: "A McDermott-COOEC consortium won the first package of Aramco's Marjan increment, over $3 billion, for the gas-oil separation plant (GOSP) EPCI. In August 2024 COOEC delivered the Marjan gathering-and-transport platform (GOSP-4 tie-in) from Qingdao — the heaviest, strongest international offshore oil-and-gas platform made in China." },
  4364: { descEn: "Datang's 912 MW Pak Beng hydro on the Mekong mainstream in Laos, 95% to Thailand.", detailEn: "The Pak Beng hydro plant on the Mekong mainstream in Oudomxay, Laos is the third dam in the lower-Mekong mainstream cascade, ~912 MW, a JV of China Datang Overseas (51%) and Thailand's Gulf Energy (49%). A PPA with EGAT was signed in September 2023 selling 95% to Thailand, the rest to Laos, targeting 2033." },
  4391: { descEn: "A Huafeng-Tsingshan 1-million-tonne aluminium smelter at the Morowali park.", detailEn: "Huafon-Tsingshan Aluminium at the Tsingshan Morowali park in Indonesia plans 1 million tonnes/year of aluminium; by April 2025 a 500,000-tonne phase 1 was built and producing, with the remaining 500,000 tonnes being prepared and captive power, marking Tsingshan's expansion into aluminium." },
  4392: { descEn: "A Tsingshan-Xinfa aluminium-smelting JV at Weda Bay and Morowali.", detailEn: "Tsingshan and Xinfa are building aluminium projects in Indonesia: the Juwan smelter at the IWIP Weda Bay park (~250,000 t/year) and the Taijing smelter at Morowali (~180,000 t/year); Tsingshan also plans a ~$3 billion large Indonesian aluminium plant, expanding its aluminium chain." },
  4484: { descEn: "GEM's IGIP green-industry park in Indonesia, up to $8 billion planned.", detailEn: "GEM is building the International Green Industrial Park (IGIP) at Sambalagi in Morowali, Central Sulawesi, with up to $8 billion planned (~$2 billion phase 1). In April 2025 GEM and Korea's ECOPRO signed a strategic deal in Pohang to build a nickel-precursor-cathode chain; cathode plants are planned at ~50,000 tonnes each in phases 1-2 and ~100,000 in phase 3 (~200,000 tonnes/year total), aiming for first cathode by end-2026 for Korean, Southeast Asian, European and US markets." },
  4503: { descEn: "CATL supplies EnerC/TENER container storage to the US, Middle East and Europe — world #1 in storage cells.", detailEn: "CATL supplies overseas grid-side and behind-the-meter storage with its EnerC, EnerOne and TENER container liquid-cooled systems. In 2024 its overseas storage-cell shipments reached 137.3 GWh (+50%+, ~40% of the global market), about half going to the US in Q3; it has led global storage-cell shipments for several years, serving large storage plants in the US, Middle East, Europe, South America, Southeast Asia and Australia." },
  3550: { descEn: "A 21-billion-yuan Hami compute-industry signing, coupling AI centres with renewables.", detailEn: "At a Hami industrial-investment signing, compute-industry projects totalling 21 billion yuan were signed, including two 2,000-PFLOPS and two 1,000-PFLOPS AI centres coupled with wind and solar, building a western green-compute hub." },
  1576: { descEn: "East Africa's largest hydro plant, full capacity in service.", detailEn: "On the Rufiji River, 2,115 MW (9×235 MW), with PowerChina installing seven units and guiding two; the ninth unit was handed over in late March 2025 and full capacity reached in April, generating over 3.1 billion kWh a year (over 40% of Tanzania's generation) — a milestone East African project." },
  2416: { descEn: "A 2,115 MW Rufiji River hydro plant reaching full commercial operation in mid-2026.", detailEn: "On the Rufiji River, 2,115 MW, Africa's fourth-largest hydro plant; multiple units are connected, with full commercial operation expected by mid-2026 to transform Tanzania's power mix — this entry covers its final units and full-operation phase." },
  3280: { descEn: "IOCL's Gujarat Koyali refinery to 18 million tonnes with 500,000-tonne polypropylene.", detailEn: "IOCL's Gujarat refinery (Koyali, Vadodara) LuPech upgrade raises capacity from 13.7 to 18 million tonnes/year, integrating lube base oils and petrochemicals with two units (240 billion rupees) for 500,000 tonnes/year of polypropylene and 150,000 tonnes of butyl acrylate." },
  904: { descEn: "A west-to-east corridor carrying northwest clean power to East China.", detailEn: "From the Baotashan converter in Yan'an, Shaanxi to the Hezhou converter in Hefei, Anhui across Shaanxi, Henan and Anhui, 1,069 km, started in March 2024; the Shaanxi section was through by December 2025, delivering over 36 TWh of green power a year once online in 2026." },
});

/* ===== 批次12：全库投资额 TOP（约 24–28 亿美元）===== */
Object.assign(window.ENERGY_EN, {
  186: { descEn: "A UHV AC ring grid covering all of Zhejiang.", detailEn: "New 1,000 kV substations at Jiaxing, Ningbo and Wenzhou plus an expanded Lishui station and ~2×490 km of 1,000 kV lines form Zhejiang's UHV backbone, approved in 2025 with equipment tendering in 2026 and completion targeted for 2028." },
  327: { descEn: "Thailand's largest deep-water port phase-3 expansion.", detailEn: "On a PPP basis (state 47%, private 53%), with China Harbour building the F1 terminal, Laem Chabang's phase 3 finished major dredging and reclamation in 2025, targeting 2028 completion and full operation in 2031 to lift throughput from 11 to 18 million TEU." },
  384: { descEn: "The largest US lithium mine under construction.", detailEn: "In Nevada, one of the world's largest clay-type lithium deposits, with a $2.26 billion DOE loan and GM investing $625 million for 38%; over 1,800 workers peak in 2026, mechanical completion targets late 2027, and it would supply 40,000 tonnes/year of lithium carbonate." },
  540: { descEn: "A core node of the Beijing-Tianjin-Hebei 'east-data-west-compute' hub.", detailEn: "Using wind, solar and a cold climate, Zhangjiakou has 30 operating data centres, 440,000 racks, 1.6 million servers and ~22,800 PFLOPS, with over a billion kWh of green power in 2024, absorbing Beijing's compute spillover, targeting 50,000+ PFLOPS and 70%+ AI compute by 2025." },
  701: { descEn: "An expansion of the world's largest iron mine, S11D.", detailEn: "At Carajás in Pará, Brazil, this adds 20 Mtpa to Vale's flagship S11D mine at ~$2.8 billion; it won an IBAMA operating licence in September 2025 and targets trial production in H2 2026, reaching 120 million tonnes a year at full capacity." },
  800: { descEn: "The world's largest planned floating offshore wind project.", detailEn: "About 75 km off Peterhead in northeast Scotland, developed by Flotation Energy and Vargronn (Eni's Plenitude + HitecVision), ~35 floating turbines total 560 MW; it won Scottish consent in 2024, supplying North Sea oil platforms and the onshore grid, targeting 2029 to become the world's largest floating offshore wind farm." },
  828: { descEn: "The 5th cascade hydro plant on the middle Yalong River.", detailEn: "On the Yalong at the Jiulong-Muli border in Sichuan, 2.4 GW with a 201 m dam and ~10.4 TWh a year; on 28 October 2025 it closed the river together with Yagen-1 (the Yalong's first same-day twin closure), entering main construction." },
  1209: { descEn: "A state-approved Zhundong coal-to-gas plant, restarted 2025.", detailEn: "In the Zhundong zone of Xinjiang, China Energy is building a coal-to-gas plant using crushed-coal pressurised gasification for 2 bcm/year of synthetic natural gas. Approved by the NDRC in March 2025 and restarted on 22 March, it targets full completion and start-up in 2027, converting Zhundong coal into clean gas for the West-East pipeline." },
  1711: { descEn: "Búzios's eleventh FPSO, a pre-salt expansion unit.", detailEn: "P-83 is the planned 11th production platform at the Búzios field, producing 225,000 b/d and processing 12 million m³/day of gas. Part of Petrobras's 2025-2029 pre-salt expansion batch with P-78/79/80/82, it targets 2027, cementing Búzios as the company's largest ultra-deepwater field toward 1.5 million b/d." },
  1817: { descEn: "A CRRC-led concession, Brazil's fastest passenger railway.", detailEn: "A CRRC Hong Kong-Comporte consortium won the ~R$14.2 billion concession to design, build and operate (30 years) the São Paulo-Campinas intercity line. The Jundiaí-Campinas section started in April 2026 (due 2029), with the full 101 km opening in 2031 at ~60,000 riders a day — a deep export of Chinese rail technology." },
  2303: { descEn: "A strategic north-south Nigerian gas trunkline, first gas July 2026.", detailEn: "The Ajaokuta-Kaduna-Kano (AKK) pipeline is 614 km, with mainline welding including the Niger River crossing done; the Ajaokuta-Gwagwalada section targets first gas in July 2026. At full capacity 2.2 bcf/d, it supports three new power plants and is the first section of the Trans-Saharan gas pipeline." },
  3021: { descEn: "A 2.25-mile driverless electric people mover at LAX, opening summer 2026.", detailEn: "The 2.25-mile, six-station Automated People Mover links the central terminals, rental-car centre, transit hub and an LAX/Metro station. At ~$2.8 billion, with the airport urging completion via a $550 million incentive, testing runs in April 2026 with opening in early summer 2026 ahead of the 2028 Olympics." },
  3045: { descEn: "A Permian-to-Agua Dulce gas pipeline, FID July 2024.", detailEn: "The Blackcomb pipeline is ~366 miles and 2.5 bcf/d from the Permian to Agua Dulce, Texas to serve Gulf Coast LNG exports. A WhiteWater JV with Targa took FID in July 2024, targeting H2 2026 with transport deals signed with Devon and Diamondback." },
  3100: { descEn: "A 13 GW Ladakh solar-wind hybrid park with 12 GWh storage.", detailEn: "At ~4,500 m around Pang, Debring and Karnak in Ladakh, 13 GW of solar and wind with 12 GWh of storage, plus 713 km of transmission (480 km HVDC) to the national grid via Himachal and Punjab, at ~2.0774 trillion rupees, implemented by POWERGRID, targeting FY2029-30." },
  3131: { descEn: "North India's first nuclear plant, indigenous 700 MW heavy-water reactors.", detailEn: "At Gorakhpur in Fatehabad, Haryana, North India's first nuclear plant has a first phase of two indigenous 700 MW PHWRs at ~206 billion rupees; foundation improvement is over 70% done and steam generators were delivered 7 months early, with the first unit targeting June 2028." },
  3132: { descEn: "Gorakhpur phase 2, fleet-mode 700 MW heavy-water reactors.", detailEn: "Gorakhpur units 3-4 (700 MW PHWRs each) are among India's 10 fleet-mode indigenous reactors approved in 2017, in preparation with steam generators delivered ~7 months early, awaiting phase-1 progress to start main construction." },
  3135: { descEn: "Madhya Pradesh's first inland nuclear plant, two indigenous 700 MW reactors.", detailEn: "At Chutka village in Mandla, Madhya Pradesh by the Bargi reservoir, two indigenous 700 MW PHWRs (fleet mode) are planned; land acquisition, environmental and forest clearances and water allocation were all in place by October 2025, with a resettlement area largely built, over a ~6-7-year schedule." },
  3501: { descEn: "A 20-billion-yuan 12-inch high-end analog IC line in Haicang, Xiamen.", detailEn: "Silan Microelectronics signed with Xiamen in October 2025 for 45,000 wafers/month (540,000/year at full capacity across two phases) at 20 billion yuan; phase 1 takes land in Q4 2025 and starts by year-end, with a production line in Q4 2027, focused on high-end analog and power-management chips." },
  4504: { descEn: "CATL's nickel-smelting, battery-materials and recycling base at the FHT park, East Halmahera.", detailEn: "As the upstream of CATL's nearly $6 billion integrated project with ANTAM and IBC, CATL subsidiary CBL is building a nickel-smelting, battery-materials and recycling base at the FHT park in East Halmahera, North Maluku: a pyrometallurgical plant from early 2027 (88,000 tonnes/year of refined nickel), a hydrometallurgical plant by 2028 (55,000 tonnes of MHP) and a 30,000-tonne NCM cathode unit (from 2028), forming a full Indonesian battery chain with the Karawang plant." },
  1113: { descEn: "A new southern-Shaanxi high-speed line through the Qinling.", detailEn: "The Xi'an-Ankang high-speed railway runs at 350 km/h through the Qinling Mountains with 20 tunnels. The Jiutianshan tunnel was holed through in May 2025 (all tunnels through) and track-laying began in October, targeting 2026 to cut Xi'an-Ankang from ~3 hours to under one and open the Xi'an-Chongqing route." },
  1120: { descEn: "The world's longest underwater road shield tunnel.", detailEn: "From Haimen in Nantong to Taicang in Suzhou, 39.07 km with an 11.19 km river-crossing tunnel, six lanes at 100 km/h — the world's longest underwater road shield tunnel. Two giant TBMs ('Jianghai' 16.64 m and 'Cangyuan' 16.66 m, China's largest diameter) bore toward each other; both entered the river in 2025, passing 3,000 m (~a third), targeting 2028." },
  1284: { descEn: "A Rondonópolis-Lucas grain trunk railway.", detailEn: "Rumo's 743 km state railway links Rondonópolis to Lucas do Rio Verde (with a Cuiabá branch) through 16 municipalities, hauling grain to Santos port. ~2 billion reais was invested in 2025, with a 2-billion-reais BNDES loan for 162 km." },
  180: { descEn: "China's first 'wind-solar-thermal-storage integrated' UHV export line.", detailEn: "From Qingyang in Gansu to Dongping in Shandong, 915 km at ±800 kV; started in June 2023 and commissioned on 8 May 2025 — the first UHVDC to start at full capacity all at once, bundling wind, solar, thermal and storage for 36 TWh a year." },
  1968: { descEn: "The Philippines' first large offshore wind project.", detailEn: "Developed by Denmark's CIP in Camarines Sur, this is the Philippines' first large offshore wind project and CIP's first in Southeast Asia, ~163 billion pesos (~$2.77 billion). In May 2025 ACEN agreed to buy 25%, with CIP committing ~$3 billion to Philippine offshore wind; it targets 2028 to launch scaled Philippine offshore wind." },
  1281: { descEn: "A grain corridor from inland Piauí to Pecém port.", detailEn: "Linking Eliseu Martins in Piauí with Pecém port in Ceará via Salgueiro in Pernambuco, ~1,209 km through 3 states and 53 municipalities, hauling grain, ore, gypsum and fuel, with over 8.2 billion reais invested; a first corn freight test ran on 19 December 2025." },
  276: { descEn: "A hyperscale data centre at King Abdullah Economic City, Jeddah.", detailEn: "North of Jeddah at King Abdullah Economic City, $2.7 billion and 480 MW, this is part of Saudi Arabia's Vision 2030 digital infrastructure, drawing sovereign-fund and global tech investment." },
  314: { descEn: "A strategic Iraqi deep-water port, the core node of the 'Development Road'.", detailEn: "On the northwest Persian Gulf coast, with ~$17 billion of total long-term investment; phase 1 is built by Korea's Daewoo E&C for $2.7 billion, with five berths for 23,000-TEU ships, a 62 km link road and a 2,400 m underwater tunnel — a strategic Asia-Europe trade hub." },
  913: { descEn: "A Shaanxi wind-solar-thermal-storage export line to Henan.", detailEn: "One of the 'three AC, nine DC' UHV corridors, from Shaanxi to Henan at 8 GW rated; environmental disclosure is done, and it is a 2026 State Grid priority to approve and start, delivering over 36 TWh of green power a year." },
  914: { descEn: "A Kubuqi desert renewable base sending power directly to Shanghai.", detailEn: "With a generation base in the Kubuqi Desert of Ordos, Inner Mongolia planning 12 GW of renewables and over 40 TWh a year (over 20 TWh green), feasibility tendering finished in November 2025, with approval expected mid-2026 and completion in 2029." },
  915: { descEn: "A Tengger desert clean-energy line to central China's Jiangxi.", detailEn: "From the Tengger Desert renewable base in Alxa, Inner Mongolia to Jiangxi at 8 GW rated, listed in early 2026 by State Grid's central-China branch as a priority reserve DC project to approve and start — a core 15th-Five-Year desert-base export corridor." },
  946: { descEn: "The UK's first high-capacity east-coast DC subsea power superhighway.", detailEn: "EGL1 links Torness in East Lothian, Scotland with Hawthorn Pit in County Durham, England, ~196 km and 2 GW; it won a ~£2 billion Ofgem funding package in November 2024 and started on 13 February 2025 — the UK's first ASTI fast-track project, targeting 2029." },
  1151: { descEn: "The São Paulo-Campinas intercity railway, concession signed 2025.", detailEn: "The TIC north axis links São Paulo, Jundiaí and Campinas, 101 km at 140 km/h, ~14.2 billion reais. On 29 May 2025 São Paulo's governor authorised signing the 30-year concession, won by the C2 Mobilidade consortium of Comporte (60%) and CRRC's Hong Kong arm (40%), formally signed on 3 June; the express line targets end-2031." },
  1173: { descEn: "A Gulf-coast Mexican floating-LNG export expansion.", detailEn: "New Fortress Energy is deploying a second floating-liquefaction line beside its existing import terminal at Altamira, Mexico, ~1.4 million tonnes/year with onshore pipelines. Its first FLNG produced LNG in 2024; construction of the second line starts in Q3 2025, targeting mechanical completion by end-2026 and commercial operation in H1 2027." },
  1272: { descEn: "Two new cloud and AI data centres in São Paulo.", detailEn: "Microsoft pledged $2.7 billion over three years to strengthen cloud and AI infrastructure in Brazil and opened two new data centres in São Paulo, expanding Azure regional compute and AI capacity on Brazil's high-renewables grid — among its largest Latin American commitments." },
  1563: { descEn: "A giant Yoshlik I copper-gold expansion, plant 3 online March 2026.", detailEn: "Almalyk's third copper concentrator, fed by the Yoshlik-1 deposit on 196 hectares, is $2.7 billion over ~4 years, processing 60 million tonnes of ore a year for ~900,000 tonnes of copper concentrate (raising daily output from 2,400 to 5,000 tonnes); it puts Almalyk among the world's top-ten copper complexes, creating 6,000+ jobs." },
  1776: { descEn: "A Guanabara Bay subsea tunnel linking Rio city with São Gonçalo.", detailEn: "Rio Metro Line 3 runs from Praça XV in central Rio via Niterói to Guaxindiba in São Gonçalo, 21.7 km with 15 stations, including a Guanabara Bay subsea tunnel, ~14.6 billion reais, expected ~650,000 riders a day, cutting the Niterói-São Gonçalo trip from 2 hours to 40 minutes. Coppe began a 30-month feasibility study in June 2025, with first tenders in 2026 and the first section targeting 2031." },
  1871: { descEn: "NEOM's phase-1 pumped hydro, ~11 hours of long-duration storage.", detailEn: "ENOWA's first of four NEOM pumped-hydro plants, Nestor, is 2,200 MW with 23.1 GWh (~11 hours) at ~$2.7 billion on a 40-year BOOT; it received qualification documents in June 2024 and an RFP at year-end, supporting NEOM's off-grid system with the later Al-Qimmah/Nima/Beach Mountain plants (~7 GW)." },
  2410: { descEn: "An 1,800 MW Omo River hydro plant, EPC by Italy's Webuild.", detailEn: "On the Omo River in southwest Ethiopia, 1,800 MW at ~$2.7 billion, built by Italy's Webuild with a ~200 km² reservoir; ~72% complete by January 2026, it is Ethiopia's largest hydro project after GERD, boosting energy independence and power exports." },
  2833: { descEn: "An enrichment expansion supplying high-assay fuel for advanced reactors.", detailEn: "In January 2026 the US DOE awarded ~$2.7 billion to expand domestic uranium enrichment, giving LEU and HALEU contracts to Centrus, Orano and Urenco to end reliance on Russian fuel and supply advanced reactors and SMRs like Natrium, centred in places like Piketon, Ohio." },
  3044: { descEn: "A Permian-to-Dallas gas trunkline, FID late 2024.", detailEn: "Energy Transfer took FID in December 2024 to carry gas from Waha in the Permian to Maypearl in the Dallas-Fort Worth area; phase 1 is ~644 km of 42-inch pipe at 1.5 bcf/d, with phase-2 compression lifting bidirectional flow to 2.2 bcf/d, ~$2.7 billion total." },
  3587: { descEn: "An 800,000-tonne East Hope coal-to-olefins plant in Zhundong, started 2025.", detailEn: "In the East Hope industrial park in Zhundong, Xinjiang, ~18.967 billion yuan converts ~6 million tonnes/year of coal, with 2.2 million tonnes of coal-to-methanol, 800,000 tonnes of MTO, 400,000 tonnes of PE and 500,000 tonnes of PP. Ground was broken in late 2024 and full works in March 2025 (~24-month build) — a large low-carbon coal-chemical project coupling green power and hydrogen." },
  4202: { descEn: "Huayou's Pomalaa HPAL nickel project with Vale and Ford, 120,000 t/year nickel.", detailEn: "At Pomalaa in Southeast Sulawesi, Indonesia, this Huayou-Vale Indonesia-Ford HPAL project plans 120,000 tonnes/year of nickel-in-MHP (a 60,000-tonne-nickel + ~5,000-tonne-cobalt first phase). Started in Q1 2025, it targets early 2027; Huayou sought ~$2.7 billion of syndicated financing in 2024." },
  4297: { descEn: "State Grid's third Brazilian ±800 kV UHVDC concession, Maranhão to Brasília.", detailEn: "State Grid won the 30-year concession on 15 December 2023 for Brazil's third ±800 kV UHVDC — ~1,468 km of line, converter stations at both ends and AC works at 5 GW rated through Maranhão, Tocantins and Goiás to mainly supply Brasília, aggregating northeast and northern wind, solar and hydro, targeting 2029." },
  639: { descEn: "A large Peruvian copper-molybdenum deposit, 726 million tonnes of resources.", detailEn: "In Apurímac, Peru, held by Southern Copper, ~726 million tonnes of resources, one of Peru's largest undeveloped copper deposits, in environmental review and land acquisition, ~$2.6 billion planned for 130,000 tonnes of copper and 7,500 tonnes of molybdenum a year, targeting a 2027 start." },
  788: { descEn: "France's second offshore wind farm, online May 2024.", detailEn: "Off northern Brittany, developed by Iberdrola with 62 Siemens Gamesa 8 MW turbines (496 MW), fully commercial in May 2024 — France's second commercial offshore wind farm after Saint-Nazaire, generating ~1.82 TWh a year (~9% of Brittany's power)." },
  1491: { descEn: "Doubling Siberian hydro-powered green aluminium to 600,000 tonnes.", detailEn: "The RUSAL-RusHydro JV Boguchansky smelter in Krasnoyarsk Krai uses Siberian hydropower for low-carbon aluminium; it plans to double capacity to 600,000 tonnes/year by 2030, with works from 2025 (phase 1 started in 2019), ~$2.6 billion total." },
  1993: { descEn: "Pumped hydro at three reservoirs totalling 2,472 MW, turning dams into giant batteries.", detailEn: "EGAT plans ~90 billion baht (~$2.6 billion) for pumped hydro at the Chulabhorn, Vajiralongkorn and Krathoon dams totalling 2,472 MW — Chulabhorn 801 MW (2034), Vajiralongkorn 891 MW (~2036) and Krathoon 780 MW (~2037); Chulabhorn's EIA is approved, advancing ministry and cabinet review." },
  2601: { descEn: "The Southern Hemisphere's largest wind farm, 1.33 GW in Victoria in two phases.", detailEn: "Near Rokewood in Victoria, 1.33 GW in two phases — the Southern Hemisphere's largest onshore wind farm under construction. Phase 1 (756 MW, 122 turbines) came online from Q1 2025; phase 2 (577 MW) reached financial close (with CEFC) and started in 2025, targeting mid-2027 with 150 MW/600 MWh of storage." },
  2702: { descEn: "A 960 MW German North Sea offshore wind farm, built subsidy-free.", detailEn: "In the German North Sea, EnBW's He Dreiht is 960 MW with 64 Siemens Gamesa 15 MW turbines — among Europe's first large subsidy-free offshore wind farms, doubling EnBW's offshore capacity to nearly 2 GW. 23 turbines were installed by October 2025, targeting full operation in spring 2026." },
  3410: { descEn: "CNOOC's first large offshore wind, 1.5 GW off western Dongfang, Hainan.", detailEn: "West of Dongfang in Hainan, 1.5 GW in two phases — CZ7-1 (~29 km offshore, 600 MW) and CZ7-2 (~38 km, 900 MW) — at ~18.2 billion yuan for ~4.88 TWh a year, self-developed by a CNOOC-Mingyang JV." },
  4256: { descEn: "Rebuilding Argentina's 1,813 km San Martín freight line, restoring service and upgrades.", detailEn: "China Railway Construction signed ~$2.6 billion to overhaul Argentina's San Martín freight line, ~1,813 km from Buenos Aires to the Cuyo/northwest farm belt — rail replacement, subgrade and signalling upgrades to restore full freight service. Part of Argentina's rail-modernisation plan, it aims to greatly boost bulk farm and mineral export and cut logistics costs." },
  1988: { descEn: "A 600 MW pumped-hydro plant in Rizal, 6,000 MWh daily storage.", detailEn: "Developed by Enrique Razon's Prime Infra in Rizal, the Philippines, 600 MW with 6,000 MWh of daily storage at ~$2.57 billion, listed as a national energy project; with the 1,400 MW Pakil project it forms a ~2 GW portfolio targeting December 2030." },
  2051: { descEn: "A regional express linking central Hanoi with the Hoa Lac tech park.", detailEn: "Nearly 39 km (6.5 km underground, 2 km elevated, ~30 km surface) from Van Cao in Ba Dinh to the Hoa Lac Hi-Tech Park in Thach That with 21 stations (6 underground), over 65 trillion dong; ground was broken on 19 December 2025 — a westward backbone of Hanoi's long-term rail plan." },
  1441: { descEn: "One of the world's most efficient Dead Sea potash and bromine bases.", detailEn: "At Sodom in southwest Israel's Dead Sea, ICL's Dead Sea works makes ~3.8 million tonnes of potash and ~170,000 tonnes of bromine a year — among the world's most concentrated, efficient mineral extraction — with a captive power plant. In January 2026 ICL signed a binding deal with the Israeli government on a ~$2.54 billion base price for transferring Dead Sea assets before the 2030 concession expiry." },
  1620: { descEn: "An EPC for Iraq's national seawater-supply backbone pipeline, a mega-contract.", detailEn: "CNPC's China Petroleum Pipeline Bureau signed a $2.524 billion (~18 billion yuan) EPC with Basra Oil for a seawater pipeline, 950 km total, initially 5 million b/d (later 7-8 million), prioritising water injection for the Rumaila, Zubair and West Qurna fields; with a Hyundai E&C seawater plant it covers over 80% of southern Iraq's crude production, over 54 months." },
  194: { descEn: "Exporting Ladakh's 13 GW solar base to Haryana.", detailEn: "713 km (480 km HVDC) linking Pang in Ladakh (4,700 m) with Kaithal in Haryana using ±350 kV VSC technology; India's cabinet approved funding, targeting 2031 — India's highest-altitude, most challenging HVDC." },
  196: { descEn: "A key National Electricity Market interconnector expansion.", detailEn: "Linking Dinawan in NSW with new substations at Kerang and Bulgana in Victoria, 240 km of 500 kV double-circuit line for 3.5 GW of bidirectional transfer; Iberdrola won the Victorian section in November 2025, targeting an H2 2026 start and 2030 completion." },
  271: { descEn: "Home to western China's largest Tencent AI-compute centre.", detailEn: "Zhongwei in Ningxia, using 'zero-carbon' green power, hosts western China's largest Tencent AI-compute centre with 88,000 GPUs; ZeroStone Data plans ~50 billion yuan and a CICC zero-carbon compute base of 2,050 MW IT, making it a national compute hub." },
  603: { descEn: "A 500 MW AI factory in Morocco by Korea's Naver and Nvidia.", detailEn: "In June 2025 Naver Cloud, Nvidia, Nexus Core Systems and Lloyds Capital announced a 500 MW AI factory at Tamesna near Rabat, Morocco, with a 40 MW first phase using GB200 due Q4 2025, powered by TAQA renewables, for the EMEA market." },
  607: { descEn: "OpenAI and Sur Energy plan a 500 MW AI data centre in Patagonia.", detailEn: "In October 2025 OpenAI and Argentina's Sur Energy signed an LOI for a 500 MW AI data centre in southern Patagonia (named Stargate Argentina), ~$25 billion total, with a 100 MW first phase in 2027 running zero-carbon on Patagonian wind." },
  758: { descEn: "Cross-border Saudi green power exported to Bahrain, signed December 2025.", detailEn: "In December 2025 Saudi Arabia's ACWA Power and Bahrain's Bapco Energies signed a joint-development deal to build 2.8 GW of solar with large storage in Saudi Arabia's Eastern Province, exporting all the green power to Bahrain via the Saudi-Bahrain interconnection — making Saudi Arabia a cross-border clean-energy export hub." },
  1038: { descEn: "Germany's green-steel flagship phase 1, hydrogen-based DRI plus arc furnace.", detailEn: "SALCOS phase 1 at the Salzgitter Flachstahl plant builds a 100 MW electrolyser, a 2-million-tonne-plus hydrogen-based DRI plant and an arc furnace to replace blast-furnace ironmaking with green hydrogen, ~€2.3 billion (with ~€1 billion of German federal and Lower Saxony subsidy). Ground was broken in February 2025 for one of Europe's largest green-hydrogen plants (~9,000 tonnes a year from 2026), with phase 1 due in 2027." },
  1048: { descEn: "North America's first ingot-to-module fully integrated solar plant.", detailEn: "At Cartersville, Georgia, online April 2025 at 3.3 GW a year, this is the only plant in North America doing ingots, wafers, cells and modules in one site and the largest US ingot-and-wafer plant, with a ~$1.45 billion DOE loan guarantee; ingot pulling is a continuous high-power process, a major grid load." },
  1295: { descEn: "Búzios's eighth production system, online ahead of plan.", detailEn: "A Seatrium-built P-series FPSO at the Búzios pre-salt field in the Santos Basin; first oil in H1 2026, ahead of Petrobras's 2026-2030 plan. Búzios will host 12 FPSOs in total, with P-79 a key unit for accelerating toward a million barrels a day." },
  1296: { descEn: "A high-capacity Seatrium FPSO, a Búzios follow-on unit.", detailEn: "P-80 is one of six Seatrium-built P-series FPSOs, 225,000 b/d, at the ultra-deepwater Búzios field in the Santos Basin (over 2,000 m of water). Advancing with P-82 and P-83, it targets 2027, pushing Búzios toward 12 FPSOs and a million-barrel scale." },
  1369: { descEn: "A round-the-clock 2.7 GW wind-solar-storage scheme in Oman.", detailEn: "Oman's O-Green Energy (a JV of state Naqaa Sustainable Energy and OQ Alternative Energy) signed a 2.7 GW integrated wind-solar-storage PPA with Nama Power Procurement in May 2026, at Mahmout and Duqm, integrating solar, wind and batteries for round-the-clock power, targeting commercial operation in summer 2028." },
  1543: { descEn: "Eastern Siberia's first ethane-fed polymer plant.", detailEn: "INK's Irkutsk polymer plant at Ust-Kut is its largest project and eastern Siberia's first to use its own ethane, making 650,000 tonnes each of ethylene and polyethylene a year, EPC by Toyo Engineering with McDermott supplying the cracker; it produced first trial polyethylene pellets from purchased feed in December 2024." },
  1719: { descEn: "A new Brazilian offshore frontier, deepwater drilling in the Foz do Amazonas and Potiguar basins.", detailEn: "The Equatorial Margin is seen as Brazil's new offshore frontier, with ANP estimating over 30 billion barrels recoverable. Petrobras's 2026-2030 plan invests ~$2.5 billion in 15 wells (8 in the Foz do Amazonas basin); in February 2026 ANP approved re-drilling the FZA-M-59 pilot well and committed to more Potiguar deepwater drilling — core to the company's reserve replacement." },
  1726: { descEn: "Phases 3-4 of the Açu LNG-to-power hub.", detailEn: "Açu's GNA (a Prumo/BP/Siemens Energy/SPIC Brasil JV) is Latin America's largest combined gas-power and LNG-import project, with GNA I (2021) and GNA II (May 2025) running. GNA III/IV have environmental permits totalling ~3.4 GW, bringing combined capacity to 6.4 GW; they will bid in the 2026 capacity auction (LRCap) and study a second FSRU." },
  1782: { descEn: "Line 2 (Green) extended east via Penha to Guarulhos Dutra.", detailEn: "Line 2 (Green) extends from Vila Prudente via Penha to Guarulhos Dutra, ~13.4 billion reais total, becoming the system's longest line. Phase 1 (to Penha) is ~55% done, opening in segments in 2027-2028; the phase-2 Guarulhos section (5.8 km, 5 stations) has a Chinese dual-mode TBM arriving at Penha in 2026 with boring expected by end-2026." },
  1794: { descEn: "A giant Amazon potash mine to cut Brazil's import reliance.", detailEn: "At Autazes on the Madeira River in Amazonas in the Amazon potash basin, designed for ~2.4 million tonnes/year of potassium chloride over a ~23-year life, ~$2.5 billion. In 2026 it moved from late development to early construction, awarding FEED for the plant, tailings, barge terminal and a ~13 km road to a Wood-Promon consortium, targeting ~2028 to largely replace Brazilian potash imports." },
  1925: { descEn: "Saudi Manara holds 10% of Vale Base Metals.", detailEn: "Manara bought 10% of Vale Base Metals (VBM, UK-headquartered, with assets including Brazil's Salobo copper mine and Canadian and Indonesian nickel) for ~$2.5 billion, closing in April 2024 to lock in energy-transition-metal exposure. VBM plans $25-30 billion over a decade to grow copper from ~350,000 to 900,000 tonnes a year and nickel above 300,000 (a Saudi entity's overseas asset, shown at the flagship Salobo mine)." },
  2059: { descEn: "A cross-strait rapid transit linking Johor Bahru and Singapore.", detailEn: "Linking Bukit Chagar in Johor Bahru with Woodlands North in Singapore across the Johor Strait, a few-minute trip designed for ~10,000 passengers/hour each way to relieve the world's busiest land crossing. Line testing began in November 2025, with works due in late 2026 and operation in early 2027, run by a binational JV." },
  2085: { descEn: "Indonesia's second-largest copper-gold mine with a new smelter.", detailEn: "The Batu Hijau mine entered its 8th phase, extending mine life to 2030 (tailings to 2033). A new ~$1.1 billion copper smelter reached full capacity in H1 2025, processing 900,000 tonnes of concentrate for 220,000 tonnes of cathode copper, with the mill expanded from 40 to 85 Mtpa and the giant Elang copper-gold mine to follow to 2046." },
  2301: { descEn: "Two 38-inch gas pipelines from offshore Bonny to the Lekki Dangote complex.", detailEn: "Dangote's offshore gathering system comprises two ~550 km, 38-inch pipelines from offshore Bonny Island to the Lekki industrial complex, interconnecting six platforms, each carrying 1.5 bcf/d (3 bcf/d total) to supply the refinery and fertiliser plant." },
  2602: { descEn: "A 1.3 GW wind farm in central-west NSW, powering 730,000 homes.", detailEn: "About 130 km east of Coolah in central-west NSW, a 2025 NSW approval raised max capacity to 1.3 GW, enough for ~730,000 homes — one of NSW's largest approved onshore wind projects, feeding the New England REZ export corridor." },
  2658: { descEn: "A Browse Basin gas field supplying the Prelude FLNG.", detailEn: "In the northern Browse Basin off WA, Shell-led Crux won approval for new drilling and facilities in 2024 to provide key backfill for the Prelude floating LNG, extending its full-capacity life, targeting gas around 2027." },
  2672: { descEn: "One of the Pilbara's largest undeveloped iron ore deposits.", detailEn: "In the Pilbara of WA, Rhodes Ridge is one of the world's largest, highest-grade undeveloped iron-ore deposits; the JV approved ~$191 million of feasibility work in 2025 for a phase-1 development of huge capacity, targeting first ore in the early 2030s — a core growth pole of Rio Tinto's iron-ore capacity." },
  2738: { descEn: "Nvidia and partners building large-scale UK AI compute.", detailEn: "Nvidia announced £2 billion in the UK AI market, partnering with Nscale, CoreWeave, Microsoft and others to build next-generation UK AI infrastructure (Blackwell GPU clusters), supporting sovereign and generative-AI compute, landing in phases over 2025-2027." },
  2822: { descEn: "India launches a $2.5 billion small-modular-reactor R&D mission.", detailEn: "India's FY2025-26 budget formally launched a 'Developed India Nuclear Mission', allocating ~200 billion rupees (~$2.5 billion) for SMR R&D, targeting five indigenous SMRs by 2033 to greatly expand nuclear capacity and open the sector to private capital." },
  2824: { descEn: "The world's first lead-cooled fast reactor, a closed-fuel-cycle demonstration.", detailEn: "At Seversk in Siberia, Russia, Rosatom's BREST-OD-300 is the world's first industrial-demonstration lead-cooled fast reactor (300 MW), with on-site mixed-oxide fuel fabrication and reprocessing for a closed fuel cycle (the 'Proryv' project), at the Gen-IV frontier, targeting around 2027." },
  3009: { descEn: "HIVE plans a ~C$3.5 billion AI gigafactory near Toronto.", detailEn: "HIVE Digital Technologies announced a ~C$3.5 billion AI gigafactory near Toronto, potentially one of Canada's largest AI data centres — a flagship of the country's sovereign-AI compute wave." },
  3031: { descEn: "A new three-berth container terminal at Vancouver port, +2.4 million TEU/year.", detailEn: "About C$3.5 billion, Roberts Bank Terminal 2 won federal approval in April 2024 (with 370 environmental conditions); procurement launched in summer 2025 and three consortia were shortlisted in November, using progressive design-build to add 2.4 million TEU a year (over 30% more Vancouver container capacity), starting in 2028." },
  3113: { descEn: "India's largest green-ammonia project at Gopalpur, Odisha, 1.3 million tonnes, with IHI 30%.", detailEn: "At the Tata Steel SEZ in Gopalpur, Odisha, ACME with Japan's IHI plans 1.3 million tonnes/year of renewable ammonia (IHI 30%, ACME 70%); land is secured and FEED done, with $2.5 billion from REC for the first phase." },
  3122: { descEn: "A 1,200 MW Punatsangchhu hydro plant in Bhutan, India-financed.", detailEn: "On the Punatsangchhu River in Bhutan, 1,200 MW, a Bhutan-India project with Indian credit; its sister Punatsangchhu II (1,020 MW) fully started in August 2025, with India also announcing 40 billion rupees of concessional credit for Bhutanese energy." },
  3523: { descEn: "A Shanshan coal-power-silicon integrated base in Xinjiang, 200,000 tonnes of polysilicon plus 20 GW modules.", detailEn: "Hoshine Silicon's eastern Shanshan project is ~17.6 billion yuan for 200,000 tonnes of polysilicon, 20 GW of solar modules and 1.5 million tonnes of ultra-thin solar glass, using Xinjiang's coal-power-silicon closed-loop cost edge; its metallurgical-silicon capacity leads the industry." },
  4023: { descEn: "A Norinco-RPCL 1,320 MW ultra-supercritical coal plant at Payra, over $2.5 billion.", detailEn: "Norinco and Bangladesh's RPCL formed a 50:50 JV, RNPL, to build a 1,320 MW (2×660 MW) ultra-supercritical coal plant at Patuakhali in the Payra port area, on the Rabnabad River, over $2.5 billion, with China Exim Bank and Bank of China leading the syndicate. Started in August 2019, with units progressively online." },
  4144: { descEn: "Envision supplies 1.67 GW of turbines to the world's largest green-hydrogen project.", detailEn: "Envision supplies 1.67 GW of EN171-6.5MW turbines to Saudi Arabia's NEOM Green Hydrogen Company (NGHC) as an Air Products (EPC) subcontractor. The 3.9 GW green-hydrogen project at NEOM Oxagon will make 600 tonnes/day of carbon-neutral hydrogen (as green ammonia) from 2026, with all turbines online in 2026." },
  4173: { descEn: "Huaneng wholly owns Tuas Power, ~1/5 of Singapore's generation market.", detailEn: "Huaneng bought 100% of Tuas Power in 2008; at 2,670 MW (2×600 MW oil steam turbines and 4×367.6 MW gas combined-cycle units) it holds ~19.2% of Singapore's generation market, supplying about a quarter of demand, with ~18.7 billion yuan of Singapore revenue in 2025." },
  4187: { descEn: "GCL building an integrated gas-power-transport ecosystem on Ogaden Basin gas.", detailEn: "GCL is building an integrated gas, power, transport and sales ecosystem in Ethiopia using Ogaden Basin gas with LNG receiving and global channels; in 2026 it signed a 25-year gas-supply deal with the Dadot Group to supply an Ethiopian urea-fertiliser project." },
  4221: { descEn: "Kazakhstan's largest polyethylene project; an SEG-Técnicas Reunidas EPC consortium.", detailEn: "The Silleno petrochemical complex in Atyrau, Kazakhstan builds 1.25 million tonnes/year of polyethylene, owned by KazMunayGas, Sinopec and SIBUR. Sinopec Engineering (SEG) and Spain's Técnicas Reunidas (50/50) signed a ~$2.5 billion EPC over 2024-2025 for the polyethylene and utilities, led by Shanghai Engineering with Ningbo Engineering and Tecnimont." },
  4233: { descEn: "An Atyrau Silleno ethane cracker, with CNCEC handling piling/civil and the cracker EPC consortium.", detailEn: "The Silleno complex in Atyrau, Kazakhstan builds 1.25 million tonnes/year of polyethylene; CNCEC's 13th Construction Company won the ethane-cracker piling and civil works, and the group with Técnicas Reunidas (50/50) takes the ~$2.5 billion cracker EPC, deepening China-Kazakhstan cooperation." },
  4463: { descEn: "A CPEC flagship ±660 kV, 886 km DC link from Karachi to Lahore, Pakistan's first.", detailEn: "The Matiari-Lahore ±660 kV DC line, EPC-led by State Grid's CET, is a key CPEC energy project and Pakistan's first DC transmission line. It runs 886 km linking the southern Karachi and central Lahore load centres at ~4,000 MW rated, over 30 TWh a year, greatly improving grid stability and south-to-north transfer." },
  4520: { descEn: "GCL's $2.5 billion Gode refinery in Ethiopia, ~3.5 million tonnes/year.", detailEn: "A ~$2.5 billion refinery at Gode in Ethiopia's Somali region broke ground, built by GCL in two phases (phase 1 in 24 months) for ~3.5 million tonnes/year of crude at full capacity. Drawing on GCL's Ogaden Basin upstream, it forms a full upstream-pipeline-refining chain — a key downstream link of GCL's Ethiopia oil-and-gas project." },
  3604: { descEn: "A phase-2 expansion of China's largest copper mine, adding 200,000 t/day, like 1.3 more Julongs.", detailEn: "At Mozhugongka in Lhasa, Tibet, the ~17.46 billion-yuan phase 2 was structurally completed and linked for trial on 29 December 2025, adding 200,000 tonnes/day for 350,000 tonnes/day across phases 1-2, with phase 3 advancing in parallel." },
  153: { descEn: "Central Asia's largest onshore wind project under construction.", detailEn: "Three 500 MW wind farms with 300 MW of storage in Karakalpakstan, Uzbekistan, with ~1,450 km of new lines, developed by ACWA Power with AIIB financing; it would cut 2.5 million tonnes of CO₂ a year and power ~1.6 million households." },
  256: { descEn: "The world's largest single green-electrolytic-aluminium base.", detailEn: "In the green-aluminium park at Yanshan in Wenshan, Yunnan, designed for 2.03 million tonnes/year, with over 80% of power from Yunnan clean hydro for carbon intensity ~40% of the national average, featuring the world's first AI smart aluminium-electrolysis line." },
  748: { descEn: "Europe's largest solar cluster, built on a former lignite mine.", detailEn: "In the former lignite area of West Macedonia, Greece, PPC's cluster of 14 plants — including the 550 MW Phoebe and 940 MW Amyntaio (with RWE) — totals 2.13 GW for ~3.15 TWh a year (~6% of Greece's power), completing in April 2026 as Europe's largest single solar cluster." },
  760: { descEn: "Connected in 2024, once the world's largest single solar plant.", detailEn: "In the Gobi of Midong, Urumqi, Xinjiang, 5 GW connected in June 2024, a core second-batch desert-base project over ~130 km², with UHVDC export to central China and ~8 TWh a year; at start-up it was billed as the world's largest single solar plant." },
  794: { descEn: "A 1 GW deep-water offshore wind project off Yangjiang, Guangdong.", detailEn: "About 60 km south of Nanpeng Island off Yangjiang, 1,000 MW with 73 13.6-14 MW turbines, one of Guangdong's first scaled deep-water projects; it installed China's first offshore-wind reactive-compensation station in August 2025, targeting December 2026 to become one of the world's largest operating single offshore wind farms." },
});

/* ===== 批次13：全库投资额 TOP（约 20–24 亿美元）===== */
Object.assign(window.ENERGY_EN, {
  916: { descEn: "A northeast Songliao clean-energy base line to North China ('Jilin-into-Beijing').", detailEn: "From a sending end in Jilin or eastern Inner Mongolia to North China at 8 GW rated; feasibility tendering is done, a 15th-Five-Year priority northeast export project supporting over 36 TWh of green power a year from the northeast desert base." },
  985: { descEn: "A 500 kV backbone linking Snowy Mountains hydro with eastern NSW.", detailEn: "HumeLink runs ~360 km linking the Maragle, Snowy and Wagga Wagga substations in NSW at 500 kV AC; tower-foundation works began in early 2025, laying the key transmission for Snowy 2.0 pumped hydro's output." },
  1152: { descEn: "Mumbai's second airport, India's largest greenfield airport.", detailEn: "Built to relieve Mumbai's Chhatrapati Shivaji airport, Navi Mumbai International is an Adani PPP greenfield hub over ~1,160 hectares, with a single runway and terminal in phase 1. PM Modi unveiled it on 8 October 2025 and commercial operation began on 25 December with an IndiGo first flight; planned for 90 million passengers ultimately, with SAF storage and ~47 MW of solar, forming a twin-hub with the existing airport." },
  1293: { descEn: "A Búzios pre-salt FPSO setting a company single-unit output record.", detailEn: "An SBM-built, leased high-capacity FPSO started up at the Búzios pre-salt field in the Santos Basin on 15 February 2025 — the field's first high-capacity unit, connecting 15 wells. On 14 August 2025 it reached full 225,000 b/d, three months early, becoming Petrobras's highest single-unit output ever and helping push Búzios past a million b/d in H2." },
  1727: { descEn: "Pre-salt gas deep-processing for lube oils and resins at Itaboraí.", detailEn: "Petrobras is advancing phase 2 at the Itaboraí Boaventura complex (formerly GasLub/Comperj), ~13 billion reais for lube base oils, resins and other high-value derivatives. Phase-1 Rota 3 gas processing fully started in May 2025; phase 2 was tendered in 2024 and started in 2025, targeting 2028." },
  2510: { descEn: "A new critical-minerals railway from Zambia to Angola.", detailEn: "The Lobito Corridor's ~800 km new railway from Chingola in Zambia to Luacano in Angola is a flagship of the EU Global Gateway and US PGII, ~$6 billion total (the US pledging $4 billion), cutting copper-cobalt export time from 35 days to a week, targeting an early-2026 start." },
  2664: { descEn: "An inland NSW coal-seam gas project easing east-coast shortages.", detailEn: "Near Narrabri in NSW, Santos's coal-seam gas project plans ~200 TJ/day, enough for about half of NSW's gas demand, easing east-coast supply. After long approvals and community disputes, it advanced development approval and pipeline arrangements in 2025." },
  2990: { descEn: "Converting the Spring Hill plant to LFP storage cells, online Q2 2026.", detailEn: "GM-LG's Ultium JV is converting its Spring Hill, Tennessee plant to LFP cells; announced in July 2025 with ~$70 million to switch to storage LFP, it produces from Q2 2026 for LG's Vertech storage, using the existing ~$2.3 billion Ultium phase-2 capacity." },
  3469: { descEn: "Inner Mongolia's first desert-base export DC, started end-2025.", detailEn: "From the Dalad converter in Ordos, Inner Mongolia to the Xiongnan converter in Cangzhou, Hebei, ~699 km at ±800 kV and 8 GW, exporting 12 GW of Kubuqi Desert wind and solar to North China. Approved in June 2025 and started on 30 December, it gives Inner Mongolia a four-AC, four-DC export pattern." },
  4409: { descEn: "COOEC won Aramco's CRPO 149 and 152 offshore EPCI lots, lifting its Aramco total to $5 billion.", detailEn: "In November 2024 Aramco awarded three offshore EPCI contracts at once; COOEC won CRPO 149 and 152, building jackets, production decks, subsea pipelines and cables for the Abu Safah and Arabiyah-Hasbah fields, ~$230-330 million combined, lifting its cumulative Aramco awards to $5 billion." },
  1955: { descEn: "A large run-of-river hydro plant on the Mekong mainstream in Laos.", detailEn: "On the Mekong mainstream in Oudomxay, northern Laos, ~92 km from the Thai border, this run-of-river plant is 912 MW with ~4.775 TWh a year, 51% China Datang Overseas / 49% Thailand's Gulf Energy, mostly selling to Thailand. A 29-year PPA with EGAT was signed in September 2025 with a 2033 target — a key lower-Mekong cascade project, with cross-border ecological and resettlement disputes." },
  182: { descEn: "An Ordos desert wind-solar base export line to Beijing-Tianjin-Hebei.", detailEn: "From Dalad in Ordos, Inner Mongolia to Xiongnan in Cangzhou, Hebei, ~700 km, started on 30 December 2025 for 2027 completion, using a 'double-800' hybrid DC to deliver ~36 TWh of renewables a year to Beijing-Tianjin-Hebei." },
  2037: { descEn: "Thailand's largest AI data centre, a CP Group 77-billion-baht investment.", detailEn: "CP Group's True IDC is investing 77 billion baht (~$2.36 billion) in Thailand's first hyperscale AI data centre in the EEC, totalling 250 MW across Chonburi and Samut Prakan (223 MW). Fully modular, it is Thailand's first operator able to host advanced-GPU AI systems, BOI-approved, with the first phase targeting 2027." },
  393: { descEn: "Zambia's largest copper mine, developed by Gates- and Bezos-backed KoBold.", detailEn: "In Zambia's Copperbelt near the DRC border, KoBold Metals (80%) broke ground in May 2026 on a ~$2.3 billion mine with ore to 1,700 m depth, designed for over 300,000 tonnes of copper a year, targeting first production in the early 2030s." },
  873: { descEn: "A 500 MW AMEA Power green hydrogen-ammonia project in Egypt.", detailEn: "At Ain Sokhna in Egypt's Suez Canal Economic Zone, the UAE's AMEA Power plans ~$2.3 billion, with a 500 MW phase-1 electrolyser making 350,000 tonnes of green ammonia a year, fed by 550 MW of solar and 700 MW of wind, with FID targeted for Q4 2025 and start-up in 2028." },
  1052: { descEn: "A VW Scout-brand electric-off-roader gigafactory.", detailEn: "At Blythewood, South Carolina on 1,100 acres, ~$2.3 billion for 200,000 electric pickups/SUVs a year; the assembly plant topped out in 2025 with paint and body equipment arriving and a $300 million supplier park added in September. It pioneers an industrial heat-pump system (a US auto-plant first) — a highly electrified manufacturing load." },
  1133: { descEn: "A US-EU-backed copper-export corridor.", detailEn: "The US-EU-backed Lobito Corridor builds ~800 km of new railway connecting Angola's Benguela line with Zambia's network at Chingola and upgrades the ~1,300 km existing line from Lobito port to the DRC border. In 2025 the AFC signed concessions with Angola and Zambia; the consortium won $753 million of loans (US DFC $553 million, DBSA $200 million) for track, signalling and locomotives, with the extension due in 2029 and ~$3 billion of expected benefit." },
  2025: { descEn: "Malaysia's first Nvidia AI data centre, online November 2025.", detailEn: "YTL Power with Nvidia is investing ~$2.3 billion in AI compute at the 1,640-acre YTL Green Data Center park in Kulai, Johor (600 MW planned), powered by solar and the grid. The first GB200 NVL72 liquid-cooled AI data centre (YTL AI Cloud) went live in November 2025 with 300 MW built and commissioned, full within two years, focused on sovereign AI." },
  2904: { descEn: "An 875 MW Mojave Desert solar plus 3,287 MWh storage, once the world's largest.", detailEn: "Near Edwards Air Force Base in California's Mojave Desert, operated by Terra-Gen, 875 MWdc of solar plus 3,287 MWh of storage (1,300 MW interconnect); at full operation in January 2024 it was the world's largest solar-storage facility, providing peaking for California's grid." },
  2906: { descEn: "A 700 MW Nevada solar plus 2,800 MWh storage, the state's largest.", detailEn: "Developed by Arevia Power, 700 MWac of solar plus 700 MW/2,800 MWh of storage with an NV Energy PPA, ~$2.3 billion — Nevada's largest solar-storage after the 690 MW Gemini, targeting commercial operation by end-2027." },
  2952: { descEn: "A 525 kV underground DC backbone delivering 3,000 MW to the Loudoun data-centre corridor.", detailEn: "Dominion plans a ~$2.3 billion 525 kV underground DC backbone with converter stations at both ends (~$1.5 billion) delivering 3,000 MW to Loudoun County, Virginia — the world's densest data-centre area — targeting operation by June 2032." },
  3148: { descEn: "Evacuating 7 GW of renewables from Khavda, Gujarat, awarded across five TBCB lots.", detailEn: "In eight segments (five TBCB, three RTM), this builds 765/400/220 kV substations south of Olpad and 765 kV/400 kV double-circuit lines. Sterlite won lot C, Adani lots A/D and POWERGRID lots B/E2, all awarded in FY2025, well over 190 billion rupees total." },
  3184: { descEn: "A 3,000 MW/18 GWh Raigad pumped hydro, billed as India's largest.", detailEn: "Torrent Power commissioned L&T to build the 3,000 MW/18,000 MWh Saidongar phase-1 pumped hydro in Raigad, Maharashtra, with 6 hours of daily discharge — billed as India's largest pumped hydro, needing new upper and lower reservoirs to support grid reliability and renewable integration." },
  3206: { descEn: "Hindalco adds 360,000 tonnes of aluminium at the Aditya plant in Sambalpur, Odisha, ~210 billion rupees.", detailEn: "Hindalco plans ~210 billion rupees to add 360,000 tonnes/year of aluminium at the Aditya park in Lapanga, Sambalpur, Odisha (existing 360,000 tonnes), plus a 170,000-tonne flat-rolled and battery-grade foil plant; Odisha aluminium up- and downstream totals ~370 billion rupees, adding 15,000+ jobs." },
  3402: { descEn: "A 4 GW Ruoqiang solar plant on the east Taklamakan, full capacity May 2025, a single-plant record.", detailEn: "At Ruoqiang in Bayingol, Xinjiang on the eastern Taklamakan, 4 GW using large-scale heterojunction modules, a supporting source for the fourth west-to-east power corridor; fully grid-connected on 29 May 2025, adding ~1.38 TWh a year." },
  4122: { descEn: "TBEA won a Saudi Electricity Company EHV/HV transformer-and-reactor localisation framework, ~16.4 billion yuan.", detailEn: "On 28 August 2025 TBEA became one of the winners of SEC's localisation framework for EHV and HV transformers and reactors, ~16.4 billion yuan over a 7-year term, requiring a local Saudi factory (to start 2027-2028) to supply most equipment." },
  4413: { descEn: "COOEC builds topside modules for Petrobras's pre-salt P-series FPSOs, with a giant float sailing for Brazil in 2025.", detailEn: "Petrobras deploys P-78/79/80/82/83 P-series FPSOs at the Búzios and other pre-salt fields (~180,000 b/d each); COOEC builds related topside modules, with a giant Chinese-built float sailing for Brazil in July 2025 — a $2.3 billion milestone — and COOEC International funded to deepen Brazilian localisation." },
  803: { descEn: "A 1 GW offshore wind project off Sheyang, Yancheng, Jiangsu.", detailEn: "Southeast off the Sheyang river mouth in Yancheng, a Longyuan-China Energy Jiangsu JV plans 126 turbines (1,000 MW), a 2025 Jiangsu major project built in 2026-2027, set to be one of China's largest single offshore wind farms with ~2.8 TWh a year." },
  825: { descEn: "China's largest tunnel-diversion hydro plant.", detailEn: "On the Dadu River at Luding in Garze, Sichuan, 1.116 GW using twin diversion tunnels (~14.4 km each) to raise the head from 26 m to 116 m; the first unit started in December 2024 and full operation came in August 2025 with over 5.18 TWh a year, enough for 2.15 million homes." },
  958: { descEn: "A 2 GW German North Sea offshore DC connection backbone.", detailEn: "BalWin1 is 2 GW at ±525 kV, with an onshore converter station at Wehrendorf — an Amprion Offshore North Sea wind-export backbone. Main converter-platform and cable contracts were signed in early 2025, built in parallel with BalWin2, targeting around 2030." },
  1015: { descEn: "VW's first unified-cell plant in Europe, in production December 2025.", detailEn: "VW's PowerCo plant at Salzgitter, Germany is its first European cell plant and the template for its Valencia and St. Thomas plants; phase 1 is 20 GWh (expandable to 40 GWh) making VW's 'unified cell' on renewable power. The first European unified cells rolled off as planned in mid-December 2025, ramping through 2026." },
  1806: { descEn: "Toyota's second São Paulo plant at Sorocaba, online November 2026.", detailEn: "Toyota is investing 11 billion reais (~$2.2 billion) in Brazil by 2030 to expand and shift to flex hybrids; its second plant at Sorocaba in São Paulo, ~160,000 m², starts in November 2026, making the Corolla, Yaris Cross and Corolla Cross with flex-hybrid lines, adding ~2,000 jobs." },
  2021: { descEn: "Microsoft's largest Malaysian investment, a new Johor SEA3 cloud region.", detailEn: "Microsoft is investing $2.2 billion in three hyperscale data centres in Greater KL and Johor; it opened Malaysia's first cloud region in Q2 2025 and in November 2025 disclosed a second region, Southeast Asia 3, at Nusa Cemerlang Industrial Park in Johor, with 100+ acres bought in Kulai and Tebrau, using biofuel backup and closed-loop chip-level zero-water cooling, expected to drive over $37 billion of revenue by 2028." },
  2074: { descEn: "Northern Vietnam's first LNG-to-power plant, at Cam Pha.", detailEn: "The Quang Ninh LNG power project at Cam Pha covers 56 hectares (13.38 offshore) with a 1,500 MW plant, storage and a 2.4-million-tonne LNG jetty, owned 25% each by PV Power, Colavi, Tokyo Gas and Marubeni, ~$2-2.2 billion. It plans to install its first and second turbines in April and June 2027 with commercial operation in 2028 — northern Vietnam's first LNG plant." },
  2911: { descEn: "An 800,000-tonne/year clean-ammonia plant on the Texas Gulf coast, tied to 1 GW of transmission.", detailEn: "On the Texas Gulf coast, ~800,000 tonnes/year of clean ammonia mixing blue and electrolytic hydrogen, $2.2 billion capex; it has completed FEED and secured ~1 GW of transmission — the first large clean-ammonia facility in the US to finish FEED." },
  2991: { descEn: "A low-carbon recycled-aluminium flat-rolled mill in Columbus, Mississippi, ramping from 2025.", detailEn: "Steel Dynamics is investing ~$2.2 billion in a 650,000-tonne/year low-carbon recycled-aluminium flat-rolled mill in Columbus, Mississippi, with two satellite slab centres (US Southwest and Mexico); first cast succeeded in 2025 with can and automotive sheet, at ~40-50% utilisation by year-end." },
  3028: { descEn: "A $2.2 billion on-dock rail yard at Long Beach port, lifting on-dock capacity to 4.7 million TEU.", detailEn: "Expanding the existing Pier B rail yard from 82 to 171 acres with fuelling/maintenance and a classification yard raises on-dock volume from 1.5 to 4.7 million TEU. Started in 2024, due 2032, with a $283 million MARAD grant approved in May 2026 and ~$1.28 billion invested." },
  3283: { descEn: "ONGC raises its OPaL stake to 95.69%, bringing imported ethane to the Dahej dual-feed cracker.", detailEn: "The government approved ONGC injecting 1.84 trillion rupees to lift its OPaL stake to 95.69%; OPaL runs Southeast Asia's largest single dual-feed cracker at Dahej (1.1 million tonnes of ethylene, 400,000 of propylene). In 2025 ONGC and Petronet signed for new ethane tanks to import ~800,000 tonnes/year of US ethane as cracker feed from 2028." },
  3441: { descEn: "The world's first fusion-fission hybrid demonstration, in Nanchang, targeting power by 2030.", detailEn: "Built by Jiangxi Fusion New Energy at the Yaohu Science Island in Nanchang, based on a high-temperature-superconducting compact tokamak, with >40 MW equivalent fusion power and 300 MW total, achieving 100 MW-class hybrid grid power; the EIA is by the Nuclear Power Institute of China." },
  4129: { descEn: "The world's largest grid-scale battery storage, across three Saudi sites.", detailEn: "In July 2025 Sungrow and Saudi Arabia's Algihaz signed a 7.8 GWh storage deal across three 2.6 GWh projects at Najran, Madaya and Khamis Mushait, deploying 1,500+ PowerTitan 2.0 liquid-cooled systems. Fully grid-connected in December 2025, it became the world's largest operating storage system at ~2.2 billion kWh of cycling a year." },
  4352: { descEn: "CGN's Abu Dhabi Taweelah B gas combined-cycle plant with desalination, 2,000 MW, via Malaysia's Edra.", detailEn: "CGN bought Malaysia's Edra Power for ~$2.3 billion in 2016; its Taweelah B plant in Abu Dhabi's Taweelah zone is a gas combined-cycle (CCGT) power-and-desalination plant of ~2,000 MW — one of CGN's largest overseas conventional power assets, steadily supplying the UAE grid and water system." },
  4407: { descEn: "SEG's Jafurah phase-3 gas processing for Aramco, signed 2024, over 20% done.", detailEn: "Jafurah is Aramco's flagship unconventional (shale) gas field in Saudi Arabia's Eastern Province. Sinopec Engineering (SEG) took the Jafurah phase-3 gas-processing project, signing in June 2024 and running design, procurement and construction in parallel at over 20% progress — core support for Saudi gas-output growth, after SEG's phase-2 contract." },
  3124: { descEn: "An 800 MW concrete-face rockfill dam on the Swat River, online 2026.", detailEn: "A multipurpose concrete-face rockfill dam on the Swat River in Mohmand, KP ~37 km north of Peshawar, with four 200 MW units (800 MW) and ~2.862 TWh a year, ~309 billion rupees, co-financed by IsDB/OPEC/Kuwait/Saudi funds with Voith turbines." },
  3065: { descEn: "An Arizona critical-minerals mine, the only advanced US project producing both zinc and manganese.", detailEn: "South32's Patagonia-mountains Hermosa project in Arizona has the Taylor zinc-lead-silver and Clark zinc-manganese-silver deposits — the first mine in FAST-41. The board approved $2.16 billion for Taylor (~114,000 tonnes of zinc a year over ~28 years), with a manganese plant winning $166 million of federal funding." },
  2048: { descEn: "A new 4F international airport in Phnom Penh, open September 2025.", detailEn: "About 20 km south of Phnom Penh in Kandal, designed by Foster + Partners and built by a Chinese state firm with three runways, cost up to over $2.15 billion. Commercial operation began on 9 September 2025 and it formally opened on 20 October, with 13 million passengers a year in phase 1 (30 million phase 2, 50 million ultimately), replacing the old Pochentong airport." },
  4037: { descEn: "A cross-border section of Tanzania's Central Line SGR, from Dar es Salaam port to Burundi's nickel.", detailEn: "A China Railway-led consortium signed lots 7 and 8 of Tanzania's Central Line standard-gauge railway, ~$2.154 billion. Lot 7 runs ~156 km Uvinza-Malagarasi and lot 8 ~84 km Malagarasi-Musongati (Burundi) over 72 months, forming a corridor from Dar es Salaam port to Burundi's nickel zone — a major African standard-gauge breakthrough." },
  4343: { descEn: "A €2 billion Envision AESC battery gigafactory at Douai, France, for the Renault 5.", detailEn: "Envision AESC is building a battery gigafactory at Douai in Hauts-de-France, ~€2 billion, planning 2,500 jobs by 2030; its first line started in August 2024 and it has supplied batteries for the electric Renault 5 since March 2025 — a core part of France's EV battery chain." },
  1660: { descEn: "A world-class CMOC copper-cobalt mine; the 10K mixed-ore project at full capacity.", detailEn: "At Tenke Fungurume in the Katanga copper-cobalt belt, CMOC's core DRC asset has over 450,000 tonnes/year of copper. The 10K mixed-ore project (initial $2.124 billion) added 12.4 million tonnes/year of ore for ~200,000 tonnes of copper and 17,000 of cobalt, at full capacity in 2025; CMOC's 2025 DRC output reached 741,100 tonnes of copper and 117,500 of cobalt — world #1 in cobalt." },
  258: { descEn: "A core base of the world's fourth-largest polysilicon maker.", detailEn: "In the rare-earth hi-tech zone of Baotou, Inner Mongolia, phase 2 adds 100,000 tonnes of high-purity polysilicon, completed by end-2024, lifting company capacity to 305,000 tonnes/year." },
  949: { descEn: "The former EuroAsia interconnector, stalled in 2025 over funding disputes.", detailEn: "The Great Sea Interconnector would link the Greek, Cypriot and Israeli grids — 898 km Greece-Cyprus, ~1,208 km total — with €657 million of EU funding approved, but Greece suspended payments in March 2025 and Nexans withdrew its bid in December, leaving it severely stalled, with a renegotiation window pending." },
  1020: { descEn: "A CALB high-performance lithium-battery project in Xiamen, started February 2025.", detailEn: "On 5 February 2025 CALB's high-performance lithium-battery project started in Xiang'an, Xiamen, ~15 billion yuan and 30 GWh of new capacity, taking the Xiamen base toward ~60 GWh. Among the world's leading battery makers (bases in Changzhou, Luoyang, Xiamen, Chengdu), CALB targets 500+ GWh by end-2025 — a big new South China grid load." },
  1235: { descEn: "The world's largest second-generation ethanol, expanding 5+ plants to supply Shell.", detailEn: "Raízen's 11.5 billion-reais second-generation cellulosic-ethanol and biomethane expansion makes 82 million litres a plant a year, with a 2G carbon footprint 85% below petrol. It signed a long-term deal to supply Shell with 3.3 billion litres, with five new plants from 2025-2027 and a long-term goal of 1.6 billion litres a year for SAF, green hydrogen and marine fuel." },
  1303: { descEn: "Restarting the RNEST line 2 in Pernambuco, adding S-10 diesel capacity.", detailEn: "In 2025 Petrobras signed all contracts and restarted the second line of the RNEST refinery at Ipojuca, in its 2025-2029 plan, over 8.3 billion reais. About 12 billion reais finishes line 2 and overhauls line 1, adding 130,000 b/d to reach 260,000 b/d for the whole plant by 2029, mainly S-10 diesel plus petrol, LPG and naphtha, with ~15,000 jobs." },
  1381: { descEn: "Saudi Arabia's largest mono-silicon ingot-and-wafer plant.", detailEn: "TCL Zhonghuan's Singapore arm Lumetech and PIF's RELC and Vision Industries (40:40:20) are building a 20 GW solar ingot-and-wafer plant in Saudi Arabia, ~$2.08 billion, completing the upstream of Saudi solar." },
  1884: { descEn: "A three-availability-zone hyperscale Azure region in Saudi Arabia's Eastern Province.", detailEn: "Announced in February 2023 in the Eastern Province with three independent availability zones, site civil works finished in December 2024; in February 2026 Microsoft confirmed opening to customers in Q4 2026, ~$2.1 billion, supporting Vision 2030 sovereign cloud." },
  1967: { descEn: "A core project of the Sarawak green-hydrogen hub.", detailEn: "At Bintulu in Sarawak, Malaysia, developed by SEDC Energy with Japan's ENEOS and Sumitomo, this is a core of the Sarawak hydrogen hub using abundant local hydropower for green hydrogen. With Korea's Samsung E&A's H2biscus it can make ~240,000 tonnes a year, with ~$4.2 billion of Sarawak green-hydrogen cooperation; on rising costs, H2ornbill scaled to ~50,000 tonnes a year in October 2025, with phase 1 targeting 2028." },
  2618: { descEn: "Transmission for NSW's first renewable energy zone.", detailEn: "The high-voltage network for NSW's first renewable energy zone, Central-West Orana, is ~240 km of 500 kV line and substations connecting ~4.5 GW of wind, solar and storage; designed, built and operated by the ACEREZ consortium, with works from 2025 and completion targeted for 2028 — a backbone of NSW's energy roadmap." },
  4274: { descEn: "The Hungarian section of the Budapest-Belgrade railway, built by a China Railway JV.", detailEn: "The Hungarian section of the Budapest-Belgrade railway is a key China-Europe rail link, built by a China Railway-led China-Hungary JV, ~158.6 km from Budapest to the Serbia-Hungary border — double-track electrified, 160 km/h, mixed passenger-freight. Started in 2022 and fully in track-laying from November 2024, it targets 2025-2026 to join the operating Belgrade-Novi Sad section into the Budapest-Belgrade high-speed railway." },
  4200: { descEn: "Huayou's HPAL nickel project at the IWIP Weda Bay park, 120,000 t/year nickel.", detailEn: "At the IWIP Weda Bay park on Halmahera, Indonesia, this makes 120,000 tonnes/year of nickel-in-MHP; trial production began in June 2023 and full capacity by end-Q1 2024, steadily exceeding capacity — a core hydrometallurgical project of Huayou's integrated Indonesian nickel chain." },
  4064: { descEn: "China's largest overseas nickel-cobalt mine, a laterite HPAL benchmark.", detailEn: "In Madang, PNG, this world-class integrated laterite nickel-cobalt project has ~186 million tonnes of proven nickel ore, making ~32,600 tonnes of nickel and ~3,335 tonnes of cobalt a year in intermediates. At $2.041 billion, it is China's largest overseas nickel-cobalt investment and the largest in the South Pacific, with MCC and ENFI advancing a phase-2 mine expansion and upgrade." },
  340: { descEn: "A 100-billion-yuan refining-petrochemical complex at Longkou, Yantai, phase 1 online 2025.", detailEn: "On Yulong Island in Longkou, Yantai, Shandong, with approved total investment of 149.3 billion yuan, this is one of China's largest refining-petrochemical complexes under construction; phase 1 (20 million tonnes of refining and two 1.5-million-tonne ethylene units) started up through 2025, driving Shandong's teapot-refinery consolidation." },
  155: { descEn: "Saudi Arabia's largest solar plant to date.", detailEn: "About 80 km south of Jeddah in Mecca province, 2.06 GW (AC), held by ACWA Power, Badeel and Aramco's SAPCO; with the 600 MW phase 1 it totals 2.6 GW, commercial from February 2025 powering ~350,000 homes — a Vision 2030 milestone." },
  159: { descEn: "A landmark of Morocco's shift from CSP to solar-plus-storage.", detailEn: "Two 400 MW solar plants with 602 MWh of battery storage, tendered by Morocco's renewable agency and won by ACWA Power in August 2025 on a 30-year BOO — marking Morocco's shift from CSP to solar-plus-storage, cutting ~1.2 million tonnes of CO₂." },
  226: { descEn: "The most important FERC-licensed pumped hydro in the US in 20 years.", detailEn: "In the Columbia River Gorge of Washington State, this closed-loop pumped-hydro project won a 40-year FERC licence in January 2026, targeting a 2027 start and 2032 operation to absorb abundant Pacific Northwest wind and solar." },
  257: { descEn: "A large integrated polysilicon and metallurgical-silicon base.", detailEn: "At Ordos, Inner Mongolia, using cheap coal power and renewables, phase 1 makes 200,000 tonnes each of metallurgical and poly silicon a year, targeting end-2025 to cement Tongwei's global polysilicon lead." },
  380: { descEn: "The world's highest-altitude largest copper mine, phase 2 online January 2026.", detailEn: "In Nagqu, Tibet, this world-class supergiant copper mine, controlled by Zijin, brought phase 2 online in January 2026, raising mining-and-milling from 150,000 to 350,000 tonnes/day for 105 million tonnes of ore and up to 350,000 tonnes of copper a year, cementing Zijin's global copper lead." },
  387: { descEn: "The world's largest platinum-group-metals underground mine.", detailEn: "In Limpopo, South Africa, developed by Ivanhoe Mines, phase 1 is ~$2 billion; the Platreef concentrator first took ore in October-November 2025 producing platinum, palladium, nickel, rhodium, gold and copper concentrate, with phase 2 targeting over 460,000 ounces of 3PE+gold a year after 2027, reshaping global PGM supply." },
  503: { descEn: "Georgia's AI super-factory second site, online November 2025.", detailEn: "Fairwater 2 on a 615-acre campus in Fayette County south of Atlanta entered service in November 2025, using closed-loop liquid cooling without UPS or diesel, networked with Wisconsin's Fairwater 1 via dedicated backbone fibre into a distributed AI super-factory for hundreds of thousands of Nvidia GB200/GB300 in joint training." },
  520: { descEn: "A 400 MW AI data centre for CoreWeave in North Dakota.", detailEn: "Applied Digital is building the Polaris Forge 1 campus at Ellendale, North Dakota — three phases totalling 400 MW fully leased long-term to CoreWeave (~$11 billion) — using a cold climate and renewables to cut PUE; phase 1 came online in October 2025, expandable to 1 GW." },
  522: { descEn: "Twin Microsoft campuses at Granger and LaPorte, Indiana.", detailEn: "In northwest Indiana, Microsoft is simultaneously building the St. Joseph Farm campus at Granger (900+ acres, 6 buildings, groundbreaking March 2026) and a LaPorte campus (~$1 billion), over $2 billion combined, extending the data-centre cluster around AWS's Project Rainier." },
  601: { descEn: "One of Asia's largest AI superclusters.", detailEn: "In February 2026 Yotta announced 20,736 liquid-cooled Nvidia Blackwell Ultra GPUs at its D2 centre in Greater Noida, building one of Asia's largest AI superclusters, over $2 billion, with 10,000+ GPUs serving the government's IndiaAI Mission, online in August 2026, expandable to 250 MW." },
  677: { descEn: "One of the world's largest undeveloped rare-earth deposits, with US EXIM loan interest.", detailEn: "In southern Greenland, ~4.7 billion tonnes of resources; Critical Metals Corp won Greenland approval and 92.5% in May 2026, with US EXIM submitting a $120 million letter of interest (the Trump administration's first overseas mining project), at ~85,000 tonnes/year of rare-earth oxides initially, with supply deals signed with Saudi Arabia and others." },
  793: { descEn: "China's furthest-offshore grid-connected wind farm (85.5 km).", detailEn: "Off northeast Dafeng in Yancheng, comprising four sites, 98 turbines and 800 MW; the H8-1 site's furthest point is 85.5 km offshore, a national record. First connection came in July 2025 and full capacity in December, with over 2.6 TWh a year." },
  823: { descEn: "The 11th cascade on the Mekong mainstream, mostly exporting to Thailand and Vietnam.", detailEn: "On the Mekong mainstream in Luang Prabang province, Laos, 1,460 MW with seven 200 MW units; started in 2020 and targeting 2027, mostly exporting to Thailand and Vietnam, drawing international attention for its proximity to the Luang Prabang World Heritage town." },
  948: { descEn: "The first Spain-France subsea DC link across the Bay of Biscay.", detailEn: "Linking the Spanish Basque Country with Cubnezais in France, ~390 km (300 km subsea), 2 GW rated (expandable to 5 GW); the EIB approved a €1.6 billion loan in June 2025, with converter-station civil works begun at both ends, targeting 2028." },
  988: { descEn: "South America's first long-distance high-capacity HVDC, sending northern desert solar to Santiago.", detailEn: "Kimal-Lo Aguirre runs 1,346 km linking Kimal in Antofagasta with Lo Aguirre in Greater Santiago at ±600 kV/3,000 MW — Chile's first HVDC line, built by a Transelec, ISA and China Southern Power Grid International consortium, formally started in February 2026." },
  1017: { descEn: "Gotion's US LFP battery plant in Illinois, in production 2025.", detailEn: "Gotion High-Tech's $2 billion LFP battery and storage base at Manteno, Illinois (~150 acres, 1.5 million sq ft beside I-57) is the state's largest EV battery plant. Five lines are built, with commercial storage products in mass production in 2025 and EV batteries from year-end, ~450 staff at year-end and 1,400 targeted in 2026 — a big new local grid load." },
  1060: { descEn: "One of the largest US solar-storage plants, full capacity August 2025.", detailEn: "In Kern County's Mojave Desert in California, developed by Arevon in two phases (Eland 1, Eland 2), over $2 billion, with 758 MWdc of solar and 300 MW/1,200 MWh (4-hour) lithium storage. Storing surplus daytime solar to supply the LADWP in the evening, Eland 1 started in December 2024 and Eland 2 reached commercial operation in August 2025." },
  1160: { descEn: "Bangladesh's first deep-water port, JICA-financed.", detailEn: "On Maheshkhali Island in Cox's Bazar, Matarbari is Bangladesh's first deep-water port, JICA yen-loan-financed. In April 2025 Bangladesh signed a terminal-construction deal with Japan's Penta-Ocean and Toa, launching main works; the channel is dredged, with 2.15 km north and 670 m south breakwaters built. Phase 1 is ~619.7 billion taka, targeting 2029 completion and large mother-vessel operation in 2030 — Bangladesh's maritime gateway and regional transhipment hub." },
  1238: { descEn: "An 800,000-tonne Pecém green-ammonia project with 2.5 GW of renewables.", detailEn: "AES Brasil filed an EIA for the Ceará SEZ (Pecém park) to make up to 800,000 tonnes of green ammonia a year with ~2.5 GW of renewables — one of ten strategic Ceará ZPE projects approved by CZPE in November 2025, aimed at clean-fuel export." },
  1364: { descEn: "Cross-border solar-storage supplying Bahrain.", detailEn: "Saudi Arabia's ACWA Power and Bahrain's state Bapco Energies signed a joint-development deal to build 2.8 GW of solar with battery storage in Saudi Arabia's Eastern Province in phases; the power goes to Bahrain's Bapco Energies, supporting Bahrain's 30%-by-2035 emissions cut and 2060 net-zero strategy — a landmark Gulf cross-border solar-storage supply project." },
  1367: { descEn: "One of the world's largest solar-storage projects, with 6 GWh of batteries.", detailEn: "Dubai's DEWA is advancing phase 7 of the Mohammed bin Rashid Solar Park, 1,600 MW of solar (expandable to 2,000 MW) with 1,000 MW/6-hour (6,000 MWh) battery storage, developed IPP-style — one of the world's largest solar-storage projects, with ~4.5 TWh a year." },
  1390: { descEn: "Six 50 MW hyperscale campuses for Saudi Arabia's communications ministry.", detailEn: "QST is building a 300 MW data-centre project for Saudi Arabia's Ministry of Communications and IT, six 50 MW facilities across Riyadh, Dammam, Jeddah and NEOM. The first hyperscale facility is at King Salman Energy Park (SPARK) in Dammam, adding ~60 MW a year to 2026, at a project budget of at least $2 billion." },
  1442: { descEn: "Iran's largest copper complex, continuing to expand.", detailEn: "At Rafsanjan in Kerman province, Iran, operated by NICICO, Iran's largest copper complex; ~$2 billion of new projects started in 2024 added ~300,000 tonnes/year of copper concentrate capacity via the Sarcheshmeh and Sungun concentrators (Sarcheshmeh adding ~160,000 tonnes of copper and ~1,100 tonnes of molybdenum a year)." },
  1498: { descEn: "A Kazakh sovereign-AI compute hub, Nvidia-powered.", detailEn: "On 7 November 2025 Freedom Holding signed with Kazakhstan's AI and digital-development ministry for a $2 billion sovereign AI Hub based on exaflop-scale Nvidia compute, run by Freedom with ~100 MW of power, serving sensitive government workloads and the national AI ecosystem." },
  1501: { descEn: "Central Asia's most powerful supercomputer, H200-driven at 2 exaflops.", detailEn: "Launched by President Tokayev in July 2025, the Alem.cloud supercomputer in Astana has 64 HGX servers and 512 Nvidia H200 GPUs for ~2 exaflops (FP8) — Central Asia's most powerful — part of a ~$2 billion Nvidia-related plan with a planned 100 MW Tier IV park; an expansion was announced in April 2026." },
  1522: { descEn: "Uzbekistan's first dedicated high-speed railway, advancing in planning.", detailEn: "Uzbekistan's president announced a new Tashkent-Samarkand-Navoi-Bukhara high-speed railway at an AIIB summit, ~300 km at ~185 km/h average, cutting Tashkent-Samarkand to ~1.5 hours. A Korean consortium does feasibility, with China Exim Bank and the EIB interested; the president reaffirmed it in his December 2025 address, requiring full design documents by 1 May 2026 and targeting H1 2030." },
  1533: { descEn: "Doubling a southern Kazakh refinery to 12 million tonnes/year.", detailEn: "PetroKazakhstan is expanding the Shymkent refinery to double capacity from 6 to 12 million tonnes/year, boosting Euro-V petrol, diesel and jet fuel and adding polypropylene at the KPI petrochemical complex. The previous 2018 upgrade was $1.8 billion (to 6 million tonnes); this round targets 2029, with ~3.07 million tonnes processed in H1 2025." },
  1678: { descEn: "The world's largest grid-scale storage portfolio, five sites totalling 12.5 GWh.", detailEn: "In February 2025 BYD Energy Storage and the Saudi Electricity Company (SEC) signed for the world's largest grid-scale storage portfolio — five 500 MW/2,500 MWh stations totalling 12.5 GWh at Riyadh, Qaisumah, Dawadmi, Al Jouf and Rabigh, using BYD's MC Cube-T system — supporting Saudi Arabia's 50%-renewables-by-2030 goal; with an earlier 2.6 GWh order it totals 15.1 GWh." },
  1689: { descEn: "An AI hyperscale campus at Kempas Tech Park, Johor, next to Singapore.", detailEn: "DayOne's second large campus at Kempas Tech Park in Johor, with the Nusajaya campus, forms its Johor hub of over 478 MW operating capacity (toward 500 MW), both in the Johor-Singapore SEZ. AI-focused with liquid cooling and renewables targeting LEED Gold; in February 2026 DayOne announced a regional ops and engineer-training centre in Johor for 1,000+ technicians." },
  1717: { descEn: "A 134 km gas-export trunkline from the SEAP platforms to the Sergipe coast.", detailEn: "This 134 km pipeline (111 offshore, 23 onshore) carries up to 18 million m³/day of SEAP I/II gas to the Sergipe coast — key to activating the Sergipe deepwater project and tying it to the national grid. EPE issued a positive opinion, with Petrobras planning a 2026 pipeline tender for 2031 gas export." },
  1784: { descEn: "A mega-bridge across All Saints Bay linking Salvador with Itaparica Island.", detailEn: "Spanning All Saints Bay for 12.4 km with a 900 m cable-stayed section and 85 m clearance, set to be Latin America's longest sea bridge, built by a CCECC-CCCC consortium, ~10.4-11 billion reais. Bay surveys finished in 2025 with shop drawings from December; temporary platforms install in May 2026 and main works start in June over a 6-year contract, targeting 2031." },
  1831: { descEn: "A 7th Jubail ammonia/urea unit with carbon capture for low-carbon production.", detailEn: "Allocated gas feedstock in July 2024, initially for 1.2 million tonnes of low-carbon (blue) ammonia plus 1.1 million tonnes of urea; a 2026 optimisation lifted it to 1.2 million tonnes of ammonia and 2.6 million tonnes of urea, raising company capacity from ~4.8 to ~7.4 million tonnes (+54%), tied to Jubail CCS for low carbon, with FID and EPC pending and start-up around 2029." },
  1835: { descEn: "An expansion of the world's largest offshore oilfield, with pipelines and platforms.", detailEn: "Safaniyah is the world's largest offshore oilfield; Aramco is adding ~700,000 b/d of capacity from 2027 (~350,000 b/d delivered in 2027). It awarded COOEC ~$1 billion of EPCI and Saipem ~$500 million of 48-inch subsea/onshore trunkline (February 2026), covering jackets, production decks, subsea pipelines and cables, with gas processing." },
  1841: { descEn: "A Tanajib gas-plant phase 2 processing offshore associated-gas growth.", detailEn: "The onshore Tanajib gas plant phase 1 started in December 2025, processing associated gas from the Marjan and Zuluf offshore fields with gas processing, NGL recovery and desalination, reaching 2.6 bcf/d of raw gas in 2026. Phase 2, tied to Marjan/Zuluf growth, targets 2027 to process new associated gas and condensate for the 2030 gas-output goal." },
  1858: { descEn: "A four-station VSC DC link, a 7 GW central-south-west corridor.", detailEn: "In SEC's national-grid upgrade, four ±500 kV VSC-HVDC converter stations at Riyadh, Jizan and Jeddah transmit 7,000 MW, opening central-to-south and west power transfer and renewable integration — core of a five-year 'two 7 GW DC lines' plan, with system commissioning targeted for end-2026 to 2027." },
  1873: { descEn: "A smart-device gigafactory at Riyadh's SILZ free zone, online 2026.", detailEn: "PIF's Alat and Lenovo, in a $2 billion strategic partnership, broke ground in September 2025 at Riyadh's logistics special zone for a 200,000 m² manufacturing and R&D centre, with first computers in 12-18 months; planning 2 million Saudi-made devices in year 1 rising to 9 million, with an AI and robotics R&D centre, ~15,000 direct jobs." },
  1919: { descEn: "A 400,000-tonne greenfield copper smelter-refinery at Ras Al Khair.", detailEn: "In November 2024 Vedanta Copper International signed with Saudi Arabia to build a ~$2 billion 400,000-tonne/year greenfield copper smelter-refinery and a 300,000-tonne copper-rod plant at Ras Al Khair Industrial City. The rod plant started in September 2025 (first 125,000-tonne line due 2026); the smelter targets 2028, with an eighth-round Jabal Sayid exploration permit won in November 2025." },
  1956: { descEn: "A Mekong-mainstream hydro plant near the Thai border.", detailEn: "On the Mekong mainstream near the Thai border in Laos, 684 MW with ~3.803 TWh a year, developed by China Datang (Laos) Sanakham Hydropower, with Thailand's Gulf Energy set to take 30-35%. It completed the MRC's PNPCA process, with 2025 signs of approval and a likely start; but with the dam just ~2 km from Thailand, Thailand formally asked Laos to reconsider the site in April 2025." },
  1962: { descEn: "Indonesian green power exported across the border to Singapore.", detailEn: "On Bulan Island west of Batam in the Riau Islands near Singapore, developed by the Pacific Medco Solar Energy consortium, phase 1 is ~670 MWp of solar with large battery storage, sending ~100 MW of steady power to Singapore via a 400 kV dedicated subsea cable. It won a conditional Singapore EMA import licence (to 600 MW) in 2024; Singapore plans ~2 GW of low-carbon imports a year from Indonesia within five years, with this as the flagship." },
});

/* ===== 批次14：全库投资额 TOP（约 18–20 亿美元）===== */
Object.assign(window.ENERGY_EN, {
  2002: { descEn: "A second memory assembly-and-test plant, expanded on AI demand.", detailEn: "Micron's second smart-manufacturing plant at Batu Kawan, Penang opened in October 2023, expanding from 600,000 to 1.5 million sq ft; in December 2024 it added ~$2 billion for AI-chip-related capacity, running on 100% renewables." },
  2018: { descEn: "A KIPI green-park aluminium smelter, phase 1 with power $2 billion.", detailEn: "PT Kalimantan Aluminium Industry is building a smelter at the KIPI green park in North Kalimantan, with a ~$2 billion phase 1 (including power) at 500,000 tonnes/year, expanding in three phases (2025, Q4 2026, Q4 2029) to 1.5 million tonnes; first pots start by end-2025, aligned with Indonesia's downstreaming policy." },
  2022: { descEn: "Google's first Malaysian data centre, started October 2024.", detailEn: "Google is investing $2 billion in its first Malaysian data centre and cloud region at Elmina Business Park in Selangor — Southeast Asia's second Google data centre after Singapore. Announced in May 2024 and broken ground by Gamuda in October, it targets early 2026 using water cooling, expected to create 26,500 jobs and over $3.2 billion of economic benefit by 2030." },
  2077: { descEn: "Malaysia's first nearshore floating LNG, at Sipitang, Sabah.", detailEn: "Petronas's third floating LNG (ZLNG/PFLNG Tiga) at the Sipitang oil-and-gas park (SOGIP) in Sabah is 2 MTPA — Malaysia's first nearshore FLNG. First steel was cut at Samsung Heavy's Geoje yard in April 2024, targeting commercial operation in H2 2027 to lift Malaysian floating-LNG capacity from 2.7 to 4.7 million tonnes; Sabah has bought 25%." },
  2087: { descEn: "One of PT Vale's three HPAL projects.", detailEn: "At Sorowako in South Sulawesi, PT Vale's three HPAL projects (Pomalaa/Bahodopi/Sorowako) total ~$9 billion; the Sorowako plant makes 60,000 tonnes/year of MHP nickel using 11.5 million tonnes of limonite, ~17% built by end-2025 and targeting 2027, with saprolite-ore sales from Q3 2025 for extra revenue." },
  2099: { descEn: "Vietnam's state-owned downstream bauxite expansion in the Central Highlands.", detailEn: "Dak Nong holds ~73% of Vietnam's bauxite reserves; Vinacomin plans ~$7.3 billion across projects, expanding Nhan Co alumina to 2 million tonnes/year (2029) and building the Dak Nong 2 bauxite-alumina-aluminium complex (2 million tonnes alumina + 500,000 tonnes aluminium before 2030), with Duc Giang Chemicals also signing for an integrated plant in October 2025." },
  2256: { descEn: "A Jorf Lasfar battery-materials plant online June 2025, a CNGR-Al Mada JV.", detailEn: "China's CNGR and Morocco's royal-controlled Al Mada formed COBCO, ~€1.8-2 billion at Jorf Lasfar for NMC and LFP cathode, precursor and battery recycling, starting battery-materials production in June 2025 — a key part of Morocco's full battery chain, mainly for the European EV market." },
  2265: { descEn: "A giant southwest iron mine, first 4-million-tonne pretreatment plant in April 2026.", detailEn: "Gara Djebilet in Tindouf has ~3.5 billion tonnes of reserves, one of the world's largest iron mines. Algeria's Sonarem with China's Sinosteel and Turkey's Tosyali plan to mine ~7 billion tonnes with Mecheri Abdelaziz; production starts in Q1 2026 with a first 4-million-tonne/year pretreatment unit by end-April 2026, aiming to stop imports and become a net exporter." },
  2278: { descEn: "Libya's first bid round since 2007, 22 blocks drawing 37 oil majors.", detailEn: "Libya's NOC launched its first upstream bid round since 2007 in March 2025, offering 22 onshore and offshore exploration blocks across major basins; over 37 oil majors expressed interest, with bids closing in November 2025. Aligned with NOC's 2-million-b/d goal, bidders include TotalEnergies, Eni, OMV and Repsol." },
  2317: { descEn: "An Abidjan port modernisation, aiming to double capacity by 2030.", detailEn: "Abidjan's $2 billion port modernisation aims to double capacity by 2030; the phase-2 container terminal is 37.5 hectares with an 1,100 m berth for 1.5 million TEU a year. Two all-electric quay cranes and nine electric rubber-tyred gantries were added in July 2025, with throughput up from 840,000 TEU in 2022 to 1.6 million in 2024." },
  2467: { descEn: "A 360 MW hyperscale data-centre park in Cape Town.", detailEn: "Cavaleros Group announced a 360 MW data-centre park on a 100-hectare Cape Town site plus a 200 MW, 40-hectare park at Kosmosdal/Samrand north of Johannesburg; together they would more than double South Africa's existing data-centre power demand, with Cape Town a new growth pole on cable landings and renewables." },
  2508: { descEn: "Zambia's largest copper mine under construction.", detailEn: "Barrick's $2 billion super-pit expansion at the Lumwana copper mine in Zambia's North-Western Province aims to double output — Zambia's largest copper project under construction. By August 2025 progress was slightly ahead of plan, targeting 2028, with payback expected within two years at current copper prices." },
  2517: { descEn: "Mozambique's largest gas power plant.", detailEn: "The 450 MW Temane gas plant in Inhambane province uses Pande and Temane field gas — Mozambique's largest gas plant, raising national capacity ~16%. Damage to a temporary jetty by Tropical Storm Filipo in March 2025 delayed it to early 2026." },
  2532: { descEn: "The Polihali dam, transfer tunnel and hydropower.", detailEn: "Lesotho Highlands Water phase 2 includes the Polihali dam and a 38.5 km transfer tunnel carrying water to Katse dam. Two TBMs began boring in January 2025 (Katse side) and January 2026 (Polihali side), with an 80.3 MW Oxbow hydro scheme; water supply is expected in 2028/29 with hydro ~a year later." },
  2551: { descEn: "A cross-border SEZ making battery precursors and cells from cobalt, copper and manganese.", detailEn: "Promoted by the UN Economic Commission for Africa and Afreximbank, this cross-border SEZ uses DRC cobalt-copper and Zambian copper-manganese to make 100,000 tonnes/year of NMC precursor and EV batteries; a pre-feasibility study shows precursor costs in DRC at a third of US levels, with SME and finance capacity-building from September 2025." },
  2565: { descEn: "Gabon's first large gas development, online 2026.", detailEn: "Perenco is building floating liquefaction at the Cap Lopez oil terminal, ~$2 billion, deploying an FLNG vessel for 700,000 tonnes of LNG and 25,000 tonnes of LPG a year with 137,000 m³ storage — Gabon's first large gas development to monetise offshore gas and cut flaring; in April 2025 it bought the LNG Bayelsa for conversion to floating storage, targeting 2026." },
  2605: { descEn: "The world's largest off-grid renewable network, decarbonising iron-ore power.", detailEn: "Fortescue's off-grid clean-energy network in the Pilbara iron-ore region of WA has ~1 million solar modules (~600 MW), 600 MW of wind and 5.4 GWh of battery storage (BYD batteries, Envision turbines) to replace mining diesel and gas for net-zero land operations by 2030 — the world's largest off-grid renewable system, with works through 2025-2026." },
  2620: { descEn: "A western Victoria 500 kV artery connecting western wind and solar.", detailEn: "AusNet's western Victoria 500 kV transmission is ~190 km linking Bulgana-Ballarat-northwest Melbourne, connecting large western-Victoria wind and solar and tying into VNI West — a key corridor for Victoria's 95%-renewables-by-2035 goal." },
  2621: { descEn: "NSW's largest REZ, planned to connect ~8 GW of wind-solar-storage.", detailEn: "The transmission for NSW's New England Renewable Energy Zone is planned to connect ~8 GW of wind, solar and storage — the largest of NSW's five REZs. In 2025 large projects like Forest won grid access, with the high-voltage network advancing in design and construction." },
  2670: { descEn: "A Rio Tinto-Baowu iron mine, built on time and budget.", detailEn: "Near Paraburdoo in WA, developed by Rio Tinto (54%) and China Baowu (46%), 25 million tonnes/year at ~$2 billion, built on time and budget — a landmark China-Australia iron-ore project securing Pilbara supply to China." },
  2705: { descEn: "A 795 MW Dutch offshore wind farm coupled with green-hydrogen electrolysis.", detailEn: "In the Dutch North Sea, an RWE-TotalEnergies JV of 795 MW, partly coupled to TotalEnergies's ELYgator green-hydrogen project at Rotterdam Maasvlakte — an 'offshore wind + green hydrogen' model, advancing construction in 2025." },
  2717: { descEn: "An eco-friendly offshore wind demonstration off the Dutch coast.", detailEn: "In the Hollandse Kust West VII zone of the Dutch North Sea, developed by the Shell-Eneco JV Ecowende, 760 MW with eco-friendly design favouring marine life and birds — a Dutch 'nature-inclusive' offshore wind demonstration, advancing in 2025 for 2026." },
  2723: { descEn: "A UK internal DC subsea cable linking Kent and Suffolk.", detailEn: "National Grid's 2 GW HVDC subsea cable links Pegwell Bay in Kent with the Suffolk coast, ~130 km, easing southeast-England congestion and absorbing more offshore wind; a DCO application was filed in March 2025, targeting the early 2030s." },
  2831: { descEn: "The first US nuclear unit restarted after retirement.", detailEn: "In Michigan, Holtec's Palisades plant (~800 MW PWR) is the first US nuclear unit to restart after closing, backed by a federal loan guarantee; after a 2025 overhaul and regulatory approval it reconnected and generated, setting a precedent for nuclear 'revival' to extend low-carbon baseload." },
  2905: { descEn: "A 2 GW-class Kern County solar-storage, the largest approved US solar-storage plant.", detailEn: "In the Mojave at Kern County, California, AES (acquired from Avantus) plans 1 GW of solar plus 1 GW/4,000 MWh of storage in two 500 MW phases; phase 1 started in 2025 and phase 2 targets end-2026, with ~3.2 million MWh a year." },
  2966: { descEn: "A 5 GW-class off-grid AI data-centre campus in West Texas, with 1.8 GW of batteries.", detailEn: "In Pecos County, Texas, an 8,000+ acre private-grid generation campus powers hyperscale AI data centres, planning up to 7.65 GW of gas, 1.8 GW of batteries and 750 MWac of solar, fully off-grid; approved by the state environmental commission in early 2026, with first power in Q1 2027 and full 5+ GW by 2031." },
  3041: { descEn: "A Texas Jefferson County carbon-storage project with EPA Class VI permits, tying into a Gulf CCS network.", detailEn: "In Jefferson County, Texas, this won EPA permits for three Class VI injection wells in 2025, with three storage wells via an 18-mile pipeline. The operator runs the largest US CO₂ network (over 1,300 miles), already transporting and storing up to 2 million tonnes/year for CF Industries in 2025." },
  3059: { descEn: "A large nickel-cobalt sulphide mine north of Timmins, ~40,000 t/year nickel.", detailEn: "An open-pit nickel-cobalt sulphide mine 42 km north of Timmins, Ontario, ~38,000-42,000 tonnes of nickel a year over ~41 years; it was accepted by the federal Major Projects Office in November 2025, committing to break ground by end-2026, with a $20 million convertible Indigenous investment." },
  3114: { descEn: "A 1.2-million-tonne green-ammonia project at Tuticorin VOC port, in three phases.", detailEn: "At VOC port in Tuticorin, Tamil Nadu, 1.2 million tonnes/year of green ammonia in three phases, with a 10-year binding SECI green-ammonia purchase deal supplying four fertiliser firms, ~200 billion rupees." },
  3442: { descEn: "China's new-generation artificial sun; first double-100-million-degree run in 2025, entering burning experiments.", detailEn: "At Chengdu in Sichuan, built and run by the Southwestern Institute of Physics, this is China's largest magnetic-confinement fusion device. In March 2025 it first reached a double 117-million-degree ion and 160-million-degree electron run, marking entry into the fusion-burning experiment phase." },
  3473: { descEn: "A 2.1 GW pumped hydro in Luxi, Honghe — among Yunnan's largest.", detailEn: "At Luxi in Honghe, Yunnan, 2.1 GW, approved on 14 May 2025 — the largest pumped-hydro approval of H1 2025, providing Yunnan-grid peaking, frequency regulation and renewable integration." },
  3510: { descEn: "CATL's Luoyang battery base phase 2 online, 60 GWh across two phases.", detailEn: "CATL's 13th battery plant at Yibin in Luoyang, Henan; phase 1 (30 GWh) completed in November 2024 and phase 2 (another 30 GWh) started up in October 2025 for 60 GWh combined, total investment up to 14 billion yuan, mainly EV and storage batteries." },
  3574: { descEn: "The Greater Bay Area's largest single automated container terminal, started May 2026.", detailEn: "Building four 200,000-tonne container berths (1,880 m of quay) and 15 5,000-tonne barge berths, designed for 6.7 million TEU a year at ~14.447 billion yuan — a 14th Five-Year major project and the Bay Area's largest single container-terminal investment. Sea-use was approved by the State Council, with works from 15 May 2026 over 2026-2032." },
  3590: { descEn: "A Yuheng coal-to-ethanol chain, building a coal-methanol-ethanol-EVA-POE chain.", detailEn: "In the Yuheng industrial zone of Yulin, Shaanxi, built by Yanchang Petroleum Kaiyue Coal Chemical, centred on coal-based methanol-to-ethanol and extending downstream to vinyl acetate, EVA and POE — China's first complete coal-methanol-ethanol-vinyl-acetate-POE chain, upgrading northern Shaanxi's coal chemicals into new materials." },
  4036: { descEn: "A China Railway consortium won HCMC Metro Line 2, including track and traction power.", detailEn: "China Railway and Vietnam's Thaco formed a consortium that won the Ho Chi Minh City Metro Line 2, ~14 billion yuan. With a Ben Thanh-Tham Luong section, a groundbreaking was held in January 2026 and a construction permit won in April; it covers tunnels, stations, track, traction power and the four-electric systems — a flagship of Vietnamese urban-rail cooperation." },
  4168: { descEn: "Southeast Asia's largest gas combined-cycle plant, a CGN-Edra flagship.", detailEn: "CGN bought Edra Power in 2015; the Malacca EMPP plant is 2,242 MW with three 745 MW single-shaft combined-cycle units, online 2022 — Southeast Asia's largest low-carbon gas plant, meeting ~10% of Malay Peninsula demand, with a 720 MW Telok Gong phase 2 also held." },
  4185: { descEn: "The Middle East's first polysilicon plant, a GCL-Mubadala JV.", detailEn: "GCL Technology and Abu Dhabi sovereign fund Mubadala's MDC Power are building the Middle East's first polysilicon (granular silicon) plant in the UAE, ~120,000 tonnes/year, as a low-carbon, low-cost granular-silicon R&D and manufacturing base — GCL's first overseas silicon project." },
  4196: { descEn: "The world's largest, highest-grade producing hard-rock lithium mine, run by Tianqi via Windfield.", detailEn: "At Greenbushes in WA, the world's largest, highest-grade producing spodumene mine, with Tianqi holding 51% via Windfield Holdings and Albemarle 49%, operated by Talison. Current spodumene capacity is 1.62 million tonnes/year (~1.48 million chemical-grade + ~140,000 technical-grade); the CGP3 plant from 2025 lifts capacity above 2.1 million tonnes." },
  4251: { descEn: "A ~$2 billion Norinco EPC framework for the Iraqi TQ refinery expansion.", detailEn: "Norinco and AWSAT Energy FZE signed an EPC framework for the Iraqi TQ refinery expansion at the third Belt and Road forum's entrepreneur conference, tentatively ~$2 billion, expanding the Nasiriyah refinery in Thi Qar province, strengthening Norinco's oil-and-gas engineering arm." },
  4342: { descEn: "A $2 billion Envision AESC battery gigafactory in Bowling Green, Kentucky, 30 GWh (expandable to 40).", detailEn: "Envision AESC is investing $2 billion in a lithium-ion battery gigafactory in Warren County, Bowling Green, Kentucky, 30 GWh a year (expandable to 40), enough for ~300,000 EVs (2027) — an important capacity addition after its Tennessee plant." },
  4381: { descEn: "Huayou's Sorowako HPAL nickel project with PT Vale Indonesia, 60,000 t/year nickel.", detailEn: "Huayou and PT Vale Indonesia's HPAL project at Sorowako, Sulawesi makes ~60,000 tonnes/year of nickel-in-MHP with associated mining, ~$2 billion total, starting construction in 2026, supplying the battery chain." },
  4388: { descEn: "A Tsingshan-Guangxin HPAL nickel-cobalt project in Indonesia, 80,000 t/year intermediates.", detailEn: "Tsingshan and Guangdong's state Guangxin Holdings are building an 80,000-tonne/year (nickel-equivalent) nickel-cobalt-intermediate HPAL project at the Tsingshan park in Bahodopi, Morowali, Central Sulawesi, ~$2 billion, with trial production expected by end-2026 and ~2 billion yuan a year in profit at capacity — a benchmark HPAL project." },
  4389: { descEn: "A Tsingshan-POSCO 2-million-tonne stainless plant at the Morowali park.", detailEn: "Tsingshan and Korea's POSCO signed to build a 2-million-tonne/year stainless-steel plant at the IMIP Morowali park in Indonesia, with works from 2026; POSCO also sold its 1.1-million-tonne Chinese stainless plant to Tsingshan in July 2025, deepening their stainless cooperation." },
  4400: { descEn: "HQC's pretreatment and utilities services for Qatar's North Field LNG expansion.", detailEn: "Qatar's North Field expansion includes NFE (East, four 8-MTPA trains) and NFS (South, two trains), adding ~48 MTPA of LNG — the world's largest single LNG expansion, starting up from 2026. HQC (Huanqiu), drawing on its large-LNG EPC capability, provides pretreatment and utilities services for the onshore liquefaction, deepening its Qatar LNG presence." },
  4487: { descEn: "CPECC builds associated-gas recovery for the TotalEnergies-led GGIP, cutting Basra flaring.", detailEn: "CPECC won the associated-gas-processing EPC package of Iraq's Basra GGIP (Gas Growth Integrated Project), ~$2 billion in two phases, to recover and process Basra-region associated gas (600 million cubic feet/day capacity) instead of flaring. The owner consortium is TotalEnergies (45%), Basra Oil (30%) and QatarEnergy (25%) — a key gas-processing unit of Iraq's $10 billion GGIP." },
  905: { descEn: "A Sichuan-Chongqing UHV AC ring spur tying Aba hydro and renewables into the Chengdu-Chongqing grid.", detailEn: "From the Aba 1,000 kV substation to the Chengdu East 1,000 kV substation, 371.7 km of double-circuit line, started in July 2024 with the first section through in January 2026, targeting completion and energisation by December 2026." },
  1599: { descEn: "A CPEC 884 MW hydro plant on the Kunhar River, Energy China's largest overseas hydro investment.", detailEn: "Built as a greenfield investment by China Energy's overseas arm on the Kunhar River in KP, Pakistan, 265 km from Islamabad with over 900 m of head, four impulse units totalling 884 MW, $1.962 billion. All four units connected within four days on 14 August 2024 for ~3.212 TWh a year, powering over a million homes — China Energy's largest overseas-built hydro plant." },
  302: { descEn: "A Chongqing-Kunming line through Sichuan and Yunnan, cutting the trip to ~2.5 hours.", detailEn: "From Chongqing West via Sichuan and Guizhou to Kunming South, 699 km at 350 km/h, 141.6 billion yuan; all bridges finished by February 2026 with an opening expected by year-end, connecting Kunming Changshui Airport station directly to the high-speed network." },
  1573: { descEn: "One of the world's largest solar-storage projects.", detailEn: "PowerChina's Abu Dhabi branch and ECIDI formed a consortium with Masdar for an EPC building 2.1 GWp of solar plus 7.75 GWh of storage for near round-the-clock supply, ~13.962 billion yuan over NTP+21 months — a world-leading solar-storage project." },
  4428: { descEn: "An Abu Dhabi Mshayrif solar-storage EPC, ~13.962 billion yuan.", detailEn: "On 12 March 2026 PowerChina's Abu Dhabi branch and ECIDI formed a consortium that signed the Masdar RTC solar-storage EPC, ~13.962 billion yuan, at Mshayrif in Abu Dhabi — 2.1 GWp of solar DC-side and 7.75 GWh of storage, covering civil, substation, solar and storage design, procurement and construction over NTP+21 months — a super-large solar-storage EPC won by a Chinese firm in the Middle East." },
  218: { descEn: "The world's first 700 m-head-class 400 MW pumped hydro.", detailEn: "At Yangjiang in Guangdong, six 400 MW reversible units total 2.4 GW — China's largest single-unit pumped hydro — achieving home-grown 700 m super-high-head core technology; accepted in June 2024, absorbing ~6.5 TWh of clean energy a year." },
  324: { descEn: "A flagship Seoul-area express commuter rail.", detailEn: "82 km linking Paju and Dongtan at 180 km/h; the GTX-A first section opened in March 2024 and extended to Seoul Station in December (Unjeong to Seoul Station in ~22 minutes), on a PPP basis." },
  986: { descEn: "A Tasmania-Victoria HVDC subsea cable across Bass Strait.", detailEn: "Marinus Link phase 1 is a 255 km Bass Strait HVDC subsea cable and 90 km of Victorian onshore cable with converter stations at both ends. FID came in August 2025 with a A$994 million main-build contract in December, starting in 2026 and targeting 2030." },
  987: { descEn: "A 900 km three-state interconnector linking South Australia, Victoria and NSW.", detailEn: "Australia's longest interconnector, Project EnergyConnect, links Robertstown in South Australia with Wagga Wagga in NSW and extends to Victoria. The western section energised a first 150 MW in April 2025 and the eastern substation expansion finished in June, with the full 800 MW capacity expected by July 2027." },
  1888: { descEn: "A 187 MW Sino-Saudi multi-site data-centre group.", detailEn: "ICS Arabia and Shanghai LMT with China Mobile International are building a 187 MW Saudi data-centre group, started September 2024. The phase-1 Riyadh 65 MW is due March 2026 and the phase-2 Jeddah 50 MW (from early 2025) by Q4 2026, ~$1.9 billion total, offering cloud, AI and 2-100 kW racks." },
  1905: { descEn: "Upgrading two container terminals at King Abdulaziz Port, Dammam, +120% capacity.", detailEn: "Saudi ports authority Mawani awarded Saudi Global Ports (SGP) a 7 billion-riyal (~$1.9 billion) BOT to upgrade two container terminals at King Abdulaziz Port in Dammam, refurbishing terminal 1 and expanding terminal 2's berths and yards plus a tech test zone — lifting capacity 120% to 7.5 million TEU and creating 4,000+ jobs; terminal-2 berth expansion was unveiled in November 2025 with a Dammam logistics zone." },
  2209: { descEn: "Egypt's largest hyperscale data centre, with desert-cooling innovation.", detailEn: "NEOIX's 150-500 MW hyperscale data centre in Egypt's New Administrative Capital spans 500,000 m², ~€1.8 billion (~$1.9 billion), endorsed by Egypt's ICT ministry as a digital-transformation cornerstone. Using desert-specific cooling for up to 60% lower energy use, phase 1 is due 2026 with full capacity in 2029 — core to Egypt's 1 GW data-centre plan." },
  3241: { descEn: "Bangalore Metro phase 3: two corridors, 44.65 km, 31 stations.", detailEn: "Phase 3 has the Outer Ring West (JP Nagar-Kempapura, 32.15 km) and Magadi Road (Hosahalli-Kadabagere, 12.5 km) corridors, ~156 billion rupees, with another 97 billion approved for double-deck viaducts; works start by end-2025 with completion in the early 2030s for a 220 km network." },
  3257: { descEn: "A phase-2 expansion of the Vizhinjam deep-water transhipment port, Adani ~160 billion rupees.", detailEn: "Vizhinjam port in Kerala opened in December 2024 (~1.32 million TEU in year one); phase 2 launched in January 2026, Adani ~160 billion rupees, extending berths from 800 to 2,000 m and breakwaters to ~3,900 m, lifting capacity to ~5.7 million TEU on completion in 2028." },
  3281: { descEn: "IOCL's Bihar Barauni refinery from 6 to 9 million tonnes with 200,000-tonne polypropylene.", detailEn: "IOCL is expanding the Barauni refinery (Begusarai, Bihar) from 6 to 9 million tonnes/year, ~160 billion rupees, with a 200,000-tonne/year polypropylene plant due in FY25-26, benefiting from Urja Ganga pipeline gas." },
  3522: { descEn: "A Tongwei Ordos metallurgical-silicon and polysilicon integrated project, counter-cyclical expansion.", detailEn: "Tongwei is building a green-base-material project at Ordos, ultimately 500,000 tonnes of metallurgical silicon and 400,000 of high-purity polysilicon; phase 1 (200,000 tonnes each) is ~13-14 billion yuan over 15-18 months, cementing its global silicon lead." },
  4500: { descEn: "CATL's first overseas plant, the Arnstadt battery plant in Thuringia, 14 GWh, in production.", detailEn: "CATL is building its first overseas battery plant (CATT) at Arnstadt in Thuringia, Germany, up to €1.8 billion and 14 GWh, with ~2,000 jobs. In production since late 2022 — the first Chinese lithium-battery plant in Germany — it supplies cells for the Porsche Macan and Audi Q6 e-tron; the plant turned profitable in 2024 and expanded its test centre in 2025, winning VW cell and module test certifications." },
  1283: { descEn: "A Goiás-to-Mato Grosso grain railway.", detailEn: "A 383 km section linking Mara Rosa in Goiás with Agua Boa in Mato Grosso for soy and corn export, built by Vale as consideration for early renewal of its Vitória-Minas (EFVM) railway contract, ~10.2 billion reais through Alto Horizonte, Crixás and Aruanã." },
  4086: { descEn: "A high-grade Kalahari copper-belt mine, acquired in 2024.", detailEn: "MMG completed its acquisition of Khoemacau's parent at $1.875 billion enterprise value in March 2024. The 4,040 km² licence holds ~6.4 million tonnes of copper and ~263 million ounces of silver; producing 50,000-65,000 tonnes of copper-equivalent a year since 2021, the board approved ~$900 million of expansion in December 2025 (a new 4.5-million-tonne mill to ~130,000 tonnes of copper), starting in February 2026 with first concentrate in H1 2028." },
  1597: { descEn: "A 73 m-dam hydro plant on the Santa Cruz River, Argentina's largest under construction.", detailEn: "Built by China Energy's Gezhouba (54%) with Argentina's Eling Energía (36%) and Hidrocuyo (10%) on the Santa Cruz River ~180 km west of Puerto Santa Cruz, a 73 m dam with five Francis units and ~3.167 TWh a year, China providing $1.85 billion of financing. On 18 July 2025 Argentina's Enarsa and the consortium signed an MoU to restart work." },
  1813: { descEn: "Brazil's first battery-storage capacity auction, in domestic and open rounds.", detailEn: "In June 2026 Brazil's MME released rules for its first battery-storage capacity auction (LRCAP 2026-Storage), with 2 December 'domestic-content' and 4 December 'open' rounds. Requiring ≥30 MW systems, ≥4 hours, ≥85% efficiency, 6-hour charging and grid-forming, with 15-year contracts from August 2028; just 2 GW would unlock ~10 billion reais, with up to 5 GW potential." },
  2050: { descEn: "A central HCMC metro from Ben Thanh to Tham Luong, starting early 2026.", detailEn: "11.3 km (9.3 km underground, 2 km elevated) from Ben Thanh in District 1 to Tham Luong in District 12, ~47 trillion dong; civil works broke ground on 15 January 2026 led by a THACO consortium, targeting Q4 2030 — the first fully-started core line of HCMC's planned 355 km, seven-line network." },
  1265: { descEn: "Latin America's largest data-centre park, at Barueri Tamboré.", detailEn: "Beside the Rodoanel in Barueri, Greater São Paulo, planned for 600 MW at full capacity, 17 buildings and three substations — Latin America's largest planned and a global top-ten park. Seven buildings (120+ MW) run with a 158 MW phase 2 partly online; in October 2025 it signed a master-plan MoU with Barueri, over 10 billion reais invested." },
  133: { descEn: "Supporting CSP plus wind and solar for the Qinghai-Henan ±800 kV UHV phase 2.", detailEn: "In Hainan, Qinghai, ~200 MW of molten-salt tower CSP (≥5 hours storage) plus ~600 MW of solar and ~200 MW of wind; in September 2025 the 100-MW-class CSP molten-salt-tank chemical salt-making started — part of Qinghai's clean-energy demonstration province." },
  154: { descEn: "Central Asia's largest solar-storage portfolio.", detailEn: "Comprising Samarkand (500 MW/668 MWh) and Bukhara (500 MW/668 MWh), totalling 1 GW/1.34 GWh, financed by the EBRD, ADB and Japan's JBIC, for ~2,300 GWh a year, targeting 2027." },
  317: { descEn: "Egypt's first monorail, linking eastern Cairo with the New Administrative Capital.", detailEn: "53 km with 16 stations, with Alstom supplying 70 driverless monorail cars at up to 80 km/h, all-electric; it opened on 20 March 2026 and to passengers on 6 May, a ~60-minute end-to-end trip." },
  366: { descEn: "The UAE's first integrated PVC complex.", detailEn: "At Ruwais Industrial City, a $1.99 billion EPC was awarded to CNCEC's Seventh Company in November 2025 for 1.9 million tonnes/year of PVC, EDC, VCM and caustic soda — the UAE's first integrated PVC project, with mechanical completion in Q4 2028." },
  519: { descEn: "A $1.8 billion AI data centre in Kenilworth, New Jersey.", detailEn: "CoreWeave broke ground on a nearly $1.8 billion AI data centre in Kenilworth, New Jersey, 393,000 sq ft, among the first approved under New Jersey's EDA tax-credit program, expected online in early 2027." },
  638: { descEn: "An Arequipa copper mine, first production 2027.", detailEn: "In Arequipa, Peru, after rounds of community protest the Zafranal mine won approval to start, ~23% built by October 2025, ~$1.8 billion, using SX-EW for 120,000 tonnes/year of cathode copper, with first production in 2027 and $18.2 billion of Peruvian export revenue over 20 years." },
  664: { descEn: "One of Argentina's largest undeveloped lithium brine resources.", detailEn: "In Salta, Argentina, with combined resources of 15.1 million tonnes LCE — one of the world's largest undeveloped lithium brines — Lithium Argentina and Ganfeng have invested ~$1.8 billion in three 50,000-tonne phases, with phase-1 first production targeted for Q1 2029." },
  1157: { descEn: "Kanpur Metro's underground section open to the central station.", detailEn: "The Kanpur Metro Orange Line (Corridor 1), built by UPMRC, links IIT Kanpur with Kanpur Central station over ~24 km. On 30 May 2025 PM Modi unveiled five underground stations from Chunniganj to Kanpur Central, putting all 14 stations of Corridor 1 (9 elevated, 5 underground) in service and bringing the city's commercial and rail core into the metro — a key transit upgrade for a Ganga-plain industrial city." },
  1273: { descEn: "An expansion of the São Paulo sa-east-1 region to 2034.", detailEn: "AWS pledged 10.1 billion reais (~$1.8 billion) in Brazil through 2034 to expand, build, connect, operate and maintain data centres in São Paulo — its only Latin American cloud region (live 2011, three availability zones) — after 19.2 billion reais in 2011-2023." },
  1360: { descEn: "Five 500 MW/2,000 MWh stations starting together.", detailEn: "In early 2025 the Saudi Electricity Company awarded BYD a 2.5 GW/12.5 GWh grid-scale storage contract across five sites — Riyadh, Qaisumah, Dawadmi, Al Jouf and Rabigh, each 500 MW/2,000 MWh using BYD's MC Cube-T system. The five broke ground together in April 2025, ~6.73 billion riyals, among the world's largest single battery-storage procurements at the time." },
  1516: { descEn: "Central Asia's first urban light rail, driverless.", detailEn: "Built by a China Railway-China Construction Sixth consortium, 22.4 km with 18 stations (11 surface, 7 elevated) at up to 80 km/h, fully driverless. Linking Nazarbayev International Airport with Nurly Zhol station via Abu Dhabi Plaza and the Grand Mosque, after ~10 years' delay it was launched by President Tokayev on 16 May 2026 — Central Asia's first urban LRT." },
  1523: { descEn: "A new dedicated coal terminal at Vanino port in the Russian Far East.", detailEn: "The Elga coal terminal at Vanino port in the Russian Far East is designed for 30 million tonnes a year, targeting 2029; aligned with eastbound BAM expansion, it serves coal exports to China, Korea and Japan. Vanino's coal transhipment hit 36.3 million tonnes in 2025 (+50.3%), with Far East port expansion key to Russia's Asia-Pacific energy exports." },
  1544: { descEn: "A large Tatarstan ethylene unit online with an ethylene pipeline.", detailEn: "Nizhnekamskneftekhim's (NKNKh) EP-600 ethylene unit was completed in December 2024 at 600,000 tonnes/year, producing first on-spec ethylene in early 2025 for NKNKh and Kazanorgsintez downstream. SIBUR is building the Nizhnekamsk-Kazan ethylene trunkline (online 2026), raising transport capacity ~2.5-fold to 500,000 tonnes a year." },
  1663: { descEn: "The world's second-largest niobium producer, record output in 2025.", detailEn: "CMOC Brasil (including the Catalão mines) is the world's second-largest niobium producer and Brazil's second-largest phosphate-fertiliser producer, open-pit. In 2025 both niobium and phosphate output hit records (10,348 tonnes and 1.2135 million tonnes), with 7.693 billion yuan of segment revenue (+17.61%) — a stable earner in CMOC's South American resources and phosphate chain." },
  1725: { descEn: "Converting São Paulo refineries to make SAF and HVO, responding to a future-fuels law.", detailEn: "Part of a 37 billion-reais São Paulo package, Petrobras is converting hydrotreaters at refineries like REVAP (São José) to co-process waste and plant/animal oils into SAF and HVO renewable diesel, targeting end-2026; it also plans an ethanol-to-jet (ATJ) unit after 2030, supporting aviation decarbonisation under SAF blending from 2027." },
  1749: { descEn: "Brazil's largest planned solar, with green hydrogen and ammonia.", detailEn: "Spain's Solatio signed with Piauí to build 4 GW of solar at the Bom Princípio free-export zone, ~10.3 billion reais. A 3 GW phase 1 builds from mid-2025 to 2028, directly supplying co-located green-hydrogen and green-ammonia plants — among Brazil's largest planned solar projects, anchoring a northeast green-export industrial base." },
  1758: { descEn: "A 702 MW nearshore offshore wind farm off Rio Grande do Sul.", detailEn: "Tramandaí offshore wind, ~6 km off Rio Grande do Sul, developed by Ocean Winds, plans 702 MW with 52 13.5 MW turbines, one of OW's five Brazilian offshore projects; in early environmental licensing as a southern nearshore demonstration, it awaits Brazil's first offshore auction." },
  1773: { descEn: "A new trunk railway extending the North-South line to the Vila do Conde port in Pará.", detailEn: "A 535 km new freight railway linking Açailândia in Maranhão with Barcarena/Vila do Conde port in Pará, through 12 municipalities crossing 36 rivers and 10 highways, to open a grain and mineral export route independent of the Carajás railway. Feasibility finished in 2025, with a draft concession to the Court of Accounts and a federal auction planned for 2026." },
  1926: { descEn: "A gigawatt onshore wind farm powering NEOM, core of its all-renewable grid.", detailEn: "ENOWA's 1.2 GW Gayal wind farm in Tabuk province, tendered EPC-style with turbines, substation and facilities over ~31 months. After four best-and-final rounds, PowerChina, Orascom, Alfanar and L&T were shortlisted, with an award expected in 2026 and grid connection ~2028, serving NEOM's all-renewable 2030 goal." },
  1984: { descEn: "Clean Kalimantan power sent across the sea to Java.", detailEn: "One of four island interconnections in Indonesia's green super-grid, this HVDC would carry clean Kalimantan power (~13 GW of Kayan and Mentarang river hydro potential) across the sea to Java's load centre, alongside the Sumatra-Java, Sulawesi-backbone and Sumba-Bali-Java corridors. The Kalimantan link is ~$1.8 billion — core of the 2025-2034 RUPTL's 48,000 km transmission expansion." },
  2060: { descEn: "A new export gateway port on the West Java north coast.", detailEn: "At Subang in West Java serving the Jakarta metro, with container and ro-ro car terminals. Japan's JICA provides phased ODA loans — ~¥118.9 billion phase 1, ~¥70.2 billion phase 2, ~¥272.5 billion across three phases. The 37.05 km Patimban access toll road opened in 2025; with an ultimate 14 million TEU target it would be one of Indonesia's largest ports." },
  2205: { descEn: "The Middle East-North Africa's first large cross-border HVDC interconnector.", detailEn: "About 1,350 km between Egypt and Saudi Arabia (with Red Sea subsea cable) at ±500 kV, 3,000 MW total exchange, ~$1.8 billion — MENA's first large HVDC interconnector, with three converter stations including Badr. ~95% complete by early 2026, phase 1 targets late 2025/early 2026 and phase 2 ~April 2026, boosting both grids' flexibility and cross-border renewable trade." },
  2550: { descEn: "DR Congo's largest copper smelter, first anode copper end-2025.", detailEn: "Kamoa Copper's direct-to-blister smelter at the mine makes 500,000 tonnes of blister copper a year; it took feed on 21 November 2025 and produced first anode copper on 29 December, with a sulphuric-acid plant — moving DRC copper from concentrate export to on-site value-add and cutting reliance on Zambian smelters." },
  2610: { descEn: "A South Australian Burra wind-solar-storage mega-base.", detailEn: "Near Burra in South Australia, developed by France's Neoen, planning ~1.2 GW of wind plus solar and large battery storage. Phase-1 wind is operating, with more phases following — a flagship wind-solar-storage base supporting high-renewables stability in South Australia, with some power for future green hydrogen." },
  2669: { descEn: "A $1.8 billion Rio Tinto life-extension of West Pilbara Brockman.", detailEn: "In the western Pilbara of WA, Rio Tinto is investing ~$1.8 billion in the Brockman Syncline 1 (BS1) mine to extend the Brockman hub's life, with first ore now set for 2027 — a key replacement project to sustain Rio's Pilbara iron-ore capacity." },
  2734: { descEn: "CALB building a new lithium-battery base in Portugal.", detailEn: "In January 2026 China's CALB signed an investment deal with Portugal to build a lithium-battery base for the European EV and storage markets — emblematic of Chinese battery firms expanding in Europe, leveraging Iberian green power and ports." },
  2956: { descEn: "A 290-mile 500 kV line from eastern Oregon to southwest Idaho.", detailEn: "Led by Idaho Power, the Boardman-to-Hemingway line is 500 kV and ~293 miles linking the Longhorn substation east of Boardman with the Hemingway substation in Owyhee County. Construction began in Malheur County in June 2025, targeting late 2027." },
  3049: { descEn: "A California Salton Sea geothermal-brine lithium flagship, phase 1 of 25,000 tonnes of lithium hydroxide with geothermal power.", detailEn: "In the Salton Sea geothermal field of Imperial County, California — the area's first new geothermal project in a decade — phase 1 is 49.9 MW and ~25,000 tonnes of lithium hydroxide, with full potential of 300,000 tonnes LCE and 1,100 MW of baseload a year, ~$1.8 billion; Stellantis has invested over $100 million and signed an offtake." },
  3056: { descEn: "The G7's largest graphite mine, ~106,000 tonnes/year of flake concentrate, with a Bécancour anode plant.", detailEn: "Matawinie in Quebec is the G7's largest graphite mine; the phase-2 open pit makes ~106,000 tonnes/year of flake graphite concentrate, with a Bécancour battery-materials plant (13,000 tonnes of anode). ~$1.8 billion total, with ~$297 million from the Canada Growth Fund, Eni and others." },
  3205: { descEn: "JSW Steel's Karnataka Vijayanagar plant to 18 million tonnes, India's largest integrated steel works.", detailEn: "JSW Steel is investing ~150 billion rupees to expand the Vijayanagar integrated plant at Ballari, Karnataka to 18 million tonnes/year, cementing its place as India's largest single integrated steel base — a core part of the group's higher-capacity roadmap." },
  3242: { descEn: "A ~58 km driverless airport express from the Outer Ring Road to Kempegowda airport.", detailEn: "The Blue Line (phases 2A+2B) from Central Silk Board via K.R. Pura to Kempegowda International Airport, ~58 km, ~147.9 billion rupees, with driverless trains and luggage racks; ~52.5% complete by June 2025, targeting December 2027." },
  3289: { descEn: "Crown LNG plans a 7.2-million-tonne gravity-based LNG terminal 11 km off Kakinada, Andhra Pradesh.", detailEn: "Crown LNG plans a 7.2-million-tonne/year gravity-based regasification unit (GBSRU) ~11 km off Kakinada in Andhra Pradesh; it partnered the India Gas Exchange (IGX) in February 2025 and signed a pipeline-interconnection MoU with Pipeline Infrastructure in July, targeting a 2026 start and 2028 operation." },
});

/* —— 批次15：全库投资额 TOP（约15-18亿美元）约100条 —— */
Object.assign(window.ENERGY_EN, {
  3616: { descEn: "A 15-million-tonne/year open-pit coal mine supporting the Hami energy base, feeding coal-to-liquids.", detailEn: "In the Chaha­quan industrial park of Hami, Xinjiang, this 15-million-tonne/year open-pit mine supports the National Energy Group's 170-billion-yuan Hami integrated-innovation energy base, supplying a 4-million-tonne/year coal-to-liquids plant. Targeting commissioning by end-2027, it will consume 14.2 million tonnes of coal a year." },
  4045: { descEn: "The Salvador–Itaparica sea bridge in Bahia, one of South America's longest sea crossings.", detailEn: "China Railway Construction and CCCC signed the Salvador–Itaparica sea bridge in Bahia, Brazil — a ~12.4 km main bridge linking the city of Salvador to Itaparica Island. The works include a cable-stayed bridge, approach spans and power/lighting infrastructure; on completion it will be one of South America's longest sea bridges, a landmark Chinese bridge project in Latin America." },
  4065: { descEn: "The first long-process plain-carbon-steel base Chinese firms built in Indonesia.", detailEn: "In the Central Sulawesi Morowali Industrial Park, built by MCC South and others, this is the first long-process long-products plain-carbon-steel base Chinese firms invested in and built in Indonesia. After a phase-1 expansion to 3.5 million tonnes in September 2023, capacity reached 7 million tonnes of steel and 2.8 million tonnes of coke. It began making SS400 hot coil in July 2024, with refining-furnace commissioning successful and steel grades and efficiency steadily improving." },
  4172: { descEn: "The first large energy project completed under the China–Pakistan Economic Corridor.", detailEn: "Operated by Huaneng Shandong Ruyi (Pakistan) Energy, the Sahiwal plant has 2×660 MW ultra-supercritical coal units. It was the first large energy project completed and commissioned under the China–Pakistan Economic Corridor, easing Pakistan's power shortage. In 2025 the Pakistan business generated revenue of ~41.75 billion yuan." },
  4253: { descEn: "The Middle East's first light rail, built and operated by a Chinese firm, linking Mecca's pilgrimage sites.", detailEn: "The Mashair (Mecca) light rail is the Middle East's first urban rail and the first overseas railway a Chinese firm delivered under an integrated design-procure-build-operate model: ~18.1 km, 9 stations, designed for 72,000 passengers/hour. It runs only 7 days a year during the Hajj, as a shuttle between holy sites to ease congestion. In 2024 China Railway Construction completed its 10th Hajj operation, running 2,206 train trips and carrying ~2.094 million pilgrims over 7 days. It greatly relieves traffic pressure between Mecca's holy sites — a landmark project in the Middle East's premium rail market." },
  4385: { descEn: "A Huayou–Tsingshan nickel-cobalt JV in Indonesia, 120,000 tonnes/year of nickel-cobalt hydroxide via HPAL.", detailEn: "Huayou and Tsingshan's Qingshan Technology set up Huashan Nickel-Cobalt in Indonesia (Huayou indirectly ~68%), building a 120,000-tonne/year (nickel metal) MHP hydrometallurgical project over ~3 years, further expanding Huayou's Indonesian HPAL nickel capacity." },
  4406: { descEn: "Sinopec Engineering's EPC for Sonatrach's Hassi refinery in Algeria, in detailed design with civil works begun on site.", detailEn: "Algeria's Sonatrach plans a new ~5-million-tonne/year (~110,000 bpd) refinery near the Hassi Messaoud oil-and-gas hub. Sinopec Engineering Group (SEG) holds related EPC works; by 2024–2025 it was in detailed design with civil works begun on site, overall progress past 10% — a key foothold in North Africa's refining market." },
  4473: { descEn: "CMOC advances the TFM Western Zone expansion, sprinting for million-tonne copper capacity by 2028.", detailEn: "CMOC's TFM (Tenke Fungurume) copper-cobalt mine spans over 1,500 km², one of the world's largest and highest-grade producing copper-cobalt mines. Under its five-year plan, the company is advancing the Western Zone expansion; both the Western Zone and KFM phase 2 are in early exploration. TFM's existing 10K, 15K and three mixed-ore lines total 450 kt/year copper and 37 kt/year cobalt; Western Zone development will unlock more, helping CMOC sprint for million-tonne copper capacity and a top global ranking by 2028." },
  4494: { descEn: "BYD and Saudi Electricity Company sign 12.5 GWh of grid-side storage, billed as the world's largest grid-side storage project.", detailEn: "In 2025 BYD Energy Storage signed a 12.5 GWh grid-side storage contract with Saudi Electricity Company (SEC), bringing cumulative cooperation to 15.1 GWh — billed as the world's largest grid-side storage project. Using BYD's MC Cube-T system and CTS cell-to-system integration, it is deployed across five Saudi sites with ~2,364 modular MC Cube units delivered in batches, setting an industry deployment-speed record. It supports high renewable penetration and grid peaking under Saudi Vision 2030." },
  4515: { descEn: "A 220 MW renewables deal between Datang Overseas and Zambia's ZESCO, Datang's first project in Africa.", detailEn: "During the September 6, 2024 FOCAC summit, China Datang Overseas Investment signed an MoU with Zambia's national utility ZESCO to invest in and build the Taiji and other renewables projects totaling 220 MW (mostly solar), aiming to deliver three plants before 2026 to ease severe drought-driven shortages. This is Datang Overseas's first investment in Africa and Zambia, a 'from-zero' breakthrough, sited around Lusaka and nearby." },
  354: { descEn: "Woodside's $17.5-billion U.S. LNG export project in Louisiana.", detailEn: "In Calcasieu Parish, Louisiana, three liquefaction trains total 16.5 million tonnes/year — the state's largest-ever foreign direct investment. FID came in April 2025 with Stonepeak holding 40%, targeting first cargo in 2029." },
  1075: { descEn: "A giant battery-plus-data-center park next to Brisbane's South Pine substation.", detailEn: "Developed by Quinbrook next to the South Pine substation — a core node of Queensland's grid — at Brendale, this is one of Australia's largest battery projects under construction at 780 MW/3,074 MWh, partly designed for 8-hour duration. The 250 MW phase 1 reached the key backfeed/grid-connection milestone in October 2025. It has long-term capacity contracts with Origin and Stanwell and integrates a hyperscale data center, providing long-duration flexibility for Queensland's renewable transition." },
  1633: { descEn: "The first large hydropower investment project under the Belt and Road.", detailEn: "On the Jhelum River in Punjab, the Karot plant is a CPEC priority project and the first large hydropower investment under the Belt and Road, invested, built and operated by Three Gorges South Asia. ~$1.74 billion and 720 MW, it reached full commercial operation in 2022, generating ~3.2 billion kWh a year — enough for ~5 million people — and cutting ~3.5 million tonnes of CO₂ a year." },
  4091: { descEn: "A $1.355-billion expansion of Chinalco's Toromocho copper mine in Peru, to 300,000 tonnes of copper a year.", detailEn: "Chinalco's Toromocho copper mine at Morococha, Junín, Peru underwent a ~$1.355-billion expansion lifting throughput from 140,000 to 170,000 tonnes/day, raising copper output ~45% to ~300,000 tonnes/year. The expansion finished in June 2024, with a further ~$357 million for optimization and exploration in October. Open-pit at 4,500 m elevation, it is one of Peru's flagship copper mines." },
  224: { descEn: "A giant pumped-storage scheme that would double the UK's storage capacity.", detailEn: "On the shore of Loch Lochy in Scotland's Great Glen, Coire Glas is 1.5 GW with 30 GWh of storage and holds the world's first Gold-standard pumped-storage sustainability certification. SSE has put £100 million into early works and plans FID after securing a 2026 contract-for-difference, with a ~5-year build." },
  325: { descEn: "One of the largest recent U.S. airport rebuilds.", detailEn: "Designed by Gensler+HDR, Pittsburgh International's new 75,000 m² terminal consolidates check-in, security and baggage and adds 6,000 parking spaces, fully funded by airport-revenue bonds and private finance. It opened on November 18, 2025, cutting processing time 50%." },
  352: { descEn: "The world's largest offshore sour-gas development, with net-zero emissions.", detailEn: "Northwest of Abu Dhabi, Hail and Ghasha is the world's largest offshore sour-gas development, producing 1.8 billion scf/day with net-zero emissions. FID came in 2023, $11 billion of financing closed in December 2025, and production is expected in 2028." },
  801: { descEn: "One of Japan's first batch of commercial offshore wind tenders.", detailEn: "In nearshore waters from Happo Town to Noshiro City in Akita, Japan, developed by an Equinor-led consortium, this 375 MW project is among Japan's first round of promotion-zone offshore wind tenders, targeting operation in 2027 after rescheduling. Akita is Japan's most active offshore-wind region." },
  994: { descEn: "India's Green Energy Corridor phase 2 intra-state transmission across seven states, integrating 20 GW of renewables.", detailEn: "The Green Energy Corridor phase-2 intra-state scheme covers seven states including Gujarat, Karnataka, Rajasthan and Tamil Nadu, building 10,750 circuit-km of lines and 27,500 MVA of substation capacity to integrate 20 GW of renewables. Total ~120.3 billion rupees with a 33% central subsidy, targeting completion by March of FY2025-26." },
  1425: { descEn: "Ruwais chemical ecosystem's first methanol and blue ammonia.", detailEn: "TA'ZIZ (an ADNOC–ADQ JV) is building the UAE's first methanol plant (nameplate 1.8 million tonnes/year, built by Samsung E&A) and a 1-million-tonne/year low-carbon ammonia plant (built by Tecnimont, with Fertiglobe and others) in the Ruwais chemical ecosystem. Phase 1 targets 4.7 million tonnes/year of chemicals." },
  1622: { descEn: "CPECC's first win at Saudi Aramco, the largest Chinese oil-and-gas EPC in Saudi Arabia.", detailEn: "On April 24, 2024 CPECC signed a $1.699-billion EPC contract with Saudi Aramco for the Master Gas System phase-3 compression-station expansion, upgrading compression stations #1 (+3 trains), #3 (+2) and #5 (+2) plus camp pump expansion. It is the largest Chinese oil-and-gas EPC in Saudi Arabia to date and CPECC's first entry to the Aramco market, with mechanical completion expected December 2027." },
  1811: { descEn: "A low-carbon-steel 'mega hub' at the Port of Açu in Rio de Janeiro.", detailEn: "Vale, H2 Green Steel (Stegra) and the Port of Açu are partnering on a low-carbon-steel 'Mega Hub' at São João da Barra, Rio de Janeiro: Vale builds a pellet/briquette plant feeding direct-reduction furnaces to make HBI, initially on natural gas, later green hydrogen, near-zero-carbon long term. Early investment ~$1.7 billion, ~2.5 million tonnes/year of HBI, targeting operation in 2028." },
  2030: { descEn: "Microsoft's largest investment in its 29 years in Indonesia, live in Q2 2025.", detailEn: "Microsoft is investing $1.7 billion in cloud and AI infrastructure in Indonesia, its largest single investment in 29 years there. The Indonesia Central hyperscale cloud region has 3 availability zones, went live in May 2025, and offers local data residency and low-latency AI compute. IDC projects the Microsoft ecosystem will bring over $15.2 billion of economic value to Indonesia in 2025–2028 and support over 100,000 jobs." },
  2055: { descEn: "Thailand's largest industrial-port expansion, a key Eastern Economic Corridor project.", detailEn: "At Map Ta Phut, Rayong, this reclaims ~1,000 rai and adds LNG import-and-regasification facilities, with the LNG portion capped at 60 billion baht. GMTP — a JV of GULF (70%) and PTT Tank (30%) — has a 35-year PPP with Thailand's industrial-estate authority. Phase-1 reclamation began December 2021 and finished March 31, 2025; the LNG terminal starts in Q4 2025, with commercial operation in Q1 2029 and initial capacity of 5 million tonnes/year." },
  3025: { descEn: "Honolulu's Skyline elevated light rail extends ~3 miles and 6 stations into downtown.", detailEn: "The City Center segment has ~3 miles of elevated guideway and 6 stations. Construction began August 2025, Tutor Perini won at ~$1.66 billion, pier shafts started in October 2025, with above-ground piers from early 2026, targeting completion in 2030 and handover in 2031." },
  3505: { descEn: "A 12-inch auto-grade power-wafer fab in Shanghai Lingang, planned for 120,000 wafers/month.", detailEn: "Wentai's controlling shareholder built (as agent) a 12-inch auto-grade wafer fab in Shanghai Lingang (Dingtai Jiangxin), ~12 billion yuan total, planned for 120,000 wafers/month, currently at 30,000 wafers/month. The post-package power devices serve automotive electronics and AI power, providing in-house capacity to backstop the Nexperia supply cutoff." },
  3515: { descEn: "CALB's Wuhan base phase 4 lifts the base's total capacity to 50 GWh.", detailEn: "In June 2025 CALB signed with Wuhan's economic zone to launch phase 4, adding 6 production lines and ~400,000 PACK sets/year. The Wuhan base runs in four phases, ~22 billion yuan total and 50 GWh planned; phases 3-4 add 30 GWh for 12 billion yuan, with phase 4 starting up in H1 2026." },
  3524: { descEn: "A granular-silicon (FBR) base in Hohhot, the lowest-carbon-footprint polysilicon.", detailEn: "GCL Technology and TCL Zhonghuan's Inner Mongolia Xinhuan (Hohhot) project — 100,000 tonnes of granular silicon plus 10,000 tonnes of electronic-grade polysilicon — totals ~12 billion yuan, uses the silane fluidized-bed (FBR) process, and cuts costs ~15% quarter-on-quarter; GCL's four granular-silicon bases together exceed 400,000 tonnes." },
  4489: { descEn: "Three compression stations for Aramco's Master Gas System phase 3, one of the largest oil-and-gas EPCs a Chinese firm has won in Saudi Arabia.", detailEn: "In May 2024 Saudi Aramco awarded CPECC a ~$1.7-billion (~9.997-billion-yuan) EPC contract for three compression stations and supporting works under the Master Gas System Phase 3, serving the ~4,000 km gas trunk-line expansion and boosting domestic gas distribution. It is the largest oil-and-gas EPC general contract a Chinese firm has won in the Saudi market." },
  3537: { descEn: "A 12-billion-yuan ten-thousand-card GPU cluster plus domestic-server base in Zhongwei, Ningxia.", detailEn: "Over 12 billion yuan total on ~400 mu. In the Zhongwei industrial park it builds a ten-thousand-card GPU data center (320 mu, 10 data-center buildings, 200,000 m², 4,200 24-kW racks and two 1,000+-server high-performance clusters); in the Haixing development zone it builds a domestic-computer production base making 25,000–30,000 units/year at full output." },
  2029: { descEn: "U.S. hyperscaler STACK enters Malaysia with a 220 MW flagship campus in Johor.", detailEn: "U.S. hyperscale operator STACK Infrastructure is investing 7 billion ringgit (~$1.66 billion) in a 220 MW flagship JHB01 campus in Johor — 10.8 hectares and a million square feet across two facilities — for cloud and AI/ML loads. The first is a 120 MW two-story building, the second 100 MW, powered by TNB 275 kV infrastructure and a self-built substation, with phase-1 delivery expected Q4 2026." },
  4105: { descEn: "Pakistan's first ±660 kV HVDC, invested, built and operated by State Grid's CET, sending power from Sindh to Lahore.", detailEn: "The Matiari–Lahore HVDC is a CPEC priority project: ±660 kV, 4-million-kW transfer capacity, ~886 km, with converter stations at Matiari and Lahore. State Grid subsidiary China Electric Power Equipment (CET) invested, built and operates it under a BOOT model with a 25-year concession; it entered commercial operation in September 2021, Pakistan's first HVDC, and has repeatedly protected the grid from blackouts." },
  311: { descEn: "A key part of Hong Kong International Airport's three-runway system.", detailEn: "Part of the HK$141-billion three-runway system, the ~HK$12.9-billion T2 terminal expansion opened on May 27, 2026, adding ~300,000 m² and extensive smart facilities, as the airport targets 120 million passengers/year by 2030." },
  4262: { descEn: "Access expressway and supporting infrastructure for Indonesia's new capital, Nusantara (IKN).", detailEn: "CCCC subsidiaries are investing ~$1.65 billion in the access expressway and supporting infrastructure for Indonesia's new capital, Nusantara (IKN), along the Balikpapan–IKN corridor in East Kalimantan, including bridges, municipal roads and power. IKN is a national strategic project; several access-expressway segments opened by end-2024, and CCCC is also active in the new capital's rail transit, airport express and urban rail." },
  4469: { descEn: "A large producing gold mine in Guyana acquired by Zijin, transitioning from open pit to underground.", detailEn: "The Aurora gold mine in Guyana's Cuyuni-Mazaruni region was fully acquired by Zijin in August 2020 for ~C$323 million (100% of Guyana Goldfields). The mill processes 7,500 tonnes/day and is transitioning from open-pit to underground, with ~5.3 tonnes/year of underground gold over 2022–2026, sharing a greenstone-belt mineralization with Zijin's Rosebel mine in Suriname. It is one of eight overseas gold mines Zijin Gold International plans to spin off for a Hong Kong listing." },
  1334: { descEn: "A 3 GW solar plant in Asir, one of Saudi Arabia's largest single solar projects.", detailEn: "Bisha, in Saudi Arabia's Asir province, is 3 GW — the largest solar among the seven gigawatt-scale projects in Saudi's sixth NREP wave. On December 1, 2025 ACWA Power, Badeel and Aramco's SAPCO closed $8.2 billion of financing in one shot for seven projects totaling 15 GW including Bisha, with $5.9 billion of senior debt from 21 institutions, targeting operation from H2 2027 to H1 2028." },
  132: { descEn: "Hainan's second large offshore-wind demonstration project.", detailEn: "In waters north of Danzhou, Hainan, this 1,200 MW project finished installing its last turbine in February 2025, generating ~3.82 billion kWh a year and supporting Hainan's self-reliant, reliable power supply." },
  556: { descEn: "A green-compute base in Ya'an, Sichuan, carrying both 'east-data' and 'west-compute' roles.", detailEn: "The Ya'an big-data park has built 40,000 racks, exceeds 5,912 PFLOPS of compute, holds PUE steadily below 1.2, and has drawn over 171 projects with cumulative investment of 11.4 billion yuan. Phase 2 invests 7.5 billion yuan; on completion compute will pass 20,000 PFLOPS." },
  832: { descEn: "Nepal's largest hydropower project under construction.", detailEn: "On the Arun River in Koshi Province, Nepal, this 900 MW project is developed by a wholly-owned subsidiary of India's SJVN. In 2024 it holed through an 11.8 km headrace tunnel — one of South Asia's largest hydro projects under construction. On completion most of its power will be exported to India, significant for Nepal's foreign-exchange earnings." },
  954: { descEn: "A 900 MW HVDC offshore connection in Germany's North Sea for the EnBW He Dreiht wind farm.", detailEn: "BorWin5's converter platform BorWin epsilon, ~12,300 tonnes, was installed offshore in May 2025; via ~110 km of submarine cable it connects the He Dreiht wind farm, then ~120 km of land cable to the Garrel/Ost converter station. The full system energized in October 2025 — TenneT's fourth HVDC offshore project near Borkum." },
  1018: { descEn: "A BMW battery plant halted and shelved in June 2025.", detailEn: "AESC's $1.6-billion plant in Florence County, South Carolina, supplying BMW with cylindrical cells (~1,600 jobs), paused construction in June 2025 amid U.S. tariff and EV-subsidy uncertainty and tariffs on its largely China-sourced equipment. As of November 2025 it remains frozen, with ~$1.2 billion invested and civil works ~75% done; officials say it may restart within 8–12 months — a sample of a major project 'on hold.'" },
  1039: { descEn: "The UK's largest steelworks replaces blast furnaces with an electric arc furnace, cutting emissions 90%.", detailEn: "Tata Steel is building a £1.25-billion electric arc furnace at Port Talbot, Wales — with £500 million of UK government support — to replace shut blast furnaces; after 2027 startup it will cut the plant's emissions ~90% (~5 million tonnes CO₂/year), saving ~5,000 jobs. Ground was broken July 14, 2025, with old annealing demolition done in autumn/winter and over a thousand piles up to 28 m deep plus a flue-gas plant started from December — a giant new grid load for the UK." },
  1180: { descEn: "Oman's low-carbon marine-LNG bunkering hub.", detailEn: "TotalEnergies (80%) and OQEP (20%) are building a 1-million-tonne/year liquefaction plant at Sohar Port in Oman, dedicated to LNG bunkering for ships, fully electric-driven with 300 MW of solar, with carbon intensity claimed ~90% below the global average. Ground was broken in May 2025, with tank topping-out within the year and ~39% overall progress, targeting LNG production in Q1 2028." },
  1294: { descEn: "The fourth production system at the Mero field in the Libra block, first oil two months early.", detailEn: "SBM Offshore built and leases this FPSO to Petrobras; it reached Brazil in March 2025 and started up at the pre-salt Mero field in the Santos Basin on May 24 — two months ahead of plan — completing a 72-hour continuous production test to formally enter service. With it, Mero's four FPSOs raise the field's total capacity from 590,000 to 770,000 barrels/day." },
  1335: { descEn: "A 3 GW solar plant in Medina, part of an $8.2-billion packaged financing.", detailEn: "Humaij solar, in Saudi Arabia's Medina province, is 3 GW — one of seven gigawatt-scale projects (15 GW total) whose $8.2-billion packaged financing ACWA Power, Badeel and SAPCO closed in December 2025. SPPC is the offtaker; using a local supply chain, it targets commercial operation from H2 2027 to H1 2028." },
  1619: { descEn: "Iraq's largest gas-processing plant, an EPSCC contract signed with TotalEnergies.", detailEn: "CPECC, a subsidiary of CNPC Engineering, signed a $1.601-billion (~11.5-billion-yuan) EPSCC contract with TotalEnergies for the Artawi field gas-processing plant in Iraq, building a 320-million-scf/day gas-processing unit and supporting facilities to process associated gas from the Artawi, West Qurna 2 and Majnoon fields. With a 39-month schedule, it is the core of TotalEnergies' GGIP integrated energy project, helping Iraq cut gas imports and end flaring." },
  2006: { descEn: "Amkor's most-advanced packaging plant, live in Q3 2025.", detailEn: "In the Anfeng 2C industrial park in Bac Ninh, Amkor is building its most-advanced packaging plant — $1.6 billion total over three phases, phase 1 at $520 million. After trial production in Q1–Q2 2025, it formally started up in Q3, reaching full output by 2035 with ~10,000 staff and 3.6 billion units/year, starting with advanced SiP and memory packaging." },
  2258: { descEn: "A southern deepwater port for green hydrogen/ammonia export and a sub-Saharan gateway, operational by 2028.", detailEn: "Investing ~$1.6 billion (~15 billion dirhams) in a deepwater Atlantic port at Dakhla, ~46% of the work was done by November 2025, with the offshore trestle near complete and basins 2 and 3 under construction. Positioned as a trade-and-industry hub and green-hydrogen/ammonia export gateway, it will create ~20,000 related jobs, targeting operation in 2028." },
  2611: { descEn: "One of Queensland's largest wind-solar-storage hybrid hubs.", detailEn: "At Clarke Creek in central Queensland, developed by Squadron Energy (Forrest's group), this plans ~1 GW of wind plus solar and battery storage, built in stages. The wind phase 1 is grid-connected — Queensland's largest wind-solar-storage hybrid hub, supporting renewable supply as the state retires coal." },
  2634: { descEn: "A flagship green-steel conversion of the Whyalla steelworks in South Australia.", detailEn: "The Whyalla steelworks in South Australia is converting from coal blast furnaces to electric arc furnaces, with low-emission energy and scrap, to make green steel and green iron. In 2025 the state and federal governments announced a A$2.4-billion support package and a A$1-billion green-iron investment fund (half to Whyalla) — Australia's green-steel flagship, targeting EAF startup around 2027." },
  2668: { descEn: "A new Pilbara iron mine, 31 million tonnes/year (Rio Tinto/Hancock).", detailEn: "In the Pilbara of Western Australia, Rio Tinto and Hancock are investing ~$1.61 billion to develop Hope Downs 2, with two above-water-table iron pits totaling 31 million tonnes/year of capacity plus supporting infrastructure, first ore expected in 2027 — extending Pilbara iron capacity." },
  2900: { descEn: "The largest single solar-plus-storage project in the U.S., approved in Morrow County, Oregon.", detailEn: "In Morrow County, Oregon, approved in November 2025 by the state's energy facility siting council, Sunstone is 1,200 MW solar plus 1,200 MW storage — nearly doubling the state's solar capacity. After original developer Pine Gate's bankruptcy, Amazon Energy's acquisition was approved by a bankruptcy court in January 2026, with phased construction planned to begin in 2026." },
  2925: { descEn: "Microsoft's 20-year PPA drives a restart of Three Mile Island Unit 1 to power AI data centers.", detailEn: "Constellation is investing ~$1.6 billion to restart the Three Mile Island Unit 1 PWR, shut in 2019, with a 20-year PPA to Microsoft taking all 835 MW of carbon-free power for its PJM data centers. Operation is expected in 2028, possibly as early as 2027 if PJM approves, with a license extension sought to 2054." },
  2930: { descEn: "A 615 MW Iowa BWR restart, with Google on a 25-year PPA (Google × NextEra).", detailEn: "Duane Arnold closed in 2020; NextEra is leading the restart, with Google on a 25-year PPA taking the output and planning up to 6 data centers just south of the site. The restart costs over $1.6 billion, with NRC licensing expected by January 2028 and a target to resume generation in early 2029." },
  3051: { descEn: "A Nevada lithium-boron co-deposit, with a $996-million DOE loan, that could quadruple U.S. lithium supply.", detailEn: "This Nevada lithium-boron co-deposit closed a $996-million DOE loan in January 2025, got BLM final approval in October 2024, and had its development upheld by a federal court in March 2026; engineering is over 70%, and on startup it would quadruple U.S. lithium supply." },
  3176: { descEn: "Adani's 2,250 MW Gandikota phase-2 pumped storage in Andhra Pradesh's YSR Kadapa, approved by the state in 2026.", detailEn: "In 2026 Andhra Pradesh approved allotting the 2,250 MW Gandikota phase-2 pumped storage to Adani Hydro, in YSR Kadapa district, requiring completion within 72 months, sited next to the 1,800 MW phase 1 — further expanding Adani's pumped-storage cluster in Andhra Pradesh." },
  3249: { descEn: "Bihar's first metro: Patna Metro's five-station segment opened in October 2025.", detailEn: "The first five stations of Patna Metro opened on October 6, 2025 — Bihar's first metro — costing ~133.76 billion rupees (excluding land acquisition)." },
  4264: { descEn: "Nigeria's first automated deepwater port, built and operated by China Harbour.", detailEn: "Lekki Deep Sea Port, ~60 km east of Lagos, is Nigeria's first automated deepwater port. China Harbour (CHEC) handled construction, secured China Development Bank (CDB) loan financing, holds 54% equity and operates it on a 16-year lease. It opened in January 2023, ending Nigeria's lack of an international transshipment hub able to handle ships over 100,000 tonnes, with ~1.2 million TEU/year of design throughput. By May 2025 it had launched bonded-vehicle and container-freight-station services, becoming a West African regional hub." },
  3121: { descEn: "A 1,125 MW plant on Bhutan's Kuri River, Bhutan's largest PPP hydropower.", detailEn: "A run-of-river project on Bhutan's Kuri River in Mongar, with 6×187.5 MW units totaling 1,125 MW. In November 2025 Tata Power and DGPC signed a commercial agreement (DGPC 60%, Tata 40%), with Tata injecting ~15.72 billion rupees; total ~131 billion rupees, making it Bhutan's second-largest hydropower and largest PPP hydropower." },
  902: { descEn: "A landmark project completing central China's UHV AC ring grid, linking Hubei and Jiangxi.", detailEn: "Running from Wuhan via Huangshi to the Nanchang Ganjiang 1,000 kV substation, this builds 451.2 km of double-circuit lines across Hubei and Jiangxi. Commissioned on November 1, 2024, it marks full completion of central China's UHV AC ring grid, raising inter-provincial exchange capacity by 4.7 million kW." },
  3472: { descEn: "A 1.4-million-kW pumped storage in Gaochang, Turpan, Xinjiang, approved June 2025.", detailEn: "In Gaochang district, Turpan, Xinjiang, this 1.4-million-kW pumped storage, ~10.834 billion yuan total, was approved by the regional NDRC in June 2025. Serving peaking for southern Xinjiang's large renewable base, it targets commissioning in 2031." },
  122: { descEn: "The world's largest single green-ammonia project.", detailEn: "In Da'an, Baicheng, Jilin, this builds 700 MW of wind plus 100 MW of solar to make 32,000 tonnes/year of green hydrogen and 180,000 tonnes of green ammonia, using the world's largest alkaline-plus-PEM hybrid hydrogen production. It started up in July 2025, cutting ~650,000 tonnes of carbon a year." },
  147: { descEn: "Indiana's largest solar plant.", detailEn: "In Indiana, Mammoth Solar has ~1.3 GW (AC) of planned capacity on ~50,000 acres, developed by Doral Renewables with Bechtel as EPC. The northern phase 1 is operational with the rest finishing in Q4 2026; over $1.5 billion of financing makes it the Midwest's largest single solar investment." },
  156: { descEn: "The largest single-contract wind project in the Middle East and Africa to date.", detailEn: "Split between Ras Ghareb and Ras Shukeir at 550 MW each, this comprises 138 Envision 8 MW turbines. ACWA Power and HAU Energy closed $1.2 billion of financing in January 2025, with PowerChina as EPC; construction began January 2025, with full operation expected in Q2 2027." },
  260: { descEn: "The UK's first EV battery gigafactory.", detailEn: "Next to Nissan's Sunderland plant, Envision AESC's gigafactory is 12 GWh/year near-term, 35 GWh long-term, creating over 4,500 jobs, backed by the UK's National Wealth Fund and export-credit guarantees — a core of UK EV-supply-chain localization." },
  272: { descEn: "Gansu's national 'east-data-west-compute' hub.", detailEn: "Qingyang has built 31,000 standard racks and exceeded 50,000 PFLOPS of compute, drawing over 300 digital-economy firms, with a target of 100,000 PFLOPS by end-2025 to build the country's largest AI-compute base, with seven domestic ten-thousand-card clusters under construction." },
  287: { descEn: "A large AI data center at Tomakomai, Hokkaido (SoftBank).", detailEn: "SoftBank is developing a 300+ MW AI data center at Tomakomai, Hokkaido, and converting a former Sharp factory in Sakai, Osaka into an AI data center — emblematic of Japan's explosive AI-infrastructure growth." },
  624: { descEn: "One of the world's highest-grade copper mines, reopening a zone idle for 18 years in 2026.", detailEn: "In Zambia's Copperbelt, Konkola Copper Mines has an average copper grade of 2.9% — among the world's highest — with a full chain of mine, mill and smelter. After Vedanta regained management in 2024, it announced a $1.5-billion expansion, reopening the Chingola B zone idle for 18 years in May 2026, targeting 300,000 tonnes/year of copper by 2031." },
  722: { descEn: "Systematic expansion by the world's largest uranium producer.", detailEn: "Kazatomprom is systematically expanding via in-situ leaching in uranium-rich areas like Turkestan province, with 2025 uranium output expected at 25,000–26,500 tonnes, ~43% of the world's. Besides KATCO's new mine startup, JV mines such as Inkai and Budenovskoye are ramping up in parallel." },
  843: { descEn: "China's first 100 MW-scale tidal-current demonstration plant.", detailEn: "In waters north of Xiushan Island, Daishan, Zhoushan, Zhejiang, a JV of SPIC Zhejiang and Hangzhou Lindong New Energy builds on the world's longest continuously-operating LHD MW-scale tidal-current base; in September 2025 it began building a 100 MW demonstration plant, with Zhoushan named a national 100 MW-scale tidal-current pilot." },
  906: { descEn: "A 1,000 kV UHV AC project forming Shandong's Jiaodong Peninsula backbone, boosting Yantai-Weihai clean-power delivery.", detailEn: "The project builds the Haiyang West 1,000 kV switching station and expands the Changle and Gaoxiang 1,000 kV substations, plus north and south lines totaling 2×564.9 km. Approved in January 2025 and started June 17, it must be commissioned before October 2026." },
  997: { descEn: "A trans-Sunda-Strait HVDC interconnection sending Sumatra's clean energy to Java.", detailEn: "Indonesia's Sumatra–Java interconnection uses HVDC across the ~112 km Sunda Strait, included in the 2025–2034 power-supply business plan, part of a 48,000 km grid-expansion program to send Sumatran geothermal and renewables to high-load Java." },
  1085: { descEn: "China's largest unit-capacity, world's highest-head pumped storage.", detailEn: "In Tiantai, Taizhou, Zhejiang, this has 4 reversible units of 425,000 kW each, totaling 1.7 million kW, with a 724 m rated head — the world's highest — Three Gorges' first pumped-storage project started in the 14th Five-Year period, ~10.7 billion yuan total. It provides peaking, frequency/phase regulation and emergency backup, supporting high-renewable integration and grid security across the Yangtze Delta. On December 25, 2025 its first unit connected to the grid, marking another key breakthrough in major pumped-storage equipment and engineering." },
  1137: { descEn: "Lagos's third urban rail line, linking Victoria Island and Lekki.", detailEn: "Lagos's metro authority LAMATA is advancing the Green Line — the third urban rail after the Blue and Red lines — built by China Harbour (CHEC). The state unveiled the full Green Line plan on April 10, 2025 and broke ground that month, with initial daily ridership projected at ~500,000; in future it will link Victoria Island, the Lekki Free Trade Zone and other growth poles and connect to Lekki Deep Sea Port's collection-and-distribution. The Blue Line has carried over 5 million riders in two years, the Red Line's first segment is open, and the Green Line will further complete Lagos's metro network." },
  1237: { descEn: "A 400,000-tonne green-ammonia export project at the Port of Pecém.", detailEn: "Norway's Fuella signed an agreement with the Port of Pecém to develop a large green-ammonia project in the Pecém industrial-port zone in Ceará, producing 400,000 tonnes/year of green ammonia entirely for export, with investment of ~9 billion reais — adding capacity to Ceará's green-hydrogen/ammonia export hub." },
  1239: { descEn: "Equinor's evaluation of 7 offshore wind projects in Brazil, including Colibri.", detailEn: "Equinor and Petrobras agreed to evaluate 7 offshore wind projects in Brazil, including Ibitucatu off Ceará and Colibri across the Rio Grande do Norte and Ceará waters, with the agreement valid to 2028. Brazil's federal environmental agency IBAMA has ~75 projects under review totaling ~185 GW, with Equinor, Shell, TotalEnergies and others involved." },
  1322: { descEn: "The world's niobium leader expands, building battery-anode-material capacity.", detailEn: "CBMM's niobium mine at Araxá, Minas Gerais is the world's largest, supplying ~80% of global niobium. The company began a ~9-billion-real expansion cycle in 2023, aiming to double sales by 2030. A 1.2-billion-real new niobium plant will add over 20,000 tonnes/year of niobium oxide; and it built the world's largest niobium-based anode-materials plant, making Echion's XNO niobium-oxide anode material for batteries." },
  1324: { descEn: "A Casa de Pedra P15 iron expansion in Congonhas, sprinting for 68 million tonnes of capacity.", detailEn: "The core of the Casa de Pedra complex expansion at Congonhas, Minas Gerais is the Itabirito P15 project. Started in late 2024, the company is investing ~15 billion reais in Minas over 2024–2027, ~8 billion of it on a new concentrator. P15 targets startup in 2027, adding ~16.5 million tonnes/year of 67.5–68% Fe high-grade pellet feed, with capacity rising from ~42 million to ~68 million tonnes by 2028." },
  1347: { descEn: "Iraq's first gigawatt-scale solar plant, part of TotalEnergies' GGIP integrated project.", detailEn: "Ratawi solar is part of TotalEnergies' $27-billion GGIP gas-and-power integrated project, near the Ratawi field in Basra, Iraq, at 1 GW (1.25 GWp) on ~2,200 hectares — Iraq's first gigawatt-scale solar. TotalEnergies (45%), Basra Oil (30%) and QatarEnergy (25%) partner; construction began March 2025, with a first 250 MW phase targeting late-2025 startup." },
  1363: { descEn: "Saudi Arabia's second batch of standalone storage, a 12 GWh tender across six sites.", detailEn: "Through its Principal Buyer subsidiary, SPPC launched a second batch of standalone-storage tenders: six 500 MW/2,000 MWh projects — Samha in Qassim, Al-Leeth/Khulis/Ashyrah in Mecca, Al-Henakiyah in Medina and Sadawi in the Eastern Province — totaling 3 GW/12 GWh. With projects under construction and already tendered, Saudi's large-scale storage under construction and tendered nears 50 GWh." },
  1370: { descEn: "An Iraqi 3 GW solar-plus-storage project, with 500 MWh of batteries.", detailEn: "U.S. developer UGT Renewables reached a deal with Iraq's federal government to build 3 GW of solar plus up to 500 MWh of battery storage and ~1,000 km of HVDC lines, with two years of technology transfer and O&M training. Backed by the U.S. EXIM Bank and UK Export Finance, with JPMorgan as lead arranger, it was signed in May 2025." },
  1389: { descEn: "Khazna's first Saudi campus, an AI data center in Dammam.", detailEn: "In December 2025 the UAE's Khazna (G42 group) announced its entry to Saudi Arabia, acquiring 225,000 m² in Dammam to build its first Saudi data-center campus offering up to 200 MW of AI-ready capacity, with a modular, scalable architecture serving cloud, AI and high-performance computing." },
  1416: { descEn: "Aramco's Zuluf field increment, building a central processing facility.", detailEn: "The Zuluf increment builds a central processing facility at the offshore Zuluf field to process a combined 600,000 barrels/day of crude — one of Aramco's largest offshore oil-boosting works. It continues EPC procurement and construction of offshore platforms, subsea pipelines and onshore processing, with production expected in 2026." },
  1494: { descEn: "Large pellet and galvanizing investments at Severstal's Cherepovets works.", detailEn: "Severstal is advancing several major investments at its Cherepovets steelworks: an iron-ore pellet complex (~116 billion rubles, its largest project since the plant was built) and, from 2026, a new continuous hot-dip galvanizing line (over 15 billion rubles, 460,000 tonnes/year, operational 2027), plus a waste-heat power plant using blast-furnace gas. Its 2026 investment plan is ~98.3 billion rubles." },
  1524: { descEn: "Key Arctic-route port and channel dredging works.", detailEn: "Sabetta Port on the Yamal Peninsula is the core hub of Yamal LNG and the Northern Sea Route. Rosatom plans to procure 10 large dredgers in 2026–2028 for Sabetta, with annual maintenance dredging estimated at 3.9–5 million m³; total NSR dredging in 2026–2030 is projected at 60 million m³. In 2025 Sabetta shipped 270 LNG cargoes, with Arctic oil and gas moving through to Asian markets." },
  1545: { descEn: "A new hydrocracker for deeper processing at the TANECO refinery in Tatarstan.", detailEn: "Tatneft is expanding its TANECO refinery at Nizhnekamsk in 2025, building a 1.2-million-tonne/year hydrocracker making 640,000 tonnes of Euro-VI low-sulfur diesel and 229,000 tonnes of naphtha, deepening crude processing and raising the share of high-value products. TANECO processed 17 million tonnes of crude in 2024, making 2.7 million tonnes of gasoline and 8.5 million tonnes of diesel. The expansion completed and the new unit started up in October 2025." },
  1558: { descEn: "Russia's largest lithium mine in Murmansk, developed by a Nornickel–Rosatom JV.", detailEn: "In Murmansk province, Russia's largest lithium mine. Polar Lithium (a JV of Norilsk Nickel and Rosatom's mining arm) won development rights in 2023, planning 45,000 tonnes/year of lithium carbonate and hydroxide, working with Beijing MMC on beneficiation/metallurgy; the feasibility study finished in Q1 2025, with startup 3–4 years ahead of the original plan." },
  1590: { descEn: "The Middle East's largest single solar plant at the time, fully commercial in 2025.", detailEn: "Built by an EPC consortium of China Energy Engineering International, Guangdong Electric Power and the Northwest Institute, Al Shuaibah comprises ASB1 (600 MW) and ASB2 (2,000 MW) over 52.54 km², using N-type bifacial modules and single-axis trackers, with an ACWA Power-led project company as owner. It fully grid-connected on January 15, 2025 and got its initial commercial-operation certificate on May 11 — the Middle East's largest single solar plant at the time." },
  1650: { descEn: "Africa's largest copper mine, with the world's largest single-line copper smelter.", detailEn: "In central Africa's Katanga copper-cobalt belt, Kamoa-Kakula is the world's fourth-largest and Africa's largest copper mine; Zijin holds ~45% as the largest shareholder, with Ivanhoe operating. In 2024 the phase-3 mill reached full output, exceeding 600,000 tonnes/year of copper. A supporting 500,000-tonne/year 'direct-to-blister' smelter was lit in November 2025 and produced its first anode copper on December 29, with Zijin subsidiary Gold Mountain offtaking 80% of the anode copper as it ramps through 2026." },
  1655: { descEn: "One of the world's ten largest gold mines, restarted in late 2023.", detailEn: "In Enga province, Porgera is one of the world's ten largest gold mines. It was placed on care-and-maintenance from April 2020 over a mining-lease renewal dispute. After over three years of negotiation, it met the conditions for full restart on December 22, 2023 and began ramping up, producing first gold in Q1 2024; Zijin's stake fell from 47.5% to 24.5%. With ~417 tonnes of gold resources, it averages ~21 tonnes/year of gold at full output, with a mine life over 20 years." },
  1720: { descEn: "A new ultra-deepwater frontier in southern Brazil, the Pelotas Basin's multiple blocks.", detailEn: "Petrobras won 29 blocks in the Pelotas Basin in ANP's fourth permanent-offer round, with Shell also holding several exploration blocks. Conjugate to Namibia's Orange Basin, the basin is seen as a high-potential new South Atlantic frontier. Petrobras plans ~$7.5 billion over five years for Santos, Pelotas and equatorial-margin exploration, with an ultra-deepwater drillship moving to the frontier after Q2 2026." },
  1746: { descEn: "A large green-hydrogen/ammonia integrated project at the Port of Pecém.", detailEn: "FRV (Abdul Latif Jameel Energy) and China's Envision allied in 2025 to build a 500 MW electrolysis plant and supporting green-ammonia works at the Port of Pecém, using Envision's AI-orchestrated integrated system. In development since 2023, it has secured land and water rights, with engineering and EIA advancing; operation is expected in 2030, expandable to 2 GW of electrolysis and 1.6 million tonnes/year of green ammonia for Brazil, Europe and Asia." },
  1747: { descEn: "Norway's Fuella green-hydrogen mega-plant at Pecém.", detailEn: "Norwegian developer Fuella signed a pre-contract with the Ceará state government to build an industrial-scale plant making 400,000 tonnes/year of renewable hydrogen in the Pecém industrial-port zone, ~$1.5 billion, expected to create over a thousand jobs. Part of Ceará's green-hydrogen hub portfolio, it leverages the port's export conditions for international markets, targeting construction in 2026–2028 alongside the hub's supporting facilities." },
  1748: { descEn: "The restart and expansion of Brazil's first industrial-scale green-hydrogen plant.", detailEn: "Unigel built Brazil's first industrial-scale green-hydrogen plant (phase-1 60 MW) in the Camaçari industrial complex in Bahia. Plans for phases 2 and 3 would expand electrolysis to ~600 MW, achieving 100,000 tonnes/year of green hydrogen and 600,000 tonnes of hydrogen-based green ammonia by 2027, ~$1.5 billion total. Integrated production uses fertilizer units leased from Petrobras, aiming to restart and greatly expand to serve fertilizer and export markets." },
  1830: { descEn: "A world-class CCS hub capturing CO₂ from Aramco gas plants for saline-aquifer storage.", detailEn: "In December 2024 three parties signed a shareholders' agreement, with Aramco holding 60% and Linde and SLB 20% each. Phase 1 captures and stores 9 million tonnes/year of CO₂ (~6 million from Aramco gas plants, ~3 million from other industrial sources), compressed via pipeline and injected into onshore saline aquifers for permanent storage, with later phased expansion. A ~$1.5-billion EPC was awarded to L&T in 2025, targeting commissioning by end-2027 and supplying carbon reductions for blue hydrogen and ammonia." },
  1834: { descEn: "Tight-gas expansion at southern Ghawar, targeting 750 million scf/day.", detailEn: "South Ghawar is Aramco's second unconventional gas stream, with first gas in late 2023, initially with 300 million scf/day of feed gas and 38,000 barrels/day of condensate processing. It plans to gradually expand production and processing to ~750 million scf/day of feed gas, fed into the national gas system, supporting the goal of ~80% growth in sales-gas capacity by 2030 vs 2021. Expansion units are expected to come online over 2026–2028." },
  1856: { descEn: "A fleet of 380 kV substations and lines for NREP round 7's 5.3 GW of renewables.", detailEn: "Supporting SPPC's round 7 (5,300 MW), SEC tendered several 380 kV BSPs and overhead lines in March 2026, including Ashayrah/Mozeraah wind, Mastura/Tumair/Al-Majmaah/NIFI wind-and-solar, and East Al-Amoah and North Asir wind — covering western, southern and central regions, plus expansions at Sudair and PP-11. Awards are expected from 2026 with operation around 2028." },
  1887: { descEn: "The world's largest AI-inference data center in Dammam, inference-only.", detailEn: "Aramco Digital and Groq are building the world's largest AI-inference data center in Dammam, opening EMEA's largest AI-compute hub at LEAP 2025. Groq got a $1.5-billion boost for expansion, targeting deployment of a billion tokens/second of inference, supporting SDAIA's Arabic LLM ALLaM, doing inference only (no training), with continued expansion in 2026." },
  1893: { descEn: "A large Riyadh colocation campus, planned for over 320 MW.", detailEn: "Gulf Data Hub is entering Riyadh, with 22 MW of IT load currently under construction; Saudi's capacity under construction and planned exceeds 320 MW. In March 2026 KKR and GDH committed over $5 billion of investment for expansion, with Riyadh a key market beyond the Gulf, the campus phased to 2027 and beyond." },
  1895: { descEn: "An Oracle NEOM cloud region, carried by ZeroPoint DC.", detailEn: "Oracle is planning three cloud regions in Saudi Arabia — Jeddah, Riyadh and NEOM — part of a $1.5-billion investment. The NEOM region is carried by ZeroPoint DC's hyperscale data center (NEOM 51%, EzdiTek 49%), with Oracle as the first tenant; after the Jeddah and Riyadh regions go live, the NEOM node is a forward-looking deployment yet to land." },
});

/* —— 批次16：全库投资额 TOP（约13-15亿美元）约100条 —— */
Object.assign(window.ENERGY_EN, {
  1902: { descEn: "The Red Line extends west from King Saud University to Diriyah Gate, adding 5 stations.", detailEn: "Riyadh's Royal Commission awarded the Red Line extension in January 2026, running 8.4 km west from King Saud University to the Diriyah Gate development with 5 new stations, including a 7.1 km deep tunnel and 1.3 km of viaduct, with one station a future interchange with Line 7. Directly linking Al-Turaif, Al-Bajiri historic areas and the opera house, it would cut ~150,000 car trips a day, with a ~6-year build." },
  1910: { descEn: "Mecca's first dedicated international airport, serving the Hajj pilgrimage.", detailEn: "In 2026 the Royal Commission for Mecca City and Holy Sites confirmed completed basic planning for Mecca's first dedicated international airport and formal approval of its strategic economic-investment scheme. Built to international standards, it serves millions of Hajj pilgrims a year, easing peak flows and improving service; the commission will bring in private capital for an investment model and ensure it does not disrupt nearby city airports. Coordinated with Mecca metro planning, it delivers Vision 2030 Hajj-capacity expansion." },
  1923: { descEn: "A northwestern iron mine supplying green-iron feedstock for NEOM.", detailEn: "One of Saudi Arabia's largest iron mines, in the NEOM northwest region southwest of Tabuk near Duba port, with ~383 million tonnes at 40% iron. The NEOM Investment Fund submitted studies and Hadeed is doing a technical evaluation of its development, positioned as upstream feedstock for the green-iron (DRI) and steel chain. It is advancing toward revival and development under Vision 2030's mining and green-steel strategies." },
  1933: { descEn: "A 100%-renewable off-grid system providing 24/7 power and water to the AMAALA wellness destination.", detailEn: "Led by EDF and Masdar (with Korea East-West Power and Suez), this won a 25-year multi-utility concession in September 2023 and closed ~$1.5 billion of financing in October–November 2024. It has 250 MW of solar, 700 MWh of battery storage, transmission/distribution and 37,000 tonnes/day of desalination, fully off-grid and 100% renewable, cutting ~350,000 tonnes of carbon a year and supplying ~65,000 people. It is advancing alongside AMAALA phase-1's opening." },
  1963: { descEn: "Thailand's large reservoir floating-solar program.", detailEn: "EGAT is building hydro-floating-solar hybrids in batches at reservoirs nationwide, planning 15 projects totaling ~2.7 GW. The first, 45 MW at Sirindhorn reservoir, came online in 2021 and was once the world's largest hydro-solar hybrid; a 24 MW project at Ubol Ratana is in tender; and a third, 140 MW at Srinagarind in Kanchanaburi, targets 2026 operation. Using existing hydropower for grid regulation and avoiding land use, it is a core lever for Thailand's carbon-neutral grid." },
  2008: { descEn: "Intel's largest global assembly-and-test base, expanding steadily.", detailEn: "Intel's assembly-and-test plant in Saigon Hi-Tech Park (SHTP) has cumulative investment of ~$1.5 billion and over 6,000 staff — its largest global packaging-and-test base, with over half its global capacity. In 2024-25 it absorbed test lines relocated from Costa Rica and Panther Lake and other 18A products, exporting $11.4 billion in 2024." },
  2012: { descEn: "Sunwoda's first ASEAN EV-cell plant, $1.5 billion.", detailEn: "Thailand's Board of Investment approved Sunwoda in March 2025 to invest over $1 billion (THB 50 billion, ~$1.5 billion) in two plants in the Chonburi EEC, making EV lithium-ion cells and storage systems — its first ASEAN EV-cell plant, starting production from 2025 with over 1,000 staff." },
  2027: { descEn: "Part of the Kuok Group's K2 Strategic, a 234 MW design campus in Sedenak, Johor.", detailEn: "The Kuok Group's K2 Strategic is building a hyperscale data center on 60 acres in Sedenak Tech Park, Johor, with 234 MW of design IT capacity and ultimately 300 MW of gross power. It signed a power-supply agreement with TNB in 2023; a first 40 MW IT load was built and commissioned within 11 months in 2024, targeting wholesale compute for hyperscale cloud providers." },
  2065: { descEn: "An upgrade of the Dumai refinery in Riau, Sumatra, cutting costs and boosting output.", detailEn: "The Dumai refinery RDMP RU II upgrade in Riau, ~$1.5 billion, aims to raise domestic fuel capacity and cut import reliance. Pertamina has signed MoUs with local Nindya Karya and Korea's DH Global Holdings for joint study, as part of Pertamina's ~$48-billion six-refinery upgrade program, targeting completion around 2027." },
  2070: { descEn: "An upgrade of Vietnam's Dung Quat refinery in Quang Ngai to Euro-5 standards.", detailEn: "The Dung Quat refinery in Quang Ngai, operated by Binh Son Refining (BSR), is undergoing a ~$1.5-billion upgrade and expansion on 51.67 hectares. On January 14, 2026 BSR signed the site-leveling contract with PETROCONs (10-month schedule); the EPC package (~$1.22 billion) opened February 3, 2026 with award in March, and ~37-month EPC. After 2028 completion, capacity rises from 148,000 to 171,000 barrels/day, with products meeting Euro-5." },
  2080: { descEn: "Thailand's third LNG terminal, phase 3 of the Map Ta Phut industrial port.", detailEn: "Gulf MTP (a JV of Gulf Development 70% and PTT Tank 30%) is building Thailand's third LNG terminal on ~200 rai of reclaimed land at Map Ta Phut industrial port phase 3, initially 8 MTPA, expandable to 10.8 MTPA. In July 2025 it signed a topside EPCC contract (~KRW 1.5 trillion) with a PEC-CAZ consortium of Korea's POSCO E&C and Thailand's CAZ. Construction starts Q4 2025, targeting Q1 2029 operation." },
  2088: { descEn: "Continued expansion of the world's largest nickel mine.", detailEn: "At Weda Bay in North Maluku, an Eramet–Tsingshan JV, the world's largest nickel mine. After completing EIA and feasibility in 2024 it planned to ramp toward ~60 million wet tonnes/year; the 2025 quota rose to 42 million wet tonnes but the early-2026 quota was sharply cut to an initial 12 million wet tonnes, with the company applying for an increase and planning a ~€500-million share issue in H2 2026 to support expansion." },
  2096: { descEn: "Expansion of the largest overseas Chinese potash base.", detailEn: "At Asia Potash's town in Thakhek, Khammouane, Laos, sitting on over a billion tonnes of pure-potash reserves. A 3-million-tonne/year potassium-chloride plant is built; an October 2023 MoU added a 5-million-tonne expansion, advancing at a million-tonne-a-year pace toward 5 million tonnes/year. Laos's potassium-chloride exports to China rose from 128,000 tonnes in 2020 to 2.07 million tonnes in 2024, China's fourth-largest source." },
  2268: { descEn: "An Arzew naphtha cracker adding 1.2 million tonnes of gasoline capacity from March 2027.", detailEn: "Part of Algeria's $7-billion (2025–2029) refining-and-petrochemical portfolio, the Arzew naphtha cracker will add 1.2 million tonnes/year of gasoline capacity from March 2027; a Skikda fuel-cracking project targets January 2029 startup. They deepen Sonatrach's hydrocarbon processing and raise the share of high-value products." },
  2271: { descEn: "Algeria's Bled El Hadba phosphate mine, 10 million tonnes/year, with integrated phosphate fertilizer.", detailEn: "Algeria is investing ~$1.5 billion to mine two phosphate deposits in the southwest — Bled El Hadba and Djebal El Onk (combined reserves ~4.7 billion tonnes); Bled El Hadba is designed to mine and transport over 10 million tonnes/year of phosphate rock, feeding the integrated Tebessa phosphate-to-fertilizer project, with Sonatrach support and state miner Sonarem operating." },
  2472: { descEn: "Sasol's 2 GW renewables-procurement portfolio for decarbonization.", detailEn: "Sasol raised its renewables target from 1.2 GW to 2 GW, via power-purchase agreements (PPAs) and direct investment at its Secunda and Sasolburg operations. The 2025 portfolio includes several wind-and-solar wheeling projects with Air Liquide, TotalEnergies, Mulilo, Reatile and others (over 6 billion rand/340 MW in one batch) — one of South Africa's largest commercial green-power procurement programs, supporting its 30% emissions-cut goal by 2030." },
  2513: { descEn: "A new 720 MW coal-fired plant at Hwange, Zimbabwe.", detailEn: "A 720 MW coal-fired plant at Hwange, Zimbabwe, led by the Titan project, broke ground in December 2024 with phased construction; an initial ~100 MW would feed the grid first, aiming to ease drought-driven power shortages and cut reliance on imports from South Africa and Mozambique." },
  2661: { descEn: "Australia's most promising shale-gas basin, developed in the Northern Territory.", detailEn: "In the Beetaloo Basin in the Northern Territory, Australia's most promising shale-gas resource area, Tamboran and Empire Energy are advancing pilot development and commercial gas production, planning pipelines to Darwin and the east-coast gas grid and studying LNG export, entering early commercial production in 2025–2026." },
  2721: { descEn: "An Adriatic Sea HVDC cable linking Marche and Abruzzo (Italy).", detailEn: "A bipolar HVDC submarine cable built by Terna, linking central Italy's Marche and Abruzzo regions, 1,000 MW and ~250 km, strengthening power exchange between Italy's central-south and central-north zones. The European Investment Bank and others provide €1.5 billion of financing, improving grid security, efficiency and renewable absorption." },
  2755: { descEn: "Geothermal-brine lithium for European automakers, zero-carbon (Upper Rhine, Germany).", detailEn: "In Germany's Upper Rhine Graben, Vulcan Energy uses direct lithium extraction (DLE) from geothermal brine, co-producing geothermal energy for near-zero-carbon lithium, planning ~24,000 tonnes/year of battery-grade lithium hydroxide, with offtake agreements signed with Stellantis, VW, Renault and others. The phase-1 Lionheart project is advancing — an EU CRMA strategic project and a benchmark for Europe's domestic lithium supply." },
  2829: { descEn: "A fluoride-salt-cooled high-temperature reactor demonstration, with a Google PPA.", detailEn: "At Oak Ridge, Tennessee, Kairos Power is building a fluoride-salt-cooled high-temperature reactor (KP-FHR). The Hermes demo reactor began construction in May 2025, with Hermes 2 breaking ground in April 2026; Google has signed a PPA to support commercialization — a leading example of U.S. advanced-nuclear (Gen-IV) engineering." },
  2959: { descEn: "An HVDC line linking El Paso, Texas and southeastern New Mexico, bridging the eastern and western grids.", detailEn: "Developed by Grid United, this HVDC line links the El Paso metro and southeastern New Mexico, creating a key path between the Western and Eastern interconnections, serving Permian load growth and renewable export, in early development." },
  2967: { descEn: "A California 500 MW 8-hour advanced compressed-air storage center, breaking ground mid-2026.", detailEn: "In Kern County, California, Canada's Hydrostor is developing its patented A-CAES, ~520 MW/4,160 MWh gross and 500 MW/4,000 MWh net. It compresses air using grid power into a man-made rock cavern and stores heat for efficiency. It got a California Energy Commission generation permit in December 2025, planning to break ground mid-2026 with a ~5-year build." },
  3029: { descEn: "A $1.54-billion Ocean Terminal rebuild at the Port of Savannah, able to berth two large container ships at once.", detailEn: "The ~$1.54-billion Ocean Terminal lets a 200-acre facility berth two large ships at once. A first 1,325-foot berth is done, phase 2 completes a 2,650-foot berth in June 2026, with yard rebuilds done 2027/2028. Garden City grows to 37 ship-to-shore cranes in 2025, raising capacity to 7.2 million TEU." },
  3050: { descEn: "Direct lithium extraction (DLE) from the Smackover formation in Arkansas, phase 1 at 22,500 tonnes/year.", detailEn: "A Standard Lithium–Equinor (55:45) Arkansas brine-lithium project, phase 1 at 22,500 tonnes/year of battery-grade lithium carbonate with a pre-tax IRR of ~20.2%. It got brine-unit integration approval in October 2025, and DOE completed NEPA with a FONSI in May 2026." },
  3108: { descEn: "A 1,000 MW plant in Kishtwar, Jammu & Kashmir — the largest under construction in the Chenab basin.", detailEn: "On the Marusudar River (a Chenab tributary) in Kishtwar district, J&K, developed by CVPPL (an NHPC–JKSPDC JV), with investment of ~126.7 billion rupees, CVPPL is executing Pakal Dul, Kiru and Kwar — three plants totaling 2,164 MW — in the Chenab basin." },
  3118: { descEn: "A 900 MW plant on Nepal's Karnali River, an Indo-Nepal JV, $1.5 billion.", detailEn: "On Nepal's Karnali River, a JV of India's IREDA, SJVN, GMR and Nepal Electricity Authority (NEA), ~$1.5 billion. The 900 MW JV agreement was signed in New Delhi on January 16, 2025 — the flagship of an Indo-Nepal hydropower portfolio of ~11.2 GW." },
  3133: { descEn: "Two 700 MW PHWRs added at Kaiga, Karnataka, with first concrete poured in 2026.", detailEn: "At Kaiga, Karnataka, two domestic 700 MW PHWRs (fleet mode) are being added. In April 2025 NPCIL awarded a ~128-billion-rupee EPC contract to Megha Engineering (MEIL), its first foray into nuclear; first concrete was poured for both units in March 2026, entering main construction." },
  3141: { descEn: "India's first domestic 700 MW PHWRs, now in full-power commercial operation.", detailEn: "At Kakrapar in Surat district, Gujarat, India's first two indigenously-designed 700 MW PHWRs (KAPS-3, 4), the prototype for later fleet-mode units. Unit 3 (2023) and Unit 4 (2024) went into full-power commercial operation, validating the maturity of the domestic 700 MW PHWR." },
  3197: { descEn: "Phase 1 of a 20 GWh battery gigafactory by Tata's Agratas at Sanand, Gujarat.", detailEn: "Tata battery subsidiary Agratas is building a 20 GWh lithium-ion gigafactory at Sanand, Gujarat (~130 billion rupees) to supply Tata-group EVs. As of December 2025 the steel structure was near topping-out with over 2,000 workers on site, targeting structure completion in 2026, startup in 2028, with future expansion." },
  3246: { descEn: "A ~29 km ring metro with 22 stations along the west of Thane in the Mumbai region.", detailEn: "The Thane Ring runs along the city's western periphery, 29 km and 22 stations at ~122 billion rupees, funded half by the central and Maharashtra governments with bilateral-agency financing, implemented by Maha Metro, approved by the center in August 2024." },
  3250: { descEn: "Phase 1 of Agra Metro, two corridors totaling 29.4 km.", detailEn: "Phase 1 has the Yellow Line (Taj East Gate–Mankameshwar) and Blue Line (Agra Cantt–Kalindi Vihar) totaling 29.4 km at ~129 billion rupees; a 5.2 km priority segment opened in March 2024." },
  3403: { descEn: "Phase 2 of the Tengger Desert renewables base in Zhongwei, Ningxia, reaching module installation in 2025.", detailEn: "On the southeast edge of the Tengger Desert in Shapotou, Zhongwei, Ningxia, this is the supporting power for the Ningxia-Hunan UHV. Phase 1 (1 million kW) fully grid-connected in April 2023; phase 2's north zone (2 million kW) has entered solar-panel installation, using straw-checkerboard sand-fixing plus under-panel restoration." },
  3411: { descEn: "Jiangsu's largest operating/under-construction offshore wind at Dafeng, 850 MW, with 100 8.5 MW turbines.", detailEn: "In waters northeast of Dafeng, Yancheng, with 100 8.5 MW turbines totaling 850 MW, Jiangsu's largest single and largest-unit offshore wind project. A 2025 Jiangsu major project, it entered large-scale construction in Q1, targeting grid connection within the year." },
  3413: { descEn: "Zhejiang Xiangshan No.4 offshore wind, 751.5 MW, approved in 2025 at ~10.8 billion yuan.", detailEn: "In waters off Zhoushan/Ningbo Xiangshan, Zhejiang, totaling 751.5 MW, by Zhejiang Xiangshan Zheneng Offshore Wind Power Company, ~10.8 billion yuan total — one of Zhejiang's 18 major offshore-wind projects for 2025 (~8.1 GW combined), advancing on a deep-sea wind home port." },
  3439: { descEn: "An upgrade of the world's only operating thorium molten-salt reactor, launching a 10 MWe research reactor in 2025.", detailEn: "At Hongshagang in Minqin, Wuwei, Gansu, led by the Shanghai Institute of Applied Physics (CAS). A 2 MWt experimental reactor has run at full power and completed the world's first molten-salt thorium-addition experiment. The research-reactor three-step strategy is advancing, with 5–10 commercial thorium molten-salt reactors planned before 2035." },
  3512: { descEn: "Phase 2 of EVE Energy's Jingmen super storage plant (60B) starts piling, a main LFP base.", detailEn: "EVE Energy's Jingmen super storage plant totals 10.8 billion yuan and 60 GWh; phase 2 (60B) piling began in January 2025. EVE shipped 71 GWh of storage in 2025 and plans ~260 GWh of new LFP capacity, with Jingmen the core carrier base." },
  3518: { descEn: "REPT's Wendingding battery base in Wenzhou, world No.1 in home-storage cell shipments.", detailEn: "REPT centers on Wenzhou, with sites across Wenzhou, Jiashan, Liuzhou, Foshan and Chongqing; in 2025 monthly Wendingding battery shipments topped 2 GWh and cumulative shipments exceeded 20 GWh, ranking world No.1 in home-storage cell exports and top 5 in storage-cell exports." },
  3520: { descEn: "Baowu Zhanjiang's hydrogen shaft furnace plus EAF short process, China's first near-zero-carbon thin-plate line.", detailEn: "Baosteel Zhanjiang uses hydrogen-based shaft-furnace direct-reduced iron plus scrap, with an efficient EAF forming a short process; on December 23, 2025 its first million-tonne-scale near-zero-carbon high-grade thin-steel-plate line was fully connected, ~1.8 million tonnes of capacity, cutting carbon 50–80%, with up to 3.14 million tonnes/year of carbon reduction." },
  3573: { descEn: "Suzhou's first civil airport (Class A1 general-aviation), aimed at the low-altitude economy, targeting end-2026 operation.", detailEn: "Sited at the junction of Shajiabang in Changshu and Bacheng in Kunshan, a new runway is 1,600 m long and 45 m wide, with aviation consumption, flight training and emergency rescue functions, plus a drone test-flight field, training base and dispatch center for the low-altitude economy. It is on Suzhou's 2025 list of new major integrated-transport projects." },
  3581: { descEn: "Shenzhen's low-altitude-economy infrastructure network (takeoff/landing pads + sensing base stations).", detailEn: "Under Shenzhen's plan for high-quality low-altitude infrastructure (2024–2026), by 2026 takeoff/landing facilities rise from 249 to over 1,200, with over 8,000 new 5G-A base stations and 500 sensing base stations, over 1,000 commercial routes opened and 10 low-altitude industrial parks built. Funded via treasury bonds, special bonds and industrial funds, the 2024 low-altitude annual output value already topped 90 billion yuan." },
  4029: { descEn: "China Railway Construction's general contract for the Kyrgyz section of the China–Kyrgyzstan–Uzbekistan railway, electrification reserved.", detailEn: "A consortium of CRCC's China Railway 11th, 12th, 14th, 15th and 19th Bureaus and the Electrification Bureau won the early-start segment and multiple pre-station works packages for the Kyrgyz section of the China–Kyrgyzstan–Uzbekistan railway, totaling ~10.5 billion yuan. The line is designed for 120 km/h with electrification reserved, including the Koshtebe and Fergana mountain control tunnels plus temporary power trunk lines and access roads — a landmark Belt-and-Road project linking the three countries." },
  4088: { descEn: "One of the world's ten largest zinc mines, with supporting solar power.", detailEn: "65 km north of Cloncurry, Queensland, Dugald River is one of the world's ten largest operating zinc mines. 2024 zinc output was ~220,000 tonnes (including Rosebery), with 2025 Dugald River zinc guidance of 170,000–185,000 tonnes. Q4 recovery hit a record 91% and October set a monthly metal-output high. The site has a supporting solar farm to cut energy carbon intensity, reflecting MMG's green-mine operations." },
  4103: { descEn: "State Grid holds 40% of NGCP, operating the Philippines' national transmission grid under concession since 2009.", detailEn: "NGCP is the concessionaire of the Philippines' national transmission grid, formally taking over in January 2009 with a 25-year concession renewable for 25 more (50 total). State Grid holds 40% of NGCP, participating in operating, expanding and repairing the Luzon-Visayas-Mindanao backbone." },
  4235: { descEn: "A major China–Saudi Belt-and-Road cooperation: North Huajin fine chemicals, with several CNCEC subsidiaries building.", detailEn: "The North Huajin fine-chemicals and feedstock project is a major China–Saudi Belt-and-Road cooperation, supporting a large refining-petrochemical integration making fine-chemical products and feedstocks. Seven CNCEC subsidiaries participate in construction — an important Middle East-market track record for the company." },
  4362: { descEn: "Huadian's Boya mine-mouth coal plant in South Sumatra, supplying ~18% of Sumatra's power.", detailEn: "Huadian (Indonesia)'s Boya 2×660 MW mine-mouth coal plant is in Muara Enim, South Sumatra, built under a BOOT model by a JV of Huadian Hong Kong and an Indonesian state coal company, controlled by Huadian Overseas Investment, totaling 1.32 million kW. Unit 2 completed a 168-hour trial in September 2023 for full operation; it supplies ~18% of Sumatra's total generation and won a 2024 China Electric Power excellent-engineering-design first prize." },
  4403: { descEn: "Sinopec Engineering's EPCC for a PDH-polypropylene complex in Atyrau, Kazakhstan, ~500,000 tonnes/year.", detailEn: "In Karabatan, Atyrau province, Kazakhstan, Sinopec Engineering (SEG) holds the EPCC for a propane-dehydrogenation (PDH) and polypropylene complex, designed for ~500,000 tonnes/year of propylene/polypropylene, using Kazakhstan's abundant propane to make high-value polypropylene. With the Silleno olefins project, it forms Kazakhstan's oil-downstream petrochemical expansion, cementing China's lead in Central Asia's downstream engineering market." },
  4468: { descEn: "A Zijin–Ajlan JV for zinc-copper-gold exploration and smelting in Saudi Arabia.", detailEn: "Through a subsidiary, Zijin signed a JV agreement with Saudi Arabia's Ajlan Brothers Mining (Manara/Ajlan) to set up a venture (Zijin 51%, Ajlan 49%) to explore and mine zinc, copper and gold potential in the Jabal Sayid mineralization belt. Zijin also signed an investment MoU with the Saudi side, planning phased investment of ~5–6 billion Saudi riyals (~9.65–11.58 billion yuan) to build a zinc smelter, lithium-carbonate extraction and a copper refinery — a key step toward integrated greenfield exploration and smelting in the Middle East." },
  4477: { descEn: "China Nonferrous signs the general agreement for a 300,000-tonne/year Balkhash copper smelter in Kazakhstan, $1.414 billion.", detailEn: "On June 3, 2024 China Nonferrous Metal Industry and its subsidiary CNMC Kazakhstan signed the 'general agreement for a 300,000-tonne/year copper smelter in Kazakhstan' with Kazakhmys, with a tax-inclusive contract value of ~$1.414 billion and initial investment of ~$1.5 billion. The project modernizes and expands the Balkhash smelter, raising copper capacity from no more than 250,000 to 300,000 tonnes/year, expected at full output in 2028 — a landmark of China Nonferrous's international capacity cooperation, driving a sharp rise in new contracts." },
  4513: { descEn: "Bridge's MY07 hyperscale campus in Johor, with 400 MW locked in from TNB.", detailEn: "Chindata's overseas brand Bridge Data Centres acquired ~20 acres in Plentong, Johor, Malaysia, to build the MY07 hyperscale data-center campus, reaching a major power-supply deal with TNB to lock in 400 MW. The campus absorbs hyperscale and AI-compute demand spilling over after Singapore's data-center moratorium — another BDC flagship in Johor after MY06, backed by $2.8 billion of senior secured bank financing obtained in March 2025." },
  3150: { descEn: "Rajasthan's 4.5 GW renewable export to Mainpuri.", detailEn: "An ISTS scheme (~122.4 billion rupees) with 1 GW at Fatehgarh, 2.5 GW at Barmer and 1 GW at Nagaur as collection points, sent via 765 kV to Mainpuri, Fatehpur and Orai in Uttar Pradesh — part of the 2030 500 GW renewable-export backbone, implemented via TBCB." },
  1927: { descEn: "Phase 1 of NEOM–Yanbu ±525 kV HVDC, among the world's first 3 GW ±525 kV HVDC Light, linking Oxagon and Yanbu.", detailEn: "The first phase of the NEOM transmission system, built by Hitachi Energy and SSEM, links Oxagon to Yanbu 650 km away, with 207 km of line, 450 towers and two 1.5 GW converter stations, awarded May 2023 at ~$145 million, expected complete July 2027. Two further 3 GW HVDC lines have preliminary agreements, for 9 GW of total transmission capacity." },
  3147: { descEn: "Khavda phase-5 segment C ±500 kV VSC HVDC export, the second VSC-HVDC works for the Khavda 8 GW renewable zone.", detailEn: "An ISTS-TBCB project with ±500 kV, 2,500 MW VSC converter stations at KPS3 and South Olpad and ~600 km of bipolar HVDC line between them. AESL won at the lowest annual charge of ~23.9 billion rupees in December 2025 and acquired the project company, with GE Vernova on the converter stations, targeting December 2029 operation." },
  108: { descEn: "One of the only large hydropower plants commissioned during the 14th Five-Year period.", detailEn: "In Diqing, Yunnan, a key cascade-development project on the upper Lancang River, totaling 1.4 million kW. All four units reached full-capacity operation in December 2024, generating ~6.23 billion kWh a year and cutting ~5.22 million tonnes of CO₂ annually." },
  253: { descEn: "One of Europe's largest single steel-decarbonization works.", detailEn: "At the Dunkirk steelworks in France, ArcelorMittal is investing €1.3 billion (50% French government subsidy) in a new EAF using scrap plus direct-reduced iron and hot metal, cutting emissions ~2/3 vs the blast furnace, confirmed February 2026 with first steel planned for 2029." },
  382: { descEn: "One of the world's largest hard-rock lithium deposits.", detailEn: "In Tanganyika province, DRC, Manono averages 1.51% Li₂O grade; Zijin holds ~55% and is investing ~$1.4 billion, with the beneficiation system starting up in phases from March 2026 and first lithium-concentrate export in June, reaching over 130,000 tonnes/year LCE capacity at full output." },
  549: { descEn: "The world's largest single liquid-cooled AI-compute center by an operator.", detailEn: "China Mobile's Hohhot AI-compute center started up in April 2024, deploying ~20,000 AI accelerator cards with 6.7 EFLOPS of compute, over 85% domestic compute, and a national-class ten-thousand-card AI training ground able to support trillion-parameter LLM training." },
  550: { descEn: "The world's largest single-cluster AI-compute center by an operator, 100% domestic AI chips.", detailEn: "China Mobile's Harbin AI-compute center started up in August 2024, deploying over 18,000 AI accelerator cards at 100% domestic AI-chip localization with 6.9 EFLOPS of compute, achieving the first commercial GSE-technology ten-thousand-card deployment as a base for trillion-scale model training." },
  557: { descEn: "Tencent's largest East China data-center base.", detailEn: "Tencent's Yizheng cloud-computing data center totals over 10 billion yuan; at full output it has 300,000 racks and over 30,000 PFLOPS of compute. Yizheng has gathered three 10-billion-yuan data centers — Tencent, China Mobile and China Telecom — totaling over 60 billion yuan, the core engine of Yizheng's digital-economy transformation." },
  560: { descEn: "Baidu's North China AI-compute base, supporting a Kunlun-chip ten-thousand-card cluster.", detailEn: "Baidu is building Xushui and Dingxing intelligent cloud-computing centers in Baoding, able to host 360,000 AI servers; in 2025 it deployed China's first third-gen Kunlun-chip (P800) ten-thousand-card cluster and got a five-star certification from the China Academy of Information and Communications Technology — the first certified domestic ten-thousand-card cluster." },
  716: { descEn: "Xinjiang's first batch of national capacity-reserve coal mines in Zhundong.", detailEn: "In the Wucaiwan mining area of Zhundong, Xinjiang, the mine field spans 96.88 km² with 2.958 billion tonnes of recoverable raw coal, designed for 23 million tonnes/year over a 128.6-year life. Started in February 2025, it is the core mine of Shandong Energy's 33.8-billion-yuan Zhundong coal-chemical integration project, selected among the first batch of national capacity-reserve coal mines." },
  720: { descEn: "The world's largest single-owner iron mine.", detailEn: "In the Pilbara of Western Australia, built by Gina Rinehart, producing ~55 million tonnes/year of iron ore with FY2025 net profit of A$1.8 billion. It recently integrated Atlas Iron and plans a life-extension expansion, exploring raising capacity above 60 million tonnes, with the new McPhee mine processed and exported via its infrastructure." },
  790: { descEn: "Guangxi's first offshore wind project, filling a provincial gap.", detailEn: "In nearshore waters of Guangxi's Beibu Gulf, built by Guangxi Investment Group, with 83 8.5 MW turbines totaling 700 MW, using China's first embedded rock-socketed pile foundation. It fully grid-connected in December 2024 and reached full operation in February 2025, laying a foundation for a trillion-yuan Beibu Gulf offshore-wind base." },
  799: { descEn: "Set a world-record-low wind power price (1.338 US cents/kWh).", detailEn: "In Saudi Arabia's Riyadh province, 1,500 MW, a sixth-round project under the national renewable-energy program, awarded October 2025 at an LCOE of 1.338 US cents/kWh — a world-record-low wind power price. On completion it meets large domestic green-power demand, a milestone of the Middle East's rapid renewable expansion." },
  955: { descEn: "GridLink, a UK–France 1.4 GW HVDC interconnection on one of the shortest routes.", detailEn: "GridLink links Kingsnorth (Kent), UK with Dunkirk, France, ~140 km long; the UK side has development consent and France's CRE regulatory process is advancing, planning construction after a 2026 FID and 2028 operation." },
  956: { descEn: "FAB Link, a France–UK 1.25 GW HVDC interconnection linking France and southwest England.", detailEn: "FAB Link is ~220 km, landing in Devon, UK, jointly developed by FAB Link Ltd and France's RTE; in 2023 capacity was cut from 1.4 GW to 1.25 GW, Ofgem in principle retains its cap-and-floor mechanism, with FID advancing in 2025 and a completion target of 2030/31." },
  957: { descEn: "Aquind, a UK–France 2 GW HVDC interconnection (Portsmouth–Normandy), stalled in approvals.", detailEn: "Aquind links Portsmouth, UK with Normandy, France, ~240 km, with a planned 2 GW capacity; UK-side approval is suspended, and in July 2025 France granted an environmental permit but the Seine-Maritime authority rejected the maritime concession, with the developer seeking legal recourse." },
  1134: { descEn: "A full refurbishment and restart of the China-built TAZARA railway.", detailEn: "The TAZARA railway, ~1,860 km, was China-built in the 1970s. On September 29, 2025 China signed a $1.4-billion overhaul agreement with Tanzania and Zambia, implemented by CCECC with a 30-year concession: 3 years of repair then 27 of commercial operation, fully upgrading track, stations and communications and procuring new locomotives and rolling stock. After the overhaul, freight capacity rises from ~100,000 to 2.4 million tonnes a year. The project formally launched in November 2025 and entered equipment mobilization, seen as a strategic link to the Lobito Corridor." },
  1153: { descEn: "The Delhi region's second airport, unveiled in 2026.", detailEn: "Noida International Airport at Jewar, Uttar Pradesh, led by Zurich Airport, aims to divert traffic from Delhi's Indira Gandhi airport and serve the Delhi-UP economic corridor. Phase 1 has one runway and a 101,600 m² T1 terminal at 12 million passengers/year, with several runways planned long term. It got DGCA aerodrome licensing on March 6, 2026, was unveiled for phase 1 by PM Modi on March 28, and is set to begin domestic commercial operation on June 15, 2026, with international routes later." },
  1320: { descEn: "A Poços de Caldas premier ionic-clay rare-earth project.", detailEn: "An ionic-adsorption clay rare-earth project ~31 km south of Poços de Caldas, Minas Gerais. In June 2025 it was selected for Brazil's strategic-minerals funding program, with Ausenco on the feasibility study (DFS). In December 2025 a pilot plant produced first mixed rare-earth carbonate (MREC), providing key operating data for the DFS. After feasibility, it will be construction-ready in 2026, targeting first production in 2028." },
  1686: { descEn: "A Vale–GEM HPAL green-nickel plant in Indonesia (IGIP), 66,000 tonnes of nickel MHP a year.", detailEn: "In November 2024, witnessed by Indonesia's president, GEM signed an investment agreement with PT Vale Indonesia (PTVI) to jointly build a zero-carbon, ESG-standard high-pressure-acid-leach (HPAL) green-nickel smelter in Central Sulawesi, processing PTVI laterite ore, targeting 66,000 tonnes/year of nickel-content MHP, with downstream cathode/precursor plants planned. GEM plans to invest up to $1.42 billion, within Indonesia's international green industrial park IGIP." },
  2072: { descEn: "Vietnam's Son My LNG terminal in Binh Thuan, supporting Son My gas power.", detailEn: "An AES–PV Gas JV, the Son My LNG terminal in Binh Thuan totals ~$1.4 billion, initially 3.6 MTPA, expandable to 10 MTPA. It got Binh Thuan's investment-policy approval in July 2023, targeting 2027 operation, supporting AES's ~$1.8-billion 2.2 GW Son My 2 combined-cycle gas plant." },
  2090: { descEn: "Merdeka ESG/SLNC nickel HPAL, with several HPAL plants supporting the SCM mine.", detailEn: "At the SCM mine in North Maluku, an MBMA–GEM JV PT ESG. The ESG plant got its industrial license in February 2025 and produced ~26,000 tonnes of nickel-content MHP that year; a third HPAL (PT SLNC) is designed for 90,000 tonnes/year of nickel-content MHP, targeting feed-in commissioning by mid-2026. SCM's limonite/saprolite output rose sharply year-on-year in 2025." },
  2678: { descEn: "Extension of the Cadia gold-copper mine, New South Wales, a block-cave area expansion (Newmont).", detailEn: "Near Orange, New South Wales, one of Australia's largest underground gold-copper mines. Newmont is advancing a new block-cave area (such as PC1-2/PC2-3) and tailings expansion, extending the mine's life into the 2040s, with continued capital spending in 2025–2026." },
  2732: { descEn: "A Hungarian large-cylindrical battery plant supplying BMW's Neue Klasse.", detailEn: "In Debrecen, Hungary, built by China's EVE Energy, with 28 GWh of large-cylindrical-battery capacity mainly for BMW's Neue Klasse models. ~HUF 400 billion (~$1.4 billion); first cells rolled off in February 2025, with scale production planned for 2026 — a new member of Hungary's battery cluster." },
  2733: { descEn: "Envision AESC's Douai gigafactory (France), supplying Renault's Ampere.", detailEn: "In Douai, northern France, built by Envision Power, phase 1 at ~9 GWh, expandable to 30 GWh+, mainly supplying Renault's EV subsidiary Ampere. One of the core plants of northern France's 'battery valley,' ~€2 billion, advancing production ramp-up in 2025." },
  3168: { descEn: "Greenko's 1,920 MW Gandhi Sagar closed-loop pumped storage in Neemuch, Madhya Pradesh, using the existing Gandhi Sagar reservoir as the lower pool.", detailEn: "Greenko is building 1,920 MW Gandhi Sagar pumped storage in Neemuch, Madhya Pradesh, with a new upper reservoir and the existing Gandhi Sagar reservoir as the lower pool, 6-hour discharge supplying ~11 GWh/day, EPC by L&T, ~115 billion rupees, with ~3 GW of supporting wind-solar — one of India's largest pumped-storage projects under construction." },
  3245: { descEn: "Phase 1 of Surat Metro, two lines totaling ~41.9 km.", detailEn: "Phase 1 plans 41.93 km at ~120.2 billion rupees, built by the Gujarat Metro Rail Corporation, with phase 1 expected complete in 2027." },
  3247: { descEn: "Indore Metro Yellow Line's super-priority segment in passenger service from June 2025.", detailEn: "Indore Metro's Yellow Line is a ring project at ~120 billion rupees; the super-priority corridor was unveiled by PM Modi on May 31, 2025 and began carrying passengers on June 1." },
  3251: { descEn: "Meerut Metro's 23.6 km phase 1 opened February 2026, sharing track with the RRTS.", detailEn: "Meerut Metro phase 1 runs from Modipuram to Meerut South, 23.6 km and 12 stations, opening February 22, 2026; merged with the Delhi-Meerut RRTS, it is owned and operated by NCRTC, costing ~115.4 billion rupees." },
  3273: { descEn: "Colombo Port City, a reclaimed special-economic-zone port city off Colombo, with ~$1.4 billion invested by China Harbour.", detailEn: "Colombo Port City is Sri Lanka's largest Chinese direct investment; since 2014 CHEC has invested ~$1.4 billion, with phase-1 infrastructure delivered. In May 2025 it delivered office space to anchor tenants of the business district, a $120-million marina broke ground in January 2025, and the overall plan is ~$15 billion." },
  3309: { descEn: "Hindustan Zinc's 250,000-tonne/year integrated zinc smelter in Debari, Rajasthan, starting the first phase of doubling capacity.", detailEn: "Hindustan Zinc's board approved in June 2025 a 250,000-tonne/year integrated zinc smelter at Debari near Udaipur, Rajasthan (~120 billion rupees), the first phase of raising refined-metal capacity from ~1.1 million to over 2 million tonnes/year, to be built in 36 months." },
  3424: { descEn: "Tongliao's national third-batch 1.2 GW wind base, accelerating construction in 2025.", detailEn: "In Tongliao, eastern Inner Mongolia, using an integrated wind-solar-thermal-storage model with advanced efficient coal power and new storage, in 2025 it aims to add 4 million kW of new-energy grid connection, topping 18 million kW total, with the third-batch 1.2 GW wind base accelerating." },
  3511: { descEn: "BYD FinDreams' Taizhou super battery plant, with the 6th-gen Blade battery in full production, energy density 267 Wh/kg.", detailEn: "The Taizhou FinDreams power-battery project totals 10.02 billion yuan and 22 GWh, using the 6th-gen Blade (lithium manganese iron phosphate) battery supporting 800V fast charging. Implementation began March 2025, with 8 lines lit simultaneously in October for full production of the 6th-gen Blade battery, ~20 billion yuan of output value at full capacity." },
  3595: { descEn: "Sinopec's Longkou LNG terminal, one of Yantai's three LNG bases, under construction.", detailEn: "In the Longkou port area of Yantai, Shandong, Sinopec's large LNG terminal, with PipeChina's Nanshan and Yantai West-port terminals forms Yantai's three LNG bases (over 20 billion yuan total). On completion Yantai port's LNG unloading capacity nears 20 million tonnes; in 2025 Yantai LNG annual unloading reached 16.5 million tonnes, building northern China's largest LNG supply-and-storage base." },
  3615: { descEn: "Hongge South vanadium-titanium magnetite, China's largest such reserve at 3.256 billion tonnes.", detailEn: "In Yanbian county, Panzhihua, Sichuan, the mining right has proven 3.256 billion tonnes of vanadium-titanium magnetite with the most associated elements. The first 8 construction projects started February 13, 2025. By end-2028 it expects 20 million tonnes/year of mining, forming capacity for 9 million tonnes of iron concentrate, 2.6 million tonnes of titanium concentrate and 50,000 tonnes of sulfur-cobalt concentrate." },
  4057: { descEn: "China Road and Bridge's Phnom Penh–Bavet expressway in Cambodia, invested and operated under BOT.", detailEn: "China Road and Bridge is building Cambodia's Phnom Penh–Bavet expressway under a BOT model (50-year concession), 138 km across three provinces, linking Phnom Penh to the Bavet border crossing with Vietnam, including mainline, interchanges, toll stations and roadside power and lighting, ~$1.4 billion. On completion the Phnom Penh-Bavet trip falls from ~2 hours to ~20 minutes — a backbone of Cambodia-Vietnam connectivity." },
  4258: { descEn: "China Railway's Tel Aviv light rail Red Line, Israel's first light rail, with CRTG building the underground section and the full chain.", detailEn: "The Tel Aviv light rail Red Line is Israel's first light rail and a rail project where a Chinese firm built the full design-manufacture-procure-construct-commission-maintain chain in a developed-market premium segment. The line is ~24 km (~12 km surface, ~12 km underground) with 24 surface and 10 underground stations, running through Bat Yam, Tel Aviv-Yafo, Ramat Gan, Bnei Brak and Petah Tikva and crossing 53 complex busy junctions. It was built by China Railway units including CRTG and the Electrification Bureau. The Red Line entered commercial operation in August 2023 and ran at high load through 2024; CRTG also took early works for the Green Line." },
  4461: { descEn: "State Grid (CET)'s Ethiopia–Kenya ±500 kV HVDC interconnection, East Africa's first cross-border HVDC, the backbone of the 'Eastern Electricity Highway.'", detailEn: "The Ethiopia–Kenya ±500 kV HVDC line, built by State Grid's China Electric Power Technology & Equipment (CET), is East Africa's first cross-border HVDC interconnection, with 1,045 km of new ±500 kV line, the Sodo converter station and supporting works, designed for 2,000 MW transfer, ~$1.4 billion, financed by the World Bank and African Development Bank. Using Chinese HVDC standards and equipment, it is the backbone of East Africa's power interconnection, linking the grids of Ethiopia, Kenya, Uganda and South Sudan." },
  1112: { descEn: "The world's largest-span cable-stayed bridge, opened September 2025.", detailEn: "The Changtai Yangtze River Bridge links Changzhou and Taizhou as a double-deck road-rail composite river crossing; the main-channel bridge is a steel-truss cable-stayed bridge with a 1,208 m main span, setting world records for the largest-span cable-stayed bridge and largest-span road-rail bridge, with a 10.03 km river crossing. It opened September 9, 2025, cutting the Changzhou-Taizhou trip from ~1h20m to ~20 minutes — a key project of Yangtze-Delta integration and a multi-channel composite of the Yan-Tai-Xi-Chang-Yi and Changtai expressways." },
  1118: { descEn: "The world's longest undersea high-speed-rail tunnel.", detailEn: "The Jintang undersea tunnel is the control project of the Ningbo-Zhoushan railway, from Beilun, Ningbo east to Jintang, Zhoushan, 16.18 km long with an 11.21 km shield section — the world's longest undersea high-speed-rail tunnel, using the super-large-diameter 'Yongzhou' TBM to cross the sea under over 6 bar of water pressure. In 2025 two-way tunneling topped 7,400 m, over half done. The tunnel is expected to hole through by end-2026 and the railway to be built by 2028, ending Zhoushan's lack of rail and cutting Hangzhou-Zhoushan to under an hour." },
  1124: { descEn: "The world's only single terminal with over 10 million boxes on a mixed automated/manual line.", detailEn: "The Meishan port area of Ningbo-Zhoushan Port is the world's only container terminal with single throughput over 10 million TEU that also runs remote-controlled automation mixed with manual trucks, topping 11.19 million TEU in 2024. In July 2025 Zhejiang approved opening berths 6–10 to foreign trade, using a model of remote-controlled quay/gantry cranes at both ends plus smart and manual trucks in between. On scaled, smart upgrades, Ningbo-Zhoushan Port has led the world in cargo throughput for 16 straight years — a model of a world-class strong port and zero-carbon port." },
  3215: { descEn: "Bashundhara builds a 1.25-million-tonne long-products plant in a national economic zone at Mirsarai, Chittagong.", detailEn: "Bashundhara Multi Steel (BMSIL) is building a 1.25-million-tonne/year long-products steel plant in the Mirsarai national special economic zone in Chittagong (~150 billion taka), using Italy's Danieli MIDA-Q endless casting-rolling, becoming Bangladesh's first maker of rebar coil and wire rod; currency depreciation raised costs to ~470 billion taka, with mid-2026 startup planned." },
  1438: { descEn: "The Middle East's largest iron-ore pellet and distribution center.", detailEn: "In the Sohar Port industrial zone of Oman, built by Brazil's Vale for ~$1.36 billion, with two 4.5-million-tonne-scale direct-reduction pellet lines (9 million tonnes/year combined) and a distribution center handling 40 million tonnes/year. As a hub for iron-ore demand in the Middle East, North Africa and Asia, it supplies high-grade direct-reduction pellets to regional steelmakers." },
  1081: { descEn: "The UK's largest and a Europe-leading battery storage, built on a retired coal-plant site.", detailEn: "On the brownfield of the retired Thorpe Marsh coal plant ~6 km north of Doncaster, South Yorkshire, developed by Edinburgh-based Fidra Energy using Sungrow battery systems, 1.4 GW/3.1 GWh — on completion the UK's largest and among Europe's and the world's largest battery storage. It got planning consent in January 2025 and broke ground in July; in September EIG and the UK National Wealth Fund provided £445 million of equity plus £594 million of debt to close financing, expecting mid-2027 operation." },
  742: { descEn: "The world's largest single-phase integrated concentrated-solar-power-plus-storage project.", detailEn: "In the Santanghu desert of Barkol, Hami, Xinjiang, totaling 1,500 MW, with a 219 m receiver tower, 20,516 heliostats and 8 hours of molten-salt storage. Started May 2024, it targets full-capacity grid connection by October 2026, becoming the world's largest single-phase CSP-plus-storage project." },
  353: { descEn: "Iraq's gas-growth integrated project to end flaring and boost oil and gas in Basra.", detailEn: "~$13 billion total, a JV of TotalEnergies, Basra Oil and QatarEnergy; gas-processing-unit construction began January 2025, with phase 2 reaching 210,000 barrels/day and zero routine flaring in 2028." },
  356: { descEn: "A Louisiana Cameron Parish LNG export project.", detailEn: "Six modular SnapLNG trains total 9.5 million tonnes/year; FID came in May 2026, using Technip Energies' modular technology to cut costs, with TotalEnergies as a stakeholder, targeting 2030 operation." },
  587: { descEn: "Mistral AI's first data center outside France, carrying Nvidia Vera Rubin.", detailEn: "Mistral AI and EcoDataCenter signed a €1.2-billion long-term agreement in February 2026 to build a 20-hectare AI data center in Borlänge, Sweden, phase 1 at 250 MW expandable to 600 MW, carrying Nvidia's latest Vera Rubin GPUs, leveraging Sweden's clean power, targeting 2027 operation." },
  589: { descEn: "AWS adds €1.2 billion to expand its Milan cloud region.", detailEn: "AWS announced over €1.2 billion of additional investment in Italy over five years to expand the Lombardy data-center cluster of its Milan region, expected to contribute €880 million of GDP and support 5,500 jobs — part of Italy's 10-billion-euro data-center investment wave in 2025-2026." },
});

/* —— 批次17：全库投资额 TOP（约12-13亿美元）约100条 —— */
Object.assign(window.ENERGY_EN, {
  1132: { descEn: "A standard-gauge extension of the Central Corridor to Mwanza on Lake Victoria.", detailEn: "Tanzania's standard-gauge railway lot 5 runs from Isaka to Mwanza on Lake Victoria, 249 km of main line plus 92 km of passing loops, built by CCECC and CRCC for ~$1.32 billion. On completion the full line runs from the Indian Ocean port of Dar es Salaam to Mwanza and on to Rwanda, Burundi and DR Congo. The first standard-gauge freight train ran on June 27, 2025, with subgrade 89% done. By early 2026 lot 5 was ~68% complete, set to be East Africa's fastest railway." },
  1330: { descEn: "A 2 GW mega solar plant in Mecca province, a flagship of Saudi's fifth NREP round.", detailEn: "Haden is one of the fifth-round projects of Saudi Arabia's National Renewable Energy Program (NREP), in Mecca province, 2 GW. In September 2024 it closed $3.2 billion of financing alongside Muwayh and Al Khushaybi, developed by ACWA Power, PIF's Badeel and Aramco's SAPCO, with power sold to SPPC, supporting Saudi's 50% renewable target by 2030." },
  1331: { descEn: "A 2 GW solar plant in Mecca province, financing closed with Haden.", detailEn: "Muwayh solar, in Saudi Arabia's Mecca province, is 2 GW — one of the fifth NREP round's three solar projects (with Haden and Al Khushaybi, 5.5 GW total). In September 2024 an ACWA Power, Badeel and SAPCO consortium closed $3.2 billion of financing and signed a 25-year PPA, targeting early-2027 operation." },
  1374: { descEn: "Saudi Arabia's first domestic-brand EV assembly plant.", detailEn: "Ceer is a PIF–Foxconn JV using BMW-licensed technology, Saudi Arabia's first domestic EV brand. The plant at KAEC spans over 1 million m²; a ~$1.3-billion (SAR 5 billion) construction contract was awarded in March 2024. Planned for 240,000 vehicles/year, it is the most advanced auto-manufacturing base in MENA, making SUVs and sedans." },
  1417: { descEn: "A giant gas plant processing associated gas from Marjan/Zuluf.", detailEn: "The Tanajib gas plant is part of the Marjan development program — one of the world's largest gas-processing facilities, handling associated gas from the offshore Marjan and Zuluf fields with feed-gas capacity of 2.6 Bcf/d, producing gas, NGL and condensate, feeding Saudi's main gas grid and petrochemicals." },
  1515: { descEn: "A doubling-track works that quintuples China-Europe transit capacity.", detailEn: "836 km long, the largest railway works in Kazakhstan's independence. After ~3 years of construction, it was unveiled and opened by President Tokayev on September 30, 2025. Daily throughput rises from 12 to 60 trains — fivefold — sharply cutting China-Europe transit time and strengthening the Middle Corridor (TITR)'s transit potential. After commissioning, line freight grew 42% vs 2022." },
  1822: { descEn: "Eneva's Ceará LNG combined-cycle gas power, with a Pecém terminal.", detailEn: "Eneva acquired the Jandaia project (formerly Ceiba), investing ~R$6.5–7.6 billion in a 2,340 MW gas plant at Caucaia with an FSRU floating terminal at Pecém port and a 6 km evacuation line. Phase 1 is 1,705 MW simple-cycle, phase 2 adds 725 MW combined-cycle, with construction starting H1 2026." },
  1839: { descEn: "An expansion of Group II/III base oils at Yanbu (Growth II), starting up H2 2026.", detailEn: "Aramco base-oils company Luberef is doing the Growth II expansion at its Yanbu plant, with a new unit that flexibly makes Group II or III base oils, raising the company's total base-oil capacity to ~1.53 million tonnes/year. The energy ministry extended the Yanbu feedstock quota to 2038 and temporarily added 65,000 barrels/day to support the expansion. Progress was ~71% in Q1 2025, with mechanical completion December 2025, pre-feed-in January 2026, and startup in H2 2026." },
  1867: { descEn: "A mega wind farm in Medina province, the seventh NREP round.", detailEn: "The seventh NREP round's flagship wind project, at Bir Allag in Medina province, 1,300 MW — the round's largest single project. SPPC issued the RFQ in September 2025 and published qualified wind developers (including Masdar, PowerChina, Goldwind, Envision and Longyuan) in January 2026, expecting a PPA in 2026-2027 and operation around 2029." },
  2078: { descEn: "A Pengerang SAF/HVO biorefinery in Johor, Malaysia.", detailEn: "Petronas, Italy's Enilive and Japan's Euglena are jointly building a biorefinery at the Pengerang Integrated Complex (PIC) in Johor, ~$1.3 billion (RM 6.05 billion), processing up to 650,000 tonnes/year of renewable feedstock into sustainable aviation fuel (SAF), hydrogenated vegetable oil (HVO) and bio-naphtha. Ground was broken November 10, 2025, targeting H2 2028 startup." },
  2560: { descEn: "Cameroon's largest hydropower plant, at full load in 2025.", detailEn: "A 420 MW plant on the Sanaga River, led by France's EDF, grid-connected in June 2024 and reached full load in March 2025, raising national capacity ~30% and sharply cutting outages. A supporting transmission line connects the southern interconnected grid, securing power to industrial hubs and cutting line losses." },
  2612: { descEn: "One of the Southern Hemisphere's largest onshore wind farms, 162 turbines.", detailEn: "Near Karara, Queensland, developed by Spain's Acciona, 1.026 GW with 162 6.2 MW turbines — one of the largest operating onshore wind farms in the Southern Hemisphere. It is grid-connecting through 2025, with power partly supplied to the Queensland government and large commercial-and-industrial users." },
  2623: { descEn: "A backbone-transmission strengthening under Queensland's energy-transition plan.", detailEn: "Under Queensland's 'Energy and Jobs Plan (SuperGrid),' this strengthens the backbone transmission, building 500/275 kV corridors along the coast and inland, connecting north/central/south Queensland renewable zones, pumped storage and offshore wind, supporting large-scale coal retirement and renewable integration." },
  2629: { descEn: "Long-duration pumped storage supporting the New England REZ, NSW.", detailEn: "In the New England Renewable Energy Zone of New South Wales, this plans ~900 MW of long-duration (~12-hour) pumped storage as a long-duration regulating source for the REZ's large-scale wind and solar, advancing feasibility and approvals in 2025, strengthening NSW's long-duration storage." },
  2646: { descEn: "Australia's sovereign-cloud leader, large campuses in Sydney/Canberra.", detailEn: "CDC Data Centres is the main carrier of Australia's government and sovereign cloud, building several large data-center campuses in Sydney and Canberra with over 500 MW of planned capacity, meeting government, defense and hyperscale-cloud needs for high availability and localization, with continued expansion in 2025-2026." },
  2647: { descEn: "An Asia-Pacific hyperscale data center, expanding in western Sydney.", detailEn: "AirTrunk (acquired by Blackstone and others)'s hyperscale campus at Huntingwood and elsewhere in western Sydney plans over 400 MW, serving global cloud and AI customers with large-scale renewable PPAs — one of the Asia-Pacific's leading hyperscale platforms, expanding continuously." },
  2941: { descEn: "TAE's Copernicus fusion demonstration in Irvine, California, backed by Google and Chevron.", detailEn: "TAE uses a field-reversed-configuration hydrogen-boron path; in April 2025 its Norm device had a breakthrough, and in June it raised over $150 million more (over $1.3 billion cumulative), with Chevron and Google investing. Copernicus is being built in Irvine, targeting net energy by the end of the decade, paving the way for the Da Vinci commercial plant in the early 2030s." },
  3042: { descEn: "The world's largest direct-air-capture facility in Ector County, Texas, live by end-2025.", detailEn: "Stratos, built by Occidental's 1PointFive in Ector County (Midland-Odessa), Texas, is the world's largest DAC, designed to capture up to 500,000 tonnes of CO₂ a year, $1.3 billion. It got an EPA Class VI well permit in April 2025, with commercial operation by end-2025, and BlackRock invested $550 million." },
  3120: { descEn: "A 756 MW reservoir-type plant on the Tamor River in eastern Nepal, handed to India's SJVN.", detailEn: "On the Tamor River in eastern Nepal, 756 MW. Nepal's government decided to hand the project to India's SJVN to develop, with the investment board requiring revised license documents to advance surveys — one of the larger items in the Indo-Nepal hydropower portfolio." },
  3172: { descEn: "Adani's 1,800 MW Gandikota pumped storage in YSR Kadapa, Andhra Pradesh, with ANDRITZ supplying electromechanical, the flagship of Adani's pumped storage.", detailEn: "Adani Green is building 1,800 MW Gandikota pumped storage in YSR Kadapa district, Andhra Pradesh, with ANDRITZ winning the electromechanical contract in September 2025. It is Adani's third pumped-storage contract to ANDRITZ after 500 MW Chitravathi and 1,500 MW Tarali, with the company targeting over 5 GW of new pumped storage by 2030." },
  3185: { descEn: "Tata Power's 1,800 MW Shirawta pumped storage in Pune, Maharashtra, breaking ground July 2026.", detailEn: "Tata Power signed an MoU with Maharashtra to build two pumped-storage projects — 1,800 MW at Shirawta in Pune and 1,000 MW at Bhivpuri in Raigad, 2,800 MW combined. Shirawta's 1,800 MW (~110 billion rupees) is planned to break ground in July 2026, providing long-duration storage from 2028." },
  3210: { descEn: "Premier Energies expands TOPCon cells and integrates toward wafers in Hyderabad, Telangana.", detailEn: "Premier Energies is expanding over 110 billion rupees at Fab City in Hyderabad, Telangana, targeting cells of 8.4 GW and modules of 11.1 GW by mid-2026, and forming a 74:26 JV with Taiwan's Sino-American Silicon (SAS) to build a 2 GW wafer-slicing line, integrating upstream toward ingots/wafers and entering inverters and storage." },
  3231: { descEn: "India's sovereign-AI compute program, with over 38,000 GPUs deployed across multiple data centers.", detailEn: "The IndiaAI Mission compute portal showed 38,231 GPUs deployed in December 2025, up over 80% from 20,000 in March, carried by Yotta, E2E, NxtGen and Jio, opened to startups with a ~150-rupee/hour subsidy; Sarvam AI got 4,096 H100s to build a sovereign LLM, with the government targeting 100,000 GPUs by end-2026." },
  3540: { descEn: "Tibet's first large-scale AI-compute center, a 9.2-billion-yuan, 2,000 PFLOPS facility filling a Qinghai-Tibet Plateau gap.", detailEn: "Tibet's first large-scale AI-compute center totals ~9.2 billion yuan with 2,000 PFLOPS planned, filling the Qinghai-Tibet Plateau's large-scale-compute gap, relying on plateau clean energy to support AI-industry development." },
  3576: { descEn: "A fully automated container terminal at Dongjiakou, Qingdao Port, designed for 3.15 million TEU/year.", detailEn: "The phase-1 container terminal in the east port of the Langyatai operating area builds one each of 70,000-, 100,000- and 150,000-tonne berths (hydraulic structures designed for 100,000-tonne container ships), designed for 3.15 million TEU/year, ~9.1 billion yuan planned — Qingdao Port's second fully automated terminal at Dongjiakou after Qianwan. Preliminary design is approved." },
  4051: { descEn: "China Harbour's Lagos Green Line rail from the Lekki Free Trade Zone to the wharf area, with traction power.", detailEn: "Lagos State, the Ministry of Finance's MOFI and China Harbour (CHEC) reached an agreement to develop the Green Line rail, with CHEC handling design, financing, construction and operation. The 68 km Green Line would run from the Lekki Free Trade Zone to the wharf area, with elevated track, stations and a traction-power system. Nigeria's federal government allocated 146.1 billion naira in early 2025 to support it — a backbone of Lagos metro rail." },
  4296: { descEn: "State Grid (SGID) acquires the Mantiqueira transmission concession in Minas Gerais from Brookfield, Brazil's largest single transmission-concession deal.", detailEn: "On November 28, 2025 a closing ceremony was held at Brazil's mining-and-energy ministry, with State Grid Brazil Holding (SGBH) acquiring Mantiqueira Transmissora from Brookfield's FIP Brasil Energia for ~7 billion reais (~$1.3 billion). The assets in Minas Gerais include 11 lines at 230/345/500 kV (~924 km) and 8 substations, ~1,222 km of total concession mileage, with the concession from ANEEL's 2015 transmission auction lot A, in operation since 2022, valid to 2046. The acquisition further cements State Grid's lead in Brazil's transmission grid." },
  4383: { descEn: "Huayou Cobalt's high-nickel cathode-materials plant in Hungary, planned for 108,000 tonnes/year, phase 1 at 25,000.", detailEn: "Huayou is building a high-nickel ternary cathode-materials plant in Hungary, with total planned capacity of 108,000 tonnes/year, ~9.585 billion yuan total; phase 1 of 25,000 tonnes/year (~1.889 billion yuan) is built and in line commissioning, deeply entering Europe's EV supply chain to supply nearby European battery plants." },
  4451: { descEn: "SPIC's 2 GW hydro-solar hybrid in Pará, Brazil, with a winning price as low as $18/MWh — a Latin American record.", detailEn: "In the Amazon basin of Pará in northern Brazil, SPIC relies on regional large hydropower's regulating ability to plan 2 GW of solar, forming a large hydro-solar hybrid clean-energy base. In a Brazilian renewables auction it won at ~$18/MWh, a Latin American solar low-price record, reflecting Chinese solar's full-chain cost advantage. On completion it will send clean power via Brazil's national grid to southeastern load centers." },
  4508: { descEn: "DayOne enters the Nordics with ~€1.2 billion, building large hyperscale campuses in Lahti and Kouvola, Finland.", detailEn: "DayOne announced in 2025 it is entering the Nordics with ~€1.2 billion, building large hyperscale data-center campuses in Lahti and Kouvola, Finland, as the core of its European strategy. The platform leverages the Nordic cold climate and clean power for low-cost, sustainable scale compute, with the second Finnish campus under construction. The Finnish platform, with Singapore–Johor–Riau, Thailand, Japan and Hong Kong, forms DayOne's global compute map." },
  1662: { descEn: "An Indonesian HPAL nickel-cobalt project (Morowali), with CMOC holding 30% and offtake.", detailEn: "In the Morowali Industrial Park, Indonesia, a laterite-nickel HPAL project led by Huayou, designed for 60,000 tonnes/year (nickel metal) of nickel-cobalt hydroxide (MHP). CMOC holds 30% via Woyuan Holdings with proportional offtake. The project reached full output; in Q2 2025 MHP made 20,700 tonnes of nickel and 1,877 tonnes of cobalt, ~38% over design — a key part of CMOC's new-energy nickel-cobalt push." },
  3541: { descEn: "China's first data-center green-power direct-connect, source-grid-load-storage integrated zero-carbon compute base in Ulanqab.", detailEn: "In the Chahar Hi-Tech Zone of Ulanqab, on 574 mu and 450,000 m², it builds 12 compute halls with ~25,000 racks planned, ~9.1 billion yuan total. It is paired with 300,000 kW of wind-solar-storage in Chayouqian (200,000 wind, 100,000 solar, 45,000 storage), self-generating and self-using 848 million kWh of green power a year." },
  4199: { descEn: "Huayou's Indonesia Morowali (IMIP) laterite-nickel HPAL project, 60,000 tonnes of nickel.", detailEn: "In the Tsingshan IMIP park at Morowali, Sulawesi, Indonesia, producing 60,000 tonnes (nickel metal) and 7,800 tonnes (cobalt metal) of nickel-cobalt hydroxide (MHP) a year. Huayou holds 57%, CMOC 30% and Qingchuang International 10%, ~$1.28 billion total. It reached full output in H1 2022 with sustained over-production; the ore-slurry pipeline is connected to further cut costs." },
  1286: { descEn: "Brazil's and Latin America's first immersed-tube undersea tunnel.", detailEn: "Crossing the Santos port channel to link Santos and Guarujá, 1.5 km long with an 870 m immersed-tube section, 3 lanes each way (one reserved for a VLT light rail), with pedestrian and bike paths. Portugal's Mota-Engil won a 30-year PPP concession, ~6.8 billion reais total." },
  1593: { descEn: "China Energy Engineering's EPC for the Sdair 2 GW wind farm in Riyadh province, $1.251 billion.", detailEn: "A China Energy Engineering International, Guangdong Electric Power and Northwest Institute consortium is the general contractor for the PIF fifth-phase Sdair 2 GW onshore wind in Saudi Arabia, ~$1.251 billion, with the project company formed by SPPC, PIF and Aramco Power (ACWA Power-led) as owner. It is a major breakthrough for China Energy Engineering in the Saudi and Middle East wind market, with a ~30-month schedule, three projects totaling 19.554 billion yuan." },
  2509: { descEn: "First Quantum's large Kansanshi expansion.", detailEn: "First Quantum Minerals' (FQM) $1.25-billion S3 expansion at the Kansanshi copper mine in Zambia's Northwestern Province adds processing capacity to sharply boost copper output — one of the core projects driving Zambia's push for million-tonne copper output by 2026." },
  2993: { descEn: "MP Materials' Northlake magnet plant (10X) in Texas, with all output going to the Pentagon for a decade.", detailEn: "MP Materials is investing over $1.25 billion in a 10X rare-earth-magnet campus at Northlake, Texas, live 2028, raising total U.S. magnet capacity to ~10,000 tonnes at full output. In 2025 it struck a strategic partnership with the Defense Department (DoD became the largest shareholder, with a guaranteed NdPr price of $110/kg), with all 10X output going to the Pentagon." },
  1289: { descEn: "An Açu port grain terminal plus EF-118 rail corridor.", detailEn: "The Port of Açu at São João da Barra, Rio de Janeiro, operated by Prumo, plans a dedicated grain terminal (~550 million reais, in use by end-2026). A supporting EF-118 railway phase 1 of 246 km links São João da Barra to Santa Leopoldina, Espírito Santo, with a 50-year concession expected to cost ~6.6 billion reais and capacity up to 24 million tonnes/year." },
  111: { descEn: "China's first million-kW-scale hydropower plant to use the EPC model for its full cycle.", detailEn: "On the middle Yalong River in Muli, Liangshan, Sichuan, totaling 1.02 million kW, the seventh step of the middle Yalong's 'one reservoir, seven steps.' The river was diverted in January 2024, dam concrete pouring began December 2025, and it targets 2029 operation." },
  117: { descEn: "A major offshore-wind project in Shandong's Bozhong waters.", detailEn: "In the Bozhong waters east of Dongying, Shandong, planned at 900 MW in north and south zones; in June 2025 the north zone (400 MW) fully grid-connected — a key part of Shandong's three offshore-wind bases of Bozhong, Peninsula North and Peninsula South." },
  119: { descEn: "A large offshore wind project off Dafeng, Yancheng, Jiangsu.", detailEn: "Off Dafeng, Yancheng, Jiangsu, ~33 km offshore, with 4 offshore wind farms totaling 850 MW, required to be approved and started by end-2025 and first units online by August 2026 — part of Yancheng's 100-billion-yuan offshore-wind industrial base." },
  149: { descEn: "ENGIE's largest operating onshore wind farm worldwide.", detailEn: "In Bahia, Brazil, 24 wind farms with 188 turbines totaling 846 MW. Commercial operation began in phases from August 2024, with full load by December 2025 — ENGIE's largest operating onshore wind farm worldwide, powering ~1.5 million households." },
  280: { descEn: "A 100,000-card GPU cluster in the Arctic Circle, hydropower-driven.", detailEn: "In Narvik in Norway's Arctic Circle, a partnership of OpenAI, Nscale and Aker, initially $1 billion, targeting 100,000 GPUs, phase 1 at 230 MW and 520 MW at full load, using Norway's cheap hydropower and cold climate, with first GPUs expected online by end-2026." },
  303: { descEn: "A key segment of the Beijing-Hong Kong (Taiwan) corridor.", detailEn: "From Xiong'an station south to Shangqiu, 552 km at 350 km/h, with 94% bridges; track-laying began September 2025, with power-on and joint commissioning in March 2026, targeting October 2026 opening — a core part of the '8 vertical, 8 horizontal' Beijing-Hong Kong (Taiwan) corridor." },
  398: { descEn: "A fully permitted Arizona copper mine.", detailEn: "In Pima County, Arizona, Hudbay holds full permits; in 2025 Mitsubishi Corporation acquired 30% for $600 million, with pre-feasibility capital of ~$1.2 billion and an FID target of mid-2026. At full output, Hudbay's consolidated copper production would rise over 50%." },
  562: { descEn: "One of China Mobile's three ten-thousand-card AI-compute clusters.", detailEn: "China Mobile deployed its third ten-thousand-card AI-compute cluster in Guiyang (the other two in Hohhot and Harbin), with the three clusters totaling ~60,000 GPU cards. By end-2025 China Mobile's total AI compute reached 92.5 EFLOPS with over 1.5 million external IDC standard racks." },
  563: { descEn: "China's first batch of domestic, fully liquid-cooled ten-thousand-card public AI-compute centers.", detailEn: "China Telecom's e-Cloud first built and commercialized domestic fully-liquid-cooled ten-thousand-card clusters in the Beijing-Tianjin-Hebei and Yangtze Delta regions; in 2025 it launched the world's first commercial compute super-node in the Greater Bay Area, with self-owned AI compute reaching 46 EFLOPS and compute investment up 22% year-on-year." },
  602: { descEn: "CtrlS builds a 400 MW AI data-center cluster in Telangana, Hyderabad.", detailEn: "At Davos 2025 CtrlS announced ~$1.2 billion to build a 400 MW AI data-center cluster of over 2 million square feet in Hyderabad, backed by the Telangana government — a sign of southern India's large-scale compute expansion." },
  633: { descEn: "Huayou's largest HPAL project in Indonesia's Weda Bay area.", detailEn: "In the Weda Bay industrial park on Halmahera Island, Indonesia, controlled by Huayou Cobalt, started up in Q1 2024, using high-pressure acid leaching to extract nickel and cobalt from laterite ore, ~120,000 tonnes/year of nickel-equivalent MHP, with 2025 shipments up 30% year-on-year — a core overseas asset of Huayou's nickel-cobalt value chain." },
  709: { descEn: "One of the world's largest coking-coal mines, expanding.", detailEn: "In Mongolia's South Gobi province, with total resources of ~6.4 billion tonnes (a quarter premium coking coal), it produced 28.64 million tonnes in 2024. In late 2025 it opened the Bortolgoi coking-coal block (424 million tonnes of reserves) to international investors, expected to generate over $1 billion of export revenue." },
  718: { descEn: "A new iron mine in Minas Gerais, Brazil.", detailEn: "In Minas Gerais, Brazil, an important capacity addition for Vale's Southeastern System, ~15 million tonnes/year of iron ore. It completed its ramp-up in H1 2025; with the Vargem Grande project, it adds ~30 million tonnes/year of new capacity for the company." },
  802: { descEn: "A 550 MW offshore wind project off Rudong, Jiangsu.", detailEn: "Off Rudong, Nantong, led by Three Gorges New Energy, 550 MW, advanced as a 2025 Jiangsu major project, with 8 MW+ turbines and a 220 kV offshore substation planned. On completion it feeds ~1.5 billion kWh a year, helping Jiangsu keep its national offshore-wind lead." },
  1031: { descEn: "The world's first 200 mm silicon-carbide fab, ramping up.", detailEn: "The Mohawk Valley plant at Marcy, New York is the world's first 200 mm (8-inch) silicon-carbide wafer fab, ~$1.2 billion, supplying power devices for EVs and the grid. Wolfspeed emerged from Chapter 11 in September 2025, cutting debt ~70%; line utilization is ramping from 20% toward 25% by year-end, relying on the new John Palmour materials plant for wafers." },
  1040: { descEn: "India's largest green-hydrogen plant directly supplying an EAF-steel DRI unit.", detailEn: "JSW Energy built India's largest green-hydrogen plant next to the JSW steelworks at Vijayanagar, Karnataka, supplying the steelworks' DRI unit 3,800 tonnes of green hydrogen and 30,000 tonnes of green oxygen a year under a seven-year deal, live November 2025. JSW Steel is concurrently planning a $1.2-billion, 1.5-million-tonne/year 'hydrogen-ready' DRI plant, initially natural-gas-blended and ultimately 100% green hydrogen, helping cut carbon intensity 42% before 2030." },
  1043: { descEn: "India's largest 525 kA cell produces first aluminum, entering the million-tonne tier.", detailEn: "Vedanta's BALCO in Korba, Chhattisgarh built India's largest 525 kA electrolytic cell, producing first aluminum in October 2025, surpassing the prior 378 kA national benchmark. With the new 435,000-tonne/year smelter line, BALCO's total capacity reaches 1 million tonnes/year, joining the 'million-tonne club,' with part of the power planned from round-the-clock renewables — a giant electrolytic grid load." },
  1086: { descEn: "Central China's largest unit-capacity pumped storage.", detailEn: "In Jiankou township, Luoning county, Luoyang, Henan, with 4 reversible units of 350,000 kW each totaling 1.4 million kW, a 604 m rated head, ~8.88 billion yuan total — central China's largest unit-capacity pumped storage. It provides peaking, frequency/phase regulation, emergency backup and black start, generating ~1.19 billion kWh a year. Its first unit started up on October 16, 2025, with all units targeted for 2026." },
  1087: { descEn: "China's first 400 MW-class super-capacity variable-speed pumped storage.", detailEn: "In Zhongdong village, Gaotan town, Huidong county, Huizhou, Guangdong, planned at 1.2 million kW with three 400 MW-class units (one a super-capacity variable-speed unit), ~8.3 billion yuan total — China's first 400 MW-class variable-speed pumped storage, with the world's highest-head (804 m) reinforced-concrete high-pressure pipeline. The variable-speed unit regulates flexibly, better serving Greater Bay Area renewable absorption and grid stability. By early 2026 the underground powerhouse entered electromechanical installation, aiming for the first unit in 2026." },
  1269: { descEn: "Latin America's first AI-native data center, in Sumaré, São Paulo, 90 MW native AI.", detailEn: "In May 2026 Ascenty announced $1.2 billion to build 4 pre-leased AI data centers totaling 150 MW within 18 months, the core being Sumaré 3 in São Paulo — 90 MW, ~48,000 m² — billed as Latin America's first data center designed from scratch for large-scale AI, supporting 1 MW/rack liquid cooling. 60 MW is already leased by a single global tech customer." },
  1270: { descEn: "Ascenty Vinhedo 3, a single-tenant AI data center in Vinhedo, São Paulo, 90 MW.", detailEn: "As part of Ascenty's $1.2-billion, 150 MW AI expansion, Vinhedo 3 is a 90 MW single-tenant data center, with Vinhedo 4 and 5 each planned at 45 MW. The program equals 40% of the capacity the company built in its 15-year history, all on 100% renewable power." },
  1346: { descEn: "A 2 GW solar plant west of Doha, with Samsung as EPC contractor.", detailEn: "Dukhan solar, ~80 km west of Doha, is 2 GW, built in two 1 GW phases. In September 2025 QatarEnergy signed the EPC contract with Samsung C&T; phase 1 supplies the Kahramaa grid by end-2028 and phase 2 completes mid-2029, supporting Qatar's over-4 GW renewable target by 2030." },
  1348: { descEn: "Oman's first green-ammonia project, phase 1 at 100,000 tonnes/year.", detailEn: "India's ACME Group is developing Oman's first green-ammonia project in the Duqm Special Economic Zone (SEZAD). Phase 1 pairs 486 MWp of solar and a 320 MW electrolyzer for ~100,000 tonnes/year of green ammonia, with a ~7-million-liter/day desalination plant and hydrogen/ammonia storage. It got a $488-million loan and started construction in May 2025, with phase 1 targeting Q1 2027 completion." },
  1350: { descEn: "Saudi's first east-to-central ±500 kV HVDC line, exporting renewables.", detailEn: "One of two ±500 kV HVDC lines Saudi Electricity Company tendered in January 2025, linking the Eastern Nariyah IPP with the central Zulfi 9064 substation, ~508 km and 3,000 MW. It is the core of nine new HVDC lines under Saudi's ~$58.7-billion grid-upgrade framework for 2025-2030, connecting the eastern and central operating zones and exporting renewables." },
  1414: { descEn: "Hamad International Airport phase B expansion, raising annual capacity above 70 million.", detailEn: "Hamad International Airport's phase B expansion finished in March 2025, extending the D and E concourses and raising annual passenger capacity above 70 million. Concourse E opened on February 1, 2025, adding 51,000 m² and 8 contact gates; phase B added 17 gates for a total of 62, with construction begun January 2023." },
  1419: { descEn: "A NGL fractionation center for the Jafurah gas field in Jubail.", detailEn: "The Riyas project builds new NGL fractionation trains, utilities, storage and export facilities in Jubail, processing NGL from the Jafurah unconventional gas field via a 320 km pipeline to Jafurah phase-1 package 6. The facilities are within the Jafurah Midstream Gas Company (JMGC), leased back to Aramco for 20 years — a key node in the petrochemical-feedstock supply chain." },
  1430: { descEn: "A new large open-pit gold mine in Saudi Arabia, FID taken in 2025.", detailEn: "In Mecca province ~200 km northeast of Taif, Ma'aden took FID in August 2025, the core of its strategy to double gold output by 2030. An open-pit mine with a modern mill, it processes ~8 million tonnes of ore a year for ~300,000 ounces of gold, with a ~12-year life. In October 2025 it awarded Bechtel a ~$104-million EPCM contract." },
  1457: { descEn: "A $1.2-billion mega wind-storage project, FID taken in 2026.", detailEn: "In April 2026 TotalEnergies took FID on the Mirny project in Zhambyl province, Kazakhstan: 1 GW of wind (150 turbines) with 300 MW/600 MWh of battery storage, $1.2 billion total, ~75% from external financing (EBRD-led). TotalEnergies holds 60%, with Samruk Energy and KazMunayGas 20% each. Construction began March 2026, generating ~4 billion kWh a year, ~4% of Kazakhstan's power — its largest onshore wind and first industrial-scale wind-storage." },
  1466: { descEn: "The flagship cross-border interconnection sending Central Asian hydropower via Afghanistan to Pakistan (CASA-1000).", detailEn: "The project includes a 485 km 500 kV AC line from Datka, Kyrgyzstan to Khujand, Tajikistan, and a ~750 km, 1,300 MW ±500 kV HVDC line from Tajikistan's Sangtuda converter station via Kabul to Nowshera, Pakistan. By April 2025 the converter station and Datka-Khujand section were largely complete; by October 2025 the Afghan section was ~75% and the Pakistan section over 90%, targeting full operation by end-2026." },
  1531: { descEn: "Deep-processing and aromatics expansion at Kazakhstan's oldest refinery, the Atyrau refinery.", detailEn: "Under KMG's lead, the Atyrau refinery is modernizing, building a new aromatics unit (~496,000 tonnes/year paraxylene, ~133,000 tonnes/year benzene) and raising throughput to 6.1 million tonnes/year. In the first 8 months of 2025 light-oil yield hit a record 77.5% with processing depth of 88.6%. The overhaul is part of Kazakhstan's 2025-2040 refining strategy, aiming to lift its three refineries' total capacity from 18.4 million to 27.4 million tonnes." },
  1559: { descEn: "Expansion of the Aktogay copper mine in Abai, Kazakhstan, with twin mills over design.", detailEn: "In Abai province, Kazakhstan, a $1.2-billion expansion doubled sulfide-ore processing to 50 million tonnes/year, with the second mill commissioned in 2021. In 2025 sulfide-ore processing hit a record 62 million tonnes, well over design, ranking it among the world's leading copper producers." },
  1561: { descEn: "ERG's hot-briquetted-iron (HBI) plant in Rudny, hydrogen-ready, with SSGPO iron-ore pellets.", detailEn: "In Rudny, Kostanay province, ERG is building a hydrogen-ready HBI plant over $1.2 billion with Primetals and Midrex, producing 2 million tonnes/year of hot-briquetted iron, metallization ≥93.5%, ~90% iron, replacing coke with natural gas and switchable to hydrogen smelting in future. Feedstock comes from subsidiary SSGPO's iron-oxide pellets. Announced October 2025, it targets 2029 startup." },
  1562: { descEn: "One of Kazakhstan's largest gold mines (Raygorodok), acquired by Zijin for $1.2 billion in 2025.", detailEn: "In Akmola province, Kazakhstan, one of the country's largest gold mines. On June 30, 2025 Zijin announced acquiring 100% of RG Gold and RG Processing for $1.2 billion, closing September 30. It produced 6 tonnes of gold in 2024; Zijin plans to lift mining-and-processing capacity to 10 million tonnes/year via pit optimization and beneficiation improvements." },
  1682: { descEn: "CATL's Karawang battery plant in Indonesia, the manufacturing end of an integrated battery project, phase 1 at 6.9 GWh.", detailEn: "CATL's Brunp (CBL) with Indonesian SOEs ANTAM and IBC is advancing a near-$6-billion full-chain integrated battery project in Indonesia; the manufacturing end is at the KNIC industrial city in Karawang, West Java, phase 1 at 6.9 GWh/year. A groundbreaking was held in Karawang on July 1, 2025 — the largest such project in Southeast Asia, expected to create 8,000 direct jobs." },
  1694: { descEn: "Thailand's first 1 GW-class digital-infrastructure platform.", detailEn: "DayOne's hyperscale AI campus at Chonburi Tech Park, Thailand is the country's first digital-infrastructure platform planned for 1 GW. Using phased rolling construction, over 100 MW of IT capacity comes online in 2026, with renewables introduced from 2027 via Amata B.Grimm (AMBRE) and PEA, strengthening Thailand's compute supply as a Southeast Asian connectivity hub." },
  1698: { descEn: "Bridge's BKK01 campus in Chonburi, one of Thailand's largest under construction.", detailEn: "Bridge Data Centres' BKK01 hyperscale campus at Mueang Khlong Tamru in Chonburi, ~100 rai (~16 hectares), phase-1 IT load ~200 MW, ~$1.2 billion total, with Thai BOI investment-promotion approval. In March 2025 the parent got a $2.8-billion syndicated loan to accelerate expansion in Malaysia, Thailand and other high-growth markets; a water-supply deal provides water from May 2026, markedly boosting Thailand's operating compute." },
  1744: { descEn: "Fortescue's green-hydrogen project at the Port of Açu.", detailEn: "Australia's Fortescue signed a cooperation agreement with the Port of Açu to build a 300 MW electrolyzer producing ~250,000 tonnes/year of green ammonia, using the port's deepwater export conditions for international markets. The project is in feasibility and permitting, advancing alongside Fortescue's larger project at Pecém, targeting an investment-decision window in 2026-2027 with the northeast's green-hydrogen pipeline." },
  1759: { descEn: "RT-One's Uberlândia AI data center, billed as Latin America's largest AI-compute park in Minas Gerais.", detailEn: "U.S.-backed RT-One acquired over 1 million m² in Uberlândia to build the southwest region's first large AI data center, supplied by Hitachi, Siemens, WEG, Vertiv, Schneider and others. Phase 1 is 100 MW, expandable to 400 MW, with first modules delivered in 2026, built in stages over 2-4 years, on 100% renewable power." },
  1791: { descEn: "Vale's Apolo iron mine, Minas Gerais's only new iron mine, with no tailings dam.", detailEn: "Between Caeté and Santa Bárbara in Minas Gerais, Vale's only planned new iron mine in the state, using natural-moisture dry processing with no tailings dam, with an 8 km spur to the Vitória-Minas railway, ~14 million tonnes/year of sinter feed. The company plans to get an installation license in early 2028 and start up around 2030 — crucial to reviving Minas iron capacity." },
  1844: { descEn: "Saudi's east-to-central ±500 kV HVDC line 3 (Nariyah-Zulff), a new HVDC corridor from the eastern grid to the central grid.", detailEn: "To connect the Eastern (EOA) and Central (COA) operating areas and absorb eastern gas power and renewables, SEC is building a ±500 kV line from the Nariyah IPP to the central Zulff 9064 BSP, ~508 km and 3,000 MW. The main contract bids were submitted, with the deadline extended to February 2026; Saudi's SSEM and Pakistan's NPCC are bidding, with operation expected around 2028." },
  1881: { descEn: "Ras Al-Khair 2&3 desalination plants, large SWRO for industrial and urban water.", detailEn: "SWPC's Ras Al-Khair 2&3 independent water plants total 1 million tonnes/day of reverse-osmosis capacity, serving the Jubail and Dammam industrial zones and Riyadh and Qassim population and industrial growth. Using low-energy reverse osmosis, they target 2028 operation, supporting the Ras Al-Khair heavy-industry base and Eastern Province expansion." },
  1929: { descEn: "Qiddiya multi-utility (solar and district cooling): solar, distribution, district cooling and water for Riyadh's entertainment city.", detailEn: "The Qiddiya PPP multi-utility, won by Alfanar, includes a 300 MW solar plant, distribution, potential potable water, sewage, irrigation, district cooling and ICT. The campus connects to the Saudi Electricity Company grid via a 380 kV substation and overhead lines (L&T built the transmission section from July 2024). Phase 1 opens 2027, the F1 track completes 2027 with the first race in 2028, with utilities delivered in step." },
  2028: { descEn: "Vantage's JHB1 campus in Johor (formerly Yondr), a 300 MW+ campus acquired from Yondr.", detailEn: "In November 2025 Vantage Data Centers completed a $1.6-billion Asia-Pacific platform capital raise (led by GIC and Abu Dhabi's ADIA) and acquired Yondr's 300 MW+ hyperscale campus JHB1 at Sedenak Tech Park, Johor. On ~73 acres across 3 data centers and over 300 MW of IT capacity at full build, using direct-to-chip liquid cooling, in the Johor-Singapore Special Economic Zone — Vantage's third campus in Malaysia." },
  2049: { descEn: "The Funan Techo Canal, a cross-border inland canal linking Phnom Penh port and the Gulf of Thailand.", detailEn: "180 km long, from Phnom Penh port via Takeo and Kampot to the Gulf of Thailand, giving Cambodia a sea route bypassing Vietnam. Investment fell from $1.8 billion to ~$1.2 billion, with Cambodia holding 51% and China 49%, led by CCCC and China Road and Bridge for construction and operation. Ground was broken August 5, 2024, targeting 2028 completion; in 2025 phase-1 land demarcation advanced and land acquisition and clearance began on some sections." },
  2089: { descEn: "Ceria's Merah Putih nickel smelter, an Indonesian low-carbon nickel-iron flagship.", detailEn: "In the Wolo area of Kolaka, Southeast Sulawesi, a fully Indonesian-owned company. Using 72 MVA rectangular RKEF technology, the first line started up April 27, 2025, producing 63,200 tonnes/year of nickel-iron (~13,900 tonnes of nickel). It plans four RKEF lines for 252,700 tonnes of nickel-iron, plus MHP/HPAL and nickel-matte refining, using PLN green-power certification." },
  2252: { descEn: "ACWA Power and Nareva win Noor Midelt II/III, two 400 MWp solar-plus-battery projects.", detailEn: "In August 2025 MASEN's international tender was decided, with Saudi's ACWA Power and Morocco's Nareva winning Noor Midelt 2 and 3, each 400 MWp solar with battery storage (BESS) discharging 230 MW for 2 hours at peak. Using a BOO model and 30-year PPAs, phase II won on a 200-free-storage-cycle bid, beating Engie, EDF and Masdar. On completion ACWA's Moroccan capacity exceeds 1.5 GW." },
  2262: { descEn: "Nexus-Nvidia Morocco sovereign AI data center, a $1.2-billion sovereign AI center at Nouaceur, Casablanca, Africa's first sovereign-AI platform.", detailEn: "A consortium of Nexus Core Systems, Nvidia, Naver and Lloyd Capital is building a $1.2-billion AI data center at Nouaceur, Casablanca, billed as Africa's first sovereign-AI infrastructure platform. The Casablanca-Settat regional council allocated 666 hectares at Nouaceur, with key land acquisition done in 2025, targeting nearshore low-cost AI/cloud compute for Europe." },
  2357: { descEn: "Winning Consortium's alumina refinery (WCAG) in Boké, Guinea, started December 2025.", detailEn: "In December 2025 Guinea's government formally launched construction of the Winning Consortium alumina refinery at Dobali in Boké province, 1.2 million tonnes/year of alumina, over $1.2 billion — one of the largest industrial projects in Guinea's history. It aims to add value through local bauxite processing, create jobs and transfer technology, with economic benefits concentrated in Boké and Lower Guinea." },
  2369: { descEn: "The Imouraren uranium mine, one of the world's largest, nationalized by Niger in 2025, with an uncertain restart.", detailEn: "In the Agadez region of Niger, discovered in 1966, with over 200,000 tonnes U of reserves — one of the world's largest uranium mines, idle since 2015. Formerly controlled by France's Orano. In late 2024 Orano lost operating control and deconsolidated it, and in June 2025 Niger unilaterally nationalized it. A restart needs heavy investment with uncertain timing; Orano estimates ~two years to restart if a deal is reached." },
  2420: { descEn: "The Kabanga nickel polymetallic refinery, a world-class undeveloped sulfide-nickel deposit, started October 2025 with a polymetallic refinery.", detailEn: "In Ngara, Kagera province, ~35 km west of Lake Tanganyika, one of the world's largest undeveloped sulfide-nickel deposits (~52-58 million tonnes of reserves, ~1.98% nickel). Tembo Nickel began mine construction in October 2025; a supporting polymetallic refinery will make battery-grade nickel, copper and cobalt, with refinery FID targeting end-2026, serving the global battery supply chain." },
  2473: { descEn: "An upgrade of the Saldanha iron-ore export corridor, the Northern Cape-to-Saldanha iron-ore rail-port corridor.", detailEn: "One of Transnet's three priority corridors, the Saldanha iron-ore corridor links the Sishen and Kolomela iron mines in the Northern Cape to Saldanha port on the west coast. Kumba is extending Sishen's and Kolomela's lives beyond 20 years on Northern Cape resources. The corridor upgrade brings in private capital to boost rail capacity and port-handling efficiency — key to reviving South Africa's mining-export logistics." },
  2562: { descEn: "Cameroon's Kribi FLNG floating liquefaction, an offshore LNG export facility off Kribi.", detailEn: "Golar LNG's Hilli Episeyo floating liquefaction vessel liquefies Cameroonian gas for export off Kribi, ~1.2 million tonnes/year. Its charter expires in 2026 and Golar has re-chartered it to Argentina, so unless a new charter is signed, Kribi FLNG may halt in 2026, underscoring gas-supply and capacity bottlenecks." },
  2641: { descEn: "Iluka's Eneabba rare-earth refinery, Australia's first full-chain rare-earth refinery.", detailEn: "At Eneabba, Western Australia, built by Iluka Resources, Australia's first full-chain rare-earth separation-and-refining plant, making neodymium-praseodymium (NdPr) and heavy rare earths like dysprosium and terbium oxides. Backed by over A$1.2 billion of federal loans, with feedstock from the Eneabba monazite stockpile and third-party concentrate, it becomes important Western non-China rare-earth separation capacity, targeting 2027 startup." },
  2665: { descEn: "Life extension of the North West Shelf (Karratha), extending Australia's oldest LNG plant to 2070.", detailEn: "The North West Shelf (NWS) at Karratha, Western Australia is Australia's earliest LNG export base; Woodside is advancing environmental approval to extend its operating license to 2070, with new gas sources like Browse backfilling. It got preliminary federal approval in 2025, extending its long-term LNG export capability." },
  2667: { descEn: "Olympic Dam copper-gold-uranium expansion (BHP), a world-class mine sprinting for 650,000 tonnes/year of copper.", detailEn: "In South Australia, one of the world's most important copper-gold-uranium-nickel deposits. BHP is putting over $840 million into growth projects in the southern mine area — declines, backfill systems, capacity ore passes and a new oxygen plant — and assessing smelter-refinery expansion to raise copper capacity to 650,000 tonnes/year, with a major expansion decision expected in 2028." },
  2676: { descEn: "Dubbo rare-earth polymetallic project (ASM), an NSW rare-earth and strategic-metals integration.", detailEn: "Near Dubbo, New South Wales, developed by ASM, with rare earths and strategic metals like zirconium, hafnium and niobium, planned as an integrated mine and refinery, linked to ASM's Korean metals plant to build a non-China rare-earth-metal-magnet supply chain, advancing financing and FID in 2025." },
  2725: { descEn: "The Baltic states' grid synchronization with continental Europe, decoupling Estonia/Latvia/Lithuania from the Russian grid.", detailEn: "In February 2025 the grids of Estonia, Latvia and Lithuania formally decoupled from the Russia-Belarus 'BRELL' synchronous zone and joined the continental-Europe synchronous grid via Poland, involving extensive grid reinforcement, synchronous condensers and control upgrades, ~€1.6 billion total. It is a landmark milestone for EU energy security and de-Russification." },
  2758: { descEn: "LKAB's Per Geijer rare-earth project (Kiruna, Sweden), Europe's largest known rare-earth deposit.", detailEn: "In Kiruna in northern Sweden, LKAB discovered at Per Geijer Europe's largest known rare-earth-oxide deposit (over 1.3 million tonnes REO), with associated phosphorus and iron. It plans to co-mine rare earths with iron ore and add separation — significant for breaking Europe's reliance on China for rare earths — advancing permits in 2025, targeting 2030s startup." },
  2816: { descEn: "The Linglong One small modular reactor (Changjiang, Hainan), the world's first onshore commercial SMR.", detailEn: "In Changjiang, Hainan, the world's first onshore commercial small modular reactor (ACP100/'Linglong One'), 125 MW. In 2025 it completed the containment integrity test in September, cold functional test in October and turbine test in December, expecting grid connection in H1 2026, usable for multipurpose power, heating and desalination." },
  2928: { descEn: "X-energy Xe-100 four units at Dow's Seadrift, Texas, with Amazon investing in X-energy deploying four high-temperature gas-cooled reactors at Dow's Seadrift.", detailEn: "The Xe-100 is a TRISO-fuel high-temperature gas-cooled reactor, 80 MWe per unit, 320 MW for four units, supplying power and steam to Dow's Seadrift site. In May 2025 the NRC accepted the construction-permit application; in November 2025 it completed a $700-million Series D and a ~$1-billion IPO; in February 2026 TRISO-X got the NRC's first Category-II fuel license." },
  3104: { descEn: "Tamil Nadu offshore wind, one of India's first commercial offshore wind, 500 MW off Tamil Nadu.", detailEn: "India's government approved 74.53 billion rupees of viability-gap funding for a first 1 GW of offshore wind (500 MW each off Tamil Nadu and Gujarat). The Tamil Nadu project is in the Gulf of Mannar; MNRE plans to launch tenders in February 2026, targeting 37 GW of offshore-wind auctions by 2030." },
  3105: { descEn: "Gujarat offshore wind, 500 MW in the Gulf of Khambhat, one of India's first commercial offshore wind.", detailEn: "In the Gulf of Khambhat off Gujarat, part of India's first 1 GW of offshore wind (74.53 billion rupees of viability-gap funding), tendered by SECI. A September 2024 tender failed for lack of interest; the center plans to relaunch it with Tamil Nadu in February 2026." },
});

/* —— 批次18：全库投资额 TOP（约10-12亿美元）约100条 —— */
Object.assign(window.ENERGY_EN, {
  3119: { descEn: "A 750 MW plant on the Seti River in western Nepal, led by NHPC.", detailEn: "On the Seti River in far-western Nepal, NHPC signed an MoU with Nepal's Investment Board (IBN) to jointly develop 750 MW West Seti and 450 MW Seti River-6 — part of the Indo-Nepal hydropower portfolio of ~11.2 GW, aimed at selling power to India." },
  3156: { descEn: "An India–Sri Lanka HVDC submarine interconnection (Madurai–New Habarana), ±320 kV, 2×500 MW VSC.", detailEn: "A ~285 km ±320 kV, 2×500 MW VSC HVDC line (with ~50 km of submarine cable) linking Madurai and New Habarana, ~99 billion rupees, with a first phase carrying 500 MW, implemented jointly by PGCIL and CEB. An MoU was signed in April 2025, with a joint working group confirming the technical scheme." },
  3169: { descEn: "Greenko's Saundatti pumped storage in Belagavi, Karnataka, with the existing Renuka Sagar reservoir as the lower pool.", detailEn: "Greenko is building 2,660 MW of integrated wind-solar-storage in Belagavi, Karnataka (1,260 MW standalone pumped storage, 1,000 MW solar, 400 MW wind), with a new upper reservoir and the existing Renuka Sagar reservoir as the lower pool — no water consumption — with GE Power India on electromechanical." },
  3177: { descEn: "Reliance Power's Kunnur solar-plus-storage in Andhra Pradesh, 930 MW solar with 465 MW/1,860 MWh storage, billed as Asia's largest single solar-storage.", detailEn: "Reliance Power subsidiary Reliance NU Suntech signed a 25-year PPA with SECI to build 930 MW (AC) solar integrating 465 MW/1,860 MWh of storage at Kunnur, Andhra Pradesh, with a ~100-billion-rupee investment cap — billed as Asia's largest single solar-storage, ensuring 4 hours of peak supply a day at a fixed 3.53 rupees/kWh, built in ~24 months." },
  3213: { descEn: "Adani Solar's Mundra integrated solar expansion, building a metallic-silicon-to-module vertically integrated solar base in Gujarat, expanding to 10 GW.", detailEn: "Adani Solar is building a vertically integrated solar base at Mundra, Gujarat covering metallurgical silicon, polysilicon, ingots, wafers, cells, modules and glass/EVA/backsheet/aluminum frames/junction boxes; in October 2024 it announced expanding integrated cell-and-module capacity to 10 GW by mid-2026 — one source of India's ALMM List-II-certified domestic cell capacity." },
  3243: { descEn: "Pune Metro phase 2, with Line-5 and a spur of ~31.6 km approved.", detailEn: "Phase 2 plans 48.86 km, of which Line-5 and a spur of ~31.64 km were approved by Maharashtra in October 2024, with a Swargate-Katraj corridor also advancing; construction is no earlier than 2026." },
  3248: { descEn: "Bhopal (Bhoj) Metro phase-1's first segment opened in December 2025.", detailEn: "Bhopal Metro is named after the 11th-century king Raja Bhoj; phase-1's first segment was unveiled on December 20, 2025 by Madhya Pradesh's chief minister and the Union urban minister, with costs rising above 100 billion rupees due to delays and overruns." },
  3258: { descEn: "Tuticorin outer harbor (V.O.C Port), planning two kilometer-long deepwater berths to build a southern-India transshipment hub.", detailEn: "The V.O.C Port outer-harbor project plans a breakwater and two 1,000-meter deepwater berths for large ships, competing with Sri Lankan and Singapore ports for transshipment cargo, tendered under a hybrid-annuity model (HAM), ~98.6 billion rupees, with bid documents sold from late 2025 to February 2026." },
  3290: { descEn: "India's Northeast gas grid (IGGL Indradhanush), an IGGL gas grid connecting the eight northeastern states, 85.35% complete by August 2025.", detailEn: "The Northeast gas grid, built by IGGL for ~100 billion rupees, connects eight states including Arunachal and Assam; by August 2025 physical progress was 85.35%, having completed the country's longest horizontal-directional drilling crossing of the Brahmaputra and commissioned the Guwahati-Numaligarh section." },
  3300: { descEn: "Expansion of the Gevra coal mine, India's largest open-pit coal mine, which after expansion will overtake Indonesia as Asia's largest.", detailEn: "In Korba, Chhattisgarh, operated by Coal India subsidiary South Eastern Coalfields. In early 2026 it got environmental approval, with rated capacity raised from 52.5 million to 70 million tonnes/year, then overtaking Indonesia's Sangatta as Asia's highest-output coal mine and the world's second-largest open-pit coal mine — the flagship of India's coal-output increase." },
  3406: { descEn: "Yalong River Suorong and Chabulang solar plants, two million-kW-class plants started up together in December 2025.", detailEn: "In the high-altitude area of Liangshan, Sichuan, with Kela and Lianghekou they form the world's largest, highest-altitude hydro-solar hybrid project. On December 31, 2025 the Suorong and Chabulang solar stations grid-connected together, achieving hydro-plus-solar complementarity at 3-million-kW class each." },
  3415: { descEn: "Hami 1,500 MW integrated CSP-storage (China Energy Engineering), the world's largest single-phase CSP-storage with single-unit CSP leaping to 150 MW.", detailEn: "In Hami, Xinjiang, 1,350 MW solar plus 150 MW tower CSP, with 8 hours of high-temperature molten-salt storage for continuous stable output, core-equipment localization over 99%, with single-unit CSP leaping from 50 MW to 150 MW. Turbine-foundation pouring was completed in July 2025." },
  3521: { descEn: "HBIS Zhangxuan's hydrogen-metallurgy green auto-sheet line, the world's first 120-million-tonne hydrogen metallurgy with a green auto-sheet casting line.", detailEn: "HBIS Zhangxuan Technology's world-first 1.2-million-tonne hydrogen-metallurgy demo continuously produces green DRI at 94% metallization; at end-2024 the world's first hydrogen-metallurgy green auto-sheet casting line started up, replacing coal with hydrogen to sharply cut carbon, ramping through 2025 and extending to vanadium-titanium-ore hydrogen-metallurgy pilots." },
  3530: { descEn: "Wanhua Chemical's 400,000-tonne POE project in Penglai, a 400,000-tonne POE solar-film material that brings total capacity to the world's largest 600,000 tonnes.", detailEn: "Wanhua Chemical's 400,000-tonne/year polyolefin-elastomer (POE) project at its Penglai base in Yantai started in March 2025, using self-developed metallocene-catalyst technology; on completion at end-2025 the company's total POE capacity reaches 600,000 tonnes/year, the world's largest single POE base, mainly supplying solar-encapsulation-film localization." },
  4099: { descEn: "State Grid (SGID) takes a stake in Greece's Crete-Attica Ariadne interconnection, joining the largest island interconnection.", detailEn: "Ariadne is Greece's largest transmission investment, ending Crete's electrical isolation with two 500 kV/500 MW HVDC submarine cables, over €1.1 billion and buried up to 1,200 m deep. In November 2024 Greek transmission operator IPTO signed an agreement to sell 20% to State Grid International Development (SGID), with the HVDC interconnection formally commissioned in May 2025." },
  4145: { descEn: "Envision's Bash & Dzhankeldy wind in Uzbekistan, Central Asia's largest wind development, 2×500 MW.", detailEn: "Envision supplies 1 GW of EN171-6.5MW turbines for ACWA Power's 500 MW Bash and 500 MW Dzhankeldy wind farms in Uzbekistan — Central Asia's largest wind development, in the Bukhara region. Envision is also building localized concrete-tower and blade capacity in Uzbekistan." },
  4160: { descEn: "Envision's Egypt ACWA 1.1 GW wind, one of MENA's first GW-scale onshore wind.", detailEn: "Envision supplies 8 MW-class turbines for ACWA Power's 1.1 GW onshore wind farm in Egypt — MENA's largest and first of its kind, in the wind-rich Gulf of Suez, helping Egypt's renewables-capacity targets." },
  4215: { descEn: "HQC's Indorama fertilizer expansion in Nigeria, gas-to-fertilizer with HQC on process design and engineering, Indorama expanding to 4.2 million tonnes of urea.", detailEn: "The Indorama fertilizer project in Rivers State, Nigeria relies on local gas, with single-line urea capacity of 1.4 million tonnes/year, the owner planning expansion to 4.2 million tonnes/year. HQC provides technical solutions, planning and engineering support for CNPC-system refining-and-fertilizer projects in Nigeria, Indonesia and elsewhere." },
  4236: { descEn: "CNCEC's coal-to-methanol complex in Indonesia, an East Kalimantan coal-to-methanol complex exporting China's core coal-chemical technology.", detailEn: "CNCEC is advancing a coal-to-methanol complex in East Kalimantan, Indonesia, leveraging the company's core and leading coal-chemical technology (a dominant domestic market share) to convert coal into methanol and other chemicals, serving Indonesia's industrialization and Belt-and-Road capacity cooperation." },
  4260: { descEn: "China Railway's Jeddah 2034 World Cup stadium and supporting facilities, general contract for the Jeddah stadium and four sports villages.", detailEn: "China Railway signed to build the stadium and supporting facilities for the Jeddah venue of Saudi Arabia's 2034 World Cup, in Mecca province, on ~500,000 m², with one large stadium and four sports villages, plus large-scale power, HVAC, electromechanical and intelligent systems. It is a landmark project for Chinese firms entering Saudi Arabia's premium building-and-public-works market, serving the 2034 World Cup." },
  4397: { descEn: "HQC's West Qurna-1 oilfield PMC in Iraq, the company's highest-value overseas service contract since 2020, in Basra.", detailEn: "On April 1, 2025 CNPC Engineering's HQC and Iraq's West Qurna company held a signing ceremony in Beijing for the West Qurna-1 oilfield PMC project. It is HQC's highest-value overseas service (project-management-contracting) project since 2020, in the West Qurna-1 oilfield in Basra, southern Iraq, taking on project-management contracting (PMC) for the oilfield's surface engineering and supporting facilities, supporting this giant field's output increase and integrated gas utilization." },
  4426: { descEn: "PowerChina's Rumah 1 1,800 MW combined-cycle plant in Saudi Arabia, ~80 km east of Riyadh, EPC.", detailEn: "On March 12, 2025 PowerChina signed the EPC contract for the Rumah 1 combined-cycle plant in Saudi Arabia with a developer consortium of ACWA Power, KEPCO and SEC. The plant ~80 km east of Riyadh is 1,800 MW, built by a PowerChina–Doosan (Korea) consortium. A key Vision-2030 project, it meets fast-growing power demand, improves the power mix and enhances grid peaking." },
  4427: { descEn: "PowerChina's Nairyah 1 1,800 MW combined-cycle plant in Saudi Arabia, ~50 km north of Al Nairyah in the Eastern Province, EPC.", detailEn: "On March 12, 2025 PowerChina, with an ACWA Power, KEPCO and SEC consortium, signed the EPC contract for the Nairyah 1 combined-cycle plant. The plant ~50 km north of Al Nairyah in the Eastern Province is 1,800 MW — with Rumah 1, 3,600 MW total — built by a PowerChina–Doosan consortium. It follows PowerChina's 2024 Taiba 1 and Qassim 1 gas plants as another large combined-cycle win in Saudi Arabia." },
  4459: { descEn: "Three Gorges International's Amaria 300 MW hydropower plant in Guinea, a dam-type plant on the Konkouré River, 300 MW, max dam height 78 m, a key Three Gorges hydropower investment in Guinea.", detailEn: "The Amaria hydropower plant is on the Konkouré River in central-western Guinea, using mixed-dam development, max dam height 78 m, reservoir 1.647 billion m³, 300 MW total. Invested by China and built by Sinohydro Bureau 3, with the Kaleta and Souapiti cascades it develops Guinea's hydropower resources. On completion it further boosts Guinea's power supply, cementing comprehensive China-Guinea hydropower cooperation." },
  4467: { descEn: "Zijin's RG (Raygorodok) gold mine in Kazakhstan, a producing gold mine acquired for $1.2 billion, entering Central Asia.", detailEn: "The RG (Raygorodok) gold mine in Akmola province, northern Kazakhstan, comprises south and north open pits ~2 km apart — one of Central Asia's largest and most technically advanced gold mines. On June 30, 2025 Zijin (Zijin Gold International) announced acquiring 100% for $1.2 billion, closing October 10 — another major gold acquisition after Ghana's Akyem, marking the company's entry to Central Asia and a 'Central Asian gold triangle.' RG holds ~197.4 tonnes of gold resources, averaging ~5.5-6 tonnes/year, strongly supporting Zijin's 2028 target of 100-110 tonnes of mined gold." },
  4483: { descEn: "GEM's Weiming/Merit high-matte nickel project in Indonesia, a pyrometallurgical high-matte nickel project planned for 50,000 tonnes of nickel a year.", detailEn: "One of GEM's four nickel-resource projects in Indonesia, built with Weiming Environmental and Merit, a pyrometallurgical high-matte nickel project planned for ~50,000 tonnes/year (nickel metal) of high-matte nickel, complementing the company's HPAL route and enriching new-energy nickel-feedstock sources. Relying on the Sulawesi/Weda Bay nickel parks, it is the upstream pyrometallurgical support of GEM's Indonesia full-chain nickel (resource–precursor–cathode), targeting 2025 startup. In H1 2025 GEM's Indonesia nickel projects produced ~44,000 tonnes of nickel metal, up 112% year-on-year." },
  4495: { descEn: "BYD's storage supply for Grenergy's Oasis de Atacama solar-storage project in Chile, one of the world's largest solar-storage projects.", detailEn: "BYD Energy Storage supplies battery storage systems (BESS) for Spanish developer Grenergy's Oasis de Atacama integrated solar-storage project in Chile's Atacama Desert. Built in seven phases, it ultimately plans 11 GWh of storage and 11 GW of solar — one of the world's largest solar-storage projects. BYD's storage provides night supply and peaking, helping northern Chile's mining zones and the grid absorb large-scale solar." },
  4512: { descEn: "Bridge's Chonburi compute-infrastructure investment in Thailand, announcing $1.2 billion over three years for hyperscale compute in Chonburi.", detailEn: "On April 10, 2025 hyperscale data-center firm Bridge Data Centres announced $1.2 billion over three years to build compute infrastructure in Chonburi, Thailand, with a new hyperscale campus serving ASEAN cloud and AI compute demand. It is BDC's major Southeast Asia expansion after Malaysia and India, backed by the $2.8-billion bank financing obtained in March 2025." },
  1287: { descEn: "The Tecon 10 container terminal at Santos port, Brazil's largest port-lease project, awaiting auction.", detailEn: "A giant container terminal at Santos, Latin America's largest port; once live, the port's annual container-handling capacity reaches 9 million boxes, up ~50%, with the winner investing ~6.4 billion reais over 25 years. The TCU approved a two-stage auction structure, with the first round excluding incumbents like Maersk and MSC, drawing over 10 interested parties including ICTSI, JBS and JSL." },
  4124: { descEn: "TBEA's Soyo-Capari 400 kV transmission works in Angola, the country's largest and highest-voltage works, building the northern backbone grid.", detailEn: "TBEA has built the Soyo-Capari 400 kV turnkey transmission project in Angola since 2014, ~$1.18 billion total, completed June 2017. It is Angola's largest and highest-voltage substation works, building the northern backbone grid and cutting Luanda's key-district outage rate from 18% to 4.5%." },
  4269: { descEn: "China Road and Bridge's Funan Techo Canal in Cambodia, an inland canal linking Phnom Penh port and the Gulf of Thailand, built and operated by CRBC under BOT.", detailEn: "The Funan Techo Canal is a ~180 km inland canal under construction in Cambodia, linking the Phnom Penh Autonomous Port with Kep/Kampot and the Gulf of Thailand, giving Phnom Penh direct access to Cambodia's only deepwater port, Sihanoukville. The canal is 100 m wide upstream, 80 m downstream and 5.4 m deep, navigable for 3,000-tonne vessels. ~$1.16 billion, built and operated by China Road and Bridge (CRBC) under a BOT model for 50 years before transfer to Cambodia (China ~49% equity). A groundbreaking was held August 5, 2024, with ~2029 completion expected, sharply cutting Cambodia's reliance on Vietnamese ports for foreign trade." },
  1578: { descEn: "PowerChina's Amaria hydropower plant in Guinea, the final cascade step on the Konkouré River, 300 MW.", detailEn: "PowerChina's Sinohydro Bureau 3 is developing the Amaria hydropower plant on Guinea's Konkouré River on an invest-plus-build basis, 300 MW, max dam height 78 m, reservoir 1.647 billion m³, a 40-year concession. On completion it meets ~30% of national power demand, supplying clean power to Conakry and mining zones. A supporting 10 MW solar grid-connected in July 2025." },
  3199: { descEn: "Amara Raja's Giga Corridor battery plant, an integrated cell-and-PACK gigafactory in Telangana with China's Gotion.", detailEn: "Amara Raja is building the Giga Corridor battery park on 260 acres at Divitipally, Mahbubnagar district, Telangana, planning 5 GWh of PACK and 16 GWh of cells, ~95 billion rupees cumulative to 2031, bringing in Gotion-InoBat JV (GIB) technology to make LFP cells. A 1.5 GWh PACK phase 1 is live, with cell mass production targeted for 2027." },
  3475: { descEn: "Mianzhu pumped storage in Deyang, Sichuan, 1.2 million kW.", detailEn: "In Mianzhu, Deyang, Sichuan, 1.2 million kW, ~8.1 billion yuan total, approved February 8, 2025, controlled by Sichuan Energy Investment. It serves Sichuan-grid regulation and Sichuan-Chongqing UHV export." },
  3477: { descEn: "Nan'an pumped storage in Quanzhou, Fujian, 1.2 million kW.", detailEn: "In Nan'an, Quanzhou, Fujian, 1.2 million kW, 8.019 billion yuan total, approved April 7, 2025, built by Fujian Energy Group. It serves peaking for Fujian's coastal load center." },
  3478: { descEn: "Lianyungang pumped storage in Jiangsu, 1.2 million kW, started April 2025.", detailEn: "In Lianyungang, Jiangsu, 1.2 million kW total, controlled by Jiangsu Guoxin Group, started April 2025, targeting commissioning by end-2031. It provides regulation for the northern Jiangsu grid and offshore-wind absorption." },
  3542: { descEn: "Yibin Data Treasure AI-compute center, an 8-billion-yuan, ≥4,000 PFLOPS three-phase center with phase 1 lit.", detailEn: "Yibin Data Treasure AI-compute center totals 8 billion yuan in three phases, with ≥4,000 PFLOPS planned. Phase 1 is lit and in use, with compute equal to ~500,000 high-performance computers computing at once, supporting southern Sichuan's AI and digital economy." },
  4257: { descEn: "China Railway Construction's Diriyah King Saud University relocation and municipal works, with municipal and power support for the Diriyah mega-development including the KSU relocation.", detailEn: "A consortium of CRCC's Saudi company and CRCC Zhongyuan Construction won the ~$1.13-billion Diriyah master-plan municipal-support works, including relocation of King Saud University campus facilities and large-scale municipal-pipeline and power relocation and new construction. Diriyah is one of Saudi Vision 2030's five flagship developments, and the contract is another CRCC breakthrough in Saudi Arabia's premium-infrastructure market." },
  1073: { descEn: "The Collie battery storage (Synergy), Western Australia state-owned and Australia's largest operating battery storage.", detailEn: "Built by WA state utility Synergy next to the Collie coal plant, using CATL cells, 500 MW/2,400 MWh and ~4-hour duration, formally commissioned in February 2026 as Australia's largest operating battery storage system. It can power ~785,000 households for over 4 hours, absorbing wind-solar surplus and releasing it at SWIS-grid peaks or low-output periods, supporting WA's pre-2030 retirement of state-owned coal units, with reserved expansion to 1 GW/4 GWh." },
  115: { descEn: "A key deep-sea project off Ningde, Fujian.", detailEn: "Approved by Fujian's NDRC in January 2024, planned at 800 MW, in the deep-sea area off Ningde, using large-capacity turbines to cut deepwater LCOE and boost Fujian's clean-energy supply." },
  116: { descEn: "The world's first GW-scale fixed offshore solar plant.", detailEn: "In waters 8 km off Dongying, Shandong, totaling 1 GW, with the first batch grid-connected in November 2024 — the world's first to use large offshore steel-truss-platform technology, developed as 'fishery-solar integration,' expected to generate 1.78 billion kWh a year." },
  120: { descEn: "A key deep-sea project off Cangnan, Wenzhou, Zhejiang.", detailEn: "In waters east of Cangnan, Wenzhou, Zhejiang, planned at 800 MW with 57 14 MW turbines, part of Zhejiang's six deep-sea wind farm areas, relying on the Zhejiang (East China) deep-sea wind home port for O&M." },
  282: { descEn: "One of the largest recent single investments by a non-hyperscale operator in the Nordics.", detailEn: "London quant-trading firm XTX Markets is investing over €1 billion in a data center in Kajaani, Finland, expected live in 2026, benefiting from Finland's hydropower, cold climate and stable environment." },
  390: { descEn: "The only producer outside Asia supplying all four magnetic rare earths.", detailEn: "In Goiás, Brazil, the first and only producer outside Asia supplying all four magnetic rare earths — neodymium, praseodymium, dysprosium and terbium — at scale, with commercial first production in early 2024. In April 2026 USA Rare Earth proposed acquiring it for ~$2.8 billion — a strategic asset for the non-China rare-earth supply chain." },
  399: { descEn: "Expansion of CMOC's Kisanfu copper-cobalt mine, one of the world's largest cobalt mines.", detailEn: "In Lualaba province, DRC, CMOC holds 71.25%; phase 1 reached full output in 2023 with over 150,000 tonnes/year of copper, and in October 2025 a $1.08-billion phase-2 expansion adding 100,000 tonnes/year of copper was approved, completing in 2027." },
  543: { descEn: "ByteDance's Volcengine Yangtze-Delta (Wuhu) compute center, a core compute deployment in the Wuhu cluster.", detailEn: "ByteDance is building the Volcengine Yangtze-Delta compute center in Wuhu, Anhui, 8 billion yuan total, designed for 21,824 racks with a 220 kV self-built substation — an important part of ByteDance's 2025 ~160-billion-yuan capex IDC-construction plan." },
  623: { descEn: "Zambia's emblematic copper mine, restarting strongly after a UAE capital injection.", detailEn: "In Zambia's Copperbelt, once sold by Glencore and then struggling; in 2024 the UAE's IRH acquired 51% for $1.1 billion and injected over $1.2 billion. In H1 2025 copper-content output rose 54% year-on-year, employing over 13,000, targeting 300,000 tonnes/year of copper by 2029." },
  798: { descEn: "A 756 MW onshore wind farm in northern Rio Grande do Norte, Brazil.", detailEn: "In northern Rio Grande do Norte, Brazil, developed by Casa dos Ventos, with 168 Vestas 4.5 MW turbines, part of Vestas's largest-ever Latin American order. Construction began late 2023, with full operation expected early 2026, generating ~3 billion kWh a year." },
  1047: { descEn: "A new vertically integrated thin-film solar-module plant in the U.S.", detailEn: "In Iberia Parish, Louisiana, $1.1 billion and ~2.4 million square feet, it started early in July 2025 and was formally unveiled in November, making 3.5 GW/year of cadmium-telluride Series 7 modules. Vertically integrated with ~800 jobs, it is a high-power thin-film solar plant, raising First Solar's U.S. capacity to 14 GW by 2026." },
  1051: { descEn: "BYD's first vehicle gigafactory in the Americas.", detailEn: "In Camaçari, Bahia, Brazil (the former Ford plant site), the first Brazilian-made Dolphin Mini rolled off on July 1, 2025. With 150,000 vehicles/year capacity, it transitions from CKD assembly to full manufacturing — BYD's first vehicle base in the Americas, with welding, painting and assembly as large industrial power loads, ~1,000 staff, 80% local." },
  1125: { descEn: "The UAE's first national passenger railway, opening in 2026.", detailEn: "Etihad Rail launched its first national passenger network on the existing freight trunk line, connecting 11 cities and regions including Abu Dhabi, Dubai, Sharjah and Fujairah. Trains run at 200 km/h carrying 400 people per train, with Abu Dhabi to Dubai in just 57 minutes, targeting 36 million passengers/year by 2030. By end-2025, 10 of 13 trains had arrived and passed testing certification, with first-stage passenger service set to formally open in 2026, reshaping travel across the seven emirates." },
  1183: { descEn: "Germany's second LNG import terminal at Wilhelmshaven.", detailEn: "Germany's state terminal operator DET commissioned a second LNG import terminal at Wilhelmshaven, centered on a 277 m FSRU (Excelsior), with regasification and grid-injection capacity reaching ~4.6 billion m³/year over the next two years. It entered commercial operation on August 29, 2025, part of Germany's strategy to break from Russian gas and secure supply, with near-term capacity once fully booked by the market." },
  1315: { descEn: "Salobo III copper mine, Brazil's largest copper mine expansion, with the third mill ramping up.", detailEn: "Salobo at Carajás in Pará is Brazil's largest copper mine. The Salobo III expansion, ~$1.1 billion, adds a third processing line, raising the complex's capacity to ~36 million tonnes/year. In Q1 2024 the third mill averaged ~90% of capacity, significantly boosting copper output and sales." },
  1319: { descEn: "The Caçapava heavy-rare-earth project, a Goiás ionic-clay heavy rare earth, the world's first such reserve.", detailEn: "An ionic-adsorption clay rare-earth mine in Nova Roma, Goiás, rich in scarce heavy rare earths dysprosium/terbium. On November 6, 2025 it filed a pre-feasibility study (PFS), declaring the world's first NI 43-101 reserve for ionic-clay rare earths, NPV ~$1.1 billion, IRR ~22%, ~175 tonnes/year of dysprosium-terbium. In April 2025 it unveiled a semi-industrial pilot plant in Goiás, with up to $5 million of U.S. DFC support for the feasibility study." },
  1333: { descEn: "Sadawi solar plant, a 2 GW solar in the Eastern Province, led by the UAE's Masdar.", detailEn: "Sadawi is a key NREP solar project in Saudi Arabia's Eastern Province, 2 GW. In August 2025 the UAE's Masdar with China's GD Power and Korea's KEPCO closed financing, ~$1.1 billion total cost, with 8 regional and international banks lending, targeting full-load generation in early 2027." },
  1336: { descEn: "Starah wind farm, a 2 GW onshore wind in Riyadh province, one of Saudi's largest wind projects.", detailEn: "Starah in Saudi Arabia's Riyadh province is 2 GW — one of two wind projects in the sixth NREP wave's seven. On December 1, 2025 it closed financing alongside Bisha, Humaij and others (15 GW total) for $8.2 billion, developed by ACWA Power, PIF's Badeel and Aramco's SAPCO, marking acceleration of Saudi large-scale onshore wind." },
  1341: { descEn: "Ajban solar plant, a 1.5 GW single solar in Abu Dhabi, one of the world's largest.", detailEn: "Ajban solar, ~70 km northeast of Abu Dhabi, is 1.5 GW, tendered by EWEC. In September 2024 EDF Renewables and Korea Western Power (20% each) with Masdar (60%) closed financing, with 6 banks lending; construction formally began June 2025, deploying ~3 million bifacial modules, and after full-capacity operation in Q3 2026 it will be one of the world's largest single solar plants." },
  1342: { descEn: "Khazna solar plant, a 1.5 GW solar between Abu Dhabi and Al Ain, financing closed in early 2026.", detailEn: "Khazna solar, between Abu Dhabi and Al Ain, is 1.5 GW; in October 2025 ENGIE and Masdar won and signed a 30-year PPA with EWEC. Financing closed January 19, 2026, with 7 regional and international banks lending, targeting 2028 operation, powering ~160,000 UAE households and cutting 2.4 million tonnes of CO₂ a year." },
  1351: { descEn: "Saudi's east-to-central ±500 kV HVDC line 2, the second HVDC corridor from the east to the center.", detailEn: "Tendered in January 2025 in the same batch as line 1, it links the Eastern Qurayyah-4 BSP/Hajer-2 IPP with the central Khari industrial city KIC 9067 substation, ~466 km, ±500 kV, 3,000 MW — part of Saudi's plan to expand the transmission grid from ~99,800 km to 160,000 km with nine new HVDC lines." },
  1439: { descEn: "Arab Potash's Dead Sea project (southern expansion), Jordan Dead Sea potash, with a 30% output boost from the southern expansion.", detailEn: "Arab Potash Company (APC) extracts potash via solar evaporation in salt pans on the southern Dead Sea shore in Jordan, exporting ~2.85 million tonnes to 59 countries last year, with a record-high output in Q1 2026. The ~$1.1-billion southern expansion raises annual capacity above 3.5 million tonnes, targeting ~30% total-capacity growth by 2030, with new pump stations, granular-potash capacity, solar salt pans and a logistics center." },
  1458: { descEn: "Masdar Kazakhstan 1 GW wind-storage in Zhambyl province, breaking ground Q1 2026.", detailEn: "Masdar is leading development of 1 GW of wind with 300 MW/600 MWh of battery storage in Zhambyl province, Kazakhstan, with partners including W Solar, Qazaq Green Power (Samruk-Kazyna) and a Kazakh investment-development fund. The investment agreement was signed at COP29 in 2024, with a PPA in May 2025, breaking ground Q1 2026. On completion it can power ~300,000 households and cut 2 million tonnes of carbon a year." },
  1760: { descEn: "RT-One's Maringá AI data center, a Paraná export-processing-zone AI park with direct Itaipu green power.", detailEn: "RT-One plans a ~1-million-m² AI data center in the export-processing zone (ZPE) next to Maringá airport, parallel to the Uberlândia project, with the same 400 MW capacity and R$6-billion investment. Power is supplied directly via an Itaipu hydropower transmission line. As of April 2026 it still awaited ZPE authorization, with first modules planned for 2026." },
  1823: { descEn: "Eneva's Azulão 950 gas-power complex, an on-site generation complex at the Amazon Azulão field.", detailEn: "Eneva is building the Azulão I+II gas plants at Silves, Amazonas, for R$5.8 billion, 950 MW total, using a reservoir-to-wire (R2W) model to generate on-site and feed the northern grid. Azulão II is a 590 MW combined cycle (360 MW gas turbine + 230 MW steam turbine), targeting completion in August 2027." },
  1845: { descEn: "Saudi's east-to-central ±500 kV HVDC line 4 (Qurayyah-Khari industrial city), a new HVDC corridor from the eastern Qurayyah/Hajer to the central Khari industrial city.", detailEn: "A ±500 kV line from the Eastern operating area's Qurayyah-4 BSP/Hajer-2 IPP to the central Khari industrial city (KIC) 9067 BSP, ~466 km and 3,000 MW; with line 3 it forms the second east-central HVDC interconnection batch, strengthening cross-zone transfer and system resilience. The main contract bid in February 2026, with completion around 2028." },
  2003: { descEn: "Texas Instruments' second Melaka assembly-and-test plant, opened November 2025.", detailEn: "In 2023 TI announced two new assembly-and-test plants in Melaka and Kulim; Melaka's TIEM2 opened in November 2025, up to RM 5 billion (~$1.1 billion), a six-story building over 900,000 square feet, totaling over 1.4 million square feet connected to the existing plant, with bump, probe, assembly and test automation, supporting TI's 2030 target of 90% in-house assembly-and-test." },
  2010: { descEn: "Hyundai-LG's HLI battery plant in Indonesia, Southeast Asia's first and largest cell plant, starting at 10 GWh.", detailEn: "Hyundai and LG Energy Solution's 50:50 JV HLI Green Power built Southeast Asia's first and largest cell plant in the new Karawang industrial city, ~$1.1 billion, started up July 2024, phase 1 at 10 GWh (enough for 150,000 EVs), expandable to 20-30 GWh; the two groups pledged up to $9.8 billion to build Indonesia's full EV chain." },
  2203: { descEn: "Egypt's Suez 1.1 GW onshore wind farm, set to become Africa's largest onshore wind after commissioning.", detailEn: "A 1.1 GW onshore wind project in the Gulf of Suez and Gabal el-Zeit area near Ras Ghareb, split into two 550 MW sites each. EBRD led arranging a $275-million syndicated loan, ~$1.1 billion total. Targeting 2026 grid connection, it will then overtake Gulf of Suez phase 2 as Africa's largest onshore wind farm — the flagship of Egypt's NWFE renewables plan." },
  3062: { descEn: "Nemaska Lithium (Bécancour lithium-hydroxide plant), a Quebec integrated lithium project with a 32,000-tonne/year Bécancour plant.", detailEn: "An integrated lithium project with the Bécancour lithium-hydroxide plant (32,000 tonnes/year) and the Whabouchi spodumene mine in James Bay. In February 2026 Rio Tinto raised its stake to 53.9% for control, with Quebec at 46.1%; Quebec injects up to $200 million and Rio Tinto over $300 million in 2026, with the site ~60% complete at end-2025." },
  3068: { descEn: "The Elk Creek critical-minerals project, a Nebraska niobium-scandium-titanium-rare-earth polymetallic project, with EXIM offering up to ~$800 million.", detailEn: "NioCorp plans to produce niobium, scandium, titanium and some rare earths at Elk Creek in southeastern Nebraska. EXIM issued a letter of interest for up to ~$800 million of debt as a priority, advancing to independent technical review; 2025 fundraising topped $370 million (including $10 million from DoD), launching ~$44.6 million of decline works." },
  3170: { descEn: "JSW Energy's Bhavali pumped storage in Nashik/Thane, Maharashtra, 1,500 MW/12 GWh, with a 40-year PPA signed.", detailEn: "JSW Energy is building 1,500 MW/12,000 MWh Bhavali pumped storage in Nashik and Thane districts, Maharashtra, with a storage-procurement agreement signed with MSEDCL, 8-hour discharge. In June 2025 L&T won the heavy civil works (cap ~25 billion rupees), including upper/lower reservoirs, pressure tunnels and underground powerhouse, to be commissioned within 48 months." },
  3171: { descEn: "JSW Neo's Sonbhadra pumped storage in UP, 1,500 MW/12 GWh, with a 40-year storage agreement with UPPCL.", detailEn: "JSW Neo signed a 1,500 MW/12,000 MWh pumped-storage procurement agreement with UP utility UPPCL, in Sonbhadra district, with a fixed capacity charge of 7.72 million rupees per MW per year over 40 years, 8-hour daily dispatch, to be commissioned within ~6 years. JSW has locked in 28.3 GWh of storage, targeting 40 GWh by 2030." },
  3173: { descEn: "Adani's Tarali pumped storage in Satara, Maharashtra, 1,500 MW, part of Adani's 5 GW pumped-storage plan.", detailEn: "Adani Green is building 1,500 MW Tarali pumped storage at Satara, Maharashtra, with electromechanical from ANDRITZ; with 500 MW Chitravathi and 1,800 MW Gandikota it forms Adani's 2030 portfolio of over 5 GW of pumped storage, supporting 24-hour supply from wind-solar bases." },
  3223: { descEn: "Sify's Siruseri AI-ready campus in Chennai, southern India's largest AI-ready data-center campus, with its own open cable landing station.", detailEn: "In April 2025 Sify opened southern India's largest AI-ready data-center campus at SIPCOT Siruseri, Chennai, ultimately 130 MW, with phase-1 Chennai-02 offering 25.92 MW IT load — the only data center in India with its own on-site open cable landing station, with Tamil Nadu cumulative investment over 100 billion rupees." },
  3423: { descEn: "Heilongjiang Jixi green-hydrogen methanol-jet-fuel integration, an 8-billion-yuan green-hydrogen methanol-jet-fuel integration started April 2025, straw-to-alcohol.", detailEn: "In Jixi, Heilongjiang, ~8 billion yuan total, using agricultural straw to make green methanol, ethanol and jet fuel, coupled with green hydrogen for biomass high-value use and sustainable-aviation-fuel supply. It formally started April 15, 2025." },
  3476: { descEn: "Yongxin pumped storage in Ji'an, Jiangxi, 1.2 million kW.", detailEn: "In Yongxin, Ji'an, Jiangxi, 1.2 million kW, 7.823 billion yuan total, approved January 2, 2025, developed by China Huaneng. It boosts the Jiangxi grid's peaking capacity." },
  3502: { descEn: "China Resources Microelectronics' Runxi 12-inch power line in Chongqing, reaching 30,000 wafers/month early with sustained full output.", detailEn: "China Resources Holdings and the Big Fund co-invested 7.55 billion yuan in a Chongqing 12-inch power-semiconductor line (Runxi); in August 2025 it reached 30,000 wafers/month a year and a half early, with sustained full output from September, having completed 35,000 wafers/month, mass-producing SGT MOS and super-junction MOS for automotive and AI-server power." },
  4071: { descEn: "Sinosteel Equipment's Tosyali steel complex phase 4 in Algeria, an $1.1-billion phase-4 expansion.", detailEn: "Sinosteel Equipment (Sinosteel International) signed a ~$1.1-billion EPC contract with the Tosyali Group to build a 2.5-million-tonne direct-reduced-iron (DRI), 2.4-million-tonne EAF steel and 2-million-tonne 1,800 mm hot-strip line in Oran province, Algeria. DRI, EAF and hot rolling started up through 2024, with 800,000 tonnes of cold rolling and 400,000 tonnes of galvanizing in 2025, cementing Sinosteel's lead in North African metallurgy EPC." },
  4276: { descEn: "CCCC's Karnaphuli River tunnel in Bangladesh, South Asia's first underwater tunnel, linking the two banks of the Karnaphuli in Chittagong.", detailEn: "The Karnaphuli River tunnel (Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujibur Rahman Tunnel) is at the mouth of the Karnaphuli in Chittagong — CCCC's first overseas large-diameter underwater shield tunnel, Bangladesh's first tunnel and South Asia's first underwater tunnel. A twin-tube, two-way four-lane tunnel with a ~3.32 km shield section, it links Chittagong city on the east bank to Anwara on the west, greatly improving Chittagong-to-Cox's Bazar mobility. It opened October 29, 2023 and continued operating in 2024 — a landmark Belt-and-Road marine tunnel." },
  4401: { descEn: "Sinopec Engineering's butadiene-and-rubber project in Atyrau, Kazakhstan, with the EPC won for over 300,000 tonnes/year of butadiene and SBS rubber.", detailEn: "On April 7, 2025 Sinopec Engineering (SEG) disclosed the EPC contract for Kazakhstan's butadiene-and-rubber project, ~$1.093 billion (~7.467 billion yuan). In Atyrau province, designed for over 300,000 tonnes/year, the product line covers butadiene and styrene-butadiene-styrene (SBS) rubber for road materials, adhesives and plastics — a major breakthrough for the company in Central Asian synthetic materials." },
  4417: { descEn: "CNCEC (Wuhuan)'s Talcher coal-to-fertilizer in India, the world's largest single-line coal-to-fertilizer project, ~71% complete.", detailEn: "India's Talcher coal-to-fertilizer project in Angul, Odisha is the world's largest single-line coal-to-fertilizer project and India's first modern large coal-to-fertilizer plant, at 730,000 tonnes/year ammonia and 1.27 million tonnes/year urea, using a coal-gasification route, a full-process EPC turnkey covering patents, design, procurement, construction and commissioning. CNCEC's China Wuhuan won the coal-gasification-purification and ammonia-urea packages in 2019, ~8 billion yuan cumulatively. By February 2026 construction was ~71.24%, targeting end-2027 startup." },
  4422: { descEn: "CNCEC's Egypt phase-3 fertilizer EPC, a single contract up to ~8.18 billion yuan, Egypt a top-10 country market for the company.", detailEn: "CNCEC's China Wuhuan signed a phase-3 fertilizer EPC general contract in Egypt, a single contract up to ~8.18 billion yuan, using Egyptian gas to build ammonia/urea fertilizer units. Egypt and Kazakhstan together account for over 70% of the company's top-10 country-market contract value — key overseas markets in 2024-2025. The project cements its position in North Africa's nitrogen-fertilizer engineering market, with products for Egyptian agriculture and export." },
  1661: { descEn: "CMOC's KFM copper-cobalt mine (phase 2) in DRC, a world-class high-grade copper-cobalt mine, phase 2 started 2025.", detailEn: "Kisanfu is one of the world's largest, highest-grade producing copper-cobalt mines; CMOC indirectly holds 71.25%, with phase 1 at full output in 2023. Phase 2 was announced October 25, 2025, investment up to $1.084 billion, adding 7.26 million tonnes/year of sulfide mining-and-processing and expanding smelting, targeting startup in H1 2027 with ~100,000 tonnes/year of added copper at full output. With TFM phase 3 it supports the company topping 800,000 tonnes of copper in 2027." },
  1785: { descEn: "A concession to deepen the Santos port channel, deepening the Santos approach channel to 17 m via PPP.", detailEn: "Brazil's largest port, Santos, plans to deepen its approach channel to 17 m via a PPP, a 20-year contract, ~5.8 billion reais, included in the next four-year plan. ANTAQ has held public consultation and hearings on the concession. In a transition period public works first deepen it to 16 m: in July 2025 APS issued a tender to dredge to 16 m and handle non-blasting rock removal." },
  3479: { descEn: "Xinfeng pumped storage in Shaoguan, Guangdong, 1.2 million kW, Guangdong's first approved pumped storage of the 15th Five-Year period.", detailEn: "In Xinfeng, Shaoguan, Guangdong, 1.2 million kW (4×300,000), 7.379 billion yuan total, announced for construction by CSG Energy Storage in March 2026, planned to start in 2026 and start up in 2031 over a 70-month build." },
  3474: { descEn: "Wulong Yinpan pumped storage in Chongqing, 1.2 million kW, approved February 2025.", detailEn: "In Wulong, Chongqing, 1.2 million kW, 7.296 billion yuan total, approved February 19, 2025. It provides peaking storage for the Chengdu-Chongqing twin-city economic circle." },
  3606: { descEn: "Shandong offshore gold mine, China's largest single gold mine, 562 tonnes of gold resources, mined undersea.", detailEn: "In waters north of Sanshandao in Laizhou, Shandong, China's only and Asia's largest undersea gold mine. With 562 tonnes of gold resources and 212 tonnes of reserves, mining-and-processing totals ~7.3 billion yuan (4.5 billion invested), at 12,000 tonnes/day, producing 15-20 tonnes/year of gold at full output. Zhaojin holds 70% of Ruihai Mining, Zijin 30%." },
  278: { descEn: "Kenya's Microsoft-G42 Azure East Africa data center, geothermal-powered.", detailEn: "A Microsoft-G42 Azure East Africa data center, initially 100 MW, planned to draw power from the Olkaria geothermal field, expandable to 1 GW long term, within a $1-billion Kenya AI investment package, also driving Swahili-LLM development." },
  395: { descEn: "Cauchari-Olaroz lithium salt lake, an emblematic newly-commissioned salt-lake mine in the Lithium Triangle.", detailEn: "In Jujuy province, Argentina, a JV of Ganfeng Lithium and Lithium Argentina, with commercial first production in October 2024; 2025 lithium-carbonate output was ~25,400 tonnes, with 35,000-40,000 tonnes targeted in 2026 and a Stage 2 expansion to 80,000 tonnes advancing." },
  396: { descEn: "POSCO's Hombre Muerto lithium-hydroxide plant, Argentina's first commercial lithium-hydroxide plant.", detailEn: "In Salta province, Argentina, wholly owned by POSCO, extracting brine from the Hombre Muerto salt lake and refining via a lithium-phosphate intermediate, with phase 1 (25,000 tonnes/year) inaugurated October 2024 and total capacity reaching 100,000 tonnes after phase 3 — a key feedstock for Korea's battery supply chain." },
  523: { descEn: "Microsoft's Douglasville data center (Georgia), a cloud-infrastructure campus in Douglas County, Georgia.", detailEn: "Microsoft is building a cloud data-center campus in Douglas County, Georgia, phase 1 near a million square feet, started 2024, expected in use 2026, forming a Georgia two-campus arrangement with the Atlanta Fairwater 2." },
  559: { descEn: "China Unicom's Shanghai Lingang ten-thousand-card AI-compute center, a Yangtze-Delta-hub ten-thousand-card flagship.", detailEn: "China Unicom built and operates a ten-thousand-card AI-compute center at Shanghai Lingang; 2025 compute investment rose 28% year-on-year, having built two ten-thousand-card clusters in Shanghai and Hohhot, with 7 hundred-megawatt AIDC campuses built in the year, total AI compute reaching 45 EFLOPS." },
  595: { descEn: "SoftBank's Sakai, Osaka AI data center, with SoftBank buying Sharp's Sakai plant to build a 400 MW-class AI data center.", detailEn: "In March 2025 SoftBank bought Sharp's ~440,000 m² former LCD plant in Sakai, Osaka for $676 million, planning a 750,000 m² hyperscale AI data center, phase 1 over 150 MW and ultimately above 400 MW, with non-lithium storage, in deep cooperation with OpenAI." },
  598: { descEn: "Google's Chonburi data center in Thailand, Google's first local data center in Chonburi.", detailEn: "In September 2024 Google announced $1 billion to build Thailand's first cloud-region data center in eastern Chonburi province, built in phases over 2025-2029, expected to contribute $4 billion to Thailand's GDP and provide 14,000 jobs a year on average — core digital infrastructure for the Eastern Economic Corridor." },
  792: { descEn: "Huaneng Peninsula North L offshore wind, China's deepest-water commercial offshore wind farm (56 m).", detailEn: "In the northern Yellow Sea ~70 km offshore, max water depth 56 m, with 42 12 MW turbines totaling 504,000 kW, overcoming deep-sea large-capacity-turbine integration. The first batch grid-connected in January 2026 and full capacity in April, generating ~1.7 billion kWh a year." },
  870: { descEn: "Oman's Hyport Duqm green-hydrogen project, Oman's first green-hydrogen project, led by BP.", detailEn: "In Oman's Duqm Economic Zone, led by BP at 49%, phase 1 has 1.4 GW of wind-solar and a 500 MW electrolyzer for 60,000 tonnes/year of green hydrogen; FID is expected 2026-2027 and commercial operation 2030-2031, with the electrolyzer expandable to 1 GW long term — the lead project of Oman's national green-hydrogen strategy." },
  983: { descEn: "The New England Clean Energy Connect (NECEC), sending Quebec clean hydropower south to Maine's New England grid.", detailEn: "NECEC delivers 1,200 MW of Quebec hydropower via northwestern Maine into the New England grid, powering 1.2 million households, formally commissioned January 2026, ending an 8-year permitting dispute and becoming New England's largest renewable supply source." },
  1021: { descEn: "Ola Electric's Krishnagiri gigafactory, India's only cell gigafactory, mass-producing domestic cells in 2025.", detailEn: "Ola Electric's 110-acre gigafactory at Krishnagiri, Tamil Nadu is India's only scaled cell plant, initially ~5-6 GWh, planned to 100 GWh long term. From mid-2025 it began mass-producing its self-developed 4680-format 'Bharat Cell' NMC cells for its vehicles; in January 2026 it rolled out the Ola Shakti home-storage product at the same plant, entering residential storage — a landmark large-power-load project for India's battery localization." },
  1182: { descEn: "ENN Zhoushan LNG terminal phase 3, Zhejiang's first 10-million-tonne-class LNG terminal.", detailEn: "China's first private large LNG terminal, ENN Zhoushan phase 3, builds 4 new 220,000 m³ full-containment tanks and rebuilds the jetty, raising tank capacity from 640,000 to 1.52 million m³ and annual throughput to ~10 million tonnes, becoming Zhejiang's first 10-million-tonne-class terminal. Four months ahead of plan, it was built and commissioned on August 6, 2025, with cold-energy power and solar multi-energy complementarity." },
  1274: { descEn: "V.tal (Tecto)'s São Paulo hyperscale data center in Santana de Parnaíba, 200 MW.", detailEn: "Telecom-infrastructure firm V.tal set up data-center subsidiary Tecto and launched a $1-billion expansion, announcing a 200 MW hyperscale data center in Santana de Parnaíba, São Paulo, on 100% renewable power, expected live 2027. Tecto is also deploying facilities in Fortaleza, Rio, Brasília and Recife." },
  1306: { descEn: "Restart of the Três Lagoas UFN III nitrogen-fertilizer plant, reviving a Mato Grosso do Sul plant to cut fertilizer-import reliance.", detailEn: "Petrobras's board approved twice — October 2024 and April 2026 — restarting construction of the UFN III nitrogen-fertilizer unit at Três Lagoas, Mato Grosso do Sul, ~$1 billion, with urea capacity ~3,600 tonnes/day and ammonia ~2,200 tonnes/day, commercial operation 2029. Gas-fed, it targets the Center-West, South and Southeast urea markets, creating ~8,000 jobs." },
});

